Johnston Peak ( 66 ° 16′S 52 ° 6′E ) is a sharp dark peak in Antarctica , 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) north of Mount Marr and 11 nautical miles ( 20 km ) northwest of Douglas Peak .
Erul Heights ( Bulgarian : Ерулски възвишения , `` Erulski Vazvisheniya '' \e-'rul - ski v&z - vi-'she - ni - ya\ ) are the heights rising to 1092 m ( Gigen Peak ) on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Mackay Point ( 67 ° 32′S 68 ° 5′W ) is a point on the southeast coast of Adelaide Island , Antarctica , about 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) to the north - northeast of Rothera Point .
O'Neal Point ( 64 ° 42′S 62 ° 18′W ) is a headland on the east side of the Arctowski Peninsula , Danco Coast , Graham Land , Antarctica .
Humboldt Graben ( German : Humboldtgraben , `` Humboldt Trench '' , 71 ° 45′S 11 ° 55′E ) is a glacier - filled valley , 20 nautical miles ( 37 km ) long , trending north -- south between the Humboldt Mountains and the Petermann Ranges in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Veto Gap ( 73 ° 24′S 162 ° 54′E ) is a gap between Tobin and Gair Mesas in the Mesa Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica which provides access from upper Rennick Glacier to the Aeronaut Glacier .
The Perennial Philosophy is a comparative study of mysticism by British novelist Aldous Huxley .
Catweazle is a British television series , created and written by Richard Carpenter which was produced and directed by Quentin Lawrence for London Weekend Television under the LWI ( London Weekend International ) banner , and screened in the UK on ITV in 1970 .
Will & Grace is an American sitcom created by Max Mutchnick and David Kohan about the relationship between best friends Will Truman ( Eric McCormack ) , a gay lawyer , and Grace Adler ( Debra Messing ) , a straight interior designer .
Sky Hooks is a painted sheet steel sculpture by Alexander Calder , constructed in 1962 .
Pepper Ann is an American animated series created by Sue Rose and aired on ABC .
Salutat is an 1898 painting by Thomas Eakins ( 1844 - -1916 ) .
Soft Construction with Boiled Beans ( Premonition of Civil War ) ( 1936 ) is a painting by Spanish Surrealist Salvador Dalí .
Neptune and Triton is an early sculpture by the Italian artist Gian Lorenzo Bernini .
The Miracle of the Jealous Husband is a fresco by the Italian Renaissance master Titian , executed in 1511 as part of the decoration of the Scuola del Santo in Padua , northern Italy .
The Stormy Sea in Étretat is an 1883 painting by founder of French impressionist Claude Monet , now preserved at the Musée des Beaux - Arts de Lyon .
Portrait of Henry VIII is a lost work by Hans Holbein the Younger depicting Henry VIII . While destroyed by fire in 1698 it is still well known today through many copies .
The Portrait of Alfonso I d'Este is a now - lost painting by Titian , dating to 1523 .
The Portrait of Frederick III of Saxony is a tempera on canvas painting by German Renaissance artist Albrecht Dürer , executed in 1496 .
Review Philippines is an English language news program produced by GMA Network .
Three Studies for Figures at the Base of a Crucifixion is a 1944 triptych painted by the Irish - born British artist Francis Bacon .
The Persistence of Memory ( Spanish : La persistencia de la memoria ; Catalan : La persistència de la memòria ) is a 1931 painting by artist Salvador Dalí , and is one of his most recognizable works .
I am a Curator was a process - based exhibition project by artist Per Hüttner that took place at Chisenhale Gallery , London , UK , 5 November -- 14 December 2003 .
Bouquet près de la fenêtre ( Bouquet by the Window ) is an oil on canvas painting by Marc Chagall dated 1959 - 1960 .
The Millers is an American sitcom that was created by Greg Garcia and stars Will Arnett as Nathan Miller and Margo Martindale as Carol Miller .
Victorious ( stylized as VICTORiOUS ) is an American sitcom created by Dan Schneider that originally aired on Nickelodeon from March 27 , 2010 through February 2 , 2013 .
The Baronci Altarpiece was a painting by the Italian High Renaissance artist Raphael .
Basket of Bread ( 1945 ) or Basket of Bread - Rather Death Than Shame is a painting by Spanish Surrealist Salvador Dalí .
Viet Rock is a rock musical by Megan Terry that was the precursor to the musical Hair .
Study after Velázquez 's Portrait of Pope Innocent X is a 1953 painting by the artist Francis Bacon .
Rugrats is an American animated television series created by Arlene Klasky , Gábor Csupó and Paul Germain for Nickelodeon .
Portrait of Susanna Lunden or Le Chapeau de Paille ( The Straw Hat ) is a painting by Peter Paul Rubens .
Chock - A - Block was a BBC children 's television programme , created by Michael Cole .
Braquo is a French crime drama television series created by Olivier Marchal and produced by Capa Drama with the participation of Canal+ in association with Marathon Group , Be - Films and RTBF .
The Off - Beats is a series of animated shorts that was created by Mo Willems ( who would later create the Cartoon Network television series Sheep in the Big City ) .
Ensueños de Amor , literally `` Daydreams of Love '' , is a `` dreamy '' oil on wood painting by Filipino painter and hero Juan Luna .
Commissario Laurenti is a German television series , with five episodes broadcast 2006 - -2009 , based on the crime novels by Veit Heinichen .
All Grown Up ! is an American animated television series created by Arlene Klasky and Gábor Csupó for Nickelodeon .
Frisky Dingo is an American animated cartoon series created by Adam Reed and Matt Thompson for Adult Swim .
The Honourable Woman is a 2014 British political spy thriller television miniseries in eight parts , directed and written by Hugo Blick for the BBC and SundanceTV .
The Justice of Trajan and Herkinbald was a set of four large panels painted by the Flemish painter Rogier van der Weyden that decorated one wall of a court - room in the Town Hall of Brussels .
International Museum Day ( IMD ) is a celebration that held every year on or around 18 May , coordinated by the International Council of Museums ( ICOM ) .
The flood of Saint - Cloud ( French : L'inondation à Saint - Cloud ) is an oil painting by French artist Paul Huet , which was first exposed in 1855 at the World Fair in Paris .
Sealing the Tomb is a great altarpiece triptych by William Hogarth in the English city of Bristol .
Portrait of Queen Henrietta Maria , as St Catherine is a painting by Sir Anthony van Dyck .
Flog It ! is a television series broadcast on the BBC since 27 May 2002 , presented by Paul Martin ( although the first five episodes were presented by Mark Harnden ) .
Incredible Crew is an American sketch comedy television series , created by Nick Cannon for Cartoon Network .
The Agnew Clinic , or , The Clinic of Dr. Agnew , is an 1889 oil painting by American artist Thomas Eakins , Goodrich # 235 .
Le Travail interrompu ( English : Work Interrupted ) is a painting painted by nineteenth century French painter William - Adolphe Bouguereau in 1891 .
The Wayfarer ( or The Pedlar ) is a Hieronymus Bosch painting .
The Dresden Altarpiece is a triptych by German Renaissance artists Albrecht Dürer , executed between 1496 and 1497 , and perhaps continued in 1503 - 1504 .
Leda Atomica is a painting by Salvador Dalí , made in 1949 .
Aeneas , Anchises , and Ascanius is a sculpture by the Italian artist Gian Lorenzo Bernini created c. 1618 - 19 .
Coming South is a 1886 painting by the Australian artist Tom Roberts .
The Madonna of the Carnation , a.k.a . Madonna with Vase or Madonna with Child , is a Renaissance oil painting by Leonardo da Vinci created around 1478 - 1480 .
Blessed Ludovica Albertoni ( Italian : Beata Ludovica Albertoni ) is a funerary monument by the Italian Baroque artist Gian Lorenzo Bernini .
Brady Street Beasts is a public art work by American artist Bill Reid located on the East Side of Milwaukee , Wisconsin near Brady Street and the Holton Street Viaduct .
Bremner , Bird and Fortune is a satirical British television programme produced by Vera Productions for Channel Four , uniting the longstanding satirical team of John Bird and the late John Fortune ( `` the Two Johns '' ) with the satirical impressionist Rory Bremner , and had 16 series , followed by several one - off episodes .
The painting Man and Woman Contemplating the Moon was created by Caspar David Friedrich in 1824 .
The Seducer ( Le Séducteur , also known as The Tempter ) is a surrealist painting by René Magritte .
Head on a Green Sofa is an oil painting by Lucian Freud executed in 1960 - 61 .
The Abbey in the Oakwood ( German : Abtei i m Eichwald ) is an oil painting by Caspar David Friedrich .
The Hay Wain is a painting by John Constable , finished in 1821 , which depicts a rural scene on the River Stour between the English counties of Suffolk and Essex .
Portrait of Daniel - Henry Kahnweiler ( Spanish : Retrato de Daniel - Henry Kahnweiler ) is a 1910 oil on canvas painting by Pablo Picasso in the Analytical Cubism style .
Niní was an Argentine children 's telenovela broadcast on Telefe from 2009 onwards , starring Florencia Bertotti and Federico Amador , written by Gabriela Fiore and Jorge Chernov .
Spiezer Schilling is a chronicle by Diebold Schilling the Elder of Bern ( 1480s ) , created after the Berner Schilling .
Jean DeWolff first appeared in Marvel Team - Up # 48 - 51 ( August -- November 1976 ) , and was created by Bill Mantlo and Sal Buscema .
Office in a Small City is a 1953 painting by the American realist painter Edward Hopper .
The Cliff Walk at Pourville is an 1882 painting by the French Impressionist painter Claude Monet .
The Sorrows of the King is a collage using cut out paper shapes by Henri Matisse from 1952 .
Based on the 1985 telenovela Ti Ti Ti , written by Cassiano Gabus Mendes , the remake is created and written by Maria Adelaide Amaral .
The Smoking Room is a British television sitcom written by Brian Dooley , who won a BAFTA for the series in 2005 .
Yang Kang is the fictional antagonist in the wuxia novel The Legend of the Condor Heroes by Jin Yong ( Louis Cha ) .
Storm of the Century , alternatively known as Stephen King 's Storm of the Century , is a 1999 horror TV miniseries written by Stephen King and directed by Craig R. Baxley .
The Geographer is a painting created by Dutch artist Johannes Vermeer in 1668 - -1669 , and is now in the collection of the Städelsches Kunstinstitut museum in Frankfurt , Germany .
Der Bastian is a German television series written by Barbara Noack , broadcast in 13 episodes between 1972 and 1973 on ZDF .
Dr. Ken is an American multi - camera sitcom created , written , and co - executive produced by its lead actor , Ken Jeong , who based the concept on his experience as a doctor prior to becoming a stand - up comedian .
Portrait of Don Luis de Góngora is a 1622 painting in oils of the poet Luis de Góngora by Diego Velázquez .
Flash Gordon is the hero of a space opera adventure comic strip originally drawn by Alex Raymond .
John Mohawk ( 30 August 1945 -- 13 December 2006 ) was an American historian , writer , and social activist .
Sir William Sidney ( 1482?--1554 ) was an English courtier under Henry VIII and Edward VI .
James Atlay ( 3 July 1817 in Wakerley , Northamptonshire -- 24 December 1894 ) was the 98th Anglican Bishop of Hereford , from 1868 to 1894 .
Ben Fain ( died early 1976 ) was an American bridge player .
Bailie Hugh Blackburn ( /ˈblækbərn/ ; 2 July 1823 , Craigflower , Torryburn , Fife -- 9 October 1909 , Roshven , Inverness - shire ) was a Scottish mathematician .
Douglas Furber ( 13 May 1885 -- 20 February 1961 ) was a British lyricist and playwright .
Jacob Eury ( born 6 April 1765 in Mirecourt - died 7 October 1848 ) was a French luthier and bow maker .
Matthäus Wieser ( 1617 - -1678 ) was a collector and songwriter of work songs , often for miners .
Mariano Andreu ( 1888 - -1976 ) was a Spanish painter , drawer , enamelling master , sculptor , and stage designer .
Ahmad Ghazi ( 1936 -- 7 June 2015 ) was a Kurdish writer and translator .
Jesse Oatman Betterton ( 1884 - 1960 ) was an metallurgist .
Harold Gifford , Sr . ( 1859 - 1929 ) was a ophthalmologist , a discrete philanthropist , and an ardent nature enthusiast .
Thomas Ansell Marshall ( 1827 -- 1903 ) was an English cleric and entomologist , mainly interested in Hymenoptera .
Francis Zorzi ( or Giorgi ) ( Italian : Francesco ) ( 1337 - -1388 ) , called Marchesotto , was a member of the Venetian Zorzi family and the Margrave of Bodonitsa in Central Greece from 1345 to his death .
Adolphe Pictet ( 11 September 1799 -- 20 December 1875 ) was a Swiss linguist , born in Geneva .
Jiang Qin ( died 219 ) , courtesy name Gongyi , was a military general serving under the warlord Sun Quan in the late Eastern Han dynasty .
Elizabeth Wynne Fremantle ( born 19 April 1778 at Falkingham , now Folkingham , Lincolnshire , died 2 November 1857 in or near Nice , France ) was the main author of the extensive Wynne Diaries and wife of the Royal Navy officer Thomas Fremantle ( 1765 - -1819 ) , a close associate of Nelson .
Edward Herbert , 1st Baron Herbert of Cherbury ( or Chirbury ) KB ( 3 March 1583 -- 20 August 1648 ) was an Anglo - Welsh soldier , diplomat , historian , poet and religious philosopher of the Kingdom of England .
James Lalor ( 1829 - -1922 ) was a politician in Queensland , Australia .
Edward Conway , 2nd Viscount Conway PC ( bapt . 10 August 1594 -- 26 June 1655 ) was an English politician , military commander and peer .
Grete Rikko ( born Grete Rindskopf ; 1908 - -1998 ) was a German - American abstract expressionist who lived most of her life in New York .
Michael Addison , 3rd Viscount Addison ( 12 April 1914 -- 23 March 1992 ) was a British civil servant and academic .
André - Jacques Garnerin ( 31 January 1769 -- 18 August 1823 ) was a balloonist and the inventor of the frameless parachute .
Erasmus Ransford Tawiah Madjitey , CBE ( 11 November 1920 -- 23 February 1996 ) was a Ghanaian police officer , diplomat and politician .
Enguerrand Quarton ( or Charonton ) ( c. 1410 -- c. 1466 ) was a French painter and manuscript illuminator whose few surviving works are among the first masterpieces of a distinctively French style , very different from either Italian or Early Netherlandish painting .
Sir Hugo Martin Wedgwood ( 27 December 1933 -- 12 October 2010 ) was a British stockbroker and linguist .
Samuel S. Koenig ( September 7 , 1872 Kingdom of Hungary -- March 1955 Manhattan , New York City ) was an American lawyer and politician .
Felicia Cornaro ( died 1111 ) , was the Dogaressa of Venice by marriage to the Doge Vitale I Michiel ( r. 1096 - 1102 ) .
Matheolus Perusinus ( Mattheolus de Perusio , Mattiolo Mattioli , Matthiolus de Matthiolis , Matthiolus de Matthiolis ) ( died 1480 ) was a professor of philosophy and medicine .
Conchobar an Abaidh Ó Cellaigh , king of Uí Maine , Chief of the Name , died 1403 .
Stephen Samuel Perry ( 1825 - -1874 ) managed Peach Point Plantation , and is credited with amassing and preserving significant historical manuscripts related to Texas history .
Antoine Sautier ( died 1801 ) was a student gardener who was invited to join the Baudin scientific expedition ( 1800 - -1804 ) in the corvettes Géographe and Naturaliste to chart the coast of New Holland ( Australia ) , make scientific observations and collect natural history specimens .
William Frederick Evans ( known as Bill Evans ) ( 24 April 1857 -- 1 July 1935 ) was a Welsh international rugby union player , who won two caps for Wales in 1882 and 1883 .
Frida Uhl Strindberg ( 4 April 1872 -- 28 June 1943 ) was an Austrian writer and translator , who was closely associated with many important figures in 20th - century literature .
Birdy Sweeney ( 14 June 1931 -- 11 May 1999 ) was an Irish actor and comedian .
Cathal Óg Mac Maghnusa ( February 1439 -- March 1498 ) was the principal compiler of the Annals of Ulster .
Evan James Williams FRS ( 8 June 1903 -- 29 September 1945 ) was a Welsh experimental physicist who worked in a number of fields with some of the most notable physicists of his day , including Patrick Blackett , Lawrence Bragg , Ernest Rutherford and Niels Bohr .
Count Louis Philippe de Roffignac ( also known as Joseph Roffignac ) ( September 13 , 1773 -- August 29 , 1846 ) was a wealthy Louisiana merchant , banker , member of the state legislature , and the tenth individual to serve as Mayor of New Orleans , in 1820 - 1828 .
Nicholas Metcalfe ( died 1539 ) was an English churchman and college head .
John Bauldie ( 23 August 1949 -- 22 October 1996 ) was a British journalist , noted as one of the foremost experts on the work of Bob Dylan .
Betsy Gray ( died 1798 ) , was an Ulster - Scots Presbyterian peasant girl from outside Lisburn in Co. Antrim , Northern Ireland who was killed as part of the 1798 Rebellion of the United Irishmen .
Raymond Huntley ( 23 April 1904 -- 19 October 1990 ) was an English actor who appeared in dozens of British films from the 1930s to the 1970s .
Francis Hay , 9th Earl of Erroll ( 30 April 1564 -- 16 July 1631 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Derek Palmer ( 1907 or 1908 -- 6 September 2001 ) was a British businessman in the import / export trade resident in Chile .
Dave Early ( 1957 -- October 1996 ) was an English drummer and percussionist .
William Abell ( born ca . 1584 , died in or after 1655 ) was an English vintner who became master of the Vintners ' Company .
Josua Heschel Kuttner or Kutner ( Hebrew : יהושע העשיל קוטנר ) ( c.1803 -- 5 July 1878 ) was a Jewish Orthodox scholar and rabbi .
George William Alexander ( 1802 - -1890 ) was an English financier and philanthropist .
Archibald Napier , 1st Lord Napier , the 9th Laird Napier of Merchiston ( c. 1576 - -1645 ) , was a Scottish politician and judge .
Benjamin Franklin Graves ( 1771 - -1813 ) was a politician and military leader in early 19th - century Kentucky .
Samuel Stutchbury ( 15 January 1798 -- 12 February 1859 ) was an English naturalist and geologist .
Carl Wilhelm Kern ( June 4 , 1874 -- August 19 , 1945 ) was an American composer , pianist , theorist , and editor .
Baron Didrik Anders Gillis Bildt ( 16 October 1820 -- 22 October 1894 ) was a Swedish parliamentarian , military officer , baron and prime minister 1888 - -1889 .
Edward Henry Lewinski Corwin ( 1885 - 1953 ) was a New York City - based author of historical books , Polish activist and physician who worked in the public health sector of the city and state , publishing several reports and other works .
Alf Brown ( 6 February 1914 -- 28 July 2002 ) was a leading Australian rules football writer covering the Victorian Football League ( which later became the Australian Football League ) from 1945 to 1979 .
The Reverend John Walker Hundley ( 1841 - -1914 ) was a prominent 19th - century Baptist minister and church leader in Virginia .
Song Hun ( 宋混 ) ( died 361 ) was a regent of the Chinese state Former Liang .
Qazim Ademi ( 1876 - 1939 ) was an Albanian folk singer and composer of Albanian polyphonic music .
Michele Angiolillo Lombardi ( Italian pronunciation : ( miˈkɛle andʒoˈlillo ) ; 5 June 1871 -- 20 August 1897 ) was an Italian anarchist , born in Foggia .
Zalkind Hourwitz ( 1751 - -1812 ) was a Polish Jew active in the political discussions of the French Revolution .
Edward King , Viscount Kingsborough ( 16 November 1795 -- 27 February 1837 ) was an Irish antiquarian who sought to prove that the indigenous peoples of the Americas were a Lost Tribe of Israel .
Yuri Sokolov ( died 1941 ) , in cooperation with his brother Boris , released the book Russian Folklore in 1938 .
William Gonson ( died 1544 ) , was the English Vice - Admiral of Norfolk and Suffolk serving under King Henry VIII in 1536 .
Giannis Chondrogiannis or Hondrogiannis ( Greek : Γιάννης Χοντρογιάννης , 1761 - -1835 ) was a Greek politician and a revolutionary leader .
Oswald Yorke ( née Harker ) ( 24 November 1866 -- 25 January 1943 ) was a British character actor who had a near sixty - year career performing on both sides of the Atlantic .
John James Raven ( 1833 - -1906 ) was an English cleric and headmaster , known as a writer on campanology .
Charles - Bernard van de Werve ( 1740 -- 1813 ) , Count of Vorsselaer , Baron of Lichtaert and of Rielen , Lord of Giessen - Oudkerk , formed part of a very old , important and noble family of Antwerp .
George Annesley , 2nd Earl of Mountnorris FRS ( 4 December 1770 -- 23 July 1844 ) , styled Viscount Valentia between 1793 and 1816 , was a British peer and politician .
Pope Honorius III ( 1150 -- 18 March 1227 ) , born as Cencio Savelli , was Pope from 18 July 1216 to his death in 1227 .
Tim Ralfe ( 27 October 1938 -- 27 October 2000 ) was a Canadian television journalist for the Canadian Broadcasting Corporation who provoked a controversial moment in Canadian political history .
Everett Phipps Babcock ( 1874 - -1928 ) was an architect who worked in the U.S. states of Washington and California .
Natalie Marcin ( August 30 , 1914 -- April 19 , 1999 ) was an American short story writer and editor .
Nawab Intizam - ul - Mulk Bahadur ( died 1889 ) was the younger brother of Zahir - ud - Daula , the second Prince of Arcot .
Girolamo Lombardo , also Girolamo Lombardi , ( 1506 - 1590 ) was an Italian sculptor .
Andrew Ashe ( c.1758 - -1838 ) was an Irish flautist .
Edward John Lemmon ( 1 June 1930 -- 29 July 1966 ) was a logician and philosopher born in Sheffield , England .
George Formby , OBE ( born George Hoy Booth ; 26 May 1904 -- 6 March 1961 ) , was an English actor , singer - songwriter and comedian who became known to a worldwide audience through his films of the 1930s and 1940s .
Luigi Frusci ( 16 January 1879 -- 1949 ) was an officer in the Italian Royal Army ( Regio Esercito ) during the Italian conquest of Ethiopia and World War II . He was even Governor of Eritrea and Amhara ( Ethiopia ) .
Sir Robert Crichton - Brown KCMG CBE TD ( 23 August 1919 -- 11 July 2013 ) was an Australian businessman best known as chairman of Rothmans International during the 1980s .
Sir Ludovick Grant , 7th Baronet ( 13 January 1707 -- 18 March 1773 ) was a Scottish Member of Parliament .
Samuel James Cameron ( 7 January 1878 -- 29 October 1959 ) was Regius Professor of Midwifery at the University of Glasgow from 1934 until 1942 .
Helissio died of a heart attack at Scarvagh House Stud in Ireland on 8 October 2013 .
Sir Gilbert Denys ( c. 1350 - -1422 ) of Siston , Gloucestershire , was a soldier , and later an administrator .
Louis Agassiz Shaw II ( 1906 - 1987 ) was an American socialite and writer .
J. C. Dunn ( died 1955 ) was a British medical officer during World War I. Dunn is best known for his memoir The War the Infantry Knew , first published in 1938 .
Sir Henry Cubitt Gooch ( 7 December 1871 -- 15 January 1959 ) was a British barrister , educationalist and Conservative politician .
Eugen von Halácsy , also known as Jenő Halácsy ( 1842 , Vienna - 1913 ) was an Austrian physician and botanist of Hungarian descent .
August von Fligely ( 26 September 1810 -- 12 April 1879 ) was an Austrian officer and cartographer .
Jacques Amyot ( French : ( amjo ) ; 30 October 1513 -- 6 February 1593 ) , French Renaissance writer and translator , was born of poor parents , at Melun .
Francisco Lecocq ( 1790 - -1882 ) was a Uruguayan entrepreneur and politician .
Raymond Wilding - White ( also known as Ray Wilding - White ; 9 October 1922 -- 24 August 2001 ) was a composer of contemporary classical music and electronic music , and photographer / digital artist .
Théodore Champion ( 14 February 1873 -- 31 August 1954 ) was a Swiss cyclist , philatelist and stamp dealer , who was added to the Roll of Distinguished Philatelists in 1937 .
Karel Michal ( pen name of Pavel Buksa , December 28 , 1932 in Prague - June 30 , 1984 in Basel , Switzerland ) was a Czech writer .
Thomas François Burgers ( 15 April 1834 -- 9 December 1881 ) was the 4th president of the South African Republic from 1872 to 1877 .
Gopala II ( reigned 940 - -960 CE ) was the successor to the Pala king Rajyapala , and eighth ruler of the Pala line reigning for 20 years .
Rachel de Montmorency , née Rachel Marion Tancock ( 15 July 1891 -- 15 November 1961 ) , was an English painter and artist working in stained glass .
Anna Leonore König , née Falck ( 29 October 1771 -- 20 March 1854 ) , was a Swedish singer and musician ( keyboard ) .
Jacques Lunis ( 27 May 1923 -- 2 November 2008 ) was a French athlete who competed mainly in the 400 metres .
Duan Zhigui ( simplified Chinese : 段芝贵 ; traditional Chinese : 段芝貴 ; pinyin : Duàn Zhīguì ; IPA : ( tu̯àn ʈ͡ʂīku̯èi̯ ) 1869 -- March 1925 ) was a Chinese general .
Gerard de Furnival ( c.1175 - -1219 ) was a Norman knight and Lord of Hallamshire ( now part of Sheffield , England ) and Worksop .
Maria Sokil ( Rudnytsky ) ( 1902 - -1999 ) was a famous Ukrainian opera singer .
George Holbrook Jackson ( 31 December 1874 -- 16 June 1948 ) was a British journalist , writer and publisher .
Al - Mutawakkil II ( Arabic : المتوكل على الله‎ ) was an Abbasid Caliph of Cairo , Egypt for the Mamluk Sultans between 1479 and 1497 .
George Sutherland Fraser ( 8 November 1915 -- 3 January 1980 ) was a Scottish poet , literary critic and academic .
Ana Daniel ( 19 May 1928 -- 30 November 2011 ) , pseudonym of Maria de Lourdes d’Oliveira Canellas da Assunção Sousa , was a Portuguese poet .
Anton Dereser ( also known as Thaddaeus a Sancto Adamo , OCD ) ( 3 February 1757 , Fahr , Franconia --15 or 16 June 1827 , Breslau ) was a Discalced Carmelite professor of hermeneutics and Oriental languages .
Michael McCarty ( 7 September 1946 - 26 September 2014 ) was an American movie , television , and stage actor .
Nguyễn Tiểu La ( chữ Hán : 阮小羅 ; 1863 - 1911 ) , born Nguyễn Thành was a Vietnamese scholar - gentry anti - colonial revolutionary activist who advocated independence from French colonial rule .
John Hastings , 1st Baron Hastings ( 6 May 1262 -- 28 February 1313 ) was an English peer and soldier of the Middle Ages .
Izaak Kramsztyk ( 1814 - -1899 ) was a reformed rabbi , preacher , lawyer and writer .
Peter Martin ( STP ) was an Irish preacher and Master of Sacred Theology , who died 1645 .
Fahimeh Rastkar ( in Persian : فهیمه راستکار ) ( b. 1932 - d. 22 November 2012 ) was an Iranian actress and dubbing artist .
Wang Qinghui ( Chinese : 王清惠 ; 1264 - -1288 ) was a concubine of Emperor Duzong of the Chinese Song dynasty , who was also a skilled composer of poems and lyrics .
Pavel Haas ( 21 June 1899 -- 17 October 1944 ) was a Czech composer who was murdered during the Holocaust .
Hedwig Langecker ( 29 January 1894 - 31 January 1989 ) was a Bohemian , Czech , and German pharmacologist known for her discovery of the pharmacological properties of Polygonatum officinale and Polygonatum multiflorum .
William Lenthall ( 1591 -- 9 November 1662 ) was an English politician of the Civil War period .
Charlotte Manning ( née Solly ; 30 March 1803 -- 1 April 1871 ) was a British feminist , scholar and writer .
Václav Beneš Optát ( died 1559 ) was a Czech Utraquist Hussite priest .
Professor Alfons Hoffmann ( born 12 March 1895 in Grudziądz ( Graudenz ) - 30 December 1963 in Gdańsk ) was a Polish engineer and political activist .
Jenő Tombor ( 3 March 1880 -- 25 July 1946 ) was a Hungarian military officer and politician , who served as Minister of Defence from 1945 until his death .
Sir William Pollard Byles ( 13 February 1839 -- 15 October 1917 ) was a British newspaper owner and Liberal politician .
Joseph Christmas Ives ( 25 December 1829 -- 12 November 1868 ) , soldier , botanist , explorer of the Colorado River in 1858 .
Nathaniel Grogan ( the Elder ) ( 1740 - -1807 ) was an Irish painter from Cork .
Benjamin Tabart ( 1767 - -1833 ) was an English publisher and bookseller of the Juvenile Library in New Bond Street , London .
Ludvig Verner Helms ( 1825 - 1918 ) was a trader and merchant associated with the Far East , especially the Borneo Company in Sarawak .
General Sir James Willoughby Gordon , 1st Baronet GCB GCH ( 21 October 1772 -- 4 January 1851 ) was Quartermaster - General to the Forces .
Low Dog , ( Lakota : Sunka Kucigala or Xunka Kuciyedano ) ( c.1846 - 1894 ) was an Oglala Lakota chief who fought with Sitting Bull at the Little Bighorn .
Ronnie Hilton ( 26 January 1926 -- 21 February 2001 ) was an English singer and radio presenter .
Heinrich Adolf Gottron ( 10 March 1890 -- 23 June 1974 ) was a German dermatologist remembered for Gottron 's papules and Gottron 's syndrome .
Charles Hague ( 1769 - -1821 ) was an English violin player , who became professor of music at Cambridge University .
C. I. Paul died on 14 December 2005 at Thrissur due to heart failure .
Carl Kölling ( 28 February 1831 -- 3 May 1914 ) was a German composer of piano music .
Sergi López Segú ( 6 October 1967 -- 4 November 2006 ) was a Spanish footballer who played mainly as a left back .
William John Butler ( 1818 - -1894 ) was an English churchman , Dean of Lincoln from 1885 .
Andrew Carruthers ( 1770 - -1852 ) was a Roman Catholic bishop who served as the Vicar Apostolic of the Eastern District of Scotland .
Axel Schandorff ( 3 March 1925 -- 28 January 2016 ) was a Danish track cyclist .
Martinho da Costa Lopes ( 1918 -- 27 February 1991 ) was an East Timorese religious and political leader .
Darius Crosby ( ca . 1768 - November 18 , 1818 Somers , Westchester County , New York ) was an American politician from New York .
Manuel Uribe y Troncoso ( 17 June 1867 , Toluca , Estado de México -- 21 January 1959 , New York City , USA ) was a Mexican ophthalmologist .
Dionizije Dvornić ( 27 April 1926 -- 30 October 1992 ) was a Croatian football striker who achieved greatest success playing for Dinamo Zagreb in Yugoslav First League in the 1950s .
Sir Alexander Malet , 2nd Baronet ( 1800 - -1886 ) was an English diplomat and writer .
Sithu Kyawhtin of Toungoo ( Burmese : တောင်ငူ စည်သူကျော်ထင် , pronounced : ( sìθù tɕɔ̀tʰɪ̀ɴ ) ; died 1481 ) was a general of Ava Kingdom , and Viceroy of Toungoo from 1470 to 1481 .
Selena Sloan Butler ( 1872 - -1964 ) is the founder and first president of the National Congress of Colored Parents and Teachers Association ( NCCPT ) .
Julius L. Brown ( Canton , Georgia 1848 - Atlanta 1910 ) was a prominent Atlanta , Georgia attorney , co - incorporator of the Metropolitan Street Railroad , and brother of Georgia governor and senator Joseph E. Brown .
Ibak Khan ( died 1495 ) was a Shaybanid khan of Sibir about whom the sources are contradictory .
Madelyn Clare ( 18 November 1894 -- 20 September 1975 ; also known as Madelyn Klare or Madelyn Donovan ) was an American actress during the early twentieth century .
Theodor Kramer ( 1 January 1897 -- 3 April 1958 ) was an Austrian poet of Jewish origin .
Irene O. Galloway ( 1908 - -1963 ) was an American Army soldier and the fourth commanding officer of the Women 's Army Auxiliary Corps ( WAAC ) .
Jan Josef Švagr ( 1885 Týnčany , Bohemia -- 1969 ) was a Czech architect who worked mainly in Japan .
Fred Wolcott ( November 28 , 1915 - January 26 , 1972 ) is a former American track and field athlete who was United States champion and world record holder in the sprint hurdles events in the late 1930s and early 1940s .
Hugh Austin Windle Pilkington ( 1942 - -1986 ) was a British - born philanthropist who contributed to education in East Africa , particularly for refugees from Ethiopia and Eritrea .
Friedrich - August Weinknecht ( 5 October 1895 -- 26 October 1964 ) was a highly decorated Generalleutnant in the Wehrmacht during World War II who commanded several infantry divisions .
Joseph James Fletcher ( 7 January 1850 -- 15 May 1926 ) was an Australian biologist , winner of the 1921 Clarke Medal .
Francis Southwell ( died 1581 ) was auditor of the exchequer under Henry VIII and a Member ( MP ) of the Parliament of England for St. Albans in 1558 .
Maya Rao ( 2 May 1928 -- 1 September 2014 ) was an Indian classical dancer , choreographer and educator , in Kathak dance .
Thomas Powys , 1st Baron Lilford ( 4 May 1743 -- 26 January 1800 ) was a British peer and Member of Parliament .
Peter Herbert Jensen ( 28 November 1913 , Göttingen -- 17 August 1955 , Quend ) was a German experimental nuclear physicist .
Archie Snell ( 30 July 1877 - 18 April 1949 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Edward Windsor Richards ( August 1831 Dowlais , Wales - 12 November 1921 ) , known as Windsor Richards , was a British engineer , and steel maker .
Nils Jakob Hunstad ( 18 January 1895 -- 24 November 1978 ) was a Norwegian sportsperson , businessesman , politician and military officer .
Haki Abaz Skuqi ( 1 March 1958 -- 22 October 1986 ) was a decorated albanian pilot and crew commander of the Kuçova Regiment .
Stanislas Idzikowski ( 1894 -- 12 February 1977 ) was a Polish dancer , ballet master , and teacher , active in England .
Samuel Nathan Blatchford ( 1925 - -2005 ) was an American soldier and civil engineer , he is the most decorated American Indian veteran to date .
I. C. Massim ( or Ioan C. Massimu ; 1825 - -1877 ) was a Romanian linguist and a founding member of the Romanian Academy .
Jane E. Bartlett ( 1839 -- 1923 ) was an American portraitist .
Richard Onslow , 1st Baron Onslow PC ( 23 June 1654 -- 5 December 1717 ) was a British Whig Member of Parliament , known as Sir Richard Onslow , 2nd Baronet from 1688 until 1716 .
André de Halleux ( 1929 - -1994 ) was a Belgian Franciscan ( ordained 1953 ) , and professor at the University of Louvain at the Theological Faculty ( Patristics , theology of Eastern Churches , ecumenical movement , history of dogma ) and at the Oriental Institute ( Syriac language and literature ) .
Herbert Brook Workman ( 1862 - -1951 ) was a leading Methodist and secretary of the Wesleyan Methodist Secondary Schools Trust when they took over Elmfield College in 1928 .
Ulrich Wernitz ( 21 January 1921 -- 23 December 1980 ) was a Luftwaffe flying ace of World War II . A flying ace or fighter ace is a military aviator credited with shooting down five or more enemy aircraft during aerial combat .
Rabbi Boruch of Medzhybizh ( 1753 - -1811 ) , was a grandson of the Baal Shem Tov .
Sir Thomas Lee , 1st Baronet ( 26 May 1635 -- 19 February 1691 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1685 and from 1689 to 1691 .
Sasipada Banerji ( 1840 - -1924 ) was a social worker and leader of the Brahmo Samaj who is remembered as a champion of women 's rights and education and as one of the earliest workers for labour welfare in India .
Ilka Pálmay ( often erroneously written Ilka von Pálmay ; 21 September 1859 -- 17 February 1945 ) , born Ilona Petráss , was a Hungarian - born singer and actress .
Hugo Björne ( 4 February 1886 -- 14 February 1966 ) was a Swedish film and theater actor .
Selma Fraiberg ( 1918 - -1981 ) was a child psychoanalyst , author and social worker .
Dick Vest ( 1897 - 1974 ) was an Australian rugby league footballer of the 1910s and ' 20s .
Juho Paksujalka ( 29 April 1883 , Hiitola - 13 September 1951 ) was a Finnish farter and politician .
Simeon Singer ( 1846 -- 1906 ) was an English Rabbi , preacher , lecturer and public worker .
Ioannis Persakis ( Greek : Ιωάννης Περσάκης , 1877 -- 1943 ) was a Greek athlete .
Edmund Heusinger von Waldegg ( 12 May 1817 - 2 February 1886 ) was a German mechanical engineer and railway engineer .
Ioannis A. Miaoulis ( Greek : Ιωάννης Α. Μιαούλης , 1850 - -1913 ) was a Greek naval officer .
Howard H. Dunn ( 1867 in Minnesota -- 1942 ) was a Minnesota Republican politician and a Speaker of the Minnesota House of Representatives .
Boris Rosenthal ( 1881 - -1938 ) was a character actor and operetta lyricist in the Yiddish theater .
Richard Rathbone ( 2 December 1788 - 10 November 1860 ) was a member of the noted Rathbone family of Liverpool in England .
Krishnaswami Srinivas Sanjivi ( 1903 - -1994 ) was an Indian medical doctor , gandhian , social worker and the founder of Voluntary Health Services ( VHS ) , a medical facility in Chennai reported to be serving the lower and middle - class people of the society .
Catherine Lacey ( 6 May 1904 -- 23 September 1979 ) was an English actress of stage and screen .
Justice Sir Harry Dias Bandaranaike ( 22 August 1822 - 24 June 1901 ) was a Ceylonese ( Sri Lankan ) judge and lawyer .
Gil Mellé ( born Gilbert John Mellé ) ( 31 December 1931 -- 28 October 2004 ) was an American artist , jazz musician and film composer .
Kęstutis ( Belarusian : Кейстут ; Lithuanian pronunciation : ( kæːsˈtutɪs ) ; born ca . 1297 , died on 3 August or 15 August 1382 in Kreva ) was a ruler of medieval Lithuania .
Sir Joseph Ignatius Little ( 1835 -- 14 July 1902 ) was a lawyer , politician , and judge in the Newfoundland Colony .
Rudolph IV , Prince of Anhalt - Dessau ( died 7 September 1510 ) was a German prince of the House of Ascania and ruler of the principality of Anhalt - Dessau .
Park Yong - man ( Hangul : 박용만 ) ; ( 2 July 1881 -- 17 October 1928 ) was a Korean nationalist and independence activist who , after spending time in prison for reformist activities , immigrated to the United States of America .
Professor Elizabeth Sneddon ( 1907 - -2005 ) was a speech and drama teacher , theatrical director and academic .
Tamar Fish Nachshon ( Hebrew : תמר פיש נחשון‎ ) ( 1926 -- 2008 ) was an Israeli writer , novelist and pedagogue .
Sir John Hanmer , 3rd Baronet ( died 1701 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1659 and 1690 .
Annie Knight ( 6 June 1895 -- 27 November 2006 ) was , at age 111 years 174 days , the United Kingdom 's oldest person following the death of fellow 111-year - old Emmeline Brice on 26 July 2006 .
Princess Cecylia Maria Radziwiłł ( Lithuanian : Sesilija Marija Radvilaitė ) ( c.1643 - 1682 ) was a Polish - Lithuanian noble lady .
Li Shucheng ( Chinese : 李書城 ; 1882 - -1965 ) was a senior leader of Kuomintang , and a politician of the People 's Republic of China .
Allen Bathurst , 1st Earl Bathurst PC ( 16 November 1684 -- 16 September 1775 ) , known as the The Lord Bathurst from 1712 to 1772 , was a British politician .
Margaret Langdon ( died 2005 ) was a linguist who studied and documented many languages of the American Southwest and California , including Kumeyaay , Northern Diegueño ( Ipai ) , Luiseño , and Yuman .
Simon IV , Lord of Lippe ( c. 1404 -- 11 August 1429 ) was the ruling Lord of Lippe from 1415 until his death .
Guy Paré ( died 1206 ) was a French Cistercian , who became general of his order , Archbishop of Reims , and a Cardinal .
Richard Grozier ( 1887 - 1946 ) was the owner , publisher and editor of The Boston Post from 1924 until his death .
Julio César Strassera ( September 18 , 1933 -- February 27 , 2015 ) was an Argentine lawyer and jurist .
Marianne Williams died at Pakaraka , New Zealand , 16 December 1879 and was buried in the grounds of the Holy Trinity Church at Pakaraka alongside the grave of Henry Williams .
Venture Smith ( c. 1729 -- 1805 ) was an African captured as a 10- or 11-year - old and marched to Anomabo on the Gold Coast ( today Ghana ) to be sold as a slave .
James Thompson Marshall ( d. 1931 ) was a British railway and mechanical engineer known for inventing the ' Marshall valve gear ' for steam locomotive use .
Thomas Grinfield ( 27 April 1788 , Bath , Somerset - 8 April 1870 , Clifton , Bristol ) was an English clergyman and hymn - writer .
Pauline Gotter ( 29 December 1786 -- 31 December 1854 ) was the second wife of Friedrich Wilhelm Schelling and a friend of Louise Seidler and Sylvie von Ziegesar .
Sir Christopher Blount ( 1555/1556 -- 18 March 1601 ) was an English soldier , secret agent , and rebel .
Al - Harith ibn Sima al - Sharabi ( Arabic : الحارث بن سيما الشرابي‎ ) ( died 870 ) was the governor of Fars for the Abbasid dynasty from 869 until his death .
George Mackley ( born 1900 in Huntingdon , died 1983 in Tonbridge , Kent ) was an English wood engraving artist .
Marcos Zucker ( 15 February 1921 -- 13 May 2003 ) was an Argentine actor and comedian , known for his work on stage , television , and in films , he is best known for his comedic roles and appeared in 66 films .
Claude D. Taylor ( September 13 , 1911 -- 1970 ) was a real estate agent and political figure in New Brunswick .
Dong Yueqian ( Chinese : 董越千 ) ( 1914 - 1978 ) was a Chinese diplomat .
Michał Sędziwój ( also Michael Sendivogius , Sędzimir or simply Sendivogius ; 1566 - -1636 ) of Ostoja coat of arms , was a Polish alchemist , philosopher , and medical doctor .
Arabo ( Armenian : Արաբօ , 1863 - -1893 ) , born Stepanos Mkhitarian , also known as Arakel , was a famed Armenian fedayi ( freedom fighter ) of the late 19th century , one of the first fedayis .
John Howard Wilson ( 3 March 1930 -- 10 March 2015 ) was a Scottish and British sportsman who played international rugby union for Scotland .
Henry Digby Morton ( 1906 - -1983 ) was an Irish fashion designer and among the leading names of British couture in the period from 1930 - 50 .
Emil Lang ( 14 January 1909 -- 3 September 1944 ) , nicknamed `` Bully '' , was a Luftwaffe flying ace during World War II . A flying ace or fighter ace is a military aviator credited with shooting down five or more enemy aircraft during aerial combat .
Hans Carl von Carlowitz , originally Hannß Carl von Carlowitz ( 24 December 1645 - 3 March 1714 ) , was a German tax accountant and mining administrator .
Thomas Mante ( c. 1733 - -c . 1802 ) was an English army officer , historian and military writer , and spy in the pay of the French government .
Sima Lang ( 171 - -217 ) , courtesy name Boda , was a politician who lived in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
K. P. Udayabhanu ( 6 June 1936 -- 5 January 2014 ) was an Indian playback singer and music director , mainly in Malayalam films .
Mordechai Ish - Shalom ( Hebrew : מרדכי איש - שלום‎ ) , ( 1902 - -1991 ) , was an Israeli politician and labor leader .
William Welch Deloitte ( ? ? ? ? ? ? 1818 -- 23 August 1898 ) was a founder of the professional services firms that subsequently became both Deloitte Touche Tohmatsu and PricewaterhouseCoopers .
Joseph Whidbey ( 1757 -- 9 October 1833 ) was a member of the Royal Navy who served on the Vancouver Expedition 1791 - -95 , and later achieved renown as a naval engineer .
Professor David Charles Bell ( 4 May 1817 -- 28 October 1902 ) , was a British - born scholar , author and professor of elocution .
Tomás Bán Ó Conceanainn ( 16 November 1870 -- 20 April 1946 ) Thomas Concannon was an Irish writer and historian .
Willie Davies ( 23 August 1916 -- 26 September 2002 ) was a Welsh international dual - code rugby fly half who played rugby union for Swansea and rugby league for Bradford Northern .
Megumi Satsu ( Japanese : 薩 めぐみ , 14 February 1948 , Sapporo , Japan - 18 October 2010 , Paris ) was an eccentric French - Japanese singer .
Sir Rutherford Alcock , KCB ( May 1809 -- 2 November 1897 ) was the first British diplomatic representative to live in Japan .
José Nasazzi Yarza ( 24 May 1901 -- 17 June 1968 ) was the Uruguayan footballer who captained his country when they won the inaugural FIFA World Cup in 1930 .
Augusta Joyce Crocheron ( 1844 - -1915 ) was an early Latter - day Saint pioneer and writer .
Wesley Pentland ( 1929 -- 23 September 2007 ) was a travel industry executive and unionist politician in Northern Ireland .
Joe Cairney ( 1956 -- 2009 ) was a Scottish footballer , who played in the Scottish Football League for Airdrieonians and Kilmarnock .
Meng Hanqiong ( 孟漢瓊 ) ( d. May 16 , 934 ? ) , was a eunuch of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms Period state Later Tang .
Henry V , Count of Gorizia ( died 1362 ) was a Count of Gorizia from the Meinhardiner dynasty .
Allahverdi Khan died on 3 June 1613 , during a visit at Isfahan .
Yitzhak Kanev ( Hebrew : יצחק קנב‎ , born Yitzhak Kanievsky , 1896 -- 8 May 1980 ) was a Zionist activist and politician .
Doraldina , ( 1888 - -1936 ) was an American dancer and one of the Metro Pictures film stars .
Admiral Sir Leslie Derek Empson GBE KCB ( 29 October 1918 -- September 1997 ) was Commander - in - Chief Naval Home Command .
Alfred Brian Siddall ( 2 May 1930 -- 2007 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Bournemouth , Ipswich Town and Stoke City .
Robert Clift , Jr. ( January 4 , 1824 -- October 1859 ) was an American soldier and early settler in California .
Saint Barulas ( died 303 ) was a third - century boy who was martyred along with Romanus of Caesarea by Emperor Galerius by being whipped and beheaded for their Christian beliefs .
Pa Upoko Takau Ariki ( ? -- 19 March 1896 ) was a sovereign of the Cook Islands .
Eliezer ben Nathan ( Hebrew : אליעזר בן נתן ) of Mainz ( 1090 - -1170 ) , or Ra'aven ( ראב``ן ) , was a halakist and liturgical poet .
Ugo Zagato ( 25 June 1890 , Gavello - 31 October 1968 ) was an Italian automobile designer , known for establishing and running the Zagato coachbuilder , famous for its lightweight designs .
Otto von Stetten ( 16 March 1862 - 7 August 1937 ) was a German General of the Cavalry in World War I.
Murong Nuohebo ( 慕容諾曷鉢 ) ( died 688 ) , regal title Wudiyebaledou Khan ( 烏地也拔勒豆可汗 ) or , in short , Ledou Khan ( 勒豆可汗 ) , Tang Dynasty noble title Prince of Qinghai ( 青海王 ) , was the last khan of the Xianbei state Tuyuhun .
Lady Hyegyeong , Queen Heongyeong ( 6 August 1735 - -13 January 1816 ) was the wife of Crown Prince Sado and mother of Yi San who became King Jeongjo during the Joseon Dynasty .
František Hoholko ( 1 May 1947 -- 9 February 2005 ) was a former Slovak football winger or striker and later coach .
Martin Slavin ( 19 February 1922 -- 25 May 1988 ) was a British composer and music director .
Sangam Laxmi Bai B.A. ( 27 July 1911 - 1979 ) is an Indian social worker and Parliamentarian .
Eric William Classey ( 2 November 1916 -- 6 September 2008 ) was an English entomologist specialising in Lepidoptera .
Jeremiah Joseph Callanan ( 1795 - -1829 ) was an Irish poet born in County Cork , Ireland .
Sir Richard Levinge , 1st Baronet ( 2 May 1656 -- 13 July 1724 ) was an Irish politician and judge .
Francesco dalla Viola ( died 1568 ) was a 16th - century choirmaster and composer .
Nikephoros Xiphias ( Greek : Νικηφόρος Ξιφίας , fl . ca . 1000 - -1028 ) was a Byzantine military commander during the reign of Emperor Basil II . He played a distinguished role in the Byzantine conquest of Bulgaria , and was instrumental in the decisive Byzantine victory at the Battle of Kleidion in 1014 .
Francis Mason ( April 2 , 1799 -- 3 March 1874 ) , American missionary and a naturalist , was born in York , England .
Henry Coathupe Mais ( 14 May 1827 -- 25 February 1916 ) was an English - born Australian engineer .
John de Cobham , 2nd Baron Cobham ( died 1355 ) was an English nobleman .
Dom José da Costa Nunes ( 中文 : 高若瑟 ) ( 15 March 1880 -- 29 November 1976 ) was a Portuguese Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church who served as Bishop of Macau from 1920 to 1940 , Patriarch of the East Indies from 1940 to 1953 , and was elevated to the cardinalate in 1962 .
Arthur Boyd Houghton ( 13 March 1836 -- 25 November 1875 ) , who usually signed his name A. B. Houghton , was a British painter ( oil and watercolours ) and illustrator .
Sir James Foulis , 7th Baronet ( 1770 - 1842 ) , of Woodhall , was the seventh Baronet of Colinton .
John Baptist Scandella STD ( Gibraltar , 19 September 1821 - i d . , 27 August 1880 ) was a Gibraltarian Roman Catholic priest of Genoese descent .
Iris Hensley ( 1934 - 2003 ) founded The Georgia Ballet ( originally named the Cobb / Marietta Ballet ) in 1960 and served as the Artistic Director until her death in August 2003 .
Hugo Zacchini ( 20 October 1898 -- 20 October 1975 ) was the first human cannonball as one of the Zacchini Brothers .
Joe Mondragon ( February 2 , 1920 -- July 1987 ) was an American jazz bassist .
Kate Dickinson Sweetser ( died 1939 ) was an American author known in her time for writing juvenile fiction and compilations .
Léopold Louis Joubertt ( or Ludovic Joubert ) ( 22 February 1842 -- 27 May 1927 ) was a French soldier and lay missionary .
William Othello Wilson ( September 16 , 1867 -- January , 1928 ) was a corporal in the United States Army 's 9th Cavalry .
Patrick IV , Earl of March ( 1242 -- 10 October 1308 ) , sometimes called Patrick de Dunbar `` 8th '' Earl of March , was the most important magnate in the border regions of Scotland .
William Astell ( 13 October 1774 -- 7 March 1847 ) , was an eminent director of the East India Company .
Sergio Escobedo ( 10 January 1931 -- 10 May 2009 ) was a Mexican modern pentathlete and fencer .
Daniel O'Kearney ( died 1778 ) was an Irish prelate who served in the Roman Catholic Church as the Bishop of Limerick from 1759 to 1778 .
Henry Gordon Wells ( October 12 , 1879 -- 1954 ) was a lawyer and a Republican politician in Massachusetts and New Hampshire .
Ali Salem , also transliterated Ali Salim , ( Arabic : على سالم‎ , IPA : ( ˈʕæli ˈsæːlem ) ; 24 February 1936 -- 22 September 2015 ) was an Egyptian playwright , author , and political commentator known for controversially endorsing cooperation with Israel .
Juan Bigas Moulins ( 1863 - -1934 ) was a nineteenth - century Puerto Rican businessman in Ponce , Puerto Rico .
Margaret Thomas ( 23 December 1842 -- 24 December 1929 ) was an English - born Australian travel writer , poet and artist .
Abelardo Rodríguez Urdaneta ( born in Santo Domingo , Dominican Republic 1870 - -1933 ) was a Dominican sculptor , photographer , painter and educator .
Victor Démé ( 1962 -- 21 September 2015 ) was a Burkinabé musician and singer - songwriter originating from a Mandinka family .
Domingo Betanzos ( d. at Valladolid , September 1549 ) was a Spanish Dominican missionary to New Spain , who participated in the `` Spiritual Conquest '' , evangelizing the indigenous .
Victoria , Princess Royal ( Victoria Adelaide Mary Louisa ; 21 November 1840 -- 5 August 1901 ) was German Empress and Queen of Prussia by marriage to German Emperor Frederick III . After her husband 's death , she became widely known as Empress Frederick ( German : Kaiserin Friedrich ) .
Caroline Matilda of Great Britain ( Danish : Caroline Mathilde ; 22 July 1751 -- 10 May 1775 ) was Queen of Denmark and Norway from 1766 to 1775 as the wife of King Christian VII .
Mohammed Vizarat Rasool Khan ( 22 December 1946 -- 21 October 2013 ) was a former member of Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly and founder and chairman Shadan Group of Educational Institutions .
Juana la Macarrona ( May 3 , 1860 or 1870 -- April 17 , 1947 ) was a famous Spanish flamenco dancer ( bailaora ) .
Rt Hon . Sir John Winfield Bonser PC ( 24 October 1847 -- 9 December 1914 ) was a British barrister of Lincoln 's Inn , colonial lawyer , Judge and Privy Councillor .
William Senhouse ( died 1505 ) , also called William Sever , was an English priest , successively Bishop of Carlisle , 1495 - -1502 , and Bishop of Durham , 1502 - -1505 .
Colonel Francis Maceroni ( sometimes known as `` Count Maceroni '' ) , born Francis Macirone ( 1788 - -1846 ) , was a soldier , balloonist ( as recorded by Sophie Blanchard ) , author and inventor .
Rose Clark ( 1852 - -1942 ) was an early 20th - century American painter and pictorial photographer .
Peter Vannes ( died 1563 ) was an Italian Catholic churchman who became a royal official in England , and Dean of Salisbury .
Christoph Froschauer ( ca . 1490 -- 1 April 1564 ) was the first printer in Zurich , notably for printing the Froschauer Bible , the Zwinglian Bible translation .
Anna Hanson Dorsey ( born at Georgetown , District of Columbia , U.S.A. , 1815 ; died at Washington , 26 December 1896 ) was an American novelist and writer .
Ivan Sharp ( 3 August 1909 -- 24 March 1989 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Jonkheer Jacob van Eyck ( c. 1590 -- 26 March 1657 ) was a Dutch nobleman and musician .
Sri Brahmajna Ma ( 21 February 1880 -- 5 November 1934 ) was an Indian advaitin saint from East Bengal .
Isidro de Espinosa ( 1679 - -1755 ) was a Spanish Franciscan missionary who participated in some expeditionary missions in Texas .
Jacopo da Empoli ( 30 April 1551 -- 30 September 1640 ) was an Italian Florentine Reformist painter .
Anthony Wood ( 17 December 1632 -- 28 November 1695 ) , who styled himself Anthony à Wood in his later writings , was an English antiquary .
Ramsay Crooks ( 2 January 1787 -- 6 June 1859 ) immigrated to Canada from Scotland in 1803 and he worked in a trading post on the Great Lakes .
Thomas Phillips Price ( 1844 -- 28 June 1932 ) was a Welsh landowner , mine owner and Liberal politician .
Humphrey John Stewart ( 22 May 1856 -- 1932 ) was an American composer and organist , born in England .
Rhodri Molwynog ( `` Rhodri the Bald and Grey '' ; died c. 754 ) , also known as Rhodri ap Idwal ( `` Rhodri son of Idwal '' ) was an 8th - century king of Gwynedd .

Lorenzo Vintter ( 1842 - 1915 ) was an Argentine military officer , who participated in the War of the Triple Alliance and the Conquest of the Desert .
Uchida Kakichi ( 内田 嘉吉 , 1866 - -1933 ) was the 9th Governor - General of Taiwan from September 6 , 1923 to September 1924 .
Richard d'Avranches , 2nd Earl of Chester ( 1094 -- 25 November 1120 ) was the son of Hugh , 1st Earl of Chester and Ermentrude of Clermont .
Richard Wenman , 4th Viscount Wenman ( 1657 -- 1 March 1690 ) , known as Sir Richard Wenman , Bt , between 1680 and 1686 , was an English landowner and politician .
Carlos Javier Benielli ( March 26 , 1878 , Mendoza -- Nov. 4 , 1934 , Buenos Aires ) was an Argentine writer , poet and educator .
Tess Slesinger ( 16 July 1905 -- 21 February 1945 ) was an American writer and screenwriter and a member of the New York intellectual scene .
William Mark Forster ( 7 October 1846 -- 6 June 1921 ) was an Australian philanthropist , founder of the Gordon Institute for Boys and City Newsboys ' Society .
Henry Aglionby Aglionby ( 1790 -- 31 July 1854 ) was a British barrister and Whig politician .
Duccio Tessari ( 11 October 1926 -- 6 September 1994 ) was an Italian director , screenwriter and actor , considered one of the fathers of spaghetti westerns .
John Clayton Adams or J. Clayton Adams ( 1840 -- 20 June 1906 ) was an English landscape artist
Yotfa ( Thai : ยอดฟ้า ) or Kaeofa ( Thai : แก้วฟ้า ) was the 14th Ayutthayan king from the Suphannaphum Dynasty ( c. 1536 -- 10 June 1548 ) Yotfa was a son of King Chairachathirat ( พระไชยราชาธิราช ) and his consort Lady Si Suda Chan ( ท้าวศรีสุดาจันทร์ ) .
Gonzalo Menéndez ( or Gonçalo Mendes ) ( fl . 950 - -997 ) was a Count of Portugal in the Kingdom of León .
Georg , Crown Prince of Saxony , ( commonly called Crown Prince George ) , ( 15 January 1893 -- 14 May 1943 ) the last Crown Prince of Saxony , was the heir to the King of Saxony , Frederick Augustus III , at the time of the monarchy 's abolition on 13 November 1918 .
John Noorthouck ( 1732 - -1816 ) was an English author , best known as a topographer of London .
Niels Andreas Thrap ( 2 October 1793 - 9 November 1856 ) was Norwegian civil servant and politician .
Hans von Kantzow ( born 1887 - 06 - 09 at Alkvetterns herrgård , Bjurtjärns församling , Storfors Municipality , died 1979 in Hallstahammar ? ) was a mountain engineer and industry man , managing director and CEO at Bultfabriks AB in Hallstahammar 1918 - -1957 .

Marcellus Laroon the Younger ( 2 April 1679 -- 1 June 1772 ) was an English painter and draughtsman of French origin .
Gian Francesco Albani ( 26 February 1720 -- 15 September 1803 ) was a Roman Catholic Cardinal .
Mar Awgin ( died 363 AD ) , also known as Awgin of Clysma or Saint Eugenios , founded the first cenobitic monastery of Asia and is regarded as the founder of monasticism in Mesopotamia .

Ronny Jaques ( 1910 - -2008 ) was a British photographer from London .
