Anna Mendelssohn ( born Anna Mendleson , 1948 -- 15 November 2009 ) , who wrote under the name Grace Lake , was a British writer , poet and political activist .
Franz Olah ( 13 March 1910 - 4 September 2009 ) was an Austrian politician who served as the country 's Interior Minister from 1963 until 1964 as a member of the Social Democratic Party ( SPÖ ) .
Derek Prag ( 6 August 1923 -- 20 January 2010 ) was a British Member of the European Parliament for Hertfordshire .
Sir Richard Wynn , 2nd Baronet ( 1588 -- 19 July 1649 ) was an English courtier and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1649 .
Phillip Blashki ( 21 February 1837 -- 21 October 1916 ) was a Polish immigrant to Australia who rose to be a successful businessman , magistrate , JP , holder of many positions of public responsibility and associated with numerous community and charitable events in Melbourne .
Moti Abba Bok'a was a King of the Gibe Kingdom of Jimma ( reigned 1859 - -1862 ) .
Sir Henry Middleton ( died 1613 ) was a sea captain and adventurer .
Priscilla Napier ( 5 October 1908 -- 10 October 1998 ) was an English author , specializing in biography .
Anders Beggerud ( 22 June 1894 , Sandsvær -- 22 June 1957 ) was a Norwegian civil servant during the Nazi regime .
Cecily Brownstone ( 18 April 1909 in Plum Coulee , Manitoba , Canada -- 30 August 2005 in New York City , New York ) , was a food writer , who wrote several cookbooks and articles about food over a period of 39 years .
Łucja Frey or Łucja Frey - Gottesman ( November 3 , 1889 in Lwów -- 1942 ? ) was a Polish physician and neurologist , known for describing the syndrome later named after her .
Jean - Baptiste Tholmé , ( 11 May 1753 -- 8 September 1805 ) , was a general of brigade in the French Revolutionary Wars and Napoleonic Wars .
Louis - Napoléon Bonaparte ( 20 April 1808 -- 9 January 1873 ) was the only President ( 1848 - -52 ) of the French Second Republic and , as Napoleon III , the Emperor ( 1852 - -70 ) of the Second French Empire .
Orlando Ramón Agosti ( 22 August 1924 -- 7 October 1997 ) was an Argentine general , Commander - in - Chief of the Argentine Air Force from 1976 to 1979 .
Charles Howard , 3rd Earl of Nottingham ( 25 December 1610 -- 26 April 1681 ) was the son of Charles Howard , 1st Earl of Nottingham by his second wife , the former Margaret Stuart .
Robert Grant Haliburton Q.C. , D.C.L. ( 3 June 1831 -- 6 March 1901 ) was a Canadian lawyer and anthropologist .
Allen Hutchinson ( 8 January 1855 -- 28 July 1929 London ) was an English sculptor .
Angela Baddeley , CBE ( 4 July 1904 -- 22 February 1976 ) was an English stage and television actress , best - remembered for her role as household cook Mrs. Bridges in the period drama Upstairs , Downstairs .
Mary Prince ( c. 1788-after 1833 ) was born in Devonshire Parish , Bermuda , to an enslaved family of African descent .
Sir Henry de Baliol of Cavers ( died 1246 ) was Chamberlain of Scotland .
Azeline Hearne ( 1825 - 1890 ? ) , was an American slave who was freed near the end of her life , and became famous for the numerous lawsuits brought against her during the Reconstruction era .
Humphrey Gower ( 1638 - -1711 ) was an English clergyman and academic , Master of Jesus College , Cambridge and then St. John 's College , Cambridge , and Lady Margaret 's Professor of Divinity .
Eva Charlotta Wersäll ( née Lewenhaupt , 12 May 1858 -- 4 April 1924 ) was a Swedish noblewoman , a daughter of Count Carl Gustaf Lewenhaupt and Charlotta Elisabet von Essen .
Clarissa Maria Young Dougall ( 10 December 1849 -- 30 April 1935 ) was a Utah suffragist and a member of the general presidency of what is today the Young Women organization of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints ( LDS Church ) .
Alan Burgess ( 1 February 1915 -- 10 April 1998 ) was an RAF pilot and English author who wrote several biographical and non - fiction books between the 1950s and the 1970s .
Colin Stanley Gum ( 1924 -- 29 April 1960 ) was an Australian astronomer who catalogued emission nebulae in the southern sky at the Mount Stromlo Observatory using wide field photography .
Rudolf Carl ( 19 June 1899 -- 15 January 1987 ) was an Austrian actor who appeared in more than 150 German language films between 1934 and 1969 .
Gidske Anderson ( 4 November 1921 -- 19 October 1993 ) was a Norwegian journalist and a member of the Labour Party .
Casimir II the Just ( Polish : Kazimierz II Sprawiedliwy ) ( 1138 -- 5 May 1194 ) was a Lesser Polish Duke at Wiślica during 1166 - -1173 , and at Sandomierz after 1173 .
Edmund Simpson ( b. England , 1784 ; d. New York City , 31 July 1848 ) was an actor and theater manager .
Ray Whitford ( 5 November 1889 -- 12 January 1970 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with University .
Nicola Paone ( 5 October 1915 - 25 December 2003 ) was an Italian - American singer , songwriter , and restaurateur , best known for his humorous , chart - topping songs about the joys and hardships of Italian immigrants in America .
Isaac Harby ( 1788 - 1828 ) was an early 19th - century teacher , playwright , literary critic , journalist and newspaper editor and advocate of reforms in Judaism in Charleston , South Carolina .
Sir John Thomas Jones , 1st Baronet ( 25 March 1783 -- 26 February 1843 ) was a British major - general in the Royal Engineers who played a leading engineering role in a number of European campaigns of the early nineteenth century .
Philip Mauro ( 1859 - 1952 ) was a lawyer and author .
Wenceslaus of Żagań ( Polish : Wacław żagański ) ( ca . 1434 -- 29 April 1488 ) was a Duke of Żagań - Przewóz since 1439 ( with his brothers as co - rulers until 1449 ) , from 1449 Duke of Przewóz ( as co - ruler of his younger brother ) .
José Matanhy de Saldanha ( Konkani : Juze Matani de Saldanea , जुझे मातानी द सालदाञ ; 24 October 1948 -- 21 March 2012 ) was a Goan social activist and school teacher , who campaigned for Goan identity , values , and culture .
`` Katır '' Cemil Gürgen Erlertürk ( 1918 -- 3 May 1970 ) was a Turkish footballer and Sailplane pilot
Edward Howard , 1st Baron Howard of Escrick ( died 24 April 1675 ) was a British nobleman and Parliamentarian .
Joseph Chatt , CBE FRS ( 6 November 1914 -- 19 May 1994 ) was a renowned British researcher in the area of inorganic and organometallic chemistry .
Aleksandr Fyodorovich Rittikh or Alexander Rittich ( Russian : Александр Фёдорович Риттих ) ( 1831 -- 1914 ? ) was an Imperial Russian general , cartographer , ethnographer and journalist , adherent of the Panslavism .
Oneal Moore ( 1931- 1965 ) was the first black deputy sheriff for the Washington Parish Sheriff 's Office in Varnado , Louisiana .
Joyce Bath ( born 27 February 1925 in Kangaroo Flat , Victoria , Australia - died 19 March 2006 in Melbourne , Australia ) was an Australian cricket player .
Jean Morton ( 1921 - 26 May 2012 ) was a British television announcer .
Emperor Wu of Southern Qi ( ( 南)齊武帝 ) ( 440 - -493 ) , personal name Xiao Ze ( 蕭賾 ) , courtesy name Xuanyuan ( 宣遠 ) , nickname Long'er ( 龍兒 ) , was the second emperor of the Chinese Southern Qi Dynasty .
Lionel Ngakane ( 17 July 1920 -- 26 November 2003 ) was a South African filmmaker and actor .
Vic Hershkowitz ( 5 October 1918 -- 23 June 2008 ) was a dominant handball player who played from the early 1940s to the early 1960s .
Kobong soensanim ( Korean : 고봉선사 , Hanja : 高峯禪師 , 1890 - -1962 ) , the 77th Patriarch in his teaching lineage , was a Korean Zen master .
Harold Alfred Manhood ( 1904 - 1991 ) , who for much of his life lived in a converted railway carriage in the Sussex countryside , was renowned for his imaginative short stories .
David Armitage Bannerman OBE , MA , SD ( Cantab ) , Hon . LL.D. ( Glasgow ) , FRSE , FZS ( 1886 -- 6 April 1979 ) was a British ornithologist .
Sir William Whitla ( 15 September 1851 -- 1933 ) was an Irish physician and politician .
Maniben Kara ( 1905 - 1979 ) was an Indian social worker and trade unionist .
Thomas Mellish ( 1773 -- 29 July 1837 in Uxbridge , Middlesex ) was an English amateur cricketer who made 52 known appearances in major cricket matches between 1791 and 1815 .
Marie d'Alençon ( 29 March 1373 -- 1417 ) was a French noblewoman , a Princess of the Blood , and the wife of John VII of Harcourt , Count of Harcourt and of Aumale , Viscount of Châtellerault , Baron of Elbeuf , of Mézières , of Lillebone , of La Saussaye .
Barjik ( died 731 ) was a Khazar prince who flourished in the late 720s .
José Pedro Varela y Berro ( 19 March 1845 - 24 October 1879 ) was an Uruguayan sociologist , journalist , politician , and educator .
Beatrice Dawson ( 26 January 1908 -- 16 April 1976 ) was a British costume designer who was nominated for an Academy Award , as well as three BAFTA nominations .
Joseph Effner ( February 4 , 1687 ( baptized ) -- February 23 , 1745 ) was a German architect and decorator .
Giselda Zani ( b. Italy , 1909 -- Argentina , 1975 ) was a Uruguayan poet , short story writer and art critic of Italian origin .
Emma Elizabeth Thoyts ( 1860 - -1949 ) , aka Mrs. John Hauntenville Cope , was an English palaeographer , historian and genealogist .
Arthur Hildersham ( 1563 - -1632 ) was an English clergyman , a Puritan and nonconforming preacher .
Abderrahmane Sbai ( Arabic : عبد الرحمان السباعي‎ -- born 1940 , Fes -- died 22 October 2010 , Rabat ) was a Moroccan politician and civil servant .
Sir Thomas Ryves ( c.1583 - 1652 ) was an English civilian .
Charles Haskins Townsend , Sc . D. ( 1859 - -1944 ) was an American zoologist .
Daniel Damásio Ascensão Filipe ( 1925 in Boa Vista Island , Cape Verde - 1964 ) was a Cape Verdean poet and journalist .
Konstantin Čomu ( 1865 - 1952 ) , often credited as Kosta Chomu ( Macedonian Cyrillic : Константин Чому ) or Konstantin Comu was Vlach ( Aromanian people ) cinema operator , first in Bitola , Macedonia .
Lü Yin ( 呂諲 ) ( 712 - -762 ) , formally Count Su of Xuchang ( 須昌肅伯 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reign of Emperor Suzong .
Peter Lindahl ( 1712 in Karlskrona -- 19 December 1792 in Ånstad , Örebro ) , was a Swedish stage actor and theatre director .
Gabrio Piola ( 15 July 1794 -- 1850 ) was an Italian mathematician and physicist , member of the Lombardo Institute of Science , Letters and Arts .
Howard Fowles ( 24 January 1894 -- 17 May 1973 ) was an Australian politician .
Erwin Ramsdell Goodenough ( 1893 - -1965 ) was a scholar in the history of religion .
Benjamin Marten ( c.1690 - -1752 ) was an English physician from `` Theobald 's Row '' near Red Lyon Square , Holborn , and one of several sons of a tailor .
Ted Croner ( 1922 - -2005 ) was an American photographer , described as an influential member of the New York school of photography during the 1940s and 1950s .
Amy Fawsitt ( 1836 - -December 1876 ) also known as Mrs. Menzies , was an English actress .
Evelyn Barron , née Bock ( 24 November 1898 -- 17 January 1985 ) , an Australian politician , was a member of the New South Wales Legislative Council from 1963 to 1976 representing the Labor Party .
Mamia III Dadiani ( Georgian : მამია III დადიანი ; died 31 January 1533 ) was a member of the House of Dadiani and eristavi ( `` duke '' ) of Odishi , that is , Mingrelia , in western Georgia from 1512 until his death .
Sergey Ivanovich Smirnov ( Russian : Серге́й Ива́нович Смирно́в ) , 12 April 1953 -- 8 November 2006 , was a Russian artist .
Tom Hanlin ( 28 August 1907 -- 7 April 1953 ) was a Scottish fiction writer , known for writing a number of novels which were influential and sold widely .
William Carr Crofts ( 1846 - -1894 ) was an English architect and entrepreneur who was a photographic pioneer .
Mosko Alkalai ( 10 March 1931 -- 1 April 2008 ) was an Israeli stage and film actor , a Jew born in Romania .
Ma Ying Piu ( Chinese 馬應彪 ; Xiangshan County , Guangdong , 1864 - 1944 ) was a Chinese businessman who founded Sincere Department Store in Hong Kong in 1900 .
Giovanni Costa ( 15 October 1826 -- 31 January 1903 ) , often known as Nino Costa , was an Italian landscape painter and patriotic revolutionary .
Lavoslav Horvat ( Croatian pronunciation : ( lâʋoslaʋ xǒrʋat ) ; 27 September 1901 - 4 October 1989 ) was a Croatian architect .
Richard von Foregger ( 27 June 1872 -- 18 January 1960 ) was an Austrian - American chemist , manufacturer and Olympic swimmer .
George Hollingsworth ( 1813 - -1882 ) was an artist in Massachusetts in the 19th century .
Maharani Chimnabai ( 1872 -- 23 August 1958 ) , also known as Chimnabai II , was the second wife of Sayajirao Gaekwad and Maharani of Baroda .
Prime Defender ( 30 March 2004 -- 24 July 2012 ) was a British Thoroughbred racehorse .
Robert Roland Hughes MB ChB MD FRCP ( 1911 - 1991 ) was a British neurologist and pioneer of Electroencephalography and neurology .
Henry Garton ( 1600 -- 1641 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1641 .
Giuseppe Pistocchi ( 1744 - -1814 ) was an Italian architect of the Neoclassic style , active mainly near his natal city of Faenza .
Sir Thomas Cheek or Cheke ( died March 1659 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in every parliament between 1604 and 1653 .
Dr. Autrey Nell Wiley ( 27 May 1901 -- 28 May 1990 ) was an American literary critic and professor .
James Marmion Gilmor Carroll ( 23 October 1884 -- 1 September 1962 ) was a prominent Anglo - Irish Roman Catholic and a businessman .
Michelagnolo Galilei ( sometimes spelled Michelangelo ; 18 December 1575 -- 3 January 1631 ) was an Italian composer and lutenist of the late Renaissance and early Baroque eras , active mainly in Bavaria and Poland .
Grigor Marzuantsi ( Armenian : Գրիգոր Մարզվանեցի ; 1662 in Marzuan city in historical Little Hayq in Western Armenia - 1730 ) was an Armenian book printer and engraver during the years 1705 - 1730 .
Roger Downes ( died 1638 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1601 and from 1621 to 1622 .
( Alfred ) Richard Twentyman ( 1903 - -1979 ) was an English architect based in Wolverhampton .
Urbain de Florit de La Tour de Clamouze , SS.CC . , ( born Alphonse de Florit de La Tour de Clamouze ; 7 October 1794 -- 2 August 1868 ) was a French nobleman and later lay brother of the Congregation of the Sacred Hearts of Jesus and Mary , a religious institute of the Roman Catholic Church .
Tong Daning ( 佟达宁 ) was a high - level government official in the People 's Republic of China who was executed for espionage on 21 April 2006 .
Zofia Zakrzewska ( 1916 -- 8 January 1999 ) was a Polish scoutmaster of the Polish Scouting Association and Naczelnik ZHP ( 1956 - -1964 ) .
Louis Hasselriis ( 12 January 1844 -- 20 May 1912 ) was a Danish sculptor known for his public statuary .
Denis Zeunert ( 12 July 1931 -- 13 February 2009 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
The Reverend John Selby Watson ( 1804 -- 6 July 1884 ) was a British classical translator and murderer .
Josef Schillinger ( 21 January 1908 - 23 October 1943 ) was an SS - guard at Auschwitz , who was shot dead by Franceska Mann , a Polish Jew ordered to undress before entering the gas chamber .
Jonathan Gili ( 19 April 1943 -- 1 October 2004 ) was an award - winning film - maker , editor and director , who produced numerous and wide - ranging television documentary and features programmes , mostly for the BBC .
Ward Cheney ( 23 February 1813 Manchester , Connecticut - 22 March 1876 ) was a pioneer manufacturer of silk fabrics .
Bridget Cleary ( Irish : Bríd Ní Chléirigh ) was an Irish woman killed by her husband in 1895 .
Ross Treleaven ( 1907 -- 4 March 1994 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Sturt in the South Australian National Football League ( SANFL ) .
Mar Abraham Shimonaya ( or Shem'onaya , circa 1862 - -1915 ) was a Bishop of the Assyrian Church of the East who converted to Catholicism in 1903 and joined the Chaldean Catholic Church .
Sir Edward Loughlin O'Malley ( 17 February 1842 -- 16 August 1932 ) was a British lawyer and judge .
Krishnalal Shridharani ( 16 September 1911 -- 23 July 1960 ) was an Indian poet , playwright and journalist .
Abu Bakr Ibn Al - Qutia ( died 997 ) was a historian and author born in Córdoba , Spain .
David Peebles ( died 1579 ? ) was a Scottish composer of religious music .
Nicolas Grollier de Servière ( 1596 - -1689 ) was a French inventor and ornamental turner who became well known for creating a series of fantastic machines .
Dame Dorothy Tutin , DBE ( 8 April 1930 -- 6 August 2001 ) was an English actress of stage , film and television .
Octavius Wigram ( 18 December 1794 -- 20 May 1878 ) was an English businessman and ship owner in the City of London , a member of Lloyds and Governor of the Royal Exchange Assurance Corporation .
Max Penson ( 1893 - -1959 ) was a noted Russian Jewish photojournalist and photographer of the Soviet Union noted for his photographs of Uzbekistan .
Bouteldja Belkacem ( 1947 -- 1 September 2015 ) was an Algerian raï songwriter , lyricist and composer .
Uncelen , Uncelin , or Uncilin ( from Latin Uncelenus ; died c. 613 ) was the Duke of Alemannia from 587 to 607 .
Ademar Jordan ( fl . 1198 - -1212 ) was a knight and troubadour from Saint - Antonin in the Rouergue .
Martin Deutsch ( 29 January 1917 -- 16 August 2002 ) was an Austrian - American physicist , who was emeritus professor of physics at MIT .
Wheeler Peckham Bloodgood ( 4 November 1871 - 17 December 1930 ) was a prominent American lawyer who was active in reforming antitrust legislation .
Sriranga II ( a.k.a . Sriranga Chika Raya ) ( r. 1614 CE ) was nominated in 1614 by King Venkata II to succeed him as king of the Vijayanagara Empire in Southern India .
Jean - Louis Berlandier ( ca . 1805 -- 1851 ) was a French - Mexican naturalist , physician , and anthropologist .
Daniel Laurens Barringer ( 1 October 1788 -- 16 October 1852 ) was a United States Representative from North Carolina between 1825 and 1834 .
Harold James Dyos ( 1921 - -1978 ) was a British historian , known for his contributions to urban history .
Charles Castle ( 26 May 1939 - 5 October 2013 ) was a South African -- born British tap dancer , writer and television producer .
James Michael Creeth ( 3 October 1924 -- 15 January 2010 ) was an English biochemist whose experiments on DNA viscosity confirming the existence of hydrogen bonds between the purine and pyrimidine bases of DNA were crucial to Watson and Crick 's discovery of the double helix structure of DNA .
Art Beaumont ( 8 December 1904 -- 8 February 1980 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John Edward Mower ( September 18 , 1815 - -June 11 , 1879 ) was a member of the Minnesota Territorial Legislature in the 1850s .
Samgeun of Baekje ( 465 - -479 ) ( r. 477 - -479 ) was the 23rd king of Baekje , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Harry Tracy ( 23 October 1875 - 6 August 1902 ) was an outlaw in the American Old West .
Professor Edward Forbes FRS , FGS ( 12 February 1815 -- 18 November 1854 ) was a Manx naturalist .
Valyantsin Byalkevich ( Belarusian : Валянцін Бялькевіч ; 27 January 1973 -- 1 August 2014 ) , also sometimes spelled `` Valiantsin Bialkevich '' ) was a Belarusian football player .
Józef Kiedroń ( 23 March 1879 in Błędowice Dolne - 25 January 1932 in Berlin ) was a Polish mining engineer and politician from Cieszyn Silesia .
Datla Venkata Suryanarayana Raju ( దాట్ల వెంకట సూర్యనారాయణ రాజు ) , better known as D. V. S. Raju ( డి. వి. యస్. రాజు ) ( b : 13 December 1928 - d : 13 November 2010 ) was an Indian film producer known for his works in Telugu Cinema and Bollywood .
Emma Nora Barlow , Lady Barlow ( née Darwin ; 22 December 1885 -- December 1989 ) , was the granddaughter of the British naturalist Charles Darwin .
Amalie of Zweibrücken - Birkenfeld - Bischweiler ( Maria Amalie Auguste ; 10 May 1752 -- 15 November 1828 ) was the last Electress and first Queen of Saxony and Duchess of Warsaw .
Axayacatl ( /ˌæksəˈjɑːkətəl/ ; Classical Nahuatl : āxāyacatl , pronounced ( aːʃaːˈjákatɬ ) ; Spanish : Axayácatl , pronounced : ( aksaˈʝakatɬ ) ; meaning `` face of water '' ; c. 1449 - 1481 ) was the sixth tlatoani of the altepetl of Tenochtitlan and ruler of the Aztec Triple Alliance .
Wilfred Hudleston Hudleston FRS ( né Simpson ) ( 2 June 1828 -- 29 January 1909 ) was an English geologist .
Stephen Wootton Bushell CMG MD ( 28 July 1844 -- 19 September 1908 ) was an English physician and amateur Orientalist who made important contributions to the study of Chinese ceramics , Chinese numismatics and the decipherment of the Tangut script .
Noel Jarvis ( 12 December 1924 -- 14 February 1975 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Niels Onstad ( 1909 -17 June 1978 ) was a Norwegian shipowner and art collector .
Syd Sutherland ( 20 April 1890 -- 17 November 1957 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sunil Dutt ( 6 June 1930 -- 25 May 2005 ) , born Balraj Dutt , was an Indian movie actor , producer , director and politician .
Erich Šlomović ( Serbian : Erih Šlomović , also known as Erich Chlomovitch ) ( 1915 - -1942 ) was a Jewish art collector in the Kingdom of Yugoslavia .
Chief Ignacio ( 1828 - -1913 ) was a chief of the Weeminuche band of the Ute tribe of American Indians , also called the Southern Utes , located in present - day Colorado north of the San Juan River .
Shaykh Abdur Rahman , also known as Abdur Rahman Shaykh , ( died 30 March 2007 ) was the spiritual leader and the administrative head of the banned terrorist organization Jagrata Muslim Janata Bangladesh ( English : Awakened Muslim Masses of Bangladesh ) .
Kjell Hvidsand ( 16 January 1941 -- 14 November 2014 ) was a Norwegian footballer .
Lupino Lane ( 16 June 1892 -- 10 November 1959 ) was an English actor and theatre manager , and a member of the famous Lupino family .
Zahir al - Dawla Vushmgir ( Persian : ظهیرالدوله وشمگیر‎‎ ) , mostly known as Vushmgir ( also spelled as Voshmgir , Wushmgir , Wushmagir and Washmgir ) , was the second Ziyarid Emir who ruled from 935 until his death in December 967 .
Anne Catherine Roberta Geddes - Harvey ( née Geddes ; 25 December 1849 -- 22 April 1930 ) was a Canadian organist , choirmaster and composer .
Seaborn McDaniel Denson ( 1854 -- April 18 , 1936 ) was a notable Alabama musician and singing school teacher within the Sacred Harp tradition .
Zawisza Czarny ( ( zaˈvʲiʂa ˈt͡ʂarn̪ɨ ) ; Zawisza the Black ; c. 1379 -- 12 June 1428 ) , Sulima coat of arms , was a Polish knight and nobleman who served as a commander and diplomat under Polish king Władysław II Jagiełło and Hungarian - Bohemian king Sigismund of Luxembourg .
Josef Wirsching ( 22 March 1903 --11 June 1967 ) sometimes credited as Joseph Wirsching , was a German cinematographer , who became a pioneer in cinematography in India and who contributed to the heritage of Cinema of India and still photography in its improvement into a scientific art of expression .
Armand Charles Emmanuel Guignard , comte de Saint - Priest ( 1782 - -1863 ) was a French aristocrat who was involved in both the politics of France and the Russian Empire during the First French Empire and the Bourbon Restoration .
Harry Garson ( 1882 -- 21 September 1938 ) was an American film director and producer .
Edward Vickers ( 1804 - 1897 ) was the founder of Naylor Vickers & Co. which became Vickers Limited .
Leonardo Patrasso ( Alatri , 1230 - Lucca , 7 December 1311 ) was an Italian Franciscan and Cardinal .
Ilyas ibn Asad ( died 856 ) was a Samanid ruler of Herat ( 819 - -856 ) .
John Notman ( 1810 - -1865 ) was a Scottish - born American architect , who settled in Philadelphia .
Lieutenant - General Jacobus Verster SSA SM ( 1919 -- 1981 ) was a South African military commander .
John Fancy ( 9 March 1913 -- 16 September 2008 ) was a British former airman whose tunnelling escapes from various German prisoner of war camps during World War II earned him the nickname The Mole , and inspired the book and film The Great Escape .
Hulbert Footner ( 1879 - -1944 ) was a Canadian writer of non - fiction and detective fiction .
Sir Charles Noel Davies ( 2 December 1933 - 10 February 2015 ) was chief executive of Vickers Shipbuilding & Engineering Ltd ( VSEL ) from 1989 to 1995 during the period when the yard built the Vanguard class submarines that replacing the former Polaris fleet .
Flavius Areobindus Dagalaiphus Areobindus , commonly simply Areobindus or Ariovindus ( Greek : Ἀρεόβινδος , fl . c. 460 - -512 ) was an East Roman ( Byzantine ) general and politician .
Antti Kukkonen ( 3 October 1889 , Kontiolahti - 14 February 1978 ) was a Finnish Lutheran pastor and politician .
John Theodore Heins ( c.1697 - -1756 ) was a painter and engraver , probably of German birth , but active in Great Britain .
Francisco José Urrutia Holguín ( 28 May 1910 -- 19 October 1981 ) was a Colombian - Ecuadorian lawyer and diplomat .
Griffith Anthony ( 1846 - -1897 ) was a musician .
Siegmund Mayer ( December 27 , 1842 -- September , 1910 ) was a German physiologist and histologist .
Yang Dongqian ( 楊洞潛 ) ( d. 935 ) , courtesy name Zhaoxuan ( 昭玄 ) , was an official of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period state Southern Han , serving as a chancellor .
Francis Guy ( 1760 - -1820 ) was an English - born American Colonial Era painter .
Lindsey Hughes ( 4 May 1949 -- 26 April 2007 ) was a British historian who studied seventeenth- and eighteenth - century Russia , especially the reign of Peter the Great .
Juan Liscano Velutini ( 7 July 1915 - 17 February 2001 ) was a Venezuelan poet , folklorist , writer and critic .
Riccardo Rognoni or Richardo Rogniono ( ca . 1550 -- before 20 April 1620 ) is the earliest known member of the Rognoni family which started one of the earliest of all violin schools , based in Milan .
François Rochebrune ( Polish : Franciszek Rochebrune ) ( born 1 June or 1 January 1830 , died 19 November 1870 ( some sources state 1871 ) ) was a French army officer and Polish general .
Adam Ferguson , FRSE ( in Scottish Gaelic : Adhamh MacFhearghais ) , also known as Ferguson of Raith ( 20 June 1723 ( O.S. ) ( 1 July , N.S. ) -- 22 February 1816 ) , was a Scottish philosopher and historian of the Scottish Enlightenment .
Shaykh Shahab al - Din Abu Hafs Umar Suhrawardi ( Kurdish : عمر سهروردى‎ c.1145 - 1234 ) was a Kurdish or Persian Sufi and nephew of Abu al - Najib Suhrawardi .
Francis Brodie Imlach ( 1819 - 1891 ) was a Scottish pioneer of modern dentistry , and the first person to use chloroform on a dental patient .
The Very Rev William Page Roberts , DD ( 2 January 1836 -- 17 August 1928 ) was an eminent English clergyman in the Church of England and Dean of Salisbury from 1907 until 1919 .
Harding of Bristol ( born circa 1048 , died circa 1125 ) was sheriff reeve of Bristol , with responsibility for managing a manorial estate and perhaps similar duties to those of a magistrate .
Robin Tanner ( Wiltshire , 1904 - -1988 ) was an English artist , etcher and printmaker .
Anthony George Charles ( born 27 June 1900 in Castries , Saint Lucia ; died 20 April 1957 ) was a boxer , commonly known as Dixie Brown .
Dixon Donnelley ( July 29 , 1915 -- January 1982 ) was United States Assistant Secretary of State for Public Affairs from 1966 to 1969 .
Eugène Eyraud ( 1820 -- 23 August 1868 ) was a lay friar of the Congregation of the Sacred Hearts of Jesus and Mary and the first Westerner to live on Easter Island .
Miran Ogrin ( 1914 - -1985 ) was a Slovene journalist who worked for the Dnevnik newspaper .
Samuel Jaudon ( 1796 - 1874 ) was a 19th - century banker and businessman who , as an employee and agent of the Bank of the United States , helped cause or worsen the Panic of 1837 .
Maurizio Cazzati ( 1 March 1616 -- 28 September 1678 ) was a northern Italian composer of the seventeenth century .
David Henry Lewis , DCNZM ( 1917 - 23 October 2002 ) was a sailor , adventurer , doctor , and Polynesian scholar .
Venerable Ludovico Sabbatini ( 30 August 1650 -- 11 June 1724 ) was an Italian priest and religious educator , who was beatified by the Catholic Church in 1765 .
Casimir Marie Gaudibert ( 4 March 1823 -- 9 June 1901 ) was a French amateur astronomer and selenographer .
Norman Vyner Fletcher ( 1867 -- 17 December 1889 ) was an Australian arts graduate and law clerk who was notable as a botanist researching eucalypts .
William Perfect ( 1734 - 1809 ) was a British surgeon , obstetrician , early psychiatrist , pioneer of humane treatment of mental illnesss , Freemason , and poet .
Franklin David Murphy ( 1916 - 16 June 1994 ) was an American administrator , educator , and medical doctor .
Clementina Morgari Lomazzi ( Guastalla,1819- Turin , 1897 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of genre scenes of intimate , family moments .
Joaquim Soeiro Pereira Gomes ( 14 April 1909 -- 5 December 1949 ) was a Portuguese writer of realist influence and became one of the major names of Portuguese literature of the 20th century .
Saint Wenna ( c. 472 -- c. 18 October 544 ) is a Cornish saint and the dedicatee of several churches , venerated in the Eastern Orthodox Church , Roman Catholic Church , and Anglican Communion .
Jakob Monau ( 4 February 1546 ; Breslau -- 6 October 1603 ; Breslau ) , also known as Jacobus Monavius or Iacobus Monaw , was a polymath ( lawyer , linguist and poet ) and leader of the Reformed Protestant faction after Johannes Crato von Krafftheim 's death .
Bernard O'Gara ( died 1740 ) was an Irish clergyman who served as the Roman Catholic Archbishop of Tuam from 1723 to 1740 .
Emil Ghuri ( Arabic : إميل الغوري‎ , alternatively spelled Emil Ghoury ) ( 1907 - -1984 ) , a Palestinian Christian , was Secretary of the Arab Higher Committee ( AHC ) , the official leadership of the Arabs in the British Mandate of Palestine .
Kate O'Mara ( 10 August 1939 -- 30 March 2014 ) was an English film , stage and television actress , and writer .
Tagtsepa Lhagyal Rabten ( Wylie : Stag rtse pa lha rgyal rab brtan ) ( died 1720 ) was the regent of the Tibetan administration during the 3-year rule of the Dzungar Khanate in Tibet ( 1717 - 1720 ) .
George Edward Anson ( 1812 -- 1849 ) was a courtier and British politician from the Anson family .
Madeleine Passot ( 28 August 1914 -- 19 September 2009 ) was a French communist who worked for the French Resistance as a liaison agent during World War II ( 1939 - -45 ) .
Robert Arbuthnot , 1st Viscount of Arbuthnott PC ( before 1625 -- 10 October 1655 ) , was a Scottish Peer and Scottish Privy Counsellor ( 1649 ) .
Anastasios Peponis ( Greek : Αναστάσιος Πεπονής ; 1924 -- 8 August 2011 ) was a Greek politician and author .
Ph.D. ( 20 December 1934 -- 14 August 2010 ) , better known as I. V. Subba Rao , was an eminent Agricultural scientist .
Kimnyole ( died ca . 1890 ) was the Nandi Orkoiyot who predicted the arrival of Europeans ( `` the white tribe '' ) and the railways ( `` the Iron Snake '' ) who were to change everything for the Nandi .
Bishop Sophianos of Dryinoupolis ( died 1711 ) was a Greek religious figure and Orthodox missionary in Ottoman Epirus around the turn of the 18th century .
Herbert Blake ( born 26 August 1894 in Bristol -- died 1958 ) was a professional footballer who played for Bristol City , Tottenham Hotspur and Kettering Town .
Charles Borromeo Fitzgerald ( 28 June 1865 -- 10 February 1913 ) was a barrister and politician from Queensland , Australia .
Sir Thomas Galloway Dunlop Galbraith KBE ( 10 March 1917 -- 2 January 1982 ) , usually known as Tam Galbraith , was a Scottish Unionist politician .
Washington Luís Pereira de Sousa ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( ˈwɔʃĩtõ luˈiʃ peˈɾejɾɐ dʒi ˈsowzɐ ) ; 26 October 1869 -- 4 August 1957 ) was a Brazilian politician and the last president of the First Brazilian Republic .
Phoebe Hesketh ( 29 January 1909 -- 25 February 2005 ) was an English poet from Lancashire notable for her poems depicting nature .
Jason Altom ( 6 October 1971 -- 15 August 1998 ) was a Ph.D. student working in the research group of Nobel laureate Elias James Corey at Harvard University .
Edwin R. Thiele ( 10 September 1895 -- 15 April 1986 ) was an American Seventh - day Adventist missionary in China , an editor , archaeologist , writer , and Old Testament professor .
John Brooks Close - Brooks ( 9 June 1850 -- 20 March 1914 ) was an English banker and amateur rower who won the Diamond Challenge Sculls at Henley Royal Regatta in 1870 and rowed for Cambridge in the Boat Race in 1871 and 1872 .
Henry Victor Deligny ( 5 September 1855 - 2 January 1938 ) was a French divisional general who served in the First World War .
Jerome Lamy ( born Linz , 1726 and died 1781 ) was an 18th - century Benedictine Biblical scholar and teacher at Salzburg .
Theodor Pallady ( Romanian pronunciation : ( teˈodor paˈladi ) ; 11 April 1871 -- 16 August 1956 ) was a Romanian painter .
Alfons Heck ( 3 November 1928 -- 12 April 2005 ) was a German Hitler Youth member , who eventually became a Hitler Youth Officer and a fanatical adherent of Nazism .
Walter Bird ( 22 July 1854 -- 27 July 1921 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket in 1880 .
Walter Kollo ( 28 January 1878 -- 30 September 1940 ) was a German composer of operettas , Possen mit Gesang , and Singspiele as well as popular songs .
Firmin Lebel ( early 16th century -- 27 - -31 December 1573 ) was a French composer and choir director of the Renaissance , active in Rome .
Donald Richie ( 17 April 1924 -- 19 February 2013 ) was an American - born author who wrote about the Japanese people , the culture of Japan , and especially Japanese cinema .
Reinhart Heinrich ( 24 April 1946 -- 23 October 2006 ) was a German biophysicist .
Vlatko Dulić ( 20 April 1943 -- 20 November 2015 ) was a Croatian theatre , television and film actor and theatre director .
Petrus Peckius the Younger , also known as Petrus Pecquius or Pierre Peckius ( born Pieter Peck ; 1562 -- 28 July 1625 ) , was a diplomat and chancellor of Brabant for the Sovereign Archdukes Albert and Isabella .
Francisco Xavier da Silva Pereira , 1st Count of Antas ( 14 March 1793 in Valença -- 20 May 1852 in Lisbon ) was a Portuguese nobleman and a leading soldier of the period of the Liberal Wars .
Lucien Ballard , A.S.C. ( 6 May 1908 -- 1 October 1988 ) was an American cinematographer and director of photography .
John David Jenkins ( 30 January 1828 -- 9 November 1876 ) was a Welsh clergyman and historian .
Kåre Hatten ( 22 January 1908 -- 14 April 1983 ) was a Norwegian cross country skier .
Qarin III ( Persian : کارین ) , was the ruler of the Bavand dynasty from 1114 to 1117 .
Jonathan Drummond - Webb ( 29 August 1959 -- 26 December 2004 ) was a South African pediatric heart surgeon .
Marie Burke ( 18 October 1894 -- 21 March 1988 ) , born Marie Rosa Holt , was an English actress of cinema and TV .
Fiona Cumming ( 9 October 1937 -- 1 January 2015 ) was a Scottish television director , noted for her work on the BBC television series , Doctor Who , during the show 's Fifth Doctor era .
Samuel Amsler ( 17 December 1791 - 18 May 1849 ) , Swiss engraver , was born at Schinznach , in the canton of Aargau .
Sharifa Alkhateeb ( 1946 -- 2004 ) was a writer , researcher and teacher on cultural communication and community building for Islam and Muslims in the United States .
Ray Wedgeworth ( February 14 , 1908 -- February 1975 ) was an American college football , baseball and basketball head coach .
Lucien Stephen Crandall ( May 4 , 1844 - 1889 ) was an American inventor of typewriters , adding machines and electrical devices .
Betsi Cadwaladr ( 24 May 1789 -- 17 July 1860 ) , also known as Beti Cadwaladr and Betsi Davis , worked as a nurse in the Crimean War alongside Florence Nightingale , although their different social backgrounds were a source of constant disagreement .
Shanta Rao ( 1930 - 28 December 2007 ) was a notable dancer from India .
Charles de Rochefort ( 7 July 1887 -- 31 January 1952 ) born as Charles d'Authier de Rochefort , son of Paul Charles Dominique d'Authier de Rochefort and Camille Caroline Rose Félicité Guelfucci
Isabella of Angoulême ( French : Isabelle d'Angoulême , IPA : ( izabɛl dɑ̃ɡulɛm ) ; c. 1188 -- 4 June 1246 ) was queen consort of England as the second wife of King John from 1200 until John 's death in 1216 .
Thomas Clydesdale , JP ( 1934 , Edinburgh , Scotland -- 2007 ) was a former member of the Legislative Council of Hong Kong .
Abraham Pierson , the elder ( died 1678 ) was an English churchman , known as a minister in New England .
Roger Welles ( 1862 - -1932 ) was a U. S. naval officer , the first commander of USS Oklahoma and appointed the first `` Navy Mayor '' of San Diego .
Sir Francis Gamull , 1st Baronet ( 1606 - -1654 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1644 .
Margaritus of Brindisi ( also Margarito ; Italian Margaritone or Greek Megareites or Margaritoni ( Μαργαριτώνη ) : c. 1149 -- 1197 ) , called the new Neptune , was the last great ammiratus ammiratorum ( Grand Admiral ) of Sicily .
Hon . Tu'i'afitu ( 21 December 1933 -- 4 October 2005 ) , born Samisoni Fonomanu Tu'i'afitu , was a Tongan nobleman , Member of Parliament , and the Governor of Vavaʻu .
Charles de Courcy Parry CBE ( died 19 November 1948 ) was a British police officer who served as Chief Constable of the Cumberland and Westmorland Constabulary from 1902 to 1927 , when he was appointed His Majesty 's Inspector of Constabulary for Wales .
Sir Wroth Palmer Acland K.C.B. ( 1770 - -1816 ) , English soldier lieutenant - general , notable for his role in the Peninsular War .
Moses Bar - Kepha ( born in Balad in Nineveh , now in Iraq , about the year 813 ; died at the age of ninety , in 903 ) was a writer and one of the most celebrated bishops of the Syriac Orthodox Church of the ninth century .
Mary Elizabeth Wilson ( c. 1893 -- 1963 ) , also known as the Merry Widow of Windy Nook , was a serial killer and the last woman to be sentenced to death in Durham , in 1958 .
Jean de la Chambre ( 1605 , Haarlem -- 1668 , Haarlem ) , was a Dutch Golden Age engraver and calligrapher best known today for his portrait by Frans Hals , which is in the collection of the National Gallery in London .
Manuel Gual Vidal ( 3 August 1903 -- 7 August 1954 ) was a Mexican jurist and educator .
József Schunda ( 1818 - -1893 ) and Vencel József Schunda ( 1845 - -1923 ) were brothers and Czech musical instrument makers .
John Robert Moore ( 1890 - -1973 ) was an American biographer and bibliographer of Daniel Defoe .
Jakub Michlewicz ( or Jakov Michaeli , served under the name Ryszard Trzaskowski , nom - de - guerre Rysiek ) ( born 1929 - 2013 , Israel ) was a Polish Jewish member of the Polish Home Army and a child soldier in the Warsaw Uprising .
Razzaq Gul ( 1977 ( ? ) -- 19 May 2012 ) was a senior Pakistani journalist covering war and politics for Express News in Turbat , Pakistan who was abducted 18 May 2012 and found murdered 19 May 2012 .
Moses Aaron Richardson ( 1793 - -1871 ) was an English publisher and antiquary .
Sigurður Nordal ( 14 September 1886 -- 21 September 1974 ) was an Icelandic scholar , writer and ambassador .
Henry Dobson ( 24 December 1841 -- 10 October 1918 ) , was an Australian politician , who served as a member of the Tasmanian House of Assembly and later of the Australian Senate .
Jorge Fick ( 1932 - -2004 ) was an American painter who is known for his `` Pod '' series of large - scale oil paintings `` depicting semi - abstract symbols of growth and regeneration . ''
Henry Crisfield ( 13 September 1877 -- 2 February 1945 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Francis Maginn ( 1861 - -1918 ) was a Church of Ireland missionary who worked to improve living standards for the deaf community by promoting sign language and was one of the co - founders of the British Deaf Association .
Ugolino di Tedice ( died after 1277 ) , was an Italian painter and the brother of Enrico di Tedice .
Leonid Fyodorovich Myasin ( Russian : Леони́д Фёдорович Мя́син ) , better known in the West by the French transliteration as Léonide Massine ( 9 August ( O.S. 28 July ) 1896 -- 15 March 1979 ) , was a Russian choreographer and ballet dancer .
Ricardo Porro Hudalgo ( November 1925 -- 25 December 2014 ) was a Cuban - born architect .
Abbot Augustus Low ( Gus Low ) ( 1844 -- 1912 ) was an entrepreneur and inventor from Brooklyn , who lived in St. Lawrence County , New York and was the owner of the Horseshoe Forestry Company .
Thomas Rochfort ( c.1450 - 1522 ) was a distinguished Irish judge and cleric who held the offices of Solicitor General for Ireland , Master of the Rolls in Ireland , and Dean of St. Patrick 's Cathedral .
Michael John Wise CBE , MC ( 17 August 1918 -- 13 October 2015 ) was an academic who served as a professor of geography at the University of London .
When Jan Olieslagers died of cancer on 23 March 1942 , Belgium was once again occupied by the Germans .
Beverly Mascoll died from complications due to breast cancer in 2001 .
César Milstein , CH , FRS ( 8 October 1927 -- 24 March 2002 ) was an Argentinian biochemist - nationalized British - in the field of antibody research .
Mathias Czwiczek also Maciej Croiczek , Cwiczeck , Cwiczek , Cwiczeke , Czwiczeck , Czwiczek , Czwiczik , Schwetzge and Schwezge ( 1601 , Královec -- 1654 , Königsberg ) , was a Bohemian painter active in Brandenburg - Prussia .
Giovanni Tebaldi ( 1787 - -1852 ) was an Italian painter , active in a Neoclassical style .
Augaire mac Ailella ( with similar spellings like Ugaire and Aililla ) was the king of Leinster , Ireland king who is said to have led the Irish forces at the Battle of Confey c. 915 - 917 .
Frank Freeman ( 1861 - -13 October 1949 ) was a Canadian - American architect based in Brooklyn , New York .
Raymond David Bowden ( 31 July 1937 -- 29 July 2004 ) was an Australian Anglican bishop , the eighth Bishop of Bendigo from 1995 to 2002 .
Jan Altink ( Dutch pronunciation : ( jɑn ˈɑltɪnk ) ; 21 October 1885 -- 6 December 1971 ) was a Dutch expressionist painter and cofounder of De Ploeg .
John Bingham , 1st Baron Clanmorris ( 1762 -- May 1821 ) was an Irish peer .
Yamato Ichihashi ( 1878 - -1963 ) was one of the first academics of Asian ancestry in the United States .
Ern Hocking ( 16 May 1882 -- 19 June 1971 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Basuki Rahmat ( 4 November 1921 -- 8 January 1969 ) was an Indonesian General and a witness to the signing of the Supersemar document transferring power from President Sukarno to General Suharto .
Jacques Danois , pseudonym of Jacques Maricq ( 11 September 1927 -- 20 September 2008 ) was a reporter and writer who was director of information at Unicef .
Jan van Buken or Jan van Beucken ( 10 March 1635 -- 6 February 1690 ) was a Flemish painter mainly known for his genre paintings and still lifes .
Philo White ( June 23 , 1796 -- February 15 , 1883 ) was a politician and newspaperman .
Lakshmipati Tirtha ( 1420 - -1487 ) was a Vaishnava saint .
Francis Edwin Murray ( 1854 - 1932 ) was a Uranian poet and publisher of the late 19th and early 20th century .
John Røen ( 22 April 1903 -- 18 March 1979 ) was a Norwegian cross - country skier from Møre og Romsdal .
Vithal Balkrishna Gandhi ( 11 November 1896 -- 3 November 1969 ) , popularly known as `` American Gandhi '' , was an Indian social reformer , political leader and businessman .
Carlton K. Mack ( 1911 -- 1995 ) was a Chinese businessman who moved to Trinidad and Tobago at a young age where he built the J.T. Allum & Co. business into one of Trinidad and Tobago 's largest enterprises .
Victor Eeckhout ( 1821 - -1879 ) , a genre painter , the son of Jacob Joseph Eeckhout , was born at Antwerp .
Landric ( or Landeric , French : Landry , † 613 ) was the mayor of the palace of Neustria .
John Dunstaple ( or Dunstable , c. 1390 -- 24 December 1453 ) was an English composer of polyphonic music of the late medieval era and early Renaissance periods .
Walter Linse ( 23 August 1903 -- 15 December 1953 ) was a German lawyer and Acting President of the Association of Free German Jurists , an organization with links to the CIA .
Ernest Earl Lockhart ( September 10 , 1912 - -July 26 , 2006 ) was a chemist and explorer .
Guido Banti ( 8 June 1852 -- 8 January 1925 ) was an Italian physician and pathologist .
Alexander Calvit ( also known as Sandy Calvit ) ( 1784 - -1836 ) was an early settler in colonial Texas and a sugar planter .
Stephen Nettles ( fl . 1595 -- 1647 ) was an English clergyman and controversialist .
Suero de Quiñones ( c. 1409 -- 11 July 1456 ) , called Él del Passo ( `` he of the pass '' ) , was a Leonese knight and author .
Mohammad Ebrahim Bastani Parizi ( محمد ابراهیم باستانی پاریزی in Persian , 12 December 1924 -- 25 March 2014 ) was an Iranian historian , translator , poet , essayist and author of non - fiction books .
Simon Gregorčič ( 15 October 1844 -- 24 November 1906 ) was a Slovene poet and Roman Catholic priest .
Richard Barrey ( died 1588 ) , of the Moat , Sevington and Dover , Kent , was an English politician .

George Cholmondeley , Viscount Malpas ( 17 October 1724 -- 15 March 1764 ) was a British soldier and Member of Parliament .
Gaetano Lococo ( 1895 - 1993 ) , also known as `` Thomas '' or `` Tano was a mobster identified as one of the ' ' Five Iron Men `` of Kansas City , Missouri by Americanmiafia.com .
Jasper Mayne ( 1604 -- 6 December 1672 ) was an English clergyman , translator , and a minor poet and dramatist .
Luciano Giancarlo ( 13 April 1972 , Morristown , New Jersey -- 16 July 2007 ) was an American film and television actor of Italian descent .
Beth Rogan , born Jenifer Puckle , ( 19 July 1931 -- 25 November 2015 ) was a British film actress and Rank Films starlet of the 1950s and 60s .
Anthony Brancato ( July 18 , 1914 -- August 6 , 1951 ) was a Kansas City , Missouri criminal who served as a freelance gunman to various Mafia and syndicate organizations .
Henri Paul René Ceuppens ( 8 January 1923 - 7 October 2012 ) , who wrote under the pseudonym Ivo Michiels , was a Belgian writer .
Lieutenant - General Francis Palmes MP ( died 1719 ) was a noted favourite general of the Duke of Marlborough .
Rafael Bash ( Hebrew : רפאל בש‎ , born 8 January 1913 , died 10 March 2000 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for three months in 1951 .
Al Kelly was the stage name of Abraham Kalish ( 18 December 1896 -- 7 September 1966 ) , a U.S. vaudeville comedian .
Diana Coupland ( 5 March 1928 - - 10 November 2006 ) was an English actress and singer best remembered for her role as Jean Abbott on Bless This House , which she played from 1971 to 1976 .
Robert Burnell ( sometimes spelled Robert Burnel ; c. 1239 -- 25 October 1292 ) was an English bishop who served as Lord Chancellor of England from 1274 to 1292 .
After a prolonged illness , Subhash Ghisingh died on 29 January 2015 at Ganga Ram Hospital in New Delhi .
Georg Wolfgang Knorr ( 30 December 1705 in Nürnberg -- 17 September 1761 in Nürnberg ) was a German engraver and naturalist .
Richard Kirkby ( c.1625 -- 9 September 1681 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1661 to 1681 .
Lech Owron ( 6 July 1893 -- 9 June 1965 ) was a Polish stage and film actor whose career began in the 1920s during the silent film era .
Thomas Ivory ( 1709 - -1779 ) was an English builder and architect , active in Norwich .
Walter Rumsey ( 1584 - -1660 ) was a Welsh judge and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1640 .
Dwarkanath Ganguly ( also spelt as Dwarka Nath Gangopadhyay ) ( Bengali : দ্বারকানাথ গাঙ্গুলী Darkanath Gangguli ) ( 20 April 1844 -- 27 June 1898 ) was a Brahmo reformer in Bengal of British India .

Sir Harcourt Lees ( 29 November 1776 -- 7 March 1852 in Blackrock , near Dublin ) was an Irish clergyman and political pamphleteer on behalf of Protestant Ascendancy in Ireland .

Innes Harold Stranger ( 21 June 1879 -- 28 July 1936 ) was a British Barrister and Liberal politician who was briefly Member of Parliament for the Newbury constituency .

William FitzClarence , 2nd Earl of Munster , ( 19 May 1824 -- 30 April 1901 ) was a British peer , and the grandson of King William IV .
Geoffrey Bazeley ( 1906 - -1989 ) was a British Modernist architect , born in Penzance , Cornwall , into a family of shipowners and traders .
Christopher Trevor - Roberts ( died 5 May 2005 , aged 77 ) was a teacher who taught all four children of Queen Elizabeth II . Christopher Trevor - Roberts is credited with helping Prince Charles overcome his aversion to mathematics .
Sir Richard Everard , 4th Baronet ( c. 1683 - 17 February 1733 ) was the last Governor of North Carolina under proprietary rule , serving in that capacity from 1725 to 1731 .
Visitacao Lobo ( died 28 June 2014 ) was an Indian professional footballer who played as a striker .
Tyge Ahrengot Christensen ( 31 March 1918 in Nykøbing Mors -- 17 January 1996 ) was a Danish botanist and phycologist .
Blessed Nicholas Garlick ( c. 1555 -- 24 July 1588 ) was an English catholic priest , martyred in Derby in the reign of Queen Elizabeth I.
Charles Garvice ( b. 24 August 1850 - d. 1 March 1920 ) was a prolific British writer of over 150 romance novels , who also used the female pseudonym Caroline Hart .
Franz Rademacher ( 20 February 1906 -- 17 March 1973 ) was an official in the Nazi government of the Third Reich during World War II , known for initiating action on the Madagascar Plan .
Ron Shapter ( 1 July 1905 -- 3 November 1977 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne , Fitzroy and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the 1930s .
Solomon Ezekiel ( 1781 - 1867 ) , was an English Jewish writer .
Peter Haas ( April 12 , 1754 -- 1804 ) was a German - Danish engraver .
Henry Valentine Knaggs ( 14 February 1859 -- 11 July 1954 ) was an English doctor and author who was a notable practitioner of nature cure methods ( now called Naturopathic medicine ) .
Isadore Ellis ( 1910 - -1994 ) , credited as I. Ellis and known throughout the animation industry as Izzy Ellis , was an American animator best known for working for Warner Bros. Cartoons under the Bob Clampett & Frank Tashlin units .
Hao Weizhen ( 1842 - -1920 ) , or Hao Wei - chen , was a Chinese t'ai chi ch'uan ( taijiquan ) teacher .

Lieutenant - General James Francis Tennant ( 10 January 1829 -- 6 March 1915 ) was a noted soldier and astronomer .
Guy Marks ( 31 October 1923 -- 28 November 1987 ) was an American actor , comedian , singer and impressionist .
Mary Beever ( 1802 -- 31 December 1883 ) was a British artist and botanist .
William Henry Bogart was born 1810 in Albany , New York and died 1888 in Aurora , Cayuga County , New York .
Masajiro Miyazaki D.O. , CM ( November 24 , 1899 - -July 23 , 1984 ) was a Japanese - Canadian osteopathic physician who practised in Vancouver prior to World War II . During World War II , he was appointed as a coroner by the British Columbia Provincial Police in the town of Lillooet , British Columbia .
Fred K. Schaefer ( 7 July 1904 - 6 June 1953 ) was a geographer .
Conrad Koellin ( Latin , Conradus Koellin ; 1476 - -1536 ) was a Dominican , professor of theology , and commentator on St. Thomas Aquinas .
Edward Lively ( 1545 -- May 1605 ) was an English linguist and biblical scholar .
Ali Ahsan Mohammad Mojaheed ( Bengali : আলী আহসান মোহাম্মদ মোজাহিদ ; 23 June 1948 -- 22 November 2015 ) was a Bangladeshi politician and convicted war criminal , who served as a Member of Parliament and as the Minister of Social Welfare from 2001 to 2007 of Bangladesh .
Sir Thomas Edward Thorpe , often called Edward Thorpe , ( 8 December 1845 -- 23 February 1925 ) was a British chemist .
Frank Trafford Taylor , KC ( 1891 -- 1 November 1943 ) , was a Canadian lawyer , and the president of Kiwanis International .
Sindeok of Silla ( died 917 ) ( r. 912 - -917 ) was the 53rd ruler of the Korean kingdom of Silla .
Frederic Mayer Bird ( 1838 - -1908 ) was an American clergyman , educator , and hymnologist born in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania .
Albert von Behaim or Albertus Bohemus ( ca . 1180 -- 1260 ) was a papal legate and supporter of papal rights against the Holy Roman Emperor Frederick II .
Heinrich Franz Brandt ( 13 January 1789 -- 9 May 1845 ) was a Swiss - born medal designer who worked in Berlin .
Nazzareno Camilleri ( 1906 - -1973 ) was a Maltese philosopher , theologian , and mystic .
Liu Hsia ( Chinese : 劉俠 ; pinyin : Liú Xiá ; 28 February 1942 -- 8 February 2003 ) , better known by her pen name `` Hsinglintzu''(Chinese : 杏林子 ; pinyin : Xìnglínzǐ ) , was a Taiwanese writer .
Ronald Crichton ( 28 December 1913 -- 16 November 2005 ) was a music critic for the Financial Times in the 1960s and 1970s .
Flora Batson ( 1864 - -1906 ) was a popular and well - known black concert singer , nicknamed `` The Double - Voiced Queen of Song '' because of her soprano - baritone range .

Katharine Stewart ( 29 August 1914 in Reading , England -- 27 March 2013 in Inverness ) was an author , crofter , teacher and postmistress .
Al - Hakim II ( Arabic : الحاكم بأمر الله الثاني‎ ) ( died 1352 ) was the Abbasid Caliph in Cairo ( 1341 - -1352 ) .

Cesare Pinarello ( 5 October 1932 -- 2 August 2012 ) was an Italian cyclist who won two bronze medal at the Summer Olympics ( 1952 and 1956 ) .
Oscarre Vicich , first name also spelled Oscar ( 26 June 1922 , Rijeka , Free State of Fiume - 17 February 1994 ) is a retired Italian professional football player .
Selina Davenport ( 27 June 1779 -- 14 July 1859 ) was an English novelist , briefly married to the miscellanist and biographer Richard Alfred Davenport .
Stephen VII Báthory ( Hungarian : Báthory István ; died 3 May 1530 ) was a Hungarian nobleman and commander .
Samuel Garbett ( 1717 - - 5 December 1803 ) was a prominent citizen of Birmingham England , during the industrial revolution , and a friend of Matthew Boulton .
James Astbury Hammersley ( 1815 - -1869 ) was an English painter , and a teacher of art and design .
José Domingo Molina Gómez ( 1896 - -1969 ) was the Commander and Chief of the Argentine Army who appears to have temporarily taken `` the reins of Government '' on September 19 , 1955 .
Antoine Frangieh ( 1 September 1941 -- 13 June 1978 ) , better known by his diminutive , Tony Frangieh , طوني فرنجية ) was a Lebanese politician and militia leader during the early years of the Lebanese Civil War .
Brian Cookman ( 22 November 1946 -- 18 February 2005 ) was an English musician and composer , magazine designer and artist , and t'ai chi practitioner .

Robert Charleton ( 1809 - -1872 ) was a Quaker , Recorded Minister and a prominent citizen of Bristol , England .
Sir John Prise ( also Prys , Price , in Welsh Syr Siôn ap Rhys ) ( ca . 1502 - -1555 ) was a Welsh public notary , who acted as a royal agent and visitor of the monasteries .
Jacob C. Isacks ( born January 1 , 1767 - died 1835 ) was an American politician that represented Tennessee in the United States House of Representatives .
Shan Lloyd ( née Shan Davies ) ( 1 July 1953 -- 13 December 2008 ) was a British journalist , writer and reporter .
William Macneile Dixon ( 1866 - 1946 ) was a British author and academic .
George Grainger ( 11 November 1887 -- 17 August 1977 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Derbyshire between 1909 and 1921 .
Marcus Boyall ( 8 October 1917 - 30 September 1985 ) was an Australian rules footballer best known for his playing career with Victorian Football League ( VFL ) club Collingwood and South Australian National Football League ( SANFL ) club Glenelg in the 1930s and 1940s .
James Tilton ( June 1 , 1745 - -May 14 , 1822 ) was an American physician and soldier from Dover , Delaware .
Russell Pascoe ( 1940 -- 17 December 1963 ) was ( along with his 22-year - old accomplice Dennis Whitty ) the third - last prisoner to be executed by hanging in a British prison .
Alexander Home , 1st Earl of Home ( 1566?--1619 ) , was a Scottish nobleman , also 6th Lord Home .
Karl Baumgartner ( 1949 -- 18 March 2014 ) was a German film producer .
John Liston ( c. 1776 -- 22 March 1846 ) , English comedian , was born in London .
Lala Jagat Narain ( 31 May 1899 − 9 September 1981 ) was the founder of the Hind Samachar group .
R. Ananthanarayan Ph.D. ( born Trivandrum , Kerala - died 1998 ) was an Indian microbiologist .
Abolhasan Farhoudi ( 1923 in Qom , Iran - 19 April 2006 in Paris , France ) was a prominent Persian medical scientist , immunologist and pediatrician .
Princess Anle ( 安樂公主 ) ( 684 ? -- 21 July 710 ) , personal name Li Guo'er ( 李裹兒 ) , was a princess of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty .
Charles T. Gidiney ( September 5 , 1813 -- June 1900 ) was an untrained African - American mathematician who made his living as a whitewasher .
Pangeran Ratu ( died 1651 ) was the ruler of Banten in Northwest Java , Indonesia , and was the first ruler anywhere on the island of Java to take the title of sultan , which he took in 1638 , under the Arabic name Abulmafakhir Mahmud Abdulkadir .
Ole Jacob Bangstad ( 9 April 1917 -- 2 June 2010 ) was a Norwegian military officer and sports official .
Ernest Collinge ( 5 December 1895 -- 15 December 1960 ) was an English footballer who played as a half - back for Port Vale in the 1920s .
Roger McKenzie ( 22 July 1971 -- 25 November 1995 ) also known under his production aliases of Wildchild or DJ Wildchild , was an English musician and DJ . Born in Southampton , England , he released many singles on labels such as Hi Life Recordings , Ultra Records , and Polydor ( UK ) .
Jan van der Vaardt ( name variations : Jan van der Vaart , John Van der Vaart , John Vander Vaart , Jan van der Waart ) ( c.1650 --1727 ) was a Dutch painter of portraits , landscapes and trompe - l'œil paintings and a mezzotint artist who was active in England for most of his career .
Boris Škanata ( 18 May 1927 -- 1962 ) was Croatian swimmer who won a bronze medal in the 100 m backstroke at the 1950 European Aquatics Championships .
Harold John Pye ( 27 November 1901 - 20 January 1986 ) was the son of William George Pye who , in 1896 , started a company called W G Pye which manufactured scientific and optical equipment .
Brajkishore Prasad ( 1877 - -1946 ) was a lawyer inspired by Mohandas Gandhi during the Indian Independence Movement .
Erin Lordan ( 8 November 1963 - 26 February 2005 ) was a British singer who had hits in the UK with BBG , Bamboo , Ascension and Shut Up and Dance .
Seyyed Mohammad - Ali Emam - Shooshtari ( born 1902 A.D. , died 1972 A.D. ) was a prominent Iranian historian and religious scholar .
Ricardo Cirera Salse ( Os de Balaguer , 1864-Barcelona , August 1932 ) was a geomagnetist who conducted the first geomagnetic survey of the Philippines and who founded the El Ebro Observatory in Roquetes ( 1904 ) , Catalonia , Spain .
John Francis Marchment Middleton ( 22 May 1921 -- 27 February 2009 ) was a British professor of anthropology in the United States , specializing in Africa .
Elemér Gyulai ( 1904 - 1945 ( on the Russian front ) ) was a Hungarian Jewish composer .
Louis Günther I , Count of Schwarzburg - Rudolstadt ( 27 June 1581 in Rudolstadt -- 4 November 1646 in Rudolstadt ) was the ruling Count of Schwarzburg - Rudolstadt from 1612 until his death .
Herman VIII , Margrave of Baden - Baden ( died 1338 ) was a titular Margrave of Baden - Baden .
Allan Codling ( 24 February 1911 -- q1 1991 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Clapton Orient and Darlington .
Francis Percy Toplis ( 20 August 1896 -- 6 June 1920 ) was a British criminal and imposter active during and after the First World War .
Lyndon Brook ( 10 April 1926 -- 9 January 2004 ) was a British actor , on film and television .
Aveline de Forz , Countess of Aumale and Lady of Holderness ( 20 January 1259 - -10 November 1274 ) was an English noblewoman .
Ramona Solberg ( 1921 - -2005 ) created large jewellery using found objects ; she was an influential teacher at the University of Washington School of Art and often referred to as the `` grandmother of Northwest found - art jewelry '' .
Hakija Pozderac ( 6 March 1919 -- 27 March 1994 ) was a Yugoslav Communist politician and Partisan .
John Morley , 1st Viscount Morley of Blackburn OM PC ( 24 December 1838 -- 23 September 1923 ) was a British Liberal statesman , writer and newspaper editor .
James Ian Keith , 12th Earl of Kintore ( 25 July 1908 -- 1 October 1989 ) , known as The Viscount Stonehaven between 1941 and 1974 , was a Scottish peer and nobleman .
Grenville Charles Lennox Berkeley ( alternatively Charles Lennox Grenville Berkeley ) ( 30 March 1806 -- 25 September 1896 ) , also known as C. L. Grenville Berkeley , was a British Liberal Party politician .
Yannis Tsarouchis ( Greek : Γιάννης Τσαρούχης ; 13 January 1910 -- 20 July 1989 ) was a Greek painter .
Thomas Cosmades ( 29 April 1924 in Istanbul -- 20 September 2010 ) was a Turkish - born ethnic - Greek , later American national , Evangelical preacher and translator of a New Testament in Turkish .
Joseph - François de Payan , known as Payan - Dumoulin ( 9 February 1759 , Saint - Paul - Trois - Châteaux - Alixan , 20 May 1852 ) was a political figure during the French Revolution , as was his younger brother Claude - François de Payan .
Sir Francis Dashwood , 1st Baronet ( c. 1658 -- 4 November 1724 ) was a British merchant .
Tenzing Norgay OSN GM ( /ˈtɛnsɪŋ ˈnɔːrɡeɪ/ ; 29 May 1914 -- 9 May 1986 ) , born Namgyal Wangdi and often referred to as Sherpa Tenzing , was a Nepalese - born Indian Sherpa mountaineer .
Georg Wilhelm Pabst ( 25 August 1885 -- 29 May 1967 ) , known professionally as G. W. Pabst , was an Austrian theatre and film director .
Helena Bochořáková - Dittrichová ( July 31 , 1894 , Vyškov , Moravia -- 28 March 1980 , Brno , Czechoslovakia ) was a highly accomplished Czech graphic artist .
Juan Agustín Maza ( 4 May 1784 -- 11 June 1830 ) was an Argentine statesman and lawyer .
Heba Selim ( died 1973 ) was an Egyptian spy who worked for the Mossad along with her fiancé Farouk Al - Fikki .
Målfrid Grude Flekkøy ( 29 November 1936 - 2 November 2013 ) was a Norwegian chief psychologist and civil servant .
Rees Howell Gronow ( 1794 -- 22 November 1865 ) , `` Captain Gronow '' , was a Welsh Grenadier Guards officer , an unsuccessful parliamentarian , a dandy and a writer of celebrated reminiscences .
Ellen Riley Wright ( 24 December 1859 - 3 August 1904 ) was an English composer of music for popular songs .
Edmund Brindholme ( Brindholm or Bryndeholme ) ( died 1540 ) was an English Catholic priest , executed under an act of attainder on a charge of involvement in a plot to betray Calais , then an English possession , to the French .
Douwe Aukes ( 1612 - -1668 ) was a Frisian sea captain of the Dutch East India Company or VOC .
Titan Leeds ( 1699 - -1738 ) was an 18th - century American almanac publisher .
Paul Starrett ( 1866 - -1957 ) was an American builder .
Sir Mordaunt Martin , 4th Baronet ( c. 1740 - 24 September 1815 ) was son of Sir Roger Martin , 3rd Baronet and Sophia Mordaunt .
Swami Lakshman Joo Raina ( 9 May 1907 -- 27 September 1991 ) was a mystic and scholar of Kashmir Shaivism or Trika .
Gustav Adolf Zwanziger ( 29 July 1837 in Schloss Neuhof near Neustadtl -- 10 June 1893 in Klagenfurt ) was an Austrian journalist , botanist and paleobotanist .
Hilaire Hiler ( 1898 - 1966 ) was an American artist , psychologist , and color theoretician who worked in Europe and United States during the mid-20th century .
Thomas Floyd ( fl . 1589 - -1603 ) was a Welsh writer at the turn of the 16th and 17th centuries .
Mike Daggett , or Ondongarte by birth , ( unknown -- February 25 , 1911 ) was a Shoshone native American who is best known for his involvement in the Battle of Kelley Creek , during which he was killed with several members of his family .
Samuel James Andrews ( 1817 - -1906 ) was an Irvingite divine .
Sir James Gray , 1st Baronet , of Denne Hill , East Kent , ( 1667 -- 27 October 1722 ) , was an armiger , and a merchant - burgess of Edinburgh , who later managed the affairs in London of James Graham , 1st Duke of Montrose .
Moses Buttenweiser ( 1862 - -1939 ) was an American Bible scholar , born at Beerfelden , Germany and educated at the universities of University of Würzburg , Leipzig , and Heidelberg .
Hippolyte Havel ( 1871 - -1950 ) was a Czech anarchist who lived in Greenwich Village , New York , which he declared to be `` a spiritual zone of mind '' .
Franciszek Pinck , also Pink , and Ping , Bing or Byng ( 1733 - 27 May 1798 ) was a Polish sculptor and stucco artist .
Serge Segay ( real name Sergey Vsevolodovich Sigov Russian : Сергей Всеволодович Сигов , 19 March 1947 - 21 September 2014 ) , also known as Sergej Sigej , was a Russian artist , poet , writer as well as specialist in Russian Futurism .
William Courtenay , 1st Earl of Devon ( 1475 -- 9 June 1511 ) , feudal baron of Okehampton and feudal baron of Plympton , was a member of the leading noble family of Devon .
John Boxall ( died 1571 ) was an English churchman and secretary of state to Mary I of England .
Thomas Alwyn Lloyd ( 11 August 1881 -- 19 June 1960 ) , known as T. Alwyn Lloyd , was a leading Welsh architect and town planner .
Edward Misselden ( fl . 1608 - -1654 ) was an English merchant , and leading member of the writers in the Mercantilist group of economic thought .
Xia Chuzhong ( Chinese : 夏楚中 ; pinyin : Xià Chǔzhōng ; Wade -- Giles : Hsia Ch'u - chung ; 30 May 1904 -- 28 December 1988 ) was a KMT general from Yiyang , Hunan province .
David Veit ( 8 November 1771 , in Breslau -- 15 April 1814 ) , was a German doctor and writer .
Gutierre Vermúdez ( or Gutier Bermúdez ) ( died 1130 ) was a nobleman of the Kingdom of León , with interests primarily in Galicia , mainly in the northeast , around Lugo .
Jalaluddin Fateh Shah ( reigned : 1481 - -1487 ) was the last ruler of later Ilyas dynasty of Bengal .
Major John Robert Perceval - Maxwell ( 1896 - -1963 ) was an Ulster Unionist Party politician from Northern Ireland .
Maria Josepha of Austria ( Maria Josepha Benedikta Antonia Theresia Xaveria Philippine , Polish : Maria Józefa ; 8 December 1699 -- 17 November 1757 ) was born an Archduchess of Austria , and from 1711 to 1717 was heiress presumptive to the Habsburg Empire .
Graham Lusk ForMemRS ( 15 February 1866 - 18 July 1932 ) was an American physiologist , and nutritionist .
Christian Sommerfeldt ( 6 January 1746 -- 30 May 1811 ) was a Norwegian geographer and civil servant .
Olga Potocka ( 1803 -- 7 October 1861 ) was a Polish countess .
Lambert de Hondt the Elder or Lambert de Hondt ( I ) ( c. 1620 - before 10 February 1665 ) was a Flemish painter and draughtsman mainly known for his equestrian and battle scenes as well as his genre and landscape paintings .
Arthur Wellesley L'Estrange Fawcett MC ( 1894 -- 1961 ) was a British screenwriter and film producer , notable for his work at Gainsborough Pictures such as Bed and Breakfast ( 1930 ) .
Theodor Hermann Dahlmann would survive until 21 January 1978 , when he died in Rimsteig , Germany at 85 years of age .
Karol Durski - Trzaska ( 1849 - -1935 ) was an officer in Austro - Hungarian Army and later , Polish Army .
Krishnan Nair ( 25 July 1939 -- 16 November 1980 ) , better known by his stage name Jayan , was an Indian film actor , naval officer , stunt performer and cultural icon of the 1970s .
Kananginak Pootoogook ( 1 January 1935 -- 23 November 2010 ) was an Inuk sculptor and printmaker who lived in Cape Dorset , Nunavut , in Canada .
Catherine of Gorizia ( died 1391 ) was a daughter of Count Meinhard VI of Gorizia and his first wife Catherine of Pfannberg .
Abraham Mendel Theben ( before 1730 -- 1768 ) was the head of the Jewish community in the Kingdom of Hungary .
Terence Mophuting ( 1965 - -2008 ) was a Botswanan footballer .
Prince Marama Teururai later known as Regent Marama ( 17 December 1851 -- 7 June 1909 ) was a member of a Tahitian royal family ( House of Teururai ) which reigned on the Tahitian island of Huahine during the 19th century .
Dharmapala Raksita ( 1268 -- 24 December 1287 ) was the head of the Sakya school of Tibetan Buddhism , which was the most powerful school in Tibet under the Yuan dynasty from 1280 - 1282 .
George Meggott ( 1669 - -1723 ) , of Stoney Lane , St. Olave 's , Southwark , was an English politician .
Leopoldo Toniolo ( 1833 - -1908 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of genre themes .
Charles Henry Grant ( 9 November 1831 -- 30 September 1901 ) was an engineer and politician in the Colony of Tasmania .
Jessie Franklin Turner ( 10 December 1881 -- 1956 ) was an American fashion designer based in New York in the early 20th century .
Zhang Xueming ( 1908 - April 9 , 1983 ) was the mayor of Tianjin .
Lemuel Chenoweth ( 1811 - -1887 ) was a carpenter , legislator and self - taught architect .
Alexis Roland - Manuel ( 22 March 1891 -- 1 November 1966 ) was a French composer and critic , remembered mainly for his criticism .
William Grant Stairs ( 1 July 1863 -- 9 June 1892 ) was a Canadian - British explorer , soldier , and adventurer who had a leading role in two of the most controversial expeditions in the history of the colonisation of Africa .
Prince Christian of Hesse ( Danish : Christian af Hessen ; German : Christian von Hessen ) ( 14 August 1776 -- 14 November 1814 ) was a German prince and member of the House of Hesse - Kassel .
Poul Hartling ( Danish pronunciation : ( pʌʊl hɑɐ̯tleŋ ) ) ( 14 August 1914 -- 30 April 2000 ) was a Danish diplomat and politician .
