Paul Gustavson ( née Karl Paul Gustafson August 16 , 1916 -- April 29 , 1977 ) was an American - immigrant comic - book writer and artist .
Asbjørn Balthazar Syrrist ( 19 October 1874 -- 1953 ) was a Norwegian jurist , newspaper editor and politician for the Conservative Party .
Bess of Hardwick died at 5 pm on Saturday 13 February 1608 , aged 81 .
Eileen Erskine ( 15 August 1914 -- 8 November 1995 ) was an English film actress from Nottingham who was mainly active in the 1940s when she appeared in This Happy Breed ( 1944 ) and Great Expectations ( 1946 ) .
Regency architect Michael Searles ( 1750 - -1813 ) was famous as an English commercial architect of large houses , particularly in London .
George Elliott Dodds ( 4 March 1889 -- 20 February 1977 ) was a British journalist , newspaper editor , Liberal politician and thinker .
George J. Fisher M.D. ( died 1960 ) was a physician and leader in the fields of youth development and physical fitness in the United States during the early twentieth century .
Jean Baptiste Virlogeux ( died 1958 ) was a French chef .
Adolf Hoel ( 15 May 1879 -- 19 February 1964 ) was a Norwegian geologist and polar researcher .
Sir Benjamin Fonseca Outram ( 1774 - -1856 ) was an English naval surgeon , physician and medical inspector .
Evelyn St. Croix Fleming , born Evelyn Beatrice St. Croix Rose , in Kensington , London , known as Eve Fleming ( 1885 -- 27 July 1964 ) , was an English socialite .
Colonel John Biddulph ( 25 July 1840 -- 24 December 1921 ) was a British soldier , author and naturalist who served in the government of British India .
François Victor Le Tonnelier de Breteuil ( 17 April 1686 -- 7 January 1743 , in Issy ) was a French nobleman .
John Moyr Smith ( 12 March 1839 -- 1 December 1912 ) was a British artist and designer , noted for his work on ceramic tiles .
Oswald Allen Harker CBE ( 1886 - -1968 ) , also called Brigadier ' Jasper ' Harker , was Acting Director General of MI5 from 1940 to 1941 .
Leta Peer ( 1964 -- 13 February 2012 ) was a Swiss painter and fine art photographer .
Winston Cooper ( c.1939 - -1995 ) , better known as Count Matchuki or Count Machuki , was the first Jamaican deejay .
Hédi Khayachi , born 1882 in Tunis and died 1948 in Marsa , was a Tunisian painter .
Władysława Markiewiczówna ( 5 February 1900 in Bochnia -- 17 May 1982 in Katowice ) was a Polish pianist and renowned educator .
General John Hely - Hutchinson , 2nd Earl of Donoughmore , GCB ( 15 May 1757 -- 29 June 1832 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician , hereditary peer and soldier .
George Hunn Nobbs ( 16 October 1799 -- 5 November 1884 ) was an English ( he claimed Irish ) missionary on Pitcairn Island and later Norfolk Island , where his many descendants still live today .
Ioannis Ladas ( Greek : Ιωάννης Λαδάς ) ( 1920 -- 16 October 2010 ) was a member of the Greek military junta of 1967 - -1974 .
William Lutley Sclater ( 23 September 1863 -- 4 July 1944 ) was a British zoologist and museum director .
Hannah Marshman ( 13 May 1767 , Bristol - 5 March 1847 , Serampore , India ) was a missionary .
Sir Nicholas Colthurst , 4th Baronet ( 1789 - -1829 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician .
Ciarán Bourke ( 18 February 1935 - -10 May 1988 ) was an Irish musician and one of the original founding members of the Irish folk band The Dubliners .
Kostas Manoussakis ( Greek : Κώστας Μανουσάκης ; January 1929 -- 26 August 2005 ) was a Greek film director and screenwriter .
Thomas Bottomley ( 26 December 1910 -- 19 February 1977 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played in six matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club in 1934 and 1935 .
William Blackburn ( 1750 - -1790 ) was the leading prison architect of the Georgian Era .
Theodoros Manetas ( Greek : Θεόδωρος Μανέτας , 1881 - -1947 ) was a Greek Army officer who rose to the rank of Lieutenant General and served as Chief of the Hellenic Army General Staff in 1931 - -1933 .
Holly Solomon ( 1934 -- 2002 ) was a prominent collector of contemporary art and founder of the Holly Solomon Gallery in New York City in 1975 .
Britton Bath Osler ( 19 June 1839 -- 5 February 1901 ) was a Canadian lawyer and prosecutor .
Harold Leidner ( 31 January 1916 -- 13 August 2008 ) was an American patent attorney and amateur scholar of early Christianity .
Charles Plumet ( 17 May 1861 -- 15 April 1928 ) was a French architect , decorator and ceramist .
Doris Schade ( 21 May 1924 -- 25 June 2012 ) was a German television actress .
Henry Kaplan ( September 13 , 1926 -- September 14 , 2005 ) was a television director known for his works on Dark Shadows , Ryan 's Hope , The Doctors and All My Children .
Domenico Annibali ( c. 1705 - 1779 ) was an Italian castrato who had an active international career from 1725 - 1764 .
Ture Lennart Bodström ( 20 April 1928 -- 30 April 2015 ) was a Swedish politician born in Gothenburg , who served as the Minister for Foreign Affairs in Olof Palme 's Social Democratic cabinet from 1982 - 85 .
Hans Fleischhacker ( 10 March 1912 in Töttleben , Erfurt -- 1992 ) was a German anthropologist with the Ahnenerbe and a Schutzstaffel Obersturmführer .
Hieronymus Andreae , or Andreä , or Hieronymus Formschneider , ( died 7 May 1556 ) was a German woodblock cutter ( `` formschneider '' ) , printer , publisher and typographer closely associated with Albrecht Dürer .
Henry Crewe Boutflower ( 25 October 1796- 4 June 1863 ) , was a Hulsean essayist and minister .
Jeanette Möller , née Holmlund ( 5 January 1825 in Stockholm - 25 March 1872 in Düsseldorf ) , was a Swedish painter .
Baron Aschwin of Sierstorpff - Cramm ( German : Freiherr Aschwin von Sierstorpff - Cramm ; 29 March 1846 -- 14 October 1909 ) was the maternal grandfather of Prince Bernhard of Lippe - Biesterfeld , Prince consort of Queen Juliana of the Netherlands .
William Herbert Shipman ( 1854 - -1943 ) was a wealthy businessman on the island of Hawaii .
Stanisław Kłodziński ( 1918 - -1990 ) was a Polish physician , lung specialist , and survivor of the Auschwitz concentration camp .
Paddy Ryan ( 15 March 1851 -- 14 December 1900 ) was an Irish American boxer , and became his sport 's world 's heavyweight champion from May 30 , 1880 when he won the title from Joe Goss until losing his title to John L. Sullivan on February 7 , 1882 .
The career of set decorator Edward G. Boyle ( 30 January 1899 -- 17 February 1977 ) kicked off in the early 30s , when he started working on the first of over 100 films .
Henry B. Christian ( 1883 - -1953 ) was a painter who was born in Minneapolis , Minnesota .
Johan Caspar Herman Wedel Jarlsberg ( 21 September 1779 -- 27 August 1840 ) was a Norwegian statesman and count .
Aldo Crommelynck ( 26 December 1931 -- 22 December 2008 ) was a master printmaker who made intaglio prints in collaboration with many important European and American artists of the 20th Century .
Jorgelina Aranda ( 19 August 1942 -- 10 January 2015 ) was an Argentine actress , television personality and model .
Magnus Magnusson , KBE ( ( ˈmaknus ˈmaknusɔn ) ; 12 October 1929 -- 7 January 2007 ) was an Icelandic journalist , translator , writer and television presenter .
Fr . Con Cottrell ( 1917 -- 3 March 1982 ) was an Irish hurler who played as a midfielder for the Cork senior team .
William Cavendish , 7th Duke of Devonshire KG , PC ( 27 April 1808 -- 21 December 1891 ) , styled as Lord Cavendish of Keighley between 1831 and 1834 and known as The Earl of Burlington between 1834 and 1858 , was a British landowner , benefactor and politician .
Carl August Julius Milde ( 2 November 1824 -- 3 July 1871 ) was a German bryologist and pteridologist born in Breslau .
Egisto Bracci ( January 1 , 1830 in Florence -- August 1909 ) was an Italian architect , active mainly in Florence , who became resident professor of architecture at the Academy of Fine Arts of Florence in 1879 .
Ralph Bocking ( died 1270 ) , was an English Dominican .
Ottomar Gern also known as Konstantin Borisovich Gern ( 16 November 1827 -- 9 November 1882 ) , was a Russian fortification engineer .
Ghafoor Butt ( Urdu : عبدالغفور بٹ‎ ; 5 June 1936 -- 23 April 2011 ) was a Pakistani cricketer and umpire .
Valery Senderov ( Russian : Валерий Сендеров ; 17 March 1945 -- 12 November 2014 ) was a Soviet dissident , mathematician , teacher , and advocate of human rights known for his struggle against state - sponsored antisemitism .
Charles Cowan FRSE ( 7 June 1801 -- 1889 ) was a Scottish politician and paper - maker .
Edward Preble ( 15 August 1761 -- 25 August 1807 ) was a United States naval officer who served with great distinction during the 1st Barbary War , leading American attacks on the city of Tripoli and forming the officer corps that would later lead the U.S. Navy in the War of 1812 .
Blessed Nunzio Sulprizio ( 13 April 1817 -- 5 May 1836 ) was an Italian from Pescara who worked as an apprentice blacksmith .
Samuel Ryder ( 24 March 1858 -- 2 January 1936 ) was an English businessman , entrepreneur , golf enthusiast , and golf promoter .
Carl Julian Sanders ( 1912 - -2007 ) was an American Bishop of the United Methodist Church who was elected to that office in 1972 .
Farman Behboud ( 1946 - March 2010 ) ( Persian : فرمان بهبود ‎ ) was an Iranian pianist and piano teacher .
Flann Óge Ó Domhnalláin ( died 1342 ) was Chief Poet of Connacht .
Illtyd Trethowan ( 12 May 1907 -- 30 October 1993 ) , born as Kenneth Trethowan , was an English priest , philosopher and author .
Tirur Nambissan ( died 1994 ) was a Kathakali singer .
Harry Frederick Oppenheimer ( 28 October 1908 -- 19 August 2000 ) was a prominent South African businessman and one of the world 's richest men .
Edward Squire ( died 1598 ) was an English scrivener and sailor , and an alleged conspirator against the life of Elizabeth I of England .
Andrew Geddes Bain ( baptised 11 June 1797 -- 20 October 1864 ) , was a South African geologist , road engineer , palaeontologist and explorer .
Lee Eastman , born Leopold Vail Epstein ( 12 January 1910 -- 30 July 1991 ) was a New York show business attorney , and art collector the son of Louis ( b. Russia ~1887 , imm . 1906 ) and Stella ( Freyer ) Epstein .
Sir Frederick Albert Bosanquet , KC , JP ( 8 February 1837 - -2 November 1923 ) was the Common Serjeant of London , the second most senior permanent judge of the Central Criminal Court after the Recorder of London .
E. Ballard Baker ( Oct. 25 , 1917 -- March 1985 ) was a Virginia jurist who served briefly as the first Chief Judge of the newly created Court of Appeals of Virginia before his death in 1985 .
Quiwe Baarsen ( died 1627 ) , was a Sami shaman .
Henrique de Meneses , 3rd Marquis of Louriçal , 7th Count of Ericeira ( 5 January 1727 - 29 May 1787 ) , was a Portuguese nobleman and statesman .
Kathir ibn Ahmad ibn Shahfur ( also known as Kuthayyir ) ( died 919 ) was the amir of Sistan from 917 until his death .
Yusuf Adil Shah ( 1450 - -1511 ) , referred as Adil Khan or Hidalcão by the Portuguese , was the founder of the Adil Shahi dynasty that ruled the Sultanate of Bijapur for nearly two centuries .
Sheridan Raynor ( 7 July 1934 -- 10 December 2011 ) was a Bermudian cricketer .
Winifred Emms ( 4 April 1883 -- 28 September 1972 ) , best known by her stage name Hetty King , was an English entertainer who played in the music halls over a period of 70 years .
Fortún Ximénez ( pronounced : ( foɾˈtun xiˈmeneθ ) ) ( died 1533 ) was Spanish sailor who led a mutiny during an early expedition along the coast of Mexico and is the first European known to have landed in Baja California .
Germaine Van Parys , also Van Parijs , ( 1893 - -1983 ) was a pioneering Belgian photojournalist .
Victor Mapes ( 10 March 1870 -- 27 September 1943 ) was an American playwright , stage manager and director .
Mullah Attiya al - Jamri ( Arabic : الملا عطية الجمري‎ , b. 1899 -- 29 August 1981 ) was a famous Bahraini khatib and poet .
Frano Kršinić ( 24 July 1897 -- 1 January 1982 ) was a renowned Croatian sculptor .
Karel Petrů ( 24 January 1891 in Březové Hory - 1949 ) was the coach of the Czechoslovakia national football team when they finished second in the 1934 FIFA World Cup .
Alfred Gregory Yewen ( 16 May 1867 -- 11 June 1923 ) was an Australian agricultural writer , journalist and socialist .
Grand Ayatollah Sheikh Ali Safi Golpaygani ( 1913 -- 3 January 2010 ) was an Iranian Twelver Shi'a Marja .
Elias de Barjols ( fl . 1191 - -1230 ) was a bourgeois Aquitainian troubadour who established himself in Provence as a landed nobleman and retired a monk .
James Booth ( born David Geeves ; 19 December 1927 -- 11 August 2005 ) was an English film , stage and television actor and screenwriter .
John Percy ( Piercey ; alias John Fisher ) ( 27 September 1569 at Holmeside , Durham -- 3 December 1641 in London ) was an English Jesuit priest and controversialist .
Edward Preston ( 1831 - -1890 ) was a lawyer and judge originally from England who served in the Kingdom of Hawaii .
Hans Kutscher ( 14 December 1911 -- 24 August 1993 ) was a member of the first and second Senate of the German Constitutional Court and later a member and then President of the European Court of Justice .
Pauline Lucille Western ( born in New Orleans , 8 January 1843 ; died in Brooklyn , New York , 11 January 1877 ) was an stage actress who worked in the United States .
Pan Yunu ( Chinese : 潘玉奴 ; died 501 ) or Pan Yu'er ( Chinese : 潘玉儿 ) was an imperial consort during the Chinese dynasty Southern Qi .
Rev. Henry Richard MP ( 3 April 1812 -- 20 August 1888 ) , `` the Apostle of Peace '' , was a Congregational minister and Welsh Member of Parliament , 1868 - 88 .
David D. Bogart ( March 31 , 1860 -- December 1912 ) was County Clerk and Recorder and the 6th Mayor of Missoula , Montana .
Colonel William McConnachie ( 10 March 1848 -- 27 January 1932 ) was a Scottish businessman , and politician He was born on 10 March 1848 in Dufftown , Scotland .
Mervyn Patrick Wingfield , 9th Viscount Powerscourt ( 22 August 1905 -- 1973 ) was an Irish peer .
Ogulsapar Muradova ( Огулсапар Мурадова ) , 1948 - 2006 ) was a Turkmen human rights activist and Radio Free Europe journalist .
Vasily Buzunov ( Russian : Василий Гаврилович Бузунов ) ( 4 February 1928 , Ishim , Kemerovo Oblast -- 18 February , 2004 ) was a Russian footballer and hockey player .
Archibald Lang McLean ( 1885 - -1922 ) was an Australian bacteriologist known for his role as chief doctor on the Sir Douglas Mawson 's Australasian Antarctic Expedition .
Kerry Juby ( 3 January 1948 -- July 2003 ) was born in Bexley , South London and was a radio DJ who worked for Pirate Radio Station Radio Caroline in the 1960s ( initially as an engineer ) under the name Kerry Clarke .
Sir Frederick Philipse Robinson , GCB ( September 1763 -- 1 January 1852 ) was a soldier , born in the Highlands , near New York , in September 1763 , who fought for Britain during the American War of Independence .
William Benson Mayo ( 7 January 1866 - 1 February 1944 ) was chief power engineer for the Ford Motor Company .
Alain Canhiart ( died 1058 ) was the Count of Cornouaille from 1020 - 1058 .
Rainiero d'Elci ( 7 March 1670 -- 22 June 1761 ) was an Italian Cardinal .
Samuel Peirson ( c. 1647 - 1720 ) was an English organist .
William Oberhardt ( 1882 - -1958 ) was an American artist , portrait painter , lllustrator and sculptor .
Pamela Bianco ( December 31 , 1906 -- 1994 ) was an English - born American painter , illustrator , and writer , who came to fame as a child prodigy in the 1910s .
Edward Penny RA ( 1 August 1714 -- 16 November 1791 ) was an English portrait and historical painter , one of the founder members of the Royal Academy .
Charles Fitch ( 1805 - -1844 ) was an American preacher in the early 19th century , who rose to prominence for his work with the Millerite movement .
Saints Theodore and Pausilippus ( died 130 AD ) were 2nd century Christian martyrs who were killed during the persecution of Christians under the Roman emperor Hadrian .
Warren T. Brookes ( died 1991 ) was a longtime journalist with the Boston Herald and the Detroit News and a nationally syndicated columnist .
Jan Gullberg ( 1936 -- 21 May 1998 ) was a Swedish surgeon and anaesthesiologist , but became known as a writer on popular science and medical topics .
John Jones ( 19 January 1810 -- October 1869 ) , known by his bardic name of Talhaiarn , was a Welsh poet and architect .
Giulio Cesare Martinengo ( Italian pronunciation : ( ˈdʒuːljo ˈtʃeːzare martiˈneŋɡo ) ; c. 1564/1568 -- 10 July 1613 ) was an Italian composer and teacher of the late Renaissance and early Baroque Venetian School .
Yaakov Abuhatzeira , also known as the Abir Yaakov and Abu Hasira ( 1806 - -1880 ) , was a leading Moroccan - Jewish rabbi of the 19th century .
Kenneth N. MacKenzie ( 26 November 1897 -- 29 September 1951 ) Master R.R.S ' DISCOVERY ' THE ' BRITISH , AUSTRALIAN & NEW ZEALAND ANTARCTIC RESEARCH EXPEDITION ' ( B.A.N.Z.A.R.E ) Voyage 1930 - -1931
Sardar Abdur Rashid Khan ( Urdu : سردار عبد الرشید خان‎ ) ( 1906 - ? 1995 ) was a senior police officer from the Khyber - Pakhtunkhwa province and cabinet minister in Pakistan .
Sir Henry Doulton ( 25 July 1820 -- 18 November 1897 ) was an English businessman , inventor and manufacturer of pottery , instrumental in developing the firm of Royal Doulton .
Frederick Howard , 5th Earl of Carlisle KG , KT , PC ( 28 May 1748 -- 4 September 1825 ) was a British diplomat and the son of Henry Howard , 4th Earl of Carlisle and his second wife Isabella Byron .
Marie - Renée Roudaut ( 3 March 1847 - 18 October 1930 ) was a Catholic missionary nun .
François de Troy ( 1645 -- 21 November 1730 ) was a French painter and engraver who became principal painter to King James II in exile at Saint - Germain - en - Laye and Director of the Académie Royale de peinture et de sculpture .
Elsje Christiaens ( Jutland , c. 1646 -- Amsterdam , 1664 ) was a Danish girl who , aged 18 , murdered her landlady with an axe in Amsterdam .
Saint Hadelin ( or Adelin , Hadelinus ) d. about 690 , born in Gascony , was one of the scholarly , mostly Irish monks , who preached Christianity and started conversion work in what is now Belgium under the pagan invaders , as did Saint Servatius and Saint Remacle .
Isaac Wilson Joyce ( 11 October 1836 -- 28 July 1905 ) was an American bishop in the Methodist Episcopal Church , elected in 1888 .
William Hunnis ( died 6 June 1597 ) was an English Protestant poet , dramatist , and composer .
Subagio Sastrowardoyo ( 1 February 1924 -- 18 July 1995 ) was an Indonesian poet , short - story writer , essayist and literary critic .
Jackie Searl ( July 7 , 1921 - 29 April 1991 ) , born John E. Searl , was an American child actor who began performing on a local Los Angeles radio at the age of three .
Talcott Williams , ( 1849 - -1928 ) , was an American journalist and educator .
Joseph Thebaud ( 1772 - -1811 ) was an agent of the French East India Company , and later in about 1792 founded Thebaud Brothers , a commission house in New York City .
Robert C. Bak ( 1908 - 1974 ) was a Hungarian - born psychoanalyst who moved to the States in 1941 , and eventually became President of the New York Psychoanalytic Society .
Francis Robert Raines ( 22 February 1805 - 17 October 1878 ) was the Anglican vicar of Milnrow , Lancashire , known as an antiquary .
Blue Corn ( c. 1920 -- May 3 , 1999 ) , also known as Crucita Calabaza , was a Native American potter from San Ildefonso Pueblo , New Mexico , in the United States .
Sir Alexander Maxwell , 2nd Baronet ( died 23 May 1730 ) was a Scottish Member of Parliament ( MP ) in the British Parliament .
Ngawang Namgyal ( later granted the honorific Zhabdrung Rinpoche , approximately at whose feet one submits ) ( Tibetan : ཞབས་དྲུང་ངག་དབང་རྣམ་རྒྱལ་ , Wylie : zhabs drung ngag dbang rnam rgyal ; alternate spellings include Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyel ; 1594 - -1651 ) was a Tibetan Buddhist lama and the unifier of Bhutan as a nation - state .
Theodore Fawcett ( 10 February 1832 -- 21 March 1898 ) was an early settler in colonial Western Australia , and became a Member of the Western Australian Legislative Council .
Magloire Ambroise , hero of the Haitian Independence , was born in Jacmel , Saint - Domingue in 1774 and died in Port - au - Prince on December 7 , 1807 .
Maria de Naglowska ( 1883 - 1936 ) was a Russian occultist , mystic , author and journalist who wrote and taught about sexual magical ritual practices while also being linked with the parisian surrealist movement .
Samuel Zimmerman ( 7 March 1815 -- 12 March 1857 ) was a Canadian railway promoter and entrepreneur instrumental in the construction of the Great Western Railway of Upper Canada .
Juan Arañés ( died c. 1649 ) was a Spanish baroque composer .
Bedri Spahiu ( July 13 , 1908 -- 11 January 1998 ) was an Albanian politician and Lieutenant - General and one of the most prominent figures of the Albanian Labour Party up to 1956 .
Claude Houghton Oldfield ( May 1889 -- 10 February 1961 ) , who published under the name Claude Houghton , was a British writer , principally of novels that have been characterised as `` psychological romances , often embodying personal mysticism and a remote allegory '' .
William John Hardy ( 29 September 1857 -- 17 July 1919 ) was an English archivist and antiquarian .
Walter Crum ( 1796 -- 1867 ) was a Scottish chemist and businessman .
Bohdan Koziy ( 23 February 1923 -- 30 November 2003 ) was a Ukrainian suspected war criminal and allegedly a member of the Ukrainische Hilfspolizei ( Ukrainian Auxiliary Police ) , a Nazi German mobile police force that operated in the General Government on July 27 , 1941 .
Ramihrdus of Cambrai , a known priest who had been practicing his own sects of religion , was accused of heresy in 1076 or 1077 for being unwilling to accept communion from priests , including the bishop , after being summoned to court because he believed that the priesthood was corrupt .
Aaron Eugene Kofi Asante Ofori - Atta ( born 12 December 1912 -- July 1978 ) was a politician and also the fourth Speaker of the Parliament of Ghana .
Anthony Richard Blake ( 1786 - -1849 ) , was an Irish lawyer , administrator and ' backstairs Viceroy of Ireland ' .
Zhang Guangdou ( 1 May 1912 -- 21 June 2013 ) was a specialist in hydraulic engineering , professor and vice president of Tsinghua University , and a member of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and Chinese Academy of Engineering .
Jones Chilengi ( 30 January 1955 -- 9 April 1999 ) was a Zambian footballer and coach .
Alice Mary Smith , married name Alice Mary Meadows White ( 19 May 1839 -- 4 December 1884 ) was an English composer .
Robert Gottschalk ( 12 March 1918 -- 3 June 1982 ) was an American camera technician and founder of Panavision .
Dame Esmerelda Cicely Courtneidge DBE ( 1 April 1893 -- 26 April 1980 ) was an English actress , comedienne and singer .
William Holder FRS ( 1616 -- 24 January 1698 ) was an English clergyman and music theorist of the 17th century .
Benjamin Tregoe ( born December 23 , 1927 ) was co - founder of Kepner - Tregoe , a management consulting firm , where he served as chairman emeritus until his death in 2005 .
Richard Henry Walthew , also known as Richard H. Walthew ( 4 November 1872 -- 14 November 1951 ) was an English composer and pianist .
Air Marshal Sir Albert Durston KBE , CB , AFC ( 19 June 1894 -- 24 January 1959 ) was a senior Royal Air Force ( RAF ) officer who served as Deputy Chief of the Air Staff from 1945 to 1946 .
Manilal Pandya ( 1905 - -1994 ) was an Indian freedom fighter and an ayurvedic practitioner from Borsad , India
Jarmo Savolainen ( 24 May 1961 -- 11 June 2009 ) was a Finnish jazz pianist and composer .
Max Grundig ( German pronunciation : ( ˈmaks.ˈgʁʊn.dɪç ) ; 7 May 1908 -- 8 December 1989 ) was the founder of electronics company Grundig AG . He was raised by his parents in Nuernberg where he delayed his final school exams ( Abitur ) and completed training as an electrician .
Angelo , called Angeluccio , a scholar of Claude Lorrain , was living in 1680 , but died young .
Memucan Hunt ( 1729 - -1808 ) was an early American statesman and the first person to hold the position of North Carolina State Treasurer in its current form .
Porter Paisley Vinson ( 1890 - -1959 ) was a surgeon at the Mayo Clinic .
Husi Chun ( 斛斯椿 ) ( 495 - -537 ) , courtesy name Fashou ( 法壽 ) , formally Prince Wenxuan of Changshan ( 常山文宣王 ) , was a general and official of the Chinese / Xianbei state Northern Wei and Northern Wei 's branch successor state Western Wei .
Greta Gynt ( 15 November 1916 -- 2 April 2000 ) , born Margrethe Woxholt , was a Norwegian singer , dancer and actress .
Sir John Carmichael ( died 16 June 1600 ) was the Keeper of Liddesdale .
Chu Suiliang ( 596 - -658 ) , courtesy name Dengshan , formally the Duke of Henan ( 河南公 ) , was a Chinese official who served as a chancellor during the reigns of the emperors Taizong and Gaozong in the Tang dynasty .
Thanasis Vagias ( Greek : Θανάσης Βάγιας , 1765 - -1834 ) was a Greek counselor and confidant of Ali Pasha , a Muslim Albanian ruler of Ottoman Epirus .
Jumaboi Ahmadjonovich Khodjiyev ( 1968 -- November 2001 ) , better known by the nom de guerre Juma Namangani , was an Uzbek Islamist militant with a substantial following who co - founded and led the Islamic Movement of Uzbekistan and received substantial Taliban patronage , allowed to operate freely in northern Afghanistan .
Mordaunt Shairp ( 13 March 1887 -- 18 January 1939 ) was an English dramatist and screenwriter born at Totnes .
Ahmed Harrak Srifi was killed in the Rif war in Morocco in 1925 .
Henry Penruddocke Wyndham ( 1736 - -1819 ) MP JP FSA FRS , was a British Whig Member of Parliament , topographer and author .
Tabitha Babbitt ( 1779 -- about 1853 ) was an early American and Shaker tool maker and inventor , including inventions for the circular saw , spinning wheel head and false teeth .
Sir William Drake , 1st Baronet ( 28 September 1606 -- 28 August 1669 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1640 and 1648 and again from 1661 to 1669 .
Willem Jacobszoon Coster ( Modern Dutch , Koster ) ( 1590 , Akersloot - 21 August 1640 ) was the Governor of Zeylan during the Dutch period in Ceylon .

Henry Misselbrook ( 16 December 1832 -- 11 July 1895 ) was an English cricketer who represented Hampshire in one first - class match in 1869 against the Marylebone Cricket Club .
Karl Spiesberger ( 29 October 1904 -- 1 January 1992 ) was a German mystic , occultist , Germanic revivalist and Runosophist .
Pavle Julinac ( 1730 - 1785 ) was a Serbian writer , historian , traveller , soldier and diplomat .
John Rolle , 1st Baron Rolle ( 1750 -- 3 April 1842 ) was a British peer who served as a Member of Parliament in general support of William Pitt the Younger and was later an active member of the House of Lords .
Cecil McGivern CBE ( 22 May 1907 , Newcastle , England -- 30 January 1963 , Buckinghamshire , England ) was a British broadcasting executive , who initially worked for BBC Radio before transferring to BBC Television in the late 1940s .
Sant Thakar Singh ( 26 March 1929 -- 6 March 2005 ) was a spiritual teacher in the Sant Mat lineage of hindu religious leaders .
Jenifer Estess ( 1963 - -2003 ) was a Moline , Illinois - born theatre producer .
Eric Schocket ( 1966 -- 2006 ) was an Associate Professor of American literature at Hampshire College in Amherst , Massachusetts .
Alexander Hume - Campbell , 2nd Earl of Marchmont PC ( 1675 -- 27 February 1740 ) , was a Scottish nobleman , politician and judge .
Pádraig Kennelly ( died 21 May 2011 ) was an Irish journalist , editor , photographer , cameraman and publisher , who co - founded and edited the Kerry 's Eye newspaper .
Avo Paistik ( 21 April 1936 − 3 December 2013 ) was an Estonian cartoonist , author , film director , painter and pastor .
Sir George Burton Hunter , KBE ( 19 December 1845 -- 21 January 1937 ) was a British shipbuilder based on Tyneside .
Hiram Kahanawai ( 1837 - -1874 ) was a Hawaiian high chief who was husband of Princess Poʻomaikelani .
Francisco Calderón Guardia ( 13 June 1906 -- 17 July 1977 ) was a Costa Rican politician .
Désiré Magnus ( né Magnus Deutz ; 13 June 1828 in Brussels -- 17 December 1883 in Paris ) was a Belgian concert pianist , teacher and composer of salon music who published under the pseudonym D Magnus .
Thomas William Davids ( 1816 - -1884 ) was a Welsh nonconformist minister and ecclesiastical historian .
Beka I Jaqeli ( Georgian : ბექა I ჯაყელი ) ( c. 1240 -- 1306 ) was a ruling prince ( mtavari ) of Samtskhe ( 1285 - -1306 ) .
Francesco Zucco ( Italian pronunciation : ( franˈtʃesko ˈdzukko ) , c.1570 -- May 3 , 1627 ) was an Italian painter .
Nicholas Monck ( c. 1610 -- 7 December 1661 ) was bishop of Hereford and provost of Eton .
Abul Hashim ( Bengali : আবুল হাশিম ; 25 January 1905 -- 5 October 1974 ) was a Bengali politician .
James Westland ( 21 July 1916 -- February 1972 ) was a footballer who played in the Football League for Mansfield Town and Stoke City .
Oreste Giorgi ( 19 May 1856 -- 30 December 1924 ) was a Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church and was former Major Penitentiary of Apostolic Penitentiary .
Fusilier Gordon Gentle ( born & originally known as Gordon MacCrae ) was a 19-year - old soldier from Pollok , Glasgow , who died in Iraq on 28 June 2004 , after completing his 26-week basic training course at the Infantry Training Centre in Catterick .
Daniel D. Whitney ( January 31 , 1819 -- November 10 , 1914 ) was a Brooklyn grocer and Mayor of Brooklyn from 1886 to 1887 .
Alfred B. Skar ( 30 January 1896 -- 24 December 1969 ) was a Norwegian newspaper editor , writer , trade unionist and politician for the Labour and Communist parties .
John Battersby Crompton Lamburn ( June 1893 -- 3 April 1972 ) was a British writer , the younger brother of the more popular author Richmal Crompton .
Matthew Stachiw ( born 1895 , Nushche , d. 1978 , also spelt ' Matwij ' or ' Mathew ' ) was a Ukrainian politician .
Cengiz Dağcı ( 9 March 1919 -- 22 September 2011 ) was a Crimean Tatar novelist and poet .
Karam Allāh Muḥammad Kurkusāwī ( died 1903 ) was a Dongolāwī Mahdist emir ( amīr ) .
Jack Bruton ( 21 November 1903 -- 13 March 1986 ) was a professional footballer and manager who spent the major part of his career in both capacities with Blackburn Rovers .
Walter Thomas Clifford Earp ( 1879 - -1921 ) was a pioneer racing motorist .
Sheikh Salem Sabah Al - Salem Al - Sabah ( Arabic : الشيخ سالم صباح السالم الصباح‎ ) ( 18 June 1938 -- 8 October 2007 ) was a senior member of the House of Al - Sabah of Kuwait .
Eric Blore ( 23 December 1887 -- 2 March 1959 ) was an English comic actor .
Alexander Abiodun Adebayo Bada ( 4 December 1930 - 8 September 2000 ) was the second Pastor of the Celestial Church of Christ ( CCC ) , succeeding the founder Samuel Biléhou Joseph Oschoffa in December 1985 .
Yevhen Holitsynsky ( birth : 1870 , Chișinău -- † 1932 , Poděbrady ) was a Ukrainian diplomat .
Ruaraidh Erskine of Marr ( 15 January 1869 - 5 January 1960 ) ( Scottish Gaelic : Ruaraidh Arascain is Mhàirr ) was a Scottish nationalist political activist , writer and Scottish Gaelic language campaigner .
Burhan Nizam Shah II ( ruled 1591 - 1595 ) was the ruler of Ahmadnagar in the Deccan .
Carey Bell died of heart failure on 6 May 2007 in Chicago .
Sir Anthony Lambert KCMG ( 7 March 1911 -- 28 April 2007 ) was a British diplomat who was UK envoy to Bulgaria , Tunisia , Finland and Portugal .
General Sir Henry Drury Harness , K. C. B. , Colonel Commandant Royal Engineers ( 29 April 1804 -- 10 February 1883 ) was a British soldier who held several notable civil posts during his career .
Leo Lösch von Hilkertshausen ( died 1559 ) was the 49th Bishop of Freising in 1552 to 1559 .
Erwin Planck ( 12 March 1893 -- 23 January 1945 ) was a German politician , and a resistance fighter in the Third Reich .
Hishikawa Moronobu ( Japanese : 菱川 師宣 ; 1618 -- 25 July 1694 ) was a Japanese artist known for popularizing the ukiyo - e genre of woodblock prints and paintings in the late 17th century .
Josy Gyr - Steiner ( 10 October 1949 -- 18 April 2007 ) was a Swiss politician from the Canton of Schwyz and member of the Swiss National Council ( 2003 - -2007 ) .
Julian of Norwich ( c. 8 November 1342 -- c. 1416 ) was an English anchoress and an important Christian mystic .
Ernest Franklin Bozman ( 1895 - -1968 ) is a British author and the editor of two editions of Everyman 's Encyclopaedia .
Joseph Potaski or John Potaskie ( c. 17641 -- 31 August 1824 ) was the first Pole to settle in Australia , and one of the first convicts to arrive in Van Diemen 's Land on the Ocean .
James Foreman ( 21 December 1763 -- 25 October 1854 ) was a Scottish immigrant to Canada who became an important force in the business community of Nova Scotia .
Johannes Isaaks ( 23 January 1941 -- 19 March 2010 ) was a Namibian teacher , politician and community activist .
In February 2005 , Alberto Castagna started presenting a new edition of Stranamore , with Emanuela Folliero , but it was never completed because of his death , which occurred on 1 March 2005 due to an internal bleeding .
Joseph Louis Cook or Akiatonharónkwen ( died October 1814 ) ( Mohawk ) was an Iroquois leader and commissioned officer in the Continental Army during the American Revolution .
James Herbert Lorrain , or Pu Buanga , ( 6 February 1870 -- 8 January 1944 ) was a Scottish Baptist missionary in northeast India , including Mizoram , Assam , and Arunachal Pradesh .
Ezra Attiya ( Hebrew : עזרא עטיא‎ ; Arabic : عزرا عطية‎ ) ( 31 January 1887 -- 25 May 1970 ) was one of the greatest teachers of Torah in the Sephardic Jewish world during the 20th century .
Alesso di Benozzo ( 1473 in Florence -- 1528 ) was an Italian painter , son of Benozzo Gozzoli .
Kálmán Mihalik ( 21 February 1896 -- 6 September 1922 ) was a Hungarian physician and composer , best known for setting the music of the Székely Himnusz .
Kjell Lund ( 18 June 1927 -- 17 August 2013 ) was a Norwegian architect , songwriter and singer .
John Keith Dunstan OAM ( 3 February 1925 -- 11 September 2013 ) , known as Keith Dunstan , was an Australian journalist and author .
Virginia Orr Maes ( 1920 - -1986 ) was an American malacologist associated with the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia .
François Lamoureux ( 17 December 1946 -- 26 August 2006 ) was a prominent European civil servant whose influential career placed him at the centre of European integration .
Ludwik Żychliński ( born 1837 in Grand Duchy of Posen , d. after 1901 in Brusno , Lubaczów County ) was a Polish patriotic activist , pułkownik , diarist .
Robert Ferrar ( died 30 March 1555 ) was a Bishop of St David 's in Wales .
George Hanger , 4th Baron Coleraine ( 13 October 1751 -- 31 March 1824 ) was a British soldier , author , and eccentric .
Darko Radovanović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Дарко Радовановић ) ( 21 September 1975 -- 11 June 2011 ) was a Serbian singer popular in Serbia and the other former Yugoslav republics .
Pandit Raghunath Seth ( 1931 -- 15 February 2014 ) was a noted Indian exponent of Hindustani classical music through the medium of Bansuri , or bamboo flute ; he was also a noted film score composer .
Sir Aubrey Vere Symonds KCB ( 1874 - 1931 ) was a senior British civil servant .
Henry Wallis ( 21 February 1830 -- 20 December 1916 ) was an English Pre - Raphaelite painter , writer and collector .
Edward Burton Gleeson ( 1803 -- 2 February 1870 ) , also known as `` Paddy '' Gleeson , was a South Australian settler , farmer and founder of the town of Clare .
William Grimaldi ( 1751 - 1830 ) was an English miniature painter .
George - Paschal Desbarats ( 11 August 1808 -- 12 November 1864 ) was a French - Canadian printer , publisher , businessman , and landowner .
Andreas Armsdorff ( also Armsdorf ; 9 September 1670 -- 31 December 1699 ) was a German composer and organist .
Thomas Parnell ( 11 September 1679 -- 24 October 1718 ) was an Anglo - Irish poet and clergyman who was a friend of both Alexander Pope and Jonathan Swift .
Anand Modak ( Marathi : आनंद मोडक ) ( 13 May 1951 -- 23 May 2014 ) was an acclaimed Marathi film composer and music director in Marathi cinema and Marathi theatre , known for his experimental style .
Vita Gollancz ( 1926 - -2009 ) was a British painter , printmaker , illustrator and draughtsman .
Hedley Fitton ( 1859 in Didsbury , Manchester - 19 July 1929 Surrey ) , was an engraver and printmaker noted mainly for his architectural etchings .
Diana Beauclerk , Duchess of St Albans ( c. 1679 - -15 January 1742 ) , born Lady Diana de Vere , was a British courtier .
Jalaluddin Jalal ( born 15 October 1923 in Kabul ; died 1977 in Kabul ) was an Afghan poet and painter .
Dolores Guinness ( 31 July 1936 -- 20 January 2012 ) , was a German born `` Freiin '' ( Baroness ) , socialite , fashion icon and jet set member of the 1950s and 1960s .
William Thomas Blanford ( 7 October 1832 -- 23 June 1905 ) was an English geologist and naturalist .
George Carl ( 7 May 1916 -- 1 January 2000 ) was a `` vaudevillian '' style comic & clown .
Air Marshal Sir Ernest Leslie Gossage KCB , CVO , DSO , MC ( 3 February 1891 -- 8 July 1949 ) .
Caterina Assandra ( c. 1590 -- after 1618 ) was an Italian composer and Benedictine nun .

Li Baozhen ( 李抱真 ) ( 733 - -794 ) , né An Baozhen ( 安抱真 ) , courtesy name Taixuan ( 太玄 ) , formally the Prince of Yiyang ( 義陽王 ) , was a general of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty .
Jan Van Bragt ( 1928 - -2007 ) was a scholar of Japanese religion and philosophy at the Nanzan Institute for Religion and Culture in Nagoya , Japan , where he served as its first acting director in 1976 .

Richard Hosmer ( 3 January 1757 at Mereworth , Kent -- 29 April 1820 at Mereworth ) was an English cricketer who played for Kent .

John Walter Fletcher ( 11 May 1847 -- 28 February 1918 ) is widely regarded as the `` father of Australian soccer '' .
Samuel Luther ( 1636 -- 20 December 1716 ) was a prominent early figure in the Massachusetts Colony .
William Watts ( 1722 -- 4 August 1764 ) was chief of the Kasimbazar ( or Cossimbazar ) factory of the British East India Company .
Gyula Lóránt ( 6 February 1923 -- 31 May 1981 ) , born as Gyula Lipovics , was a Hungarian footballer and manager of Croatian descent .
Gunnar Nylund ( 1904 - -1997 ) was a Swedish ceramic designer since the 1930s , best known as the artistic director of Rörstrand , was already a well - established ceramic artist in Denmark first at the Bing & Grøndahl Porcelain factory in Copenhagen 1925 - 28 .
Adam Rankin Alexander ( November 1 , 1781 -- November 1 , 1848 ) was an American politician who represented Tennessee in the United States House of Representatives .
Besançon Hugues ( b. 1487 - d. 1532 ) was a member of the Grand Council of Geneva and participated in the rebellion against the rule of the Savoy dynasty , which led to the independence of Geneva in 1526 .
Alice Werner ( 26 June 1859 - 9 June 1935 ) was one of seven children in the family of Reinhardt Joseph Werner of Mainz , teacher of languages , and his wife , Harriett .
Thomas Hawkesworth Ledwich ( 1823 - 29 September 1858 ) was an eminent Irish anatomist and surgeon .
Nicolae Teodorescu ( Romanian pronunciation : ( nikoˈla.e te.odoˈresku ) ; 1797 - -1880 ) was a Moldavian - born Romanian church painter ( muralist ) , and the uncle of artist Gheorghe Tattarescu .

François Joseph Albert Léon de la Fontaine , ( 18 November 1819 -- 5 February 1892 ) , was a Luxembourgish lawyer , politician and botanist .

Hans - Heinz Augenstein ( 11 July 1921 -- 7 December 1944 ) was a German Luftwaffe fighter and flying ace during World War II . A flying ace or fighter ace is a military aviator credited with shooting down five or more enemy aircraft during aerial combat .
Cyril Bridge ( 28 August 1909 -- 27 January 1988 ) was an English footballer who played as a left back .

Jeff Clifton ( 21 February 1949 -- 18 October 2010 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .

Herbert Price ( 1605 -- 14 January 1678 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1640 and 1678 .
Seyyed Mohammad Bagher Najafi Shoushtari ( January 1948 -- July 2002 ) was a prominent Iranian scholar of Iranian Studies , in particular Iranian art and culture , and Islamic Studies .
Roald Storsletten ( 2 September 1915 -- 6 February 1991 ) was a Norwegian newspaper editor .
Wim Verstappen ( 4 May 1937 -- 24 July 2004 ) was a Dutch film director and producer , television director , and screen writer .
Erik Moseholm ( 13 May 1930 -- 12 October 2012 ) was a Danish jazz bassist , composer , bandleader and music administrator .
Tobias Saunders ( b. ~1620 - d. 1695 ) was a Deputy to the Rhode Island General Assembly ( 1669 , 1671 , 1672 , 1680 , 1681 , 1683 , and 1690 ) , a Conservator of the Peace ( 1669 , 1678 , and 1695 ) and a founding settler of Westerly , Rhode Island .
Tafil Buzi ( 1792 - 1844 ) was an Albanian leader and fighter , known for his role in various rebellions against Ottoman government in South Albania during the Albanian Revolts of 1833 - 1839 .
Percival Coles ( 2 May 1865 -- 24 February 1920 ) was an English sportsman and sporting administrator .
Nicolò Maria Antonelli ( 8 July 1698 -- 24 September 1767 ) was an Italian Cardinal in the Roman Catholic Church , a learned canonist , ecclesiastical historian , and Orientalist .
Cyrus Redding ( 1785 , Cornwall - 1870 ) was a British journalist and wine writer .
Alicia Penalba ( August 7 , 1913 -- November 4 , 1982 ) was an Argentine sculptor , tapestry designer , and weaver .
Jean Baptiste Wilkie ( 1803 - -1886 ) was a Métis chief from the Pembina area .
Eliard Swanston ( died 1651 ) , alternatively spelled Heliard , Hilliard , Elyard , Ellyardt , Ellyaerdt , and Eyloerdt , was an English actor in the Caroline era .
Sissy Löwinger ( 22 June 1941 -- 25 September 2011 ) was an Austrian actress , director and theatre manager .
Hamza al - Jawfi is an Al - Qaeda commander who in June 2010 was killed in Pakistan .
Parsegh Shahbaz ( Armenian : Բարսեղ Շահբազ ; June 1883 -- 1915 ) was an Ottoman Armenian lawyer , political activist , journalist , and columnist .
Sir Stanley Matthews , CBE ( 1 February 1915 -- 23 February 2000 ) was an English footballer .
Sir William Oglander , 1st Baronet ( ca . 1611 -- 1670 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons of England from 1660 to 1670 .
Richard Frederick Thompson ( 6 September 1930 -- 16 September 2014 ) was an American behavioral neuroscientist .
María Elena Lucena Arcuri ( 25 September 1914 -- 7 October 2015 ) was an Argentine film actress of the Golden Age of Argentine Cinema ( 1940 - -60 ) .
Major Claude Scudamore Jarvis CMG OBE ( born 20 July 1879 in Forest Gate , London , died 8 December 1953 in Ringwood , Hampshire ) was a British colonial governor , Arabist and naturalist noted for his knowledge of and rapport with the desert Bedouin .
Sif Einarsdotter Ruud Fallde born Sif Einarsdotter Ruud ( 6 May 1916 -- 15 August 2011 ) , best known as Sif Ruud , was a Swedish film actress .
Joseph , Marquis de Saint Brisson ( 8 May 1867 -- 4 May 1927 ) was a French fencer .
Charles Elmore Cropley ( 1894 - -1952 ) served as Clerk of the Supreme Court of the United States for a quarter of a century , from 1927 until his death in 1952 .
Dr K. N. Kesari ( 1875 -- 8 June 1953 ) was an Indian physician , social reformer , philanthropist , author , magazine editor and patron of music .
Timothy Detudamo ( died in April 1953 ) was a Nauruan politician and linguist .
Giovanni Giacinto Achilli ( Italian pronunciation : ( dʒoˈvanni dʒaˈtʃinto aˈkilli ) ; c. 1803 -- c. 1860 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic who was discharged from the priesthood for sexual misconduct and subsequently became a fervent advocate of the Protestant evangelical cause .
Marcin Ruar ( German Martin Ruar , Latin Ruarius ) , pseudonym Aretius Crispinus ) ( 1589 - -1657 ) was a Socinian writer , advocate of religious tolerance , and rector of the Racovian Academy from 1620 to 1622 .
James Stewart , 1st Duke of Richmond , 4th Duke of Lennox KG ( 6 April 1612 -- 30 March 1655 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Generalmajor Rudolf Sieckenius ( 16 May 1896 - - 28 April 1945 ) was a German soldier , most famous for his command of 16 Panzer Division during Operation Avalanche ( Salerno Landings ) in September 1943 .
Ernesto Mangaoang ( 1902 -- 1968 ) was a Filipino American labor organizer .
Edward Windsor , 3rd Baron Windsor ( 1532 -- 24 January 1574 ) was an English peer .
Mary Rose Thacker ( April 9 , 1922 -- July 1983 ) is a former Canadian singles figure skater and is a three - time ( 1939 , 1941 - -1942 ) national and two - time ( 1939 and 1941 ) North American champion .
Egon Sassmannshaus ( 19 March 1928 , in Wuppertal -- 7 August 2010 , in Munich ) was a violinist and string pedagogue .
Thomas Cotes ( died 1641 ) was a London printer of the Jacobean and Caroline eras , best remembered for printing the Second Folio edition of Shakespeare 's plays in 1632 .
William Henry Goss ( 30 July 1833 London - 4 January 1906 Stoke upon Trent ) was an English potter notable for having started the souvenir trade in pottery .
James Worts ( ca.1792 -- 1834 ) was one of the co - founders of the Gooderham and Worts partnership which , after his death , evolved from a simple mill into a prosperous distilling company , one which would eventually become the largest in the world .
William Kempe ( died 1603 ) , commonly referred to as Will Kemp , was an English actor and dancer specialising in comic roles and best known for having been one of the original players in early dramas by William Shakespeare .
Alfred Johannes Olsen ( April 12 , 1884 - - May 20 , 1956 ) , better known under his pen name Bob Olsen , was an American science fiction writer .
Serajuddin Hossain ( 1 March 1929 -- 10 December 1971 ) was a prominent Bangladeshi journalist .
Chivu Stoica ( the family name being Chivu ; 8 August 1908 -- 18 February 1975 ) was a leading Romanian Communist politician .
James Grenville ( 12 February 1715 -- 14 September 1783 ) was a British politician .
João Mouzinho de Albuquerque ( 21 February 1797 , in Leiria -- 8 August 1881 , in Portalegre ) was a Portuguese writer and administrator .
Henry E. Nichols ( died 10 June 1899 ) was an officer in the United States Navy who served as the commander of the Department of Alaska from September 14 , 1884 to September 15 , 1884 as commander of the USS Pinta .
Sir John Guildford ( by 1508 - -1565 ) was an English Member of Parliament for Gatton , New Romney and Kent and was appointed Sheriff of Kent in 1552 .
Robert Parris ( 21 May 1924 -- 5 December 1999 ) was a composer and professor of music .
Sir William Drummond Stewart , 7th Baronet ( 26 December 1795 - 28 April 1871 ) was a Scottish adventurer and British military officer .
Kinache ( c. 1750-c . 1819 ) was a Seminole chieftain who commanded Seminole forces against the United States during the American Revolution and later during the First Seminole War .
Owen Connellan ( 1797 -- 4 August 1871 ) was an Irish scholar who translated the Annals of the Four Masters into English in 1846 .
Clotworthy Rowley , 1st Baron Langford ( 31 October 1763 -- 13 September 1825 ) , known as Hon . Clotworthy Taylor until 1796 and as Hon . Clotworthy Rowley from 1796 to 1800 , was an Irish peer .
Cheikh Anta Diop ( 29 December 1923 -- 7 February 1986 ) was a historian , anthropologist , physicist , and politician who studied the human race 's origins and pre - colonial African culture .
Fazang ( Chinese : 法藏 ; pinyin : Fǎzàng ; Wade -- Giles : Fa - tsang ) ( 643 - -712 ) was the third of the five patriarchs of the Huayan school .
Bill McCue OBE ( 1934 - -1999 ) was a traditional Scottish singer .
Sir Douglas Mawson OBE FRS FAA ( 5 May 1882 -- 14 October 1958 ) was an Australian geologist , Antarctic explorer and academic .
Patrick Mary O'Donnell ( 1897 - -1980 ) was an Irish - born Roman Catholic priest in Australia .
Enrique Oltuski Osacki ( 18 October 1930 -- 16 December 2012 ) was a Cuban government minister who participated in the Cuban Revolution .
Ahmad II ibn Muhammad was Emir of Harar ( 1794 - -1821 ) , and grandnephew of Emir Ahmad I ibn Abi Bakr .
Mary Cavendish , Duchess of Devonshire , GCVO CBE ( 29 July 1895 in Hatfield , Hertfordshire -- 24 December 1988 in Westminster , London ) was born Lady Mary Alice Gascoyne - Cecil , daughter of James Gascoyne - Cecil , 4th Marquess of Salisbury .
Dinah Sheridan ( 17 September 1920 -- 25 November 2012 ) was an English actress with a career spanning seven decades .
Nancy Phelan ( 2 August 1913 -- 11 January 2008 ) was an Australian writer who published over 25 books , including novels , biographies , memoirs , travel books and a cookbook .
Frank H. Warder ( birth date unknown - 1955 ) was the New York State Superintendent of Banks .
John H. Felt ( 1867 , Indiana -- 1938 , Missouri ) was an architect who designed many churches , schools , and government buildings in Missouri and Kansas .
Katsushika Ōi ( 葛飾 応為 , c. 1800 - 1866 ( exact dates of birth and death unknown ) ) , also known as Sakae ( 栄 ) , was a Japanese Ukiyo - e artist of the late 19th century Edo period .
Mattie Belle Davis ( 1910 - -2004 ) was a judge and the first woman from Florida elected to the American Bar Foundation and the second woman to be elected in the US .
Sir Samuel Toller ( 1764 - -1821 ) was an English advocate - general of Madras and legal writer .
Samuel Bonsall Parish ( 1838 - 1928 ) was a California botanist and curator of the herbarium at Stanford University .
Adriano Fiorentino ( 1440 - -1499 ) , also known as Adriano di Giovanni De ' Maestri , was an Italian medallist and sculptor .
Praful Bidwai ( 12 June 1949 -- 23 June 2015 ) was an Indian journalist , political analyst , and activist .
Dancing Brave ( 11 May 1983 -- 2 August 1999 ) was an American - bred , British - trained thoroughbred racehorse .
Matthieu Cottière ( Cotterius ) ( 1581 - -1656 ) was a French Reformed pastor at Tours and theological writer .
Rennequin Sualem ( 1645 − 1708 ) was a Walloon carpenter and engineer born on 29 January 1645 in Jemeppe - sur - Meuse , Wallonia , France .
Ambrosius Petruzzy ( died 1652 in Kaisersteinbruch , Kingdom of Hungary ) was an Italian master stonemason and baroque sculptor .
Walter Percy Day O.B.E. ( 1878 - -1965 ) was a British painter best remembered for his work as a matte artist and special effects technician in the film industry .
Dobrotitsa ( Bulgarian : Добротица , pronounced ( dɔˈbrɔtitsa ) ; Romanian : Dobrotici or Dobrotiţă ; Τομπροτίτζας in contemporaneous Byzantine documents ; Dobrodicie in contemporaneous Genoese documents ) was a Bulgarian noble , ruler of the de facto independent Principality of Karvuna and the Kaliakra fortress from 1354 to 1379 - -1386 .
Alf Fasmer Dahl ( 20 May 1874 -- 21 June 1933 ) was a Norwegian priest and composer .
Price Hartstonge ( 1692 - -1743 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician who sat in the Irish House of Commons as member for Charleville 1727 - 1743 .
Lavrenti Ardaziani ( Georgian : ლავრენტი არდაზიანი ) ( 1815 -- January 1 , 1870 ) was a Georgian writer and journalist and one of the forerunners of Georgian realistic fiction prose .
Abraham Cykiert ( 1926 - -2009 ) was an Australian Holocaust survivor and Melburnian playwright and Zionist activist of the 1970s .
Samuel Archer King ( 9 April 1828 , in Tinicum Township , Pennsylvania -- 3 November 1914 , in Philadelphia ) was a ballooning pioneer in the United States .
Gunnar Sommerfeldt ( 4 September 1890 -- 30 August 1947 ) was a Danish actor and film maker .
Eusebio Delfín Figueroa ( Palmira , 1 April 1893 -- Havana , 28 April 1965 ) was a Cuban trovador musician : a composer , guitarist and singer .
Daniel Joseph Wood , 1849 - 1919 FRCO 1873 ; was an English organist .
Tom Bentley Throckmorton ( January 20 , 1885 , Derby , Iowa -- 1961 ) was an American neurologist remembered for describing Throckmorton 's reflex .
Sir William David Evans ( 1767 - -1821 ) , was an English lawyer .
Jan de Jong ( 1942 - ca . 28 April 2009 ) was the ice master of the Thialf skating stadium in Heerenveen , Netherlands .
Toswel Kaua ( born 28 August 1947 in Lau , Malaita Province ; died 15 November 2010 in Honiara ) was a Solomon Islands politician , several times Cabinet minister , and Deputy Prime Minister from May to November 2007 .
Vilhelm Lauritzen ( 9 September 1894 -- 22 December 1984 ) was a leading Danish modern architect , founder of the still active architectural firm Vilhelm Lauritzen Arkitekter .
Robert Forgan ( 10 March 1891 -- 8 January 1976 ) was a British politician who was a close associate of Oswald Mosley .
Jean Gribomont ( 1920 - -1986 ) was a Benedictine scholar who professed as monk of the Abbey of Clervaux ( Luxemburg ) in 1939 .
Haller Nutt ( 1816 - 1864 ) was an American Southern planter .
Adriana Marines ( 1992 -- September 27 , 1997 ) , was a Mexican - American girl who was murdered in her Texas home .
Leonard Chappelow ( 1683 - 1768 ) was an English clergyman and orientalist .
Harry McEvoy ( 16 August 1902 -- 3 November 1984 ) was a British industrialist and food manufacturer .
Melozzo da Forlì ( c. 1438 -- 8 November 1494 ) was an Italian Renaissance painter and architect .
Zuheir Mohsen ( Arabic : زهير محسن‎ , also transcribed Zuhayr Muħsin or Zahir Muhsein ; 1936 -- 25 July 1979 ) was a Palestinian leader of the pro - Syria as - Sa'iqa faction of the Palestine Liberation Organization ( PLO ) between 1971 and 1979 .
Rev. William Holwell Carr , ( 1758 - -1830 ) was an English priest , art dealer , art collector and painter .
John Óge Burke , Irish gentleman and soldier , executed June 1601 .
Artúr Lajos Halmi ( 1866 - -December 3 , 1939 ) was a Hungarian painter who has several works on display in the Hungarian National Gallery .
Joannis Avramidis ( 23 September 1922 -- 16 January 2016 ) ( Greek : Iωάννης Aβραμίδης ) was a Greek - Austrian sculptor .
Johann Otto Boeckeler ( 12 August 1803 -- 5 March 1899 ) was a German apothecary - botanist of Oldenburg .
Robert Benjamin Lewis ( 1802 - February 1858 ) was an African and Native American author , best known for writing Light and Truth .
William Joseph Behr ( 26 August 1775 -- 1 August 1851 ) , German publicist and writer .
Paul R. Evans II ( 20 May 1931 -- 7 March 1987 ) was an American born furniture designer , sculptor , and artist , who is famous for his contributions to American furniture design and the American craft Movement of the 1970s , and with his work with the influential American manufacturer Directional Furniture .
William Horman ( c. 1440 -- April 1535 ) was a headmaster at Eton and Winchester in the early Tudor period of English history .
Cormac mac Connmhach ( died 867 ) was a scribe .
Cellach mac Rogallaig ( or Cellach Locha Cime ) ( died 705 ) was a King of Connacht from the Uí Briúin branch of the Connachta .
Harrie Wood ( 12 February 1831 -- 18 September 1917 ) was an Australian miner and civil servant .
Charlotte Sharman ( 1832 - -1929 ) was a Christian woman who ran orphanages for girls in West Square Southwark , Gravesend , Hampton , and Tunbridge Wells .
Tun Habib Abdul Majid bin Tun May Ali bin Tun Muhammad ( 1637 -- 27 July 1697 ) was the 19th Bendahara ( the ancient Malay equivalent of a Grand Vizier ) of the Johor Sultanate during the late 16th century .
Jansen Noyes , Jr. ( 1918 - -2004 ) was an investment banker and stock brokerage company executive .
Carl Abraham Pihl ( 16 January 1825 -- 14 September 1897 ) was a Norwegian civil engineer and director of the Norwegian State Railways ( NSB ) from 1865 until his death .
Juan de la Cámara or Juan Gómez de la Cámara(1525 - 1602 ) Spanish Conquistador and hidalgo was born in Alcala de Henares Spain in 1525 .
Sulejman Pitarka ( 1924 - -2007 ) was an Albanian actor , writer , and playwright , originally from Debar .
Sandford Sellers ( 1854 - 1938 ) was the Principal , Superintendent and President of Wentworth Military Academy from 1880 to 1935 .
William of Bellême ( 960/5 -- 1028 ) called William Princeps , was the Seigneur of Bellême and a member of the House of Bellême
Cynan ap Hywel ( ruled 999 - -1005 ) was a Prince of Gwynedd , one of the kingdoms or principalities of medieval Wales .
Count Ercole Graziadei ( 1900 - -1981 ) was an Italian lawyer .
Rip Van Dam ( c.1660 -- 10 June 1749 ) was the acting governor of the Province of New York from 1731 to 1732 .
John Jacob Thomas , who published as J. J. Thomas ( 1841 - 1889 ) was a Trinidadian linguist and writer .
Rangel Valchanov ( Bulgarian : Рангел Вълчанов ; 12 October 1928 -- 30 September 2013 ) ( also seen as Vulchanov ) was a Bulgarian cinema actor and director .

Mary Emelia Mayne ( 31 December 1858 -- 12 August 1940 ) , was an Australian philanthropist .
Johann Ruchrat von Wesel ( died 1481 ) was a German Scholastic theologian .
Petter Moen ( 14 February 1901 -- 8 September 1944 ) was a Norwegian resistance member later known for his diaries .
Manuel Palaiologos ( or Palaeologus ) ( 1455 - -1512 ) was the youngest child of Thomas Palaiologos and Catherine Zaccaria .
Nikolay Binev ( Bulgarian : Николай Бинев ; 5 July 1934 - 8 December 2003 ) was a Bulgarian theater and film actor .
Dr Donald Laycock ( 1936 - -1988 ) was an Australian linguist and anthropologist .
Israr Ahmed ( Urdu : ڈاکٹر اسرار احمد‎ ; 26 April 1932 -- 14 April 2010 ; Msc , MBBS ) was a prominent Pakistani Islamic theologian , philosopher , and an Islamic scholar followed particularly in South Asia as well as by the South Asian diaspora in the Middle East , Western Europe , and North America .
Benjamin Lester ( 13 July 1724 -- 25 January 1802 ) was a British politician and merchant involved in the Newfoundland fishery .
Edward Worsley ( 1605 -- 2 September 1676 ) was an English Jesuit writer and professor .
Adam Easton ( c. 1328/1338 -- 15 September 1397 ) was an English Cardinal , born at Easton in Norfolk .
Sir Frederick Handley Page , CBE , FRAeS ( 15 November 1885 -- 21 April 1962 ) was an English industrialist who was a pioneer in the aircraft industry and became known as the father of the heavy bomber .
Caroline Hodgson ( 1851 -- 11 July 1908 ) , also known as Madame Brussels , was a well - known brothel proprietor and local identity of the Little Lon district in Melbourne , Victoria , Australia , during the late 19th century .
Nina Frances Layard ( Stratford , Essex 1853 -- Ipswich 1935 ) was an English poet , prehistorian , archaeologist and antiquary who made many important discoveries , and by winning the respect of contemporary academics helped to establish a role for women in her field of expertise .
Charles Stewart Wurts ( 1790 - 1859 ) was a founder of the Delaware and Hudson Canal Company , which built the Delaware and Hudson Canal and later became the Delaware and Hudson Railway .
Auguste Legros ( 30 December 1922 -- 30 May 2008 ) was a politician of La Réunion island .
Jacques de Livron Joachim de la Tour de la Casa Martinez de Pasqually ( 1727?--1774 ) was a theurgist and theosophist of uncertain origin .
John Matthew Wilson Young ( 17 December 1822 ; Durham -- 4 March 1897 ; Lincoln ) was an English organist .
Vladimír Vašíček ( 29 September 1919 -- 29 August 2003 ) was a Czech painter , one of pioneers and classics of Czech modern and abstract painting past the Second World War .
Claude - Jean - Baptiste Hoin ( 5 June 1750 - - ? June 1817 ) was a French artist known primarily for his portraits and landscapes .
Bolko III of Strzelce ( also known as of Opole ; Polish : Bolko III Strzelecki ( or Opolski ) ; c. 1337 -- 21 October 1382 ) was a Duke of Opole during 1356 - -1370 ( with his brothers as co - rulers ) and Duke of Strzelce from 1375 until his death .
Andrea Borromeo ( c. 1615 -- 2 January 1683 ) was an Italian Theatine priest and missionary .
Peter von Bemmel ( 18 August 1686 -- 22 October 1754 ) was a German landscape artist .
Graham Joyce ( 22 October 1954 -- 9 September 2014 ) was a British writer of speculative fiction and the recipient of numerous awards , including the O Henry Award , for both his novels and short stories .
Stanley Bréhaut Ryerson ( March 12 , 1911 -- 1998 ) was a Canadian historian , educator , political activist .
Jean d'Aulon ( 1390 - -1458 ) served as Joan of Arc 's bodyguard , a position which is often attributed to Gilles De Rais .
Christopher Wyvill ( 1740 - -1822 ) was an English cleric and landowner , a political reformer who inspired the formation of the Yorkshire Association movement in 1779 .
The Soulmother of Küssnacht ( died 1577 ) was a Swiss medium and an alleged witch in the city of Küssnacht in the canton of Luzern in Switzerland .
George Byng Scott ( 1824 - 17 February 1886 ) was an English - born Australian public servant , who served as Government Resident of the Northern Territory between 1873 and 1876 .
Dr. Arthur L. Johnson ( died 1955 ) was an educator in the U.S. state of New Jersey and the namesake of Arthur L. Johnson High School in Clark .
Chan Canasta ( born Chananel Mifelew , 9 January 1920 -- 22 April 1999 ) was a pioneer of mental magic in the 1950s and ' 60s .
Jacob Jordaens ( 19 May 1593 -- 18 October 1678 ) was a Flemish painter , draughtsman and tapestry designer known for his history paintings , genre scenes and portraits .
Joseph Sembratovych ( Ukrainian : Йосиф Сембратович , Polish : Josyf Sembratowycz ; 8 November , 1821 , Krynica - Zdrój -- 23 October , 1900 ) was the Metropolitan Archbishop of the Ukrainian Greek Catholic Church from 1870 until his resignation in 1882 .
Paddy Duncan ( 1894 -- 9 April 1949 ) was an Irish footballer .
Shong Lue Yang ( RPA : Soob Lwj Yaj , Pahawh : ) ( September 15 , 1929 -- February , 1971 ) was a Hmong spiritual leader and inventor of the Pahawh script , a semi - syllabary for writing dialects of the Hmong language , as well as the Khmu language .
Ashley George Old ( born 1913 , d. 2001 ) was an artist best known for documenting the lives of prisoners of war forced to construct the Thailand - Burma Railway .
Dudley Ryder , 2nd Earl of Harrowby KG , PC , FRS ( 19 May 1798 -- 19 November 1882 ) , styled Viscount Sandon between 1809 and 1847 , was a British politician .
Rudolph Dunbar ( 26 November 1907 -- 10 June 1988 ) was a Guyanese conductor , clarinetist , and composer , as well as being a jazz musician of note in the 1920s .
Ridder Jacob Westerbaen ( 7 September 1599 -- 31 March 1670 ) , heer ( squire ) of Brantwyck - en - Ghybelant , was a Dutch poet .
Emperor Taizong of Tang ( 28 January 598 -- 10 July 649 ) , previously Prince of Qin , personal name Li Shimin , was the second emperor of the Tang Dynasty of China , ruling from 626 to 649 .
Amedeo di Castellamonte ( 1610 -- 17 September 1683 ) was an Italian architect , civil and military engineer .
Abul Kalam Shamsuddin ( November 3 , 1897 -- March 4 , 1978 ) was a journalist , politician and littérateur .
Rhys ab Owain ( died 1078 ) was a king of Deheubarth in southern Wales .
Mārtiņš Zīverts ( 27 July 1903 in Mežmuiža , Vilce parish -- 4 October 1990 ) was a Latvian playwright .
Betty Go - Belmonte ( 31 December 1933 -- 28 January 1994 ) was a Filipina journalist and newspaper publisher .
Carl Hans Lody , alias Charles A. Inglis ( 20 January 1877 -- 6 November 1914 ; name occasionally given as Karl Hans Lody ) , was a reserve officer of the Imperial German Navy who spied in the United Kingdom in the first few months of the First World War .
Sir George Gough Arbuthnot ( 28 August 1848 -- 3 May 1929 ) was a businessman and civic leader in British India .
Barry Cockcroft ( 4 October 1932 - 4 February 2001 ) was a UK television documentary director , writer and producer .
Christopher Holywood ( 1559 -- 4 September 1626 ) was an Irish Jesuit of the Counter Reformation .
James Cecil , 6th Earl of Salisbury ( 20 October 1713 -- 19 September 1780 ) was a British peer , son of James Cecil , 5th Earl of Salisbury and a member of one of England 's greatest political dynasties .
Charlotte Brewster Jordan ( 1862 -- circa 1932 ) was an American writer and translator , best known for her authorized translation of Vicente Blasco Ibañez 's Four Horsemen of The Apocalypse , which was one of the best - selling novels of the early 20th century .
Samuel Daskam ( January 31 , 1823 -- 1912 ) was Warden of the Borough of Norwalk , Connecticut from 1874 to 1877 .
Shripad Mahadev Mate ( Devanagari : श्रीपाद महादेव माटे ) ( 2 September 1886 - -25 December 1957 ) was a Marathi writer and a social reformer from Maharashtra , India .
Jean Rabier ( 16 March 1915 -- 21 October 1997 ) was a French cinematographer who frequently worked with director Claude Chabrol .
Margaret Hogg ( c. 1939 -- October 1976 ) was a manslaughter victim whose body was preserved in Wast Water lake for eight years .
José Chávez Morado ( 4 January 1909 -- 1 December 2002 ) was a Mexican artist who was associated with the Mexican muralism movement of the 20th century .
Patrociño Barela , also known as Patrocinio Barela or Patrocino Barela ( 1900 - -1964 ) , was a self - taught wood carver .
Joseph Hyde Potts ( 1793 -- 1865 ) was an accountant and in 1817 was the first employee to be engaged by the Bank of New South Wales ( now Westpac ) .
Luther Dixon ( 7 August 1931 -- 22 October 2009 ) was an American songwriter , record producer , and singer .
Laurie Paul ( 11 January 1881 -- 23 February 1957 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Francisco Bulnes ( 1847 -- 1924 ) was an influential intellectual during the regime of Mexican President Porfirio Diaz who served as the Secretary of Foreign Affairs .
Jill Fraser , MBE ( 15 April 1946 -- 10 February 2006 ) was a British theatre owner and director .
José Pantaleón Domínguez Román ( 27 July 1821 , Comitán --8 February 1894 , Comitán ) was a Mexican politician .
Rogério Duprat ( 7 February 1932 - 26 October 2006 ) was a Brazilian composer and musician .
Mirza Farhatullah Baig ( 1883 - -1947 ) was an Indian Urdu writer of humor and prose .
Ulrik Adolf Holstein , Count of Holsteinborg ( 14 April 1664 -- 21 August 1737 ) was a Danish nobleman and statesman .
Casimiro Montenegro Filho ( 29 October 1904 - -26 February 2000 ) was a Brazilian army and air force officer .
Te Rauparaha ( 1760s -- 27 November 1849 ) was a Māori rangatira ( chief ) and war leader of the Ngāti Toa tribe who took a leading part in the Musket Wars .
Émile Dubonnet ( October 18 , 1883 - 1940 ) was a French balloonist active from 1908 to 1913 .
George Vernon Meredith Frampton RA ( 17 March 1894 -- 16 September 1984 ) was a British painter and etcher , successful as a portraitist in the 1920s .
Robert Gravel ( 14 September 1944 -- 12 August 1996 ) was an actor , dramatist , theatrical director and teacher .
Markward von Annweiler ( died 1202 ) was Imperial Seneschal and Regent of the Kingdom of Sicily .
Sir William Pym , KCH ( 1772 -- 18 March 1861 ) was a British military surgeon .
James Robert Wyman ( 24 April 1909 -- 1978 ) , also known as Bob Wyman , was an ice hockey player who played in Great Britain .
Agneta de Graeff van Polsbroek ( Amsterdam , 10 November 1603 - 3 or 4 March 1656 ) , was a patrician woman from the Dutch Golden Age .
Christopher Newport ( 1561 - -1617 ) was an English seaman and privateer .
Thomas Blundeville ( c. 1522 -- c. 1606 ) was an English humanist writer and mathematician .
Sharwin I ( Persian : شروین ) was the fifth ruler of the Bavand dynasty from 772 to 817 .
Charles Erdman Petersdorff ( 1800 -- 1886 ) was a legal writer .
Yao Hong ( Chinese : 姚泓 ; 388 - -417 ) , courtesy name Yuanzi ( 元子 ) , was the last emperor of the Chinese / Qiang state Later Qin .
Nicholas Mavrogenes ( or Mavrogenous ; Greek : Νικόλαος Μαυρογένης Nikolaos Mavrogenis , Romanian : Nicolae Mavrogheni pronounced ( nikoˈla.e mavroˈɡeni ) ; died 1790 ) was a Phanariote Prince of Wallachia ( reigned 1786 - -1789 ) .
John de Bermingham , Anglo - Irish lord , died 1547 .
Andrew Leslie , 5th Earl of Rothes ( before 1541 - -1611 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Pier Leoni ( or Pierleone ) ( Latin : Petrus Leo or Petrus filius Leonis ) ( died 2 June 1128 ) was the son of the Jewish convert Leo de Benedicto and founder of the great and important medieval Roman family of the Pierleoni .
James Winthrop ( 1752 , Cambridge , Massachusetts - 26 September 1821 , Cambridge ) was an American librarian and jurist .
Sir Egerton Leigh , 1st Baronet ( 11 October 1733 -- 15 September 1781 ) was a British colonial jurist , who became HM Attorney - General of South Carolina .
Ziya Samedi ( Russian : Зия Самеди ) ( 1914 - 20 November 2000 ) was a Uyghur nationalist writer who held various Chinese government posts and then emigrated to Kazakhstan .
Lakshmi Krishnamurti ( 1 August 1925 -- 14 June 2009 ) was an Indian author and politician .
Agatha Barbara ( 11 March 1923 -- 4 February 2002 ) was a Maltese politician , having served as a Labour Member of Parliament and Minister .
James Dalrymple , 1st Viscount of Stair ( May 1619 -- 29 November 1695 ) , Scottish lawyer and statesman , was born at Drummurchie , Barr , South Ayrshire .
Alberto Alén Pérez ( 1948 in Havana -- 14 October 2004 ) was a Cuban musicologist and cellist .
Peter Vanderbank or Vandrebanc ( 1649 - -1697 ) was a French - English engraver .
Henry Thomas Mackenzie Bell ( 2 March 1856 -- 13 December 1930 ) , commonly known by his pen name Mackenzie Bell , was an English writer , poet and literary critic .
Krishna Kumar Birla ( 11 November 1918 -- 30 August 2008 ) was an Indian industrialist of the Birla family .
Dagobert Peche ( 3 April 1887 , Sankt Michael / Lungau , Land Salzburg - 16 April 1923 , Modling ) was an Austrian artist and metalworker designer .
Ezra Mir ( 1903 - 93 ) , ( fl . 1924 - -1993 ) was an Indian film - maker , known for his documentary films .
Frida Hansen ( born Frederikke Boletta Petersen , born March 8 , 1855 in Hillevåg in Stavanger , died 12 March 1931 in Oslo ) was a Norwegian tapestry maker in the Art Nouveau style .
Johann Maria Philipp Frimont , Count of Palota , Prince of Antrodoco ( 3 February 1759 -- 26 December 1831 ) was an Austrian general .
Agnolo Monosini ( Pratovecchio 1568 -- Florence 1626 ) was an Italian scholar and cleric of the 16th and 17th centuries , who played a key role in the development of the Italian language two hundred years prior to the risorgimento .
Eric Halladay ( 9 July 1930 -- 19 July 1997 ) was a British historian , academic , and rowing coach .
Jean - Marie Gonod ( 1827 - -1888 ) was a French rosarian .
Thomas Whatman ( 1576 - 1630 ) , of Chichester , Sussex , was an English politician .
Giles Jacob ( 1686 -- 8 May 1744 ) was a British legal writer whose works included a well - received law dictionary that became the most popular and widespread law dictionary in the newly independent United States .
Spiro Çomora ( 1918 - 1973 ) was an Albanian playwright of the 20th century , famous mostly as a comedist .
Sir George Hubert Wilkins MC & Bar ( 31 October 1888 -- 30 November 1958 ) was an Australian polar explorer , ornithologist , pilot , soldier , geographer and photographer .
William George Constable ( born Derby , England , 27 October 1887 , died Cambridge , Massachusetts , 3 February 1976 , was an art historian and gallery director .
Marcus Annius Verus ( 50 -- 138 AD ) was a Roman man who lived in the 1st and 2nd centuries .
Richard Paul Blakeney ( 1820 - -1884 ) was an Irish - born religious writer and cleric .
Stephen Peter Rigaud ( 1774 - -1839 ) was an English mathematical historian and astronomer .
Wei Zheng ( 580 - -643 ) , courtesy name Xuancheng , posthumously known as Duke Wenzhen of Zheng , was a Chinese statesman and historian .
József Viola ( 10 June 1896 - 18 August 1949 ) also known as Giuseppe Viola was a Hungarian football player and coach , most prominent for his time in Italy and his association with clubs such as Juventus .
Lee Oras Overholts ( 23 June 1890 -- 10 November 1946 ) was an American mycologist known for his expertise on polypore fungi .
William Cooke Taylor ( 1800 - -1849 ) was an Irish writer , known as a journalist , historian and Anti - Corn Law propagandist .
Lieutenant General Muhammad Azam Khan ( 1908 - -1994 ) was a senior general of the Pakistan army who served under General Ayub Khan , the first military ruler of Pakistan .
John Hicks Eynon ( 1801 - 1888 ) was a Bible Christian minister .
Sari Maritza ( 17 March 1910 -- July 1987 ) was an actress in British films of the early 1930s .
Malcolm Flemyng , M.D. ( d. 1764 ) , was a Scottish physiologist .
Richard Lumley , 1st Earl of Scarbrough ( 1650 -- 17 December 1721 ) was an English soldier and statesman best known for his role in the Glorious Revolution .
Gustav König ( 12 August 1910 -- 5 February 2005 ) was a German conductor and music director in Essen .
Olav Versto ( 31 July 1950 -- 7 July 2011 ) was a Norwegian journalist and editor , primarily known for his work for the newspaper Verdens Gang .
Charles Sprengel Greaves MA QC ( 1802 - -1881 ) , eldest son of William Greaves MD ( 1771 - -1848 ) of Mayfield , Staffordshire , by his first wife , Anne - Lydia , was born at Burton on 18 July 1802 .
Baba Mehar din ( 1922 - 21 October 2012 ) , better known as Chacha Pakistani or `` Uncle Pakistan '' , was a Pakistani man who was known for his daily appearance , dressed in a kurta made of a Pakistani flag , at the flag hoisting ceremony at the border point of Wagha .
George Herbert Tyson Smith ( 1883 - -1972 ) , was an English sculptor born in Liverpool .
Gustaf Lucander , also Locander ( 1724 - -1805 ) was a Finnish painter .
Thomas Olin Hathcock ( 1879 - -1966 ) was a Fulton County , Georgia judge from 1914 to 1942 .
Ogwyn Davies ( 1925 -- 26 December 2015 ) was a Welsh artist , born in Trebanos in the Swansea Valley .
Sir William Allmond Codrington Goode GCMG ( 8 June 1907 -- 15 September 1986 ) was a British colonial officer who served as governor and Colonial Secretary to various Far Eastern colonies in the 20th century .
Andien de Clermont ( died 1783 ) was a French artist who worked in England in the 18th century ( ca.1716 - 1756 ) .
Hedvig Sirenia , as married Schulzen or Schultz ( 1734 - 1795 ) , was a Swedish poet and translator , known simply as Sirenia .
Jangir Agha ( or Jahangir Agha , Cangîr Axa , Armenian : Ջահանգիր Աղա ; Russian : Джаангир Ага ) ( ca . 1874 - 1943 ) is a prominent military and social figure of Armenia in early 20th century and a national hero of the Yazidi people .
John Ferrabosco ( baptised 1626 -- died 1682 ) was organist of Ely Cathedral from 1662 until his death in 1682 .
Makarios I , was Archbishop of Cyprus from 1854 until 1865 .
Philip Stanhope Worsley ( 12 August 1835 -- 8 May 1866 ) was an English poet .
Marcel Bleibtreu ( 26 August 1918 -- 25 December 2001 ) was a French trotskyist activist and theorist .
Tahir Hussain ( 1938 -- 2 February 2010 ) was an Indian film producer and director known for his works in Hindi cinema .
Vittorio Sentimenti ( 18 August 1918 -- 27 September 2004 ) , also known as `` Sentimenti III '' , is a former Italian football player from Bomporto in the Province of Modena .
John Tracy Atkyns ( died 1773 ) , was an English barrister - at - law and compiler of the Atkyns ' Reports .
Per Berg Lund ( 1878 -- 1954 ) was the Norwegian Minister of Finance 1928 - 1931 and 1933 - 1934 .
In August or September 1518 , Bartolomeo Minio died at the age of ninety .
William Jewett Tenney ( born at Newport , Rhode Island , 1814 ; died at Newark , New Jersey , 20 September 1883 ) was an American author , editor and encyclopedist .
Saša Vegri ( true name Albina Vodopivec , née Doberšek ) ( 12 February 1934 -- 29 August 2010 ) was a Slovene poet who is also known for her books for young readers .
Cosme de Villiers de Saint Étienne ( 1683 - 1758 ) was a French Carmelite bibliographer .
Consort Dowager Cao ( 曹太妃 , personal name unknown ) ( died 562 ) was an imperial consort of the Chinese dynasty Liang Dynasty .
Stefan Tyszko was a London - based photographer who died in a car crash with two other journalists in August 1969 .
Henry Källgren ( 13 March 1931 -- 21 January 2005 ) was a Swedish former footballer who played at both professional and international levels as a striker .
Frank Horace Vizetelly ( 2 April 1864 -- 1938 ) was an English lexicographer , etymologist and editor .
Hans Zürn the Elder ( born between 1555 and 1560 , died after 1631 ) was a German sculptor and father of the famous Upper Swabian Zürn family of sculptors .
George Preston Coleman ( May 4 , 1870 -- June 16 , 1948 ) was the head of the Virginia Highway Commission from 1913 to 1922 and the mayor of Williamsburg , Va. , from 1929 to 1934 .
Albert Bassermann ( 7 September 1867 -- 15 May 1952 ) was a German stage and screen actor .
Sydney Singerman ( 24 April 1896 in Manchester , England -- 8 May 1996 ) was an editor , whose only edit work was in the silent movie The Hunchback of Notre Dame from 1923 based on the novel by Victor Hugo .
Theodone C. Hu ( J. C. Hu , Dongchao Hu , or Zhenting Hu ) ( 1872 - -1957 ) was a civil engineer in China .

Anthony Errington , D.D. ( died 1719 ? ) , was an English Catholic divine .
Ole Martin Ystgaard ( 21 June 1910 -- 19 September 1970 ) was a Norwegian dairy leader .
John W. Hancock ( April 13 , 1901 -- 1993 ) was an American football player , track and field athlete , coach of football , basketball , track , and wrestling , and college athletics administrator .
Phil Sokolof ( 1922 - 2004 ) was a multi - millionaire businessman and crusader against heart disease .
Henry of Grosmont , 1st Duke of Lancaster , 4th Earl of Leicester and Lancaster , KG ( c. 1310 -- 23 March 1361 ) , also Earl of Derby , was a member of the English nobility in the 14th century , and a prominent English diplomat , politician , and soldier .
Venerable Sumangalo died on 6 February 1963 and was cremated in Penang .
Bhagat Bhikhan ( Punjabi : ਭਗਤ ਭੀਖਨ ) ( 1480 - 1573 ) , a medieval Indian saint two of whose hymns are included in the Guru Granth Sahib .

Leland Jensen ( 22 August 1914 -- 6 August 1996 ) was the founder of a Bahá'í sect called the Bahá'ís Under the Provisions of the Covenant ( BUPC ) .
Count Frederick of Solms - Rödelheim ( 30 November 1574 -- 1649 ) was an imperial chamberlain , war councillor and colonel in the period of the Thirty Years ' War .
Margaret Jean Redcliffe - Maud , Baroness Redcliffe - Maude , née Hamilton ( 1904 -- 6 November 1993 ) , was a British pianist .
Huo Endi ( Chinese : 霍恩第 ) ( 1836 - -1917 ) was the father of famous Chinese martial artist Huo Yuanjia .
