George Schlieps - ( 1894 - 1977 ) , was an outstanding Russian violin maker/ Luthier ( of German origins ) , who came from a family of musicians .
Lieutenant James Warden ( 1736 - -1792 ) was a Royal Navy officer and Lord of the Manor of Charmouth .
William Isaac Palmer ( 1824 -- 1893 ) was a member of the Palmer family , proprietors of the Huntley & Palmers biscuit manufacturers of Reading in England .
Edith Anrep ( 1912- 2012 ) , was a Swedish lawyer and feminist .
Amos Pollard ( October 29 , 1803 -- March 6 , 1836 ) was the chief surgeon of the Alamo garrison who died during the battle on March 6 , 1836 .
Sibylla of Armenia ( c. 1240 -- 1290 ) was the daughter of Queen Isabella of Armenia and king Hethoum I of Armenia and was a member of the Hetoumid family .

Joseph Schröter ( 14 March 1837 -- 12 December 1894 ) was a noted German mycologist , doctor and scientist .
Paweł Maliński ( 1790 - 1853 ) was a Czech - born sculptor and mason who lived and worked in Poland .
Countess Magdalena of Waldeck ( 9 September 1558 -- August 1599 ) was a daughter of Philip IV of Waldeck - Wildungen ( 1493 - -1574 ) and his wife , Jutta of Isenburg ( d. 1564 ) .

James Burgh ( 1714 - -1775 ) was a British Whig politician whose book Political Disquisitions set out an early case for free speech and universal suffrage : in it , he writes , `` All lawful authority , legislative , and executive , originates from the people . ''
Paul Tournier ( 12 May 1898 -- 7 October 1986 ) was a Swiss physician and author who had acquired a worldwide audience for his work in pastoral counseling .

Garnham Edmonds ( 1866 -- 9 April 1946 ) was a British Liberal politician .
Kjell Roikjer ( 14 June 1901 -- 19 September 1999 ) was a Danish composer and bassoonist who for more than 30 years was a member of the Royal Danish Orchestra ( 1938 - -1971 ) .

Werner Haase ( 2 August 1900 -- 30 November 1950 ) was an SS - Obersturmbannführer ( lieutenant colonel ) , professor of medicine and one of Adolf Hitler 's personal physicians .

José Ximénez , José Jiménez or Jusepe Ximénez ( baptized 25 December 1601 ; died 9 August 1672 ) was a Spanish organist and the composer of 23 surviving works .

Count Pyotr Petrovich Palen ( Russian : Пётр Петрович Пален , Peter von der Pahlen ; 1778 - 1864 ) was a Russian noble and a general of the Imperial Russian Army .
Maude Storey , CBE , FRCN ( born 24 March 1930 -- died 29 March 2003 ) was a British nurse , nursing administrator and writer , as well as President of the Royal College of Nursing from 1988 to 1990 .
Robert Marmion , 3rd Baron Marmion of Tamworth ( died 1218 ) was an Anglo - Norman nobleman and itinerant justice .
Matthieu van Plattenberg , known in France as Matthieu de Plattemontagne , Matthieu de Platte Montagne and Matthieu Montaigne ( 1607 or 1608 -- 19 September 1660 ) was a Flemish Baroque painter , draughtsman , etcher and engraver who specialized in marine paintings and landscapes .
Harold Hay ( 31 December 1881 - 27 December 1955 ) was an Australian rules football player at the Melbourne Football Club in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .

John of Genoa or Johannes Balbus ( died c. 1298 ) was an Italian grammarian and Dominican priest .

Louis Hébert ( c. 1575 -- January 1627 ) is widely considered to be the first Canadian apothecary as well as the first European to farm in Canada .
George Leer ( 1748 at Hambledon , Hampshire -- 1 February 1812 at Petersfield , Hampshire ) was a famous English cricketer who played for Hampshire in the time of the Hambledon Club .
Liu Wencai ( Chinese : 刘文彩 ; 1887 - 17 October 1949 ) was a Chinese landlord from Sichuan province , and brother of the warlord Liu Wenhui .

Antonin Nechodoma ( 1877 - -1928 ) , was a Czech architect who practiced in Puerto Rico and Dominican Republic from 1905 to 1928 .
Sven Thaulow ( 24 October 1905 -- 17 September 1967 ) was a Norwegian sport swimmer .
Alexander Cunningham , 5th Earl of Glencairn ( died 1574 ) was a Scottish nobleman and Protestant reformer , prominent in the Scottish Reformation .
Anatoly Konstantinovich Rozhdestvensky ( Russian : Анатолий Константинович Рождественский , 1920 - -1983 ) was a Russian paleontologist responsible for naming many dinosaurs , including Aralosaurus and Probactrosaurus .
Juanita Miller ( 1912 - -2005 ) , patron of the arts in Dallas , Texas , played a formative role in saving the Dallas Symphony Orchestra from collapse in the 1970s and promoting the city 's cultural institutions .
Ann Mui ( 梅愛芳 ) ( 13 January 1959 -- 16 April 2000 ) was a singer and actress .

Martha Dewing Woodward ( 1856 - 1950 ) was a noted artist and art teacher .

John Bossewell ( died 1580 ) was an English heraldic writer .
George Fitzroy Seymour ( Witley 8 February 1923 - Thrumpton 12 May 1994 ) was High Sheriff of Nottinghamshire in 1966 and Deputy Lieutenant of Nottinghamshire .
John Alleyn ( died 25 March 1686 ) was a seventeenth - century London surgeon and the fifth Master of the College of God 's Gift in Dulwich ( then colloquially called Dulwich College , the name it took officially in 1882 ) .
Richard Cockle Lucas ( 24 October 1800 -- 18 May 1883 ) was an English sculptor and photographer .
Tony Cuesta ( 13 June 1926 -- 2 December 1992 ) was an anti - Castro Cuban activist .
Rabbi Dr. Aharon Chaim Zimmerman ( 1914 - -1995 ) was one of the leading rabbis of the Post - War generation .
Nadia Nerina ( 21 October 1927 -- 6 October 2008 ) was a South African dancer who was `` one of the most gifted , versatile , and inspiring ballerinas of The Royal Ballet '' during the 1950s and 1960s .
Adrian Shepherd , MBE ( 7 April 1939 -- 24 July 2013 ) was a British ' cellist and conductor , and director of the modern - instrument ensemble Cantilena .
Eulalia Ramos Sánchez ( known as Eulalia Buroz or Eulalia Chamberlain ; 1795 - 7 April 1817 ) was a heroine of the Venezuelan War of Independence .
Jurij Japelj , also known in German as Georg Japel , ( 11 April 1744 -- 11 October 1807 ) was a Slovene Jesuit priest , translator , and philologist .
Lakshman Rao Mohite ( 15 June 1932 -- 17 January 2016 ) , better known by his pen - name Geethapriya ( Kannada : ಗೀತಪ್ರಿಯ ) , was an Indian film director and lyricist of the Kannada film industry .
Peter Connolly FSA ( 8 May 1935 -- 2 May 2012 ) was a renowned British scholar of the ancient world , Greek and Roman military equipment historian , reconstructional archaeologist and illustrator .
Harrison Phoebus ( 1840 - -1886 ) was an American 19th century entrepreneur and hotelier who became the leading citizen and namesake of the town of Phoebus in Elizabeth City County , near Fort Monroe , which is now part of the independent city of Hampton , Virginia .
Edward Radclyffe , 6th Earl of Sussex ( c. 1559 -- August 1643 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1586 and 1611 and later succeeded to a peerage .
Hazel Marion Eaton ( July 4 , 1895 -- December 22 , 1970 ) was one of the first `` mile - a - minute girls '' to ride an Indian motorcycle in a carnival motordrome known as the Wall of Death .
Louis Réard ( 1897 -- 16 September 1984 ) was a French automobile engineer and clothes designer .
Charles Howard , 1st Earl of Carlisle ( 1629 -- 24 February 1685 ) was an English military leader and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1653 and 1660 and was created Earl of Carlisle in 1661 .
Adriaan Koonings ( 23 December 1895 -- 18 April 1963 ) , was a Dutch footballer who was active as a striker .
Santo Krishnan , also known as Krishnan Nair , ( 12 May 1920 -- 6 July 2013 ) was an Indian athlete and stuntsman .
Walter Carone ( 1920 -- 1982 ) was an Italian - French photographer .
Ian Douglas Ben Proctor , FRSA , known as Ian Proctor , ( 12 July 1918 -- 23 July 1992 ) was a prolific designer of both sailing dinghies and cruisers .
Lady Grizel Baillie ( née Hume ; 25 December 1665 -- 6 December 1746 ) was a Scottish songwriter .
Zheng Yuqing ( 鄭餘慶 ) ( 746 -- January 2 , 821 ) , courtesy name Juye ( 居業 ) , formally Duke Zhen of Yingyang ( 滎陽貞公 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reigns of Emperor Dezong and Emperor Dezong 's grandson Emperor Xianzong .
Raimund Falz ( 1658 - 1703 ) was a medallist active in Germany .
Miriam Yalan - Shteklis ( sometimes translated Miriam Yalan - Stekelis ) ( Hebrew : מרים ילן - שטקליס‎ ) ( 21 September 1900 -- 9 May 1984 ) was an Israeli writer and poet famous for her children 's books .
Louis Carrion ( Ludovicus Carrio ) ( 1547 -- 23 June 1595 ) was a Flemish humanist and classical scholar .
Sir Thomas Antonio Reginald Terrell ( 1889 -- 5 February 1979 ) was a British Conservative politician , MP for Henley ( UK Parliament constituency ) from 1918 until 1924 .
Johnny Collins ( 10 May 1938 -- 6 July 2009 ) was an English folk singer based in London , England , specializing in traditional maritime music .
Annamária Kinde ( 10 June 1956 -- 5 January 2014 ) was a Romanian journalist , poet and editor .
Martin Ruland the Younger ( 11 November 1569 -- 23 April 1611 ) , also known as Martinus Rulandus or Martin Rulandt , was a German physician and alchemist .
Philip Traherne , or Traheron ( /trəˈhɑːrn/ ; born in 9 August 1635 in Lugwardine ; died in 1686 in St. Nicholas , Hereford ) was an English diplomat , author of books .
Roger de Mowbray , 1st Baron Mowbray ( 1254 - -21 November 1297 ) , was an English peer and soldier .
Francis Goodricke ( 1621 -- 18 August 1673 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1659 and 1673 .
Casimir II of Łęczyca ( pl : Kazimierz II łęczycki ; ca . 1261/62 - 10 June 1294 ) , was a Polish prince member of the House of Piast , Duke of Brześć Kujawski during 1267 - -1288 , Duke of Dobrzyń during 1275 - -1288 and Duke of Łęczyca since 1288 until his death .
Peter Swanwick ( 1912 -- 14 November 1968 ) was a British actor best remembered as the `` Supervisor '' ( sometimes called the Controller ) in the 1967 TV series , The Prisoner .
Barnaby Barnewall ( died 1493 ) was an Irish barrister and judge , and a founder member of the Brotherhood of Saint George .
Johannes Honter ( also known as Johann Hynter ; Latinized as Johann Honterus or Ioannes Honterus ; Romanian sources may credit him as Ioan , Hungarian ones as János ; 1498 -- 23 January 1549 ) was a Transylvanian Saxon , renaissance humanist and theologian .
Stephan Bibrowski ( 1890 - -1932 ) , better known as Lionel the Lion - faced Man , was a famous sideshow performer .
Inderjit Singh Gill ( 1919 - -20 May 2001 ) was a Lieutenant General in the Indian army .
Benjamin Daydon Jackson ( 3 April 1846 -- 12 October 1927 ) was a pioneering botanist and taxonomer who wrote the first volume of Index Kewensis to include all the flowering plants .
Thomas P. Revelle ( 1868 - -1941 ) was a Seattle lawyer and politician who was a proponent for the founding of the city 's Pike Place Market .
T. W. Thompson ( 1888 - -1968 ) was an English collector of folklore , specialising in the ' Gypsy ' people of the Lake District .
Konstantin Saradzhev ( also Constantin Saradgeff , born Saradzhian ; 8 October 1877 -- 22 July 1954 ) was an Armenian conductor and violinist .
Alexandru - Radu Timofte ( Romanian pronunciation : ( ˈradu tiˈmofte ) ; 7 April 1949 -- 19 October 2009 ) was a Romanian soldier , politician and spy chief .
Alice Chetwynd Ley , née Humphrey ( born 12 October 1913 in Halifax , Yorkshire , England , UK - d. 2004 ) was a British writer of romance novels from 1959 to 1989 .
Carsten Klouman ( 21 August 1923 -- 2 July 2004 ) was born in Oslo and was a Norwegian pianist , arranger and composer .
Dame Elsie Marjorie Williamson , DBE ( 30 July 1913 , Wakefield , Yorkshire , England -- 12 August 2002 Lower Raydon , Suffolk ) was a British academic , educator , physicist and university administrator .
William Nevill , 4th Earl of Abergavenny ( 28 June 1792 -- 17 August 1868 ) was a British peer .
John Albert Bullbrook ( 1882 - -1967 ; born in the Medway area in what was then Kent in South - East England ) was an author , archaeologist and archaeological historian , who went to Trinidad in 1913 as a petroleum geologist .
William Henry Butler ( 24 February 1790 -- 11 October 1865 ) was an English wine merchant and Mayor of Oxford .
Pertinax ( Latin : Publius Helvius Pertinax Augustus ; 1 August 126 -- 28 March 193 ) was Roman Emperor for the first three months of 193 .
Karel Šmirous ( 1890 in Český Krumlov -- 1981 in Prague ) was Czech scientist and the only Czech photographer who specialized in color photography using the autochrome process .
Cuthbert Baillie ( died in 1514 ) , was the lord high treasurer of Scotland .
Evelyn Shirley Shuckburgh ( 1843 - -1906 ) was an English academic and schoolmaster , known as classical scholar and translator .
Primo Casale ( 1904 - -1981 ) was an Italian - born Venezuelan conductor , composer , and violinist .
Jordan of Laron ( or Jordain , from either the Latin form Jordanus or Jordanes ) was the Bishop of Limoges from 1023 until his death in 1051 .
Hans Burgkmair the Elder ( 1473 - -1531 ) was a German painter and woodcut printmaker .
Queen Seondeok of Silla ( Korean pronunciation : ( sʰʌndʌk jawʌŋ ) ; ? - 17 February 647 ) reigned as Queen Regnant of Silla , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea , from 632 to 647 .
Chen Mengjia ( or Ch'en Meng - chia ; 20 April 1911 , Nanjing -- 3 September 1966 , Beijing ) was a Chinese scholar , poet and archaeologist .
René le Brun , Comte de L'Hôpital ( 5 May 1877 -- 1929 ) was an English artist .
Heinrich Röntgen ( 1787 - -1813 ) , was one of four students recommended as explorers to Joseph Banks ' African Association by Johann Friedrich Blumenbach , the others being Friedrich Hornemann , Ulrich Seetzen , and Johann Ludwig Burckhardt .
Ferenc Hatlaczky ( sometimes shown as Ferenc Hatlaczki , 17 January 1934 - 8 September 1986 ) was a Hungarian sprint canoer who competed in the mid to late 1950s .
Pavel Kunaver ( 19 December 1889 -- 19 April 1988 ) was a Slovene pedagogue , writer of popular science books , geography , history and Slovene language teacher and pioneer of amateur astronomy in Slovenia .
Thomas Boston Gordon ( February 4 , 1816 - -January 25 , 1891 ) was born in Hartwell , Georgia and made a career as a lawyer and county judge for Bath County , Kentucky .
Ismaël Touré ( 1925/1926 - 8 July 1985 ) was a Guinean political figure and the half brother of former President Ahmed Sékou Touré .
Šime Ljubić ( 24 May 1822 -- 19 October 1896 ) was an Austrian Croat theologian , archeologist and historian .
Hamilcar I of Carthage was a Magonid king of Carthage , in present day Tunisia , from 510 to 480 BCE .
Ronald Eyre ( 13 April 1929 -- 8 April 1992 ) was an English theatre director , actor and writer .
Thomas Taylour , 1st Marquess of Headfort KP ( 18 November 1757 -- 24 October 1829 ) , styled Viscount Headford from 1766 to 1795 , and known as The Earl of Bective from 1795 to 1800 , was an Irish peer and politician .
Sir William Douglas , 1st Baronet ( died 1809 ) was a Scottish landowner and industrialist , best known for founding the planned town of Castle Douglas in the Stewartry of Kirkcudbright ( now within Dumfries and Galloway ) , south - west Scotland .
Henry Chippendale ( 2 October 1870 -- 29 September 1952 ) was an English international footballer , who played as an outside right .
William Blunt ( 1800 - -1889 ) was a British civil servant in India .
Clarence Norman Wharton ( July 28 , 1903 in Askam - in - Furness , Lancashire , England -- July 1961 ) was an English footballer .
Henry Balfour FRS ( 11 April 1863 Croydon -- 9 February 1939 ) was a British archaeologist , and the first curator of the Pitt Rivers Museum .
Zhan Shichai ( Chinese : 詹世釵 ) ( 1841 - 5 November 1893 ) was a Chinese giant who toured the world as `` Chang the Chinese Giant '' in the 19th century , the stage name is `` Chang Woo Gow '' .
Henry Parke ( 1790 - -1835 ) was an English architect and draughtsman .
Leon Chechemian ( Mar Leon ) ( 1848 - -1920 ) was an Armenian Christian cleric .
Tryphena Sparks ( 20 March 1851 - 17 March 1890 ) , born in Puddletown , Dorset , the youngest child of James and Maria Sparks , was Thomas Hardy 's cousin and possible lover , when she was 16 and he was 26 .
Mechthild of Germany ( b. 1418 -- d. 1482 ) was a princess and major patroness of the literary arts in the 15th century .
V. Ramarathnam ( 1917 - -2008 ) was a Carnatic musician , author , teacher and composer known under the mudra Rama .
Johann Bernhard Bach ( 23 May 1676 -- 11 June 1749 ) was a German composer , and second cousin of J. S. Bach .
Hồ Đắc Điềm ( 1899 - -1985 ) was the governor of Ha Dong , the area surrounding Hanoi .
Henry Greenly ( 1876 - -1947 ) was amongst the foremost miniature railway engineers of the 20th century , remembered as a master of engineering design .
Jürgen Henkys ( 6 November 1929 -- 22 October 2015 ) was a German Protestant minister and theologian .
Thomas Bermingham , 1st Earl of Louth ( 16 November 1717 -- 11 January 1799 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician and peer .
Colonel Henry Steel Olcott ( Sinhalese : කර්නල් ශ්‍රිමත් හෙන්රි ස්ටීල් ඔල්කට් ) ( 2 August 1832 -- 17 February 1907 ) was an American military officer , journalist , lawyer and the co - founder and first President of the Theosophical Society .
Moll Dyer ( died c. 1697 ? ) is the name of a legendary 17th - century resident of Leonardtown , Maryland , who was said to have been accused of witchcraft and chased out of her home by the local townsfolk on a winter night .
Francisco Lopes Suasso , second Baron d'Avernas le Gras ( ca . 1657 -- 22 April 1710 ) was a banker and financier of the Dutch Republic .
Gerhard Schrader ( 25 February 1903 -- 10 April 1990 ) was a German chemist specializing in the discovery of new insecticides , hoping to make progress in the fight against hunger in the world .
Curtis L. Lawson ( 1935 - -2008 ) was an American state politician from Tulsa , Oklahoma .
Catherine Reilly ( 4 April 1925 -- 26 September 2005 ) was a British bibliographer and anthologist of women 's poetry of the First and Second World Wars .
Major General Abdul Munim Wassel ( died 17 May 2002 ) was the commander of the Egyptian third army during the Yom Kippur War .
Ebal I of Challant ( French : Ébal Ier de Challant or Ébal le Grand , Italian : Ebalo I di Challant or Ebalo Magno ; died 1323 ) was a nobleman of the Challant family of Aosta Valley .
Duchess Louise Frederica of Württemberg ( 3 February 1722 -- 2 August 1791 ) was a Duchess consort of Mecklenburg - Schwerin .
According to legend , Amir Kror Suri died in 154 H./771 A.D. in the Battle of Poshanj ( which is a village in ancient city of Herat ) and was succeeded by his son , Amir Naser , who took control of the territories of Ghor , Sur , Bost and Zamindawar .
Henryk Woliński ( 1901 - -1986 ) was a member of the Polish resistance movement in World War II , specifically the Armia Krajowa ( AK ) , where he reached the rank of colonel .
Alfred Aaron de Pass ( 1861 - -1952 ) was a South African - born businessman , art - collector and philanthropist .
Louis Boehmer ( 30 May 1843 - 29 July 1896 ) was an ethnic German - American agronomist and government advisor in Meiji period Japan who later worked as a success entrepreneur in Yokohama .
Elisabeth Ludovika of Bavaria ( 13 November 1801 -- 14 December 1873 ) was a Princess of Bavaria and later Queen consort of Prussia .
Knut Moe ( 1921 -- 1989 ) was a Norwegian resistance member , a radio agent for the Special Intelligence Service , during World War II .
After Muhammad Ahmad 's unexpected death on 22 June 1885 , a mere six months after the conquest of Khartoum , his chief deputy , Abdallahi ibn Muhammad took over the administration of the nascent Mahdist state .
Ichabod Washburn ( 1798 - -1868 ) was a church deacon and industrialist from Worcester County , Massachusetts , United States .
Clair Omar Musser ( 1901 - -1998 ) was a marimba virtuoso , a conductor and promoter of marimba orchestras , a composer , a teacher , a designer of keyboard percussion instruments , an inventor , and an engineer for Hughes Aircraft .
Alfred Essex ( died 1871 in South Africa ) , was an English enamel - painter , who worked with his brother William Essex to popularise enamel painting in the nineteenth century .
Helen Tracy Lowe - Porter ( born Helen Tracy Porter , June 15 , 1876 / 1877 , Towanda , Pennsylvania , USA ; died April 26 , 1963 , Princeton , New Jersey , USA ) was an American translator , most well known for her pioneering translations of the works of Thomas Mann .
Robert Gouger ( /ˈɡʊdʒər/ ; 26 June 1802 -- 4 August 1846 ) was one of the founders of South Australia and first Colonial Secretary of South Australia .
Richard Kippist ( 1812 - -1882 ) was an English botanist and librarian .
General Henry Lumley ( c. 1658 -- 18 October 1722 ) was a British soldier and Governor of Jersey .
Ben - Zion Harel ( Hebrew : בן - ציון הראל‎ ; Ben - Zion Hirshowitz on 3 June 1892 -- 19 September 1972 ) was an Israeli doctor and politician , who served as a member of the Knesset for the General Zionists between 1951 and 1959 .
Charles Neaves , Lord Neaves FRSE ( 1800 - -1876 ) was a Scottish advocate , judge , theologian and writer .
Johan Jørgen Schwartz ( 1824 , Drammen -- 1898 ) was a Norwegian politician and businessperson .
Richard Churcher ( 1659 - -1723 ) was a wealthy English businessman and philanthropist , who made his fortune through interests in the British East India Company .
Ralph Coates ( 26 April 1946 -- 17 December 2010 ) was an English footballer who played at both professional and international levels as a winger .
Sir Thomas Metham ( died 1573 in York Castle ) was an English Roman Catholic knight , imprisoned with his second wife for their beliefs .
Rosalía Mera Goyenechea ( 28 January 1944 -- 15 August 2013 ) was a Spanish businesswoman and entrepreneur .
Everett S. Sherman ( 1831 - 1897 ) was a covered bridge builder in Ohio .
Archie Lewis ( 10 April 1918 - - 29 February 1988 ) was a Jamaican singer who was popular in Britain in the 1940s .
Alfred Darling ( 1862 - -1931 ) was an engineer and a key member of the loose association of early British film pioneers dubbed the Brighton School by French film historian Georges Sadoul .
Adelaide of Italy ( 931 -- 16 December 999 ) , also called Adelaide of Burgundy , was the second wife of Holy Roman Emperor Otto the Great and was crowned as the Holy Roman Empress with him by Pope John XII in Rome on February 2 , 962 .
William Davis Merry Howard ( 1818 - -1856 ) was a native of Boston , Massachusetts who came to California in 1839 as a cabin boy on a sailing ship .
Osman Nuri Pasha ( Ottoman Turkish : عثمان نوری پاشا‎‎ ; 1832 -- 5 April 1900 ) , also known as Gazi Osman Pasha , was an Ottoman field marshal and the hero of the Siege of Plevna in 1877 .
Second Lieutenant Henry Ralph Lumley ( March 1892 - 11 March 1918 ) was a First World War pilot and burn victim whose case was important to the future development of facial reconstruction and plastic surgery .
Stefan Bergman ( 5 May 1895 -- 6 June 1977 ) was a Polish - born American mathematician whose primary work was in complex analysis .
Edward J. Bermingham ( 1887 - -1958 ) was a prominent investment banker and correspondent of Dwight D. Eisenhower .
Mario Casariego y Acevedo , CRS ( 13 February 1909 -- 15 June 1983 ) was a Spanish - born Guatemalan Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church .
Mu'in al - Madi ( Arabic : معين الماضي‎ ) ( died 1957 ) was a Palestinian Arab politician and member of the Arab Higher Committee .
Ronald True , registered at birth as Angus Ronald True , ( Manchester , Lancashire , England , 1891 -- Broadmoor , 1951 ) was an English murderer .
Edwin Grasse ( 13 August 1884 -- 8 April 1954 ) was an American violinist , organist and composer .
Sven - Olov Eriksson ( 22 April 1929 -- 31 October 1999 ) was a Swedish runner who specialized in the 400 m hurdles event .
Olga Kosakiewicz ( Ukrainian : Ольга Козакевич ; 6 November 1915 -- 1983 ) was a student of Simone de Beauvoir who joined the circle of de Beauvoir and Jean - Paul Sartre in 1935 , aged 19 .
Malik Anwar Ali Noon ( died 12 September 2014 ) , son of Malik Sultan Ali Noon , was a politician and landlord of Sargodha .
Ross Bellah ( 27 January 1907 -- 2 February 2004 ) was an American art director , primarily for Columbia Pictures .
Talha ibn Tahir ( طلحة بن طاهر ) ( died 828 ) was the Tahirid governor of Khurasan from 822 until his death .
Gardiner Greene ( 1753 - -1832 ) was a cotton planter and merchant from Boston , Massachusetts who conducted business from his plantation , Greenfield , in Demerara ( Guyana ) in the late 18th and early 19th centuries .
Naziq al - Abid ( Arabic : نازك العابد ) ( 1898 - -1959 ) was known as the `` Joan of Arc of the Arabs '' .
Samuel Magowan ( February 5 , 1910 - 1976 ) was an Ulster Unionist member of the Parliament of Northern Ireland .
Sir William de Shareshull KB ( 1289/1290 - -1370 ) was an English lawyer , and Chief Justice of the King 's Bench from 26 October 1350 to 5 July 1361 .
Zuo Liangyu ( Chinese : 左良玉 ) ( 1599 - 1645 ) was a Ming dynasty general .
Jan Chełmiński nom de plume Jan van Chelminski ( 1851 - -1925 ) , born Jan Vładysław Chełmiński , was a Polish painter , who was born in Brzustów ( 27 January 1851 ) and entered the Munich Academy of Fine Arts on 14 April 1875 ( Register : 3144 ) .
Przemysław of Oświęcim ( Polish : Przemysław Oświęcimski ) ( c. 1362 -- 1 January 1406 ) was a Duke of half of both Głogów and Ścinawa since 1404 and Duke of Oświęcim from 1405 until his death .
Edmund de Grimsby ( died 1354 ) was an English cleric , Crown official and judge .
Dorcas Cochran ( ca . 1903 -- July 6 , 1991 ) was an American lyricist and screenwriter .
James Shomate ( Bakersfield , CA , November 13 , 1914 - -Manhattan , October 13 , 2001 ) was an American pianist and voice teacher .
Herbert Cecil Benyon Berens ( 16 October 1908 , in Bromley , formerly Kent -- 27 October 1981 , in Bentworth , Hampshire ) was a British accountant and aristocrat , military figure during World War II , and cricketer .
Jean Jeantot ( or Jantot ) ( c. 1666 -- 12 August 1748 ) was a Canadian Catholic brother and schoolmaster .
Wilhelm Theodor Gümbel ( 19 May 1812 , Dannenfels -- 10 February 1858 , Landau in der Pfalz ) was a German bryologist .
Alexandru Ciurcu ( 29 January 1854 , Şercaia --22 January 1922 , Bucharest ) was a Romanian inventor and publisher , famous for his invention with Just Buisson of a reaction engine .
Lenin Gani ( Bengali : লেনিন গনি ) ( December , 1967-December 2013 ) was a highly respected Bangladeshi sports journalist .
Lucius Junius Moderatus Columella ( /ˌkɒljəˈmɛlə/ ; 4 -- c. 70 AD ) is the most important writer on agriculture of the Roman empire .
Frans Kuyper ( Latin : Cuperus ) ( 1629 , Amsterdam -- 21 October 1691 , Rotterdam ) was a Dutch Socinian writer and printer .
James Bane ( or Ben ) ( died 1332 ) was Bishop of St. Andrews for a brief period in the early 14th century .
Friedrich Anders ( 4 November 1917 - 7 March 1988 ) was a German Oberleutnant in the Wehrmacht during World War II . Friedrich Anders was born on the 04.11.1917 in Eisenach and received the Knight 's Cross on the 14 August 1943 as Sergeant and platoon commander in the 3rd company of the Panzer reconnaissance battalion 2 .
Arthur Jones , 2nd Viscount Ranelagh ( died 1669 ) was an Irish politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1643 .
Rosalind Ivan ( 27 November 1880 -- 6 April 1959 ) was an English stage and film character actress .
Flora Spencer - Longhurst ( born 1985 or 1986 ) is an English stage and television actress .
Isaac Friedlander ( 1823 - -1878 ) was a wheat broker and major early California land speculator , who was known as the Wheat King or the Grain King .
Sheikh Jabr Muadi ( Arabic : جبر داهش معدي‎ ; Hebrew : ג'בר מועדי‎ , born 1 April 1919 , died 19 May 2009 ) was a Israeli Druze politician who served as a member of the Knesset for seven different parties between 1951 and 1981 .
Catherine Anne Warfield ( née Ware ) ( 1816 - -1877 ) was an American writer of poetry and fiction in Mississippi .
Alimamy Rassin ( 1825 - 1890 ) was a Fula chief from Sierra Leone who devoted his life to making peace among his people and fellow rulers .
Sooliman Ernest `` Rogie '' or S. E. Rogie ( 1926 - 1994 ) was a highlife and palm wine guitarist and singer from Sierra Leone .
Anh Thơ ( Ninh Giang , Hải Dương Province , 25 January 1921 -- 14 March 2005 ) , real name Vương Kiều Ân , was a Vietnamese woman poet .
Patrick Allan Fraser ( 1812 -- 1890 ) , was a Scottish painter and architect .
St. Cianán ( died 24 November 489 ) was a Bishop of Duleek in Ireland .
George Crichton Wells FRCP ( 13 July 1914 -- 16 January 1999 ) was a dermatologist at St Thomas 's Hospital and St. John 's Hospital for Diseases of the Skin ( now closed ) .
Peter Casserly ( 28 January 1898 -- 24 June 2005 ) was , at age 107 , the last surviving member of the 1st AIF serving in France in the First World War .
Nils Wichstrøm ( 1848 -- 1879 ) was a Norwegian actor and stage instructor .
Alfred Prinz ( 4 June 1930 -- 20 September 2014 ) was an Austrian composer , clarinetist , and music educator .
Reginald Stephen ( 1860 - -1956 ) was the Anglican Bishop of Tasmania from 1914 until 1919 and then the Bishop of Newcastle ( New South Wales ) from 1919 until his retirement in 1928 .
Charles Collin - Mezin , Jr. ( 1870 - -1934 ) was a French violin maker , and an Officier de l'Académie des Beaux - Arts .
Silas Laurence Loomis ( 1822 - -1896 ) was an American scientist , educator , and inventor .
William Oram ( died 1777 ) was an English painter and architect .
Damdinsürengiin Altangerel ( Mongolian : Дамдинсүрэнгийн Алтангэрэл ; 1945 - -1998 ) was a Mongolian teacher and writer .
Wilhelm von Gegerfelt , also Vilhelm von Gegerfelt , ( 1844 - -1920 ) was a Swedish painter .
Du Mu ( Chinese : 杜牧 ; pinyin : Dù Mù ; Wade -- Giles : Tu4 Mu4 ; 803 - -852 ) was a leading Chinese poet of the late Tang dynasty .
Bobby Marlow ( c. 1930 -- 1985 ) was a former American and Canadian football running back who played for the University of Alabama and the Canadian Football League 's ( CFL ) Saskatchewan Roughriders .
Roberto Malatesta ( c. 1441 - 1442 -- 10 September 1482 ) was an Italian condottiero , or mercenary captain , lord of Rimini , and a member of the House of Malatesta .
Too Romantic is a 1992 dramatic short film that Todd Field created while a fellow at the AFI Conservatory .
Nari Munidare Mari ( Kannada : ನಾರಿ ಮುನಿದರೆ ಮಾರಿ ) is a 1972 Indian Kannada film , directed by Geethapriya and produced by M. P. Shankar .
McFarland , USA ( also known as McFarland ) is a 2015 American sports drama film directed by Niki Caro , produced by Mark Ciardi and Gordon Gray , written by Christopher Cleveland , Bettina Gilois and Grant Thompson with music by Antônio Pinto and co - produced by Walt Disney Pictures and Mayhem Pictures .
The Flight of Dragons is a 1982 animated film produced by Jules Bass and Arthur Rankin , Jr. and loosely combining the speculative natural history book of the same name ( 1979 ) by Peter Dickinson with the novel The Dragon and the George ( 1976 ) by Gordon R. Dickson .
Robotropolis is a science - fiction action adventure film written and directed by Christopher Hatton starring Zoe Naylor , Graham Sibley and Edward Foy .
Kurigalu Saar Kurigalu ( Kannada : ಕುರಿಗಳು ಸಾರ್ ಕುರಿಗಳು ) is a 2001 Indian Kannada comedy film directed and written by Rajendra Singh Babu .
Kanasina Rani ( Kannada : ಕನಸಿನ ರಾಣಿ ) is a 1992 Indian Kannada language film directed by M. S. Rajashekar and produced by M. Sunanda and M. Krishna under the banner Sri Lakshmi Productions .
The Clown Murders is a 1976 horror film directed by Martyn Burke .
Cupid in a Dental Parlor ( also known as Love in the Dental Parlor ) is a 1913 short comedy film directed by Henry Lehrman .
Akcja pod Arsenałem ( Operation Arsenal ) is a Polish historical film , based on the novel Kamienie na szaniec by Aleksander Kamiński , released in 1978 and directed by Jan Łomnicki .
Mi novia es un fantasma is a 1944 Argentine romantic comedy film directed by Francisco Múgica and starring Mirtha Legrand , Pepe Iglesias , and Nuri Montsé .
Hell in Normandy ( Italian title : Testa di sbarco per otto implacabili , French title : Tête de pont pour huit implacables ) is a 1968 French / Italian international co - production World War II film directed by Alfonso Brescia .
Anuranan ( English : Resonance ) is the directorial debut by Bengali filmmaker Aniruddha Roy Chowdhury .
Soft Top Hard Shoulder is a 1993 British comedy drama film directed by Stefan Schwartz , produced by Richard Holmes , written by and starring Peter Capaldi , Frances Barber , Jeremy Northam and Richard Wilson .
Thiruvarutchelvar ( Tamil : திருவருட்செல்வர் ) is a 1967 Indian Tamil film , directed and produced by A. P. Nagarajan .
The Revolutionary is a 1970 political drama film directed by Paul Williams .
The Belko Experiment is an upcoming American horror thriller film directed by Greg McLean and written by James Gunn .
Hamal 18 ( also known as Hamal_18 ) is a 2004 American film starring Michael J. Minor , Yvette Ford , Wendy Cobb , Chad England , Joel Spence , Elina Madison and directed by John G. Thomas .
Morning Patrol ( Greek : Πρωινή Περίπολος , tr . Proini Peripolos ) is a 1987 Greek dramatic experimental independent surrealist underground art film directed by Nikos Nikolaidis .
Chameleon Street is a 1989 independent film written by , directed by and starring Wendell B. Harris , Jr ..
The Chess Player ( French : Le Joueur d'échecs ) is a 1927 French silent film directed by Raymond Bernard and based on a novel by Henry Dupuy - Mazuel .
Siberian Lady Macbeth ( Orig . Sibirska Ledi Magbet ) , also translated as Fury Is a Woman , is a 1962 film directed by Andrzej Wajda , based on the novella Lady Macbeth of the Mtsensk District by Nikolai Leskov .
Joe Glow , the Firefly is a 1941 cartoon directed by Chuck Jones .
Foxhole in Cairo is a 1960 British war film directed by John Llewellyn Moxey and based on a novel by Leonard Mosley itself based upon the real - life Operation Salaam .
My Flesh and Blood is a 2003 documentary film by Jonathan Karsh chronicling a year in the life of the Tom family .
Haggada Kone ( Kannada : ಹಗ್ಗದ ಕೊನೆ , English : End of the Rope ) is a 2014 Indian Kannada language crime - drama film directed by Dayal Padmanabhan and stars Naveen Krishna in the lead role .
Good Cheer is a 1926 American short silent comedy film directed by Robert F. McGowan .

Wincenty Pol ( 20 April 1807 -- 2 December 1872 ) was a Polish poet and geographer .
Jeassy , also known as J. C. or Jesey , was an Indian director and actor of Malayalam movies .

Carl Schmitt ( German : ( ʃmɪt ) ; 11 July 1888 -- 7 April 1985 ) was a German jurist and political theorist .
Sedad Hakkı Eldem ( 1908 in İstanbul -- 7 September 1988 , in İstanbul ) , was a Turkish Architect .
Fray Prudencio de Sandoval ( 1553 - -1620 ) was a Spanish historian and Benedictine monk , the Bishop of Tuy from 1608 to 1612 and Bishop of Pamplona thereafter until his death .
Joseph Ehrenfried Hofmann ( * 7 March 1900 in Munich , † 7 May 1973 in Günzburg ) was a German historian of mathematics , known for his research on Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz .

Alfred Braun ( 13 May 1888 -- 3 January 1978 ) was a German screenwriter , actor and film director .
Kārlis Baumanis ( 11 May 1835 -- 10 January 1905 ) , better known as Baumaņu Kārlis , was an ethnic Latvian composer in the Russian Empire .
Gjergj Fishta ( October 23 , 1871 -- December 30 , 1940 ) was an Albanian Franciscan , poet , rilindas , and a translator .
Nicholas Howe ( 1953 - 2006 ) was an American scholar of Old English literature and culture , whose Migration and Mythmaking in Anglo - Saxon England ( 1989 ) was an important contribution to the study of Old English literature and historiography .
Isaac Jacob Schoenberg ( April 21 , 1903 -- February 21 , 1990 ) was a Romanian - American mathematician , known for his discovery of splines .
Jorge Peixinho ( born 20 January 1940 in Montijo , Portugal ; died 30 June 1995 in Lisbon , Portugal ) was a Portuguese composer , pianist and conductor .
Prem Kumar is an Indian film actor , most popular for his Malayalam films during the 1990s .
John Glynn SL of Glynn ( 1722 - -1779 ) was an English lawyer and Member of Parliament .
Karan Trivedi ( करण त्रिवेदी Karaṇa trivēdī ) ( born January 17 , 1984 ) is an Indian television and theatre artist who speaks Hindi and Gujarati .
Jean Baptiste de Caux of Blacquetot ( 24 May 1723 , Montreuil , Pas - de - Calais - 8 September 1796 ) was a French general .
Rocco Rodio ( c. 1535 -- after 1615 ) was an Italian Renaissance composer and theorist , best known for his sacred works and keyboard ricercares .
León Artola was a Spanish screenwriter and film director .
Erich von dem Bach - Zelewski ( 1 March 1899 -- 8 March 1972 ) was a German SS - Obergruppenführer ( General ) mainly active in Central Russia , directing anti - partisan warfare , and in Poland , leading the suppression of the Warsaw uprising .
Nicolas - Louis d'Assas ( 1733 - -1760 ) , also known as Louis d'Assas du Mercou and Chevalier d'Assas , was a captain of the French Régiment d'Auvergne , whose celebrity depends on a single act of defiance .
Chen Duxiu ( Chinese : 陳獨秀 ; October 8 , 1879 -- May 27 , 1942 ) was a Chinese revolutionary socialist , educator , philosopher , and author , who co - founded the Chinese Communist Party ( with Li Dazhao ) in 1921 , serving from 1921 to 1927 as its first General Secretary .
Luis Tribaldos de Toledo ( 1558 - -1636 ) was a Spanish humanist , geographer and historian .
Ilse Stöbe ( 17 May 1911 Berlin - 22 December 1942 Berlin ) was a German journalist and anti - Nazi resistance fighter .
Oscar Browning ( 17 January 1837 in London -- 6 October 1923 in Rome ) was an English writer , historian , and educational reformer .

Heinrich Friedrich Wilhelm Gesenius ( 3 February 1786 -- 23 October 1842 ) was a German orientalist , Lutheran , and Biblical critic .
Dino Pedriali ( born 1950 ) is an Italian photographer who lives and works in Rome .
Johann Ludwig Tieck ( 31 May 1773 -- 28 April 1853 ) was a German poet , translator , editor , novelist , writer of Novellen , and critic , who was one of the founding fathers of the Romantic movement of the late 18th and early 19th centuries .
Thorbjørn Egner ( 12 December 1912 -- 24 December 1990 ) was a Norwegian playwright , songwriter and illustrator known for his books , plays and musicals for children .

Karine Saporta ( b. Grenoble , Isère , 1950 ) is a French choreographer , dancer , photographer , and short film director .
John Manners , 3rd Duke of Rutland KG PC ( 21 October 1696 -- 29 May 1779 ) was an English nobleman , the eldest son of John Manners , 2nd Duke of Rutland and Catherine Russell .
Timo Brunke ( born March 11 , 1972 ) is a German slam poet .
Jeanne Mance ( November 12 , 1606 -- June 18 , 1673 ) was a French nurse and settler of New France .
Édouard Delessert ( 15 December 1828 - -27 March 1898 ) was a French painter , archaeologist and photographer .
Clive Wake is a critic , editor and translator of modern African and French literature .
Charles Robert Ashbee ( 17 May 1863 -- 23 May 1942 ) was an English designer and entrepreneur who was a prime mover of the Arts and Crafts movement that took its craft ethic from the works of John Ruskin and its co - operative structure from the socialism of William Morris .
Jon García Aguado ( born September 28 , 1977 in Durango , Vizcaya , Spain ) is a Spanish taekwondo athlete .
P. A. Thomas is an Indian film director , producer , script writer , theater artist and actor in Malayalam movies .
René Guyon ( 27 May 1876 - 1963 ) was a French jurist , best known for having written upon the topic of sexual ethics .
Antonio Ambrosetti ( born November 11 , 1944 ) is an Italian mathematician who is active in the fields of partial differential equations and calculus of variations .
Christoph Gottfried Bardili ( 18 May 1761 -- 5 June 1808 ) was a German philosopher and cousin of Friedrich Wilhelm Joseph Schelling .
Karl Selim Lemström ( 17 November 1838 in Ingå -- 2 October 1904 in Helsinki ) , was a Finnish geophysicist .
Francisco de Villagra Velázquez ( 1511 -- 22 July 1563 ) was a Spanish conquistador , and three times governor of Chile .
Luise Rinser ( 1911 - 2002 ) was a prolific German writer , best known for her novels and short stories .
José Ros García ( 1920 - 2001 ) was a Spanish - born poet who lived and worked for the latter part of his life in Australia .
Julius Wellhausen ( May 17 , 1844 -- January 7 , 1918 ) , was a German biblical scholar and orientalist .
Thierry Lodé ( born 1956 , Tarbes ) is a French biologist and professor of evolutionary ecology in a CNRS lab at the University of Rennes 1 .
Armindo Freitas - Magalhães , Ph.D. ( born 1966 ) , is a Portuguese psychologist working on the psychology of the human smile in the context of emotion and facial expression .
Garci Rodríguez de Montalvo ( Spanish pronunciation : ( ˈɡarθi roˈðɾiɣeθ ðe monˈtalβo ) ) ( not Garci Ordóñez de Montalvo ) ( ~1450 -- 1504 ) was a Castilian author who arranged the modern version of the chivalric romance Amadis of Gaul , written in three books in the 14th century by an unknown author .
Ángeles González - Sinde Reig ( born 7 April 1965 ) is a Spanish scriptwriter , film director and politician .

Harri Czepuck ( b. Breslau 30 July 1927 -- d.14 June 2015 ) was a German journalist .
Friedrich Hermann Loew ( 19 July 1807 -- 21 April 1879 ) was a German entomologist who specialised in the study of Diptera , an order of insects including flies , mosquitoes , gnats and midges .
Marcel Labey ( 6 August 1875 , Vésinet -- 25 November 1968 , Nancy ) was a French conductor and composer .
Jesús Blasco ( 3 November 1919 -- 21 October 1995 ) was a Spanish author and artist of comic books , whose career covered most of the conventional history of comic strips .

Rembrandt Bugatti ( 16 October 1884 -- 8 January 1916 ) was an Italian sculptor , known primarily for his bronze sculptures of wildlife subjects .

Maximilien Luce ( 13 March 1858 -- 6 February 1941 ) was a prolific French Neo - impressionist artist , known for his paintings , illustrations , engravings , and graphic art , and also for his anarchist activism .
Carlo Cafiero ( September 1 , 1846 -- July 17 , 1892 ) was an Italian anarchist , champion of Mikhail Bakunin during the second half of the 19th century and one of the main proponents of anarcho - communism during the First International .
Daisy Ashford , full name Margaret Mary Julia Ashford , later Devlin ( 7 April 1881 -- 15 January 1972 ) was an English writer who is most famous for writing The Young Visiters , a novella concerning the upper class society of late 19th century England , when she was just nine years old .
Juan de Mariana , also known as Father Mariana ( 1536 -- 17 February 1624 ) , was a Spanish Jesuit priest , Scholastic , historian , and member of the Monarchomachs .

Otto Grotewohl ( German pronunciation : ( ˈɔtoː ˈɡʁoːtəvoːl ) ; 11 March 1894 -- 23 September 1964 ) was a German politician and the first prime minister of the German Democratic Republic from 1949 until his death in 1964 .

Jean - Pierre Houdin ( French : ( udɛ̃ ) ; born 1951 in Paris ) , is a French architect perhaps most notable for a theory on pyramid construction .

Wilhelm Kreis ( 17 March 1873 -- 13 August 1955 ) was a prominent German architect and professor of architecture , active through four political systems in German history : the Wilhelmine era , the Weimar Republic , the Third Reich , and the foundation of the Federal Republic .
Wilfrid Philip Ward ( 1856 - 1916 ) was an English essayist and biographer .

Arusianus Messius , or Messus , Latin grammarian , flourished in the 4th century .

William Watson , Baron Watson PC , LL.D ( 25 August 1827 -- 14 September 1899 ) was a Scottish lawyer and Conservative Party politician .

Rubik 's Cube is a 3-D combination puzzle invented in 1974 by Hungarian sculptor and professor of architecture Ernő Rubik .
The Gore Effect is an informal and satirical term which alleges a causal relationship between unseasonable cold weather phenomena and global warming activism , with particular emphasis on events attended by former Vice President of the United States and Nobel Peace Prize recipient Al Gore .

Nabalamprophyllite has a general formula of Ba(Na , Ba)(Na3Ti(Ti2O2Si4O14)(OH , F)2 ) The name is given for its composition ( Naba , meaning sodium , Na and barium , Ba ) and relation to other lamprophyllite - group minerals .
Parle Tilak Vidyalaya English Medium School ( ' P. T. V. E. M. S. ' ) is an English medium school located in Vile Parle East in Mumbai , India .
Whit Monday or Pentecost Monday ( also known as Monday of the Holy Spirit ) is the holiday celebrated the day after Pentecost , a movable feast in the Christian calendar .
Hilbert 's twenty - fourth problem is a mathematical problem that was not published as part of the list of twenty - three problems known as Hilbert 's problems , but was included in David Hilbert 's original notes .
Stockholm syndrome is named after the Norrmalmstorg robbery of Kreditbanken at Norrmalmstorg in Stockholm , Sweden .
USS Barb ( SSN-596 ) , a Permit - class attack submarine , was the second ship of the United States Navy to be named for the barb , a kingfish of the Atlantic coast .
The Undernet is the fourth largest publicly monitored Internet Relay Chat ( IRC ) network , c. 2011 , with about 12 client servers serving 3,000 users in 100 channels at any given time .
The name Duncan Dhu comes from the book Kidnapped by Robert Louis Stevenson , in which there is a character named Duncan Dhu , who is a lover of music .
Trani Cathedral ( Italian : Cattedrale di Trani ; Cattedrale di San Nicola Pellegrino ) is a Roman Catholic cathedral dedicated to Saint Nicholas the Pilgrim in Trani , Apulia , Italy .
The Freudian slip is named after Sigmund Freud , who , in his 1901 book The Psychopathology of Everyday Life , described and analyzed a large number of seemingly trivial , bizarre , or nonsensical errors and slips , most notably the Signorelli parapraxis .
Campbellite is a mildly pejorative term referring to adherents of certain religious groups that have historic roots in the Restoration Movement , among whose most prominent 19th century leaders were Thomas and Alexander Campbell .
Portland stone is a limestone from the Tithonian stage of the Jurassic period quarried on the Isle of Portland , Dorset .

Fourierism is the systematic set of economic , political , and social beliefs first espoused by French intellectual Charles Fourier ( 1772 - 1837 ) .

In mathematics , Descartes ' rule of signs , first described by René Descartes in his work La Géométrie , is a technique for determining an upper bound on the number of positive or negative real roots of a polynomial .

The term `` JPEG '' is an abbreviation for the Joint Photographic Experts Group , which created the standard .
In mathematics , the Bochner integral , named for Salomon Bochner , extends the definition of Lebesgue integral to functions that take values in a Banach space , as the limit of integrals of simple functions .

Randrianasolo 's sportive lemur ( Lepilemur randrianasoloi ) , or the Bemaraha sportive lemur , is a sportive lemur endemic to Madagascar .
The Marañón spinetail ( Synallaxis maranonica ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
The Pohnpei starling ( Aplonis pelzelni ) , also known as Pohnpei mountain starling or Ponape mountain starling , is an extremely rare or possibly extinct bird from the family of starlings ( Sturnidae ) .
Siphonocladus is a small genus of green algae , specifically of the Siphonocladaceae .
Lycopodiella is a genus in the clubmoss family Lycopodiaceae .
The Guajira stubfoot toad or Carrikeri harlequin frog , Atelopus carrikeri , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Acanthopinae is one of the three subfamilies of the family Acanthopidae .
Larocheidae is a family of small to minute sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs or micromolluscs in the superfamily Scissurelloidea .
Zarudny 's rock shrew ( Crocidura zarudnyi ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Bruskmoal bresk is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Bruskmoal .

The Rikuzen flounder , Dexistes rikuzenius , is a flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
The Ithonioidea are a superfamily of lacewing insects in the order Hemerobiiformia .
Aetheolaena is a genus of flowering plant in the aster family , Asteraceae .
Piscivory , or a diet based solely on fish , is likely the primitive condition for Cetacea , and it seems most parsimonious that Aetiocetus fed like an archaeocete , locating fish without the use of echolocation .
Tasmaniosaurus ( ' Lizard from Tasmania ' ) is an archosaur of the family Proterosuchidae , known from the Knocklofty Formation ( Early Triassic ) of West Hobart , Tasmania , Australia .
Coaxana is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , native to North and Central America .
Shipton 's mountain cavy ( Microcavia shiptoni ) is a species of rodent in the family Caviidae .
Hydrodamalinae is a recently extinct subfamily of the sirenian family Dugongidae .
Cadellia is a monotypic genus of trees in the botanical family Surianaceae .
The European green woodpecker ( Picus viridis ) is a member of the woodpecker family Picidae .
Rhopalinae is a subfamily of the hemipteran family Rhopalidae .
Thanatus is a genus of ' false crab spiders ' described by C. L. Koch in 1837 , belonging to the Order Araneae , Family Philodromidae .
Crescentia ( calabash tree , huingo , krabasi , or kalebas ) is a genus of six species of flowering plants in the family Bignoniaceae , native to southern North America , the Caribbean , Central America and northern South America .
Metriorhynchinae is one of two subfamilies of Metriorhynchidae , the other being Geosaurinae .
Cirrhipathes is a genus of black coral from the family Antipathidae .
Paraethecerus sexmaculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Paraethecerus .
Archidiptera is a suborder of Diptera under an alternative classification based largely on fossil taxa ; it has not gained wide acceptance among non - paleontological dipterists .
Red - cheeked squirrels ( genus Dremomys ) form a taxon under the subfamily Callosciurinae .
Perodicticinae is the subfamily of Lorisidae that includes the four species of African primates as shown below .
Syllectus is a genus of beetles in the family Carabidae , endemic to New Zealand .
Ericusa is a small taxonomic genus of medium - sized predatory marine gastropod molluscs in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Meliaceae , or the Mahogany family , is a flowering plant family of mostly trees and shrubs ( and a few herbaceous plants , mangroves ) in the order Sapindales .
Pseudomonacanthus elongatus Fraser - Brunner , 1940 ( Fourband leatherjacket ) Pseudomonacanthus macrurus ( Bleeker , 1857 ) ( Strap - weed filefish ) Pseudomonacanthus peroni ( Hollard , 1854 ) ( Pot - bellied leatherjacket ) Pseudomonacanthus tweediei Fraser - Brunner , 1940
Cyclolobium brasiliense ( Brazil : louveira , cabruitinga , mucitaíba ; Paraguay : ysypó copi ) is a species of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Americardia is a genus of saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs in the family Cardiidae , the cockles .
Epedanidae could be the sister group to Gonyleptoidea sensu lato ( including the Assamiidae ) , with the Stygnopsidae the sister group to the rest of Gonyleptoidea .
The Plexippinae are a subfamily of the jumping spiders ( Salticidae ) .
Poranthera is a genus of flowering plant belonging to the family Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1811 .
Omalogyra is a genus of minute marine gastropod molluscs in the family Omalogyridae .
Boselaphini is a tribe of antelopes belonging to the subfamily Bovinae of the family Bovidae .
Stempfferia ciconia , the Stork Epitola , is a butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
The Nias hill myna or Nias myna ( Gracula robusta ) is a member of the starling family .
The Yatabe blenny ( Parablennius yatabei ) is a species of combtooth blenny found in the northwest Pacific ocean along the coasts of southern Japan and Korea .
The Kivu shrew ( Crocidura kivuana ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Kerr 's noctuid moth ( Agrotis kerri ) was a species of moth in the Noctuidae family .
The Bignoniaceae , the bignonias , are a family of flowering plants in the order Lamiales .
The Tembusu ( Fagraea fragrans ) is a large evergreen tree in the family Gentianaceae .
Alforjas is an extinct genus of terrestrial herbivore the family Camelidae , endemic to North America during the Miocene through Pliocene 10.30 - -5.3 mya existing for approximately 5 million years .
The Fiji goshawk ( Accipiter rufitorques ) is a species of bird of prey in the Accipitridae family .
Euphrasia ( Eyebright ) is a genus of about 450 species of herbaceous flowering plants in the family Orobanchaceae ( formerly included in the Scrophulariaceae ) , with a cosmopolitan distribution .
Monodryxus crassus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Monodryxus .
Cinnycerthia is a genus of bird in the wren family , Troglodytidae .
Blissus is a genus in the true bug family Blissidae , commonly called chinch bugs in North America .
Antimelatoma is a genus of predatory sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Turridae , the turrids .
Hevea is a genus of flowering plants in the spurge family , Euphorbiaceae .
Strawberry mottle virus ( SMV ) is a pathogenic plant virus in Secoviridae , a family of plant - infecting picornaviruses .
Torenia is a genus of plants now classified in the family Linderniaceae .
Balaana is a genus of flies belonging to the family Bombyliidae ( bee - flies ) .
Distocercospora is a genus of three species of plant - pathogenic fungi in the family Mycosphaerellaceae .
The Cape mountain toad or Rose 's mountain toad ( Capensibufo rosei ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
The Closteriaceae are one of four families of Charophyte green algae in the order Desmidiales ( desmids ) .
The Kalinga narrowmouth toad ( Kaloula kalingensis ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Codiaeae is a tribe of the subfamily Crotonoideae , under the family Euphorbiaceae .
Heller 's broad - nosed bat , Platyrrhinus helleri , is a bat species from South and Central America .
Resnova is a genus of bulbous perennials in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Scilloideae , tribe Hyacintheae , subtribe Massoniinae , and found in South Africa .
Besla is a small genus of miniature sea snails , pyramidellid gastropod mollusks in the family Pyramidellidae within the tribe Chrysallidini ( sensu taxonomy by Bouchet & Roctroi , 2005 ) .
The Carolina mantis ( Stagmomantis carolina ) is a species of praying mantis of the subfamily Stagmomantinae .
The Aleutian skate ( Bathyraja aleutica ) is a species of skate in the family Rajidae .
The Sulawesi hawk - eagle ( Nisaetus lanceolatus ) ( earlier placed under Spizaetus ) , also known as Celebes hawk - eagle , is a medium - sized , approximately 64 cm long , crestless brown raptor in the family Accipitridae .
The Echinostomata are a suborder of the parasitic flatworm order Echinostomida .
Scholtzia is a genus of flowering plants in the family Myrtaceae , which are endemic to the south - west of Western Australia .
Lanthanopilio chickeringi is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Phalangiidae .
Dwigubskyia togatus is a species of mite placed in its own family Dwigubskyiidae , in the order Mesostigmata .
Radermachera is a genus of about 17 species of flowering plants in the family Bignoniaceae , native to southeastern Asia .
The Peronosporales are an order of water moulds ( Class Oomycetes ) which can be pathogenic .
Böhm 's flycatcher ( Muscicapa boehmi ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Pimelodus is a genus of catfishes order Siluriformes of the family Pimelodidae .
Cicindis horni is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Cicindis .
The Arctic tern ( Sterna paradisaea ) is a seabird of the tern family , Sternidae .
Norfolkia squamiceps , known commonly as the Scalyhead triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Norfolkia .
The Cuban bullfinch ( Melopyrrha nigra ) is a songbird species of the monotypic genus Melopyrrha .
Monachidium is a genus of grasshoppers belonging to the family Acrididae .
Aphelandra is a genus of about 170 species of flowering plants in the family Acanthaceae , native to tropical regions of the Americas .
Batrachedra is the largest genus in the moth family Batrachedridae .
Halichondriidae is a family of marine demosponges belonging to the order Halichondrida .
The Paraguanan ground gecko ( Lepidoblepharis montecanoensis ) is a species of lizard in the Gekkonidae family .
The Natal multimammate mouse ( Mastomys natalensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Cyphocottus megalops , or the Vitim sculpin , is freshwater fish , a deepwater sculpin endemic to Lake Baikal , Siberia .
Skenea is a genus of small to minute sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Skeneidae .
Nauclea is a member of the tribe Naucleeae and is sister to a clade consisting of Burttdavya and Sarcocephalus .
Schoenocephalium is a group of plants in the family Rapateaceae described as a genus in 1845 .
Sirystes is a genus of birds in the tyrant flycatcher family , Tyrannidae .
Paracroton is a genus of flowering plants in the Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1859 .
Hemimachairodus is an extinct genus of saber - tooth cat of the tribe Machairodontini and subfamily Machairodontinae .
The Brazilian three - banded armadillo ( Tolypeutes tricinctus ) is an armadillo species endemic to Brazil , where it is known as tatu - bola ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( tɐˈtu ˈbɔlɐ ) , lit . ball armadillo ) .
Physornis fortis is an extinct species of giant flightless predatory birds of the family Phorusrhacidae or `` terror birds '' , within the subfamily Brontornithinae , that lived in Argentina .
The Mauritian tomb bat ( Taphozous mauritianus ) is a species of sac - winged bat in the family Emballonuridae that is found in central and southern Africa and Madagascar .
The Japanese horse mackerel ( Trachurus japonicus ) is a species named after mackerel in the family Carangidae .
Temminck 's courser , Cursorius temminckii , is a bird in the pratincole and courser family , Glareolidae .
Keinstirschia is a genus of fungi in the order Diaporthales , class Sordariomycetes .
Vietotrechus minutissimus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Vietotrechus .
The Spotted snake - eel ( Myrichthys tigrinus , also known as the Tiger snake eel or the Spotted tiger snake eel ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
The Arabian golden sparrow ( Passer euchlorus ) is a sparrow found in south west Arabia and also the coast of Somalia and Djibouti where it occurs in thorn savannah and scrub habitats .
Brito 's goby(Chromogobius britoi ) is a species of goby found in the Eastern Atlantic near the coasts of the Canary Islands and Madeira where it occurs at depths of from 6 to 65 metres ( 20 to 213 ft ) on rock outcrops .
The Bibionidae ( march flies and lovebugs ) are a family of flies ( Diptera ) .
Trichomanes is a large genus of ferns in the family Hymenophyllaceae , termed bristle ferns .
Plangia is a genus of insect in family Tettigoniidae , commonly known as Bush crickets or Katydids .
The Jamaican vireo ( Vireo modestus ) is a species of bird in the Vireonidae family .
The Jackson 's francolin ( Pternistis jacksoni ) is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
Montrouziera is a genus of plants in the family Clusiaceae , endemic to New Caledonia .
Stagmomantinae is a subfamily of Mantidae , a family of insectas within the order of mantises ( Mantodea ) .
Fayolia is a prehistoric shark egg capsule morphotype of the family Xenacanthidae .
Pentarhopalopilia is a genus of plants in the family Opiliaceae described as a genus in 1987 .
Cistus ( from the Greek kistos ) is a genus of flowering plants in the rockrose family Cistaceae , containing about 20 species ( Ellul et al . 2002 ) .
Cnidarians were formerly grouped with ctenophores in the phylum Coelenterata , but increasing awareness of their differences caused them to be placed in separate phyla .
Synuchidius ganglbaueri is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Synuchidius .
Ajellomyces is a genus of fungi in the division Ascomycota , in the family Ajellomycetaceae .
The Calliphorinae are a subfamily of the blow flies family Calliphoridae .
The Myoviridae is a family of bacteriophages in the order Caudovirales .
Andescynodon is one of the most basal members of Traversodontidae , a group of cynodonts that was common in South America during the Triassic .
The Jamaican petrel ( Pterodroma caribbaea ) is ( or was ) a small seabird in the gadfly petrel genus , Pterodroma .
Emmenosperma is a small genus of mostly tropical trees in the Buckthorn family , Rhamnaceae .
The Okaloosa darter ( Etheostoma okaloosae ) is a species of darter indigenous to freshwater streams and tributary systems in Okaloosa and Walton Counties in northwest Florida .
The American dusky flycatcher , or simply dusky flycatcher , ( Empidonax oberholseri ) is a small , insectivorous passerine of the tyrant flycatcher family .

Aglaia is a genus of more than 100 species belonging to the Mahogany family ( Meliaceae ) .
The Geryoniidae are a family of jellyfish in the order Trachymedusae .

Gentianella is a plant genus in the gentian family ( Gentianaceae ) .

The Kidako moray ( Gymnothorax kidako ) is a species of marine fish in the family Muraenidae .
Cookeina is a genus of cup fungi in the family Sarcoscyphaceae , members of which may be found in tropical and subtropical regions of the world .
Bryophilinae is a subfamily of moths in the family Noctuidae .
Balaenicipitidae is a family of birds in the Pelecaniformes order , although it was traditionally placed in Ciconiiformes .
Walliserops ( named after Prof . O. Walliser of Göttingen ) is a genus of spinose phacopid trilobite , of the family Acastidae , found in Lower to Middle Devonian age rocks from the Anti - Atlas Mountains of Morocco .

Ursia is a genus of moths of the family Notodontidae , the prominents .
Ampheremus cylindricollis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Ampheremus .
The Sangihe white - eye ( Zosterops nehrkorni ) is a species of bird in the white - eye family .

The Luzon broad - toothed rat ( Abditomys latidens ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .

The Philippine serpent eagle ( Spilornis holospilus ) is an eagle found in the major islands of the Philippines .
Euarchonta and Glires together form the Euarchontoglires , one of the four Eutherian clades .
The Australasian bittern ( Botaurus poiciloptilus ) , also known as the brown bittern , is a large bird in the heron family .

Hpunalikevirus ( synonym Hp1likevirus ) is a genus of viruses in the family Myoviridae , within the subfamily Peduovirinae .
Brauer 's burrowing skink ( Janetaescincus braueri ) is a species of skink in the family Scincidae .
Heminautilus is an extinct nautiloid genus from the nautilacean family Cymatoceratidae that lived during the early Cretaceous ( Kummel 1964 ) .
Conospermum is a genus of about 50 species in the family Proteaceae that are endemic to Australia .
Dendrotriton or bromeliad salamanders is a genus of salamanders in the family Plethodontidae , endemic to South and Central America : from Southwestern Chiapas , Mexico , to Honduras .
The Lahontan redside Richardsonius egregius is a cyprinid fish of the Great Basin in eastern California and western Nevada .
The European hedgehog ( Erinaceus europaeus ) , also known as the West European hedgehog or common hedgehog , is a hedgehog species found in Europe , from Iberia and Italy northwards into Scandinavia .
Katkaenus spectaculus is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae , the only species in the genus Katkaenus .
Orectolobus is a genus of carpet sharks in the family Orectolobidae .
Austrofromia is a genus of starfish belonging to the family Ophidiasteridae .
Blephilia ( Downy Pagoda Plant or Wood Mint ) is a genus of three species of flowering plants in the family Lamiaceae .
Rhiginia is a New World genus in the subfamily Ectrichodiinae of Reduviidae ( assassin bugs ) .
The Ibaliidae are a small family of hymenopteran superfamily Cynipoidea .
Anopyxis is a genus of plant in family Rhizophoraceae , with 3 species .
The Sudanian grass rat ( Arvicanthis ansorgei ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Talamancan yellow - shouldered bat ( Sturnira mordax ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .

Sceloporus occidentalis bocourtii is a subspecies of the Western fence lizard .
The African dwarf mud turtle ( Pelusios nanus ) is a species of turtle in the family Pelomedusidae .
The Caroline flying fox or Pohnpei flying fox ( Pteropus molossinus ) is a species of megabat in the Pteropus genus , endemic to Micronesia .
Oreina is a genus of broad - shouldered leaf beetles belonging to the family Chrysomelidae , subfamily Chrysomelinae .
The genus Bipalium is one of four genera in the subfamily Bipaliinae , within the family Geoplanidae .
The Catenicellidae are a family of bryozoans in the suborder Ascophora .
Brassaiopsis is a genus of shrubs of family Araliaceae .
Crucianella ( common name Crossworts ) is a genus of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family .
The Mexican leaf frog , Pachymedusa dacnicolor , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Arachis is a genus of about 70 species of annual and perennial flowering plants in the pea family ( Fabaceae ) , native to South America , and was recently assigned to the informal monophyletic Pterocarpus clade of the Dalbergieae .
Pomatoschistus marmoratus , Marbled goby , is a species of goby native to the eastern Atlantic from the Bay of Biscay down around the Iberian Peninsula through the Mediterranean Sea , the Black Sea and the Sea of Azov .
Staurophora celsia is a moth of the family Noctuidae .
Madtoms are freshwater catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) of the genus Noturus of the family Ictaluridae .
Tyrannosauridae is a family in rank - based Linnaean taxonomy , within the superfamily Tyrannosauroidea and the suborder Theropoda .
The Erebidae are a family of moths in the Noctuoidea superfamily .
The American grass bug ( Acetropis americana ) is a rare true bug found in the Willamette Valley of the U.S. state of Oregon .
Wilhelm 's hawkfish , Itycirrhitus wilhelmi , is a species of hawkfish found in tropical waters at depths of 1 to 55 m ( 3.3 to 180.4 ft ) over rocky substrates .
The Tinginae ' are a subfamily of lace bugs ( family Tingidae ) .

The Peninsular rock agama or South Indian rock agama , Psammophilus dorsalis , is a common species of agama found on rocky hills in south India .
The Reudemannoceratidae are the ancestral and most primitive of the Discosorida , an order of cephalopods from the early Paleozoic .
Wakefieldia is a genus of two species of fungi , generally thought to belong in the Boletaceae family , but recent molecular study has shown that Wakefieldia macrospora is in fact not related to Boletales and belongs to Hymenogastraceae family .
Pseudacorethra zischkai is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Pseudacorethra .
Gigantidas is a genus of large , deepwater , hydrothermal vent mussels , marine bivalve molluscs in the family Mytilidae .
The Dipsacaceae have been recognized as a family ( the teasel family ) of the order Dipsacales containing 350 species of perennial or biennial herbs and shrubs in eleven genera .

The Philippine duck ( Anas luzonica ) is a large dabbling duck of the genus Anas .
Trocholites is a tarphycerid genus in the family Trocholitidae from the Middle and Upper Ordovician with a gradually expanding , weakly ribbed shell ; whorls in contact , dorsum slightly impressed ; cross section depressed , venter and sides rounded ; siphuncle close to but not at the dorsal margin .
Laevitrigonia is a genus of fossil clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Trigoniidae .

The Eurasian wigeon , also known as widgeon or Eurasian widgeon ( Anas penelope , and sometimes Mareca penelope ) is one of three species of wigeon in the dabbling duck genus Anas .
Anemone ranunculoides , the yellow anemone , yellow wood anemone or buttercup anemone , is a species of herbaceous perennial plant that grows in forests across most of Continental Europe , and less frequently in the Mediterranean region .
In the 1981 version of the Cronquist system it was an order placed in subclass Dilleniidae with the following circumscription : order Primulales family Myrsinaceae family Primulaceae family Theophrastaceae The APG III system includes all the plants involved in the ( expanded ) order Ericales .
Lissozodes basalis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Lissozodes .
The Bornean treepie ( Dendrocitta cinerascens ) is a passerine bird belonging to the treepies genus , Dendrocitta , of in the crow family , Corvidae .
