The Oxapampa poison frog ( Ameerega planipaleae ; formerly Epipedobates planipaleae ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family endemic to Peru near Oxapampa , in the Pasco Region .
The Omorphini are a small tribe of moths in the subfamily Plusiinae , only consisting of the genus Omorphina .
Anchieta 's pipistrelle ( Hypsugo anchietae ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
The Yunnan bush rat ( Hadromys yunnanensis ) is a species of rodent from the family Muridae .
Araeomerus is a genus of earwigs , in the family Hemimeridae , the suborder Hemimerina , and the order Dermaptera .
The Sardinian lynx is an extinct subspecies of the Eurasian lynx that once could be found on the Italian island of Sardinia .
Leptosiphon bicolor ( syn . Linanthus bicolor ) , known as true babystars , is a low annual flowering plant with clumps of needle - like leaves .
The Luzon striped babbler ( Zosterornis striatus ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Akodontini is the second most speciose rodent tribe of the subfamily Sigmodontinae .
The Manú poison frog ( Ameerega macero ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family found in southern Peru and Brazil .
The Florida black wolf ( Canis rufus floridanus ) , also known as the Florida wolf and the black wolf , was a subspecies of the red wolf , Canis rufus , though this has been contested in recent years , that lived in Florida .
Mortimer points out that Benedetto ( 1973 ) and Galton ( 1985 ) were the first to recognize that Staurikosaurus and Herrerasaurus were more closely related to each other than to sauropodomorphs or avepods , placing them both in the Herrerasauridae and Herrerasauria .
The Bocon toadfish ( Amphichthys cryptocentrus ) is a species of tropical toadfish in the family Batrachoididae found along the Caribbean - Atlantic Coast of Central and South America from Panama to Brazil .
Philine is a genus of sea slugs or sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Philinidae , the headshield slugs or paper bubbles .
The Bukoba lampeye ( Aplocheilichthys bukobanus ) is a species of fish in the Poeciliidae family .
Gerritea is a genus of Bolivian plants in the Poaceae family .
Euglandina is a genus of predatory medium- to large - sized air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Spiraxidae .
Sauteria is a genus of liverwort in the family Cleveaceae .
Nematanthus is a genus of flowering plants of the family Gesneriaceae .
Nacaduba is a genus of gossamer - winged butterflies ( Lycaenidae ) .
Steneretma laticauda is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Steneretma of the family Ulidiidae .
The subfamily Crabroninae is the most diverse group in the wasp family Crabronidae , containing over 100 genera .
Clathrina is a genus of calcareous sponge in the family Clathrinidae .
The Salvadori 's antwren ( Myrmotherula minor ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
Suphrodytes dorsalis is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Suphrodytes .
Erebonectes is a genus of crustacean in family Epacteriscidae , containing two troglobitic species .
Cucujus is a genus of beetles in the family Cucujidae , the flat bark beetles .
Kannemeyeria was a large dicynodont of the family Kannemeyeriidae , one of the first representatives of the family , and hence one of the first large herbivores of the Triassic .
Lovat 's climbing mouse ( Dendromus lovati ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
Belford 's melidectes ( Melidectes belfordi ) , also known as Belford 's honeyeater , is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .
Hydnellum is a genus of tooth fungi of the family Bankeraceae in the order Thelephorales .
Oxyurichthys is a genus of fish in the family Gobiidae , known commonly as arrowfin gobies .
Freesia is a genus of herbaceous perennial flowering plants in the family Iridaceae , first described as a genus in 1866 by Chr .
The Manado yellow tiger ( Parantica menadensis ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
The Taiwan lesser salamander ( Hynobius fuca ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family , endemic to Taiwan .
Acanthoferonia ferox is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Acanthoferonia .
The California brackish water snail also known as the mimic tryonia , scientific name Tryonia imitator , is a species of very small brackish water snails that have an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
Sclater 's golden mole ( Chlorotalpa sclateri ) is a species of mammal in the family Chrysochloridae .
Ranatra is a genus of generally slender predatory members of the family Nepidae , known as water scorpions or water stick - insects .
Ceratosauridae is a family of theropod dinosaurs belonging to the infraorder Ceratosauria .
The Rio golden - eyed tree frog , Trachycephalus imitatrix , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Argentina and Brazil .
Athertonia is a genus of a sole described species of tall trees , constituting part of the plant family Proteaceae .
McCosker 's flasher wrasse , Paracheilinus mccoskeri , is a species of wrasse native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
The Auckland merganser or Auckland Islands merganser ( Mergus australis ) was a typical merganser which is now extinct .
The subgenus Dorsilopha belongs to genus Drosophila and consists of four species .
Triboloceras is the name given to an extinct nautiloid genus from the Lower Carboniferous ( Mississippian ) , included in the nautilid family Trigonoceratidae characterized by an evolute shell bearing longitudinal ribs , with whorls in contact except in the early and very latest growth stages .
The Wuchang bream ( Megalobrama amblycephala ) is a species of cyprinid fish native to the Yangtze basin , China , including Liangzi Lake .
Lottia is a genus of sea snails , specifically true limpets , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Lottiidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Becking redefined the genus in 1970 as containing prokaryotic actinomycetes and created the family Frankiaceae within the Actinomycetales .
Laosanthus is a genus of plants in the ginger family , Zingiberaceae .
The Vernanimalcula fossils were interpreted as showing a triploblastic structure , a coelom , a differentiated gut , a mouth , an anus , and paired external pits that were believed possible sense organs , making it the earliest known member of the Bilateria ( animals with bilateral symmetry , at least as embryos ) .
The Gough finch or Gough bunting ( Rowettia goughensis ) is a songbird species .
Groenlandia is a monotypic genus of aquatic plants ( pondweed ) of the family Potamogetonaceae .
Moserella is a fungal genus in the family Sclerotiniaceae ; according to the 2007 Outline of Ascomycota , its placement in this family is uncertain .
The Makwassie musk shrew ( Crocidura maquassiensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Peismoceras is a genus of fossil Cephalopoda in the family Lechritrochoceratidae .
The Florida stone crab , Menippe mercenaria , is a crab found in the western North Atlantic , from Connecticut to Belize , including Texas , the Gulf of Mexico , Cuba , The Bahamas , and the East Coast .
Hubbsia is a lichenized genus of fungi in the family Roccellaceae .
The Botswanan long - eared bat ( Laephotis botswanae ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
The Mexican blind brotula , Typhliasina pearsei , is a species of viviparous brotula endemic to Mexico where it is found in sinkholes and caves .
Eoleptestheria ticinensis is a species of clam shrimp in the family Leptestheriidae .
Malpighiaceae Malpighiaceae - description , taxonomy , phylogeny , and nomenclature Cottsia Anderson , W. R. , and C. Davis , 2007 .
Idoceras is a genus of perisphictacean ammonite , belonging to the Perisphinctidae subfamily Idoceratinae .
The Rocky Mountain toad or western Woodhouse 's toad ( Anaxyrus woodhousii woodhousii ) is a subspecies in the Woodhouse 's toad subgroup .
The Remo flounder , Oncopterus darwinii , is an edible flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
Neochrysoprasis zajciwi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Neochrysoprasis .
Kelaart 's long - clawed shrew ( Feroculus feroculus ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Tibetan rosefinch ( Carpodacus roborowskii ) is a species of rosefinch in the finch family Fringillidae .
Kayserops is a trilobite in the order Phacopida ( family Acastidae ) , that existed during the lower Devonian in what is now Germany .
Dent 's vlei rat ( Otomys denti ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Bruchiaceae is a family of mosses within the order Dicranales .
Trichopeltum is a genus of fungi in the Microthyriaceae family ; according to the 2007 Outline of Ascomycota , the placement in this family is uncertain .
Neoicoceratoidea , formerly called Neoicocerataceae , is one of seventeen superfamilies of the Goniatitina suborder .
Dubouzetia is a genus of about eleven species known to science , growing from shrubs up to large trees , in Papuasia and Australasia and constituting part of the plant family Elaeocarpaceae .
Mantellinae is a subfamily of frogs in the family Mantellidae .
The McConnell 's spinetail ( Synallaxis macconnelli ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Serruria is a genus of flowering plants in the family Proteaceae , endemic to South Africa .
The Baikal teal ( Anas formosa ) , also called the bimaculate duck or squawk duck , is a dabbling duck that breeds in eastern Russia and winters in East Asia .
The South American fur seal ( Arctocephalus australis ) breeds on the coasts of Chile , Peru , and Argentina .
Australerpeton is an extinct genus of archegosauroidean stereospondylomorph temnospondyl within the family Archegosauridae .
Rhodomyrtus is a group of shrubs and trees in the family Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1841 .
Pygaerinae is a subfamily of the moth family Notodontidae , the silver prominents and relatives .
Fumaria officinalis ( common fumitory , drug fumitory or earth smoke ) is a herbaceous annual flowering plant in the poppy family Papaveraceae It is the most common species of the genus Fumaria in Western and Central Europe .
The Slender conger ( Uroconger lepturus , also known as the Longtail conger or the Yellow pike - conger ) is an eel in the family Congridae ( conger / garden eels ) .
Smerina is a genus of butterflies of the subfamily Heliconiinae in the family Nymphalidae .
Sydney cockle ( NSW ) , or ark cockle ( Queensland ) , Anadara trapezia , is an estuarine filter - feeding bivalve .
In the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 , Elasmognatha is treated as a clade within the larger clade Stylommatophora .
The Cape triplefin , Cremnochorites capensis , is a triplefin blenny of the family Tripterygiidae and only member of the genus Cremnochorites , found in the western Indian Ocean and southeast Atlantic , from Sodwana Bay to False Bay in South Africa .
Stirlingia , commonly known as Blueboy , is a genus of 7 species in the family Proteaceae , all of which are endemic to Western Australia .
The Cumberland pigtoe , scientific name ( Pleurobema gibberum ) , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Niptera ( syn . Nimbomollisia ) is a genus of fungi in the family Dermateaceae .
The Buxales are placed within the eudicots but outside the core eudicots , in a paraphyletic group of basal eudicots .
The Angolan fruit bat or Angolan rousette ( Lissonycteris angolensis ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
The Rothschild 's swift ( Cypseloides rothschildi ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
The Indian cobra ( Naja naja ) also known as the Spectacled cobra , Asian cobra or Binocellate cobra is a species of the genus Naja found in the Indian subcontinent ( India , Pakistan ) and a member of the `` big four '' species that inflict the most snakebites on humans in India .
The subfamily Notochthamalinae Foster and Newman , 1987 , was proposed for members of the barnacle family Chthamalidae with elongated scuta and very narrow terga deeply interlocked , sometimes concrescent .
The Dominican blind snake or Dominican worm snake ( Typhlops dominicanus ) is a species of blind snake that is endemic to the Caribbean island - nation of Dominica , in the Lesser Antilles .
Micropolyspora is a defunct genus of bacteria within family Nocardiaceae .
Pseudodromia is a genus of crabs in the family Dromiidae , often referred to as sponge crabs .
The Stephen 's lorikeet ( Vini stepheni ) , also known as the Henderson lorikeet , is a species of parrot in the Psittaculidae family .
The American cliff swallow ( Petrochelidon pyrrhonota ) is a member of the passerine bird family Hirundinidae -- the swallows and martins .
The Guinean horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus guineensis ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae .
The subfamily Catantopinae is a group of insects classified under family Acrididae .
The Canarian shrew ( Crocidura canariensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Cauvery rasbora ( Rasbora caverii ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Rasbora from India and Sri Lanka .
Acrorchis is a monotypic genus from the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) , subfamily Epidendroideae , tribe Epidendreae , subtribe Laeliinae .
Zebra goby , Zebrus zebrus , is a species of goby native to the Mediterranean Sea where it occurs in lagoons and tide pools at depths down to 3 metres ( 9.8 ft ) .
Coleostephus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Asteraceae ( daisy family ) .
Berriasellinae is a subfamily of very late Jurassic and very early Cretaceous perisphinctoid ammonites in the family Neocomitidae .
Histeroidea is a superfamily of beetles in the infraorder Staphyliniformia .
In older texts , the genus was treated in its own family Taccaceae , but the 2003 APG II system incorporates it into the family Dioscoreaceae .
The Chilean round stingray , Urobatis marmoratus , is a species of round ray , family Urolophidae .
Hyphae Pythium , like others in the family Pythiaceae , are usually characterized by their production of coenocytic hyphae , hyphae without septations .
Azemiopinae is the name of a monotypic subfamily created for the genus Azemiops that contains the venomous viper species A. feae and A. kharini .
The genus Cousinia of the tribe Cardueae (= Cynareae ) is in its current circumscription one of the larger genera in the Asteraceae , with approximately 600 - 700 species distributed in central and western Asia .
Plagerepne is a monotypic genus of moths in the Nolidae family .
Batrachomimus belongs to the family Paralligatoridae and predates all other members of the family and its immediate sister group , Eusuchia , by 30 million years .
Anoplognathus aureus , commonly known as the gold Christmas beetle , is a beetle of the family Scarabaeidae native to northern Australia , from northeastern Queensland to northern Western Australia .
The Eurasian crimson - winged finch ( Rhodopechys sanguineus ) is a pale - colored thickset finch with a heavy , dull yellowish bill .
The West African seedeater ( Crithagra canicapilla ) is a small passerine bird in the finch family .
Sanguinolaria is a genus of saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs of the family Psammobiidae .
Laos knobby newt , Tylototriton notialis , is a species of newt in the Salamandridae family .
The East Asian tailless leaf - nosed bat or tail - less leaf - nosed bat ( Coelops frithii ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
The New Caledonian stingaree ( Urolophus neocaledoniensis ) is a little - known species of stingray in the family Urolophidae , found off New Caledonia and the adjacent Chesterfield Islands and Norfolk Ridge .
Actinus is a genus of beetles of the Staphylinidae family , Staphylininae subfamily .
The Eaton 's pintail ( Anas eatoni ) is a dabbling duck of the genus Anas .
The Fox 's shrew ( Crocidura foxi ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Holopea is an extinct genus of fossil sea snails , Paleozoic gastropod mollusks in the family Holopeidae .
The Haeterini are one of the smaller tribes of the Satyrinae in the Nymphalidae ( brush - footed butterfly ) family .
Sea anemones are classified in the phylum Cnidaria , class Anthozoa , subclass Hexacorallia .
Barunius pacificus is a species of beetle in the family Monotomidae , the only species in the genus Barunius .
White eared pheasants ( Crossoptilon crossoptilon ) are a species of `` eared pheasants '' and get their name because they are white and have the prominent ear tufts of the genus , not because they have white ears .
Problepsidis argyrialis is a moth in the Drepanidae family and only species in the Problepsidis genus .
Stolonifera is a coral sub - order in the order Alcyonacea , the soft corals .
Hoffmann 's two - toed sloth ( Choloepus hoffmanni ) is a species of sloth from Central and South America .
Pegaeophyton is a plant genus in the Brassicaceae .
Oziotelphusa is a genus of freshwater crabs in the family Parathelphusidae .
The Mauritius bulbul ( Hypsipetes olivaceus ) , also known as Mauritius black bulbul , is a songbird endemic to Mauritius .
The Eurasian penduline tit or European penduline tit ( Remiz pendulinus ) is a passerine of the genus Remiz .
Pine squirrels are squirrels of the genus Tamiasciurus , in the Sciurini tribe , of the large family Sciuridae .
The Lord Howe currawong ( Strepera graculina crissalis ) , Lord Howe Island currawong or Lord Howe pied currawong , is a large and mainly black passerine bird in the Artamidae family .
Current consensus treats Charophyceae as a class under division Charophyta , with Chlorophyta remaining a distinct division .
Esseiachryson minutum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Esseiachryson .
Microlaena stipoides or Ehrharta stipoides is a species of grass that occurs naturally in all states of Australia as well as in New Zealand , Papua New Guinea , Indonesia and the Philippines .
Brockman 's rock mouse , or Brockman 's myomyscus ( Myomyscus brockmani ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .

Olenosus serrimanus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Olenosus .
The Transkei dwarf chameleon ( Bradypodion caffer ) is a chameleon endemic to the Eastern Cape Province of South Africa .
Cunoniaceae is a family of 27 genera and about 300 species of woody plants in the order Oxalidales , mostly found in the tropical and wet temperate regions of the Southern Hemisphere .
The Cameroon indigobird ( Vidua camerunensis ) is a species of bird in the Viduidae family .
The Cuban fruit - eating bat ( Brachyphylla nana ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae found in the Bahamas , Cayman Islands , Cuba , the Dominican Republic , Haiti , Jamaica , and Turks and Caicos Islands .
Pancornus is an extinct genus from the nautiloid order Discosorida that lived during the Late Devonian .
Trechiamiotes siamensis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Trechiamiotes .
Ibyka is an extinct genus of Iridopteridales , and a possible ancestor to horsetails .

Embrikiola simulans is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Embrikiola .
Ranunculales belongs to a paraphyletic group known as the basal eudicots .

The Sinaloa martin ( Progne sinaloae ) is a species of bird in the family Hirundinidae .
Megaladapis , informally known as koala lemur , is an extinct genus belonging to the family Megaladapidae , consisting of three extinct species of lemurs that once inhabited the island of Madagascar .

Albert Simonson ( 26 December 1914 in New York City -- 16 November 1965 in San Juan , Puerto Rico ) was an American chess master .
Theodor Liebisch ( 29 April 1852 , Breslau -- 9 February 1922 , Berlin ) was a German mineralogist and crystallographer .
Antoine Chazal ( 1793 in Paris - 1854 in Paris ) was a French painter of flowers and of portraits , as well as an engraver .
Giovanni Cornacchia ( 18 June 1939 -- 23 July 2008 in Pescara ) was an Italian hurdler who specialized in the 110 m distance .
Mizchif presented hip hop news on Johannesburg radio station YFM .
Edward Sloman ( 19 July 1886 , London - 29 September 1972 , Woodland Hills , California ) was an English silent film director , actor , screenwriter and radio broadcaster .
Magnus Felix Ennodius ( 473 or 474 -- 17 July 521 ) was Bishop of Pavia in 514 , and a Latin rhetorician and poet .
Hermann Friedrich Cloedt ( c. 1555 - -1560 , † 26 July 1586 ) was commander of the garrison at Neuss ( Nuys ) , near Duisburg , in July 1586 , when the city was destroyed by the Duke of Parma 's Army of Flanders .
Armand Deperdussin ( 1860 in Liege , Belgium -- June 11 , 1924 in Paris ) was a French industrialist and aviation pioneer .
Heinrich Eduard Ausfeld ( 27 May 1850 , Schnepfenthal bei Gotha -- 4 April 1906 , Magdeburg ) was a German archivist and historian .
Johann Christian Schöttgen ( Wurzen , 14 March 1687- Dresden , 16 December 1751 ) was a German biblical scholar .
Hans - Georg von Friedeburg ( 15 July 1895 in Straßburg -- 23 May 1945 in Flensburg ) was the deputy commander of the U - boat Forces of Nazi Germany and the last Commander - in - Chief of the Kriegsmarine .
Octave Maus ( 12 June 1856 , Brussels -- 26 November 1919 , Brussels ) was a Belgian art critic , writer , and lawyer .
Léonard Defrance , born at Liège in 1735 , was a scholar of J. B. Coclers .
Filippo Strozzi the Elder ( 4 July 1428 -- 14 May 1491 ) was an Italian banker and statesman , a member of the affluent Strozzi family of Florence .
Pierre Chanal ( Saint - Étienne , Loire , 18 November 1946 -- Reims , 15 October 2003 ) was a French soldier and suspected serial killer .
Ronald Colman died on 19 May 1958 , aged 67 , from acute emphysema in Santa Barbara , California , and was interred in the Santa Barbara Cemetery .
Otto Donner ( 15 December 1835 , Kokkola -- 17 September 1909 , Helsinki ) was a Finnish linguist and politician .
John Teague ( June 3 , 1833 -- October 25 , 1902 ) was a Canadian architect and politician who served as mayor of Victoria , British Columbia from 1894 until 1895 .
Abraham Oppenheim ( 24 May 1804 in Cologne -- 9 October 1878 in Cologne ) was a German banker and patron .
Mario Zampi ( 1 November 1903 , Sora , Italy -- 2 December 1963 , London , England ) was an Italian film producer and director .
José Agustín Goytisolo Gay , ( Barcelona , 13 April 1928 -- 19 March 1999 ) , was a Spanish poet , scholar and essayist .
Paolo Micallef ( 15 May 1818 - 8 March 1883 ) was a Maltese prelate who served as Archbishop of Pisa from 1871 until his death in 1883 .
Ethel Grandin ( March 3 , 1894 , New York City - September 28 , 1988 , Woodland Hills , California ) was an American silent film actress .
Nina Kirsanova ( 1898 -- February 3 , 1989 ) was one of the most important ballet artists in Belgrade , who distinguished herself as a lead principal dancer , choreographer , head of ballet and ballet teacher .
Louise Haenel de Cronenthall was born in Naumburg , Germany , the daughter of piano maker Julius Franz Hänel , and moved to Paris to study at the Conservatoire at age 17 .
Juan de Pareja ( c. 1606 in Antequera -- 1670 in Madrid ) was a Spanish painter , born into slavery in Antequera , near Málaga , Spain .
Kegham Parseghian ( Գեղամ Բարսեղեան ) ( 1883 , Constantinople , Ottoman Turkey -- 1915 Ayaş , Ottoman Turkey ) , was a famed Armenian writer , columnist , publicist , teacher , editor , and journalist .
Samuel Cromwell ( died December 1 , 1842 ) was a sailor and petty officer ( boatswain 's mate ) aboard the brig USS Somers .
Jacob Vernet ( 1698 - 1789 ) was a prominent theologian in Geneva , Switzerland who believed in a rationalist approach to religion .
Jean - François Cars ( 16 October 1661 , Lyon , France -- 30 August 1738 , Paris , France ) , was a French engraver , printer , publisher and printseller from Lyon .
Paul Clemens von Baumgarten ( born 28 August 1848 , Dresden ; died 1928 , Tübingen ) was a German pathologist .
Henry Kloss ( 1929 , Altoona , Pennsylvania -- January 31 , 2002 , Cambridge , Massachusetts ) was a prominent American audio engineer and entrepreneur who helped advance high fidelity loudspeaker and radio receiver technology beginning in the 1950s .
Radko Dimitriev ( Bulgarian : Радко Димитриев ) ( 24 September 1859 in Gradets -- 18 October 1918 near Pyatigorsk ) was a Bulgarian general , Head of the General Staff of the Bulgarian Army from 1 January 1904 to 28 March 1907 , as well as a general in the Russian Army during the First World War .

Simon Beaton ( 1888 in Inverness , Scotland -- 1959 in Middlesbrough , England ) was a professional footballer , who played for Newcastle United and Huddersfield Town .
Princess Caroline of Denmark ( Danish : Caroline af Danmark ; 28 October 1793 , Copenhagen -- 31 March 1881 , Copenhagen ) , was the eldest surviving daughter of King Frederick VI .
Eppelein von Gailingen , correct name Apollonius von Gailingen ( born c. 1315 in Illesheim , Middle Franconia ; died 15 May 1381 in Neumarkt in der Oberpfalz ) was a famous German robber baron in the Middle Ages .
Theodor Seitz ( Mannheim , 12 September 1863 - Baden - Baden , 28 March 1949 ) was a German colonial governor .
Bartolomeo Biscaino ( 1632 - -1657 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , active in his native Genoa .
Agustín de Jáuregui y Aldecoa ( Lecároz , Navarre , Spain , May 17 , 1711 ( some sources say 1708 ) -- Lima , Peru , April 29 , 1784 ) was a Spanish politician and soldier who served as governor of Chile ( 1772 - -80 ) and viceroy of Peru ( 1780 - -84 ) .
Joseph Deniker ( 6 March 1852 in Astrakhan -- 18 March 1918 in Paris ) was a French naturalist and anthropologist , known primarily for his attempts to develop highly detailed maps of race in Europe .
Italo Allodi ( Asiago , April 13 , 1928 -- Florence , June 3 , 1999 ) was an Italian association football manager who was implicated , in many attempts to fix matches .
Yuri Korneev ( March 26 , 1937 in Moscow , Soviet Union -- 2002 ) , was a Russian basketball player .

Anthony Oliver ( 4 July 1922 , Abersychan , Monmouthshire , Wales -- November 1995 , London ) was a British film , television and stage actor .
Fanny de Beauharnais , née Marie - Anne - Françoise Mouchard ( 4 October 1737 , Paris -- 2 July 1813 ) , was a French lady of letters and salon - holder .

Wannes Van de Velde ( 29 April 1937 -- 10 November 2008 ) , born Willy Cecile Johannes Van de Velde , in Antwerp , was a Flemish singer , musician , poet and artist .

Frédéric Lazard ( 20 February 1883 , in Marseille -- 18 November 1948 , in Le Vésinet ) was a French chess master , problemist and journalist .
Diether Krebs ( 11 August 1947 in Essen , Germany -- 4 January 2000 in Hamburg ) was a German actor , cabaret artist and comedian .
Edwin Cannan ( 3 February 1861 , Funchal , Madeira -- 8 April 1935 , Bournemouth ) , the son of artist Jane Cannan , was a British economist and historian of economic thought .
Arthur Woolf ( 1766 , Camborne , Cornwall -- 16 October 1837 , Guernsey ) was a Cornish engineer , most famous for inventing a high - pressure compound steam engine .
Lothar Friedrich von Metternich - Burscheid ( 1617 - -1675 ) was the Bishop of Speyer from 1652 to 1675 and also Archbishop of Mainz and Bishop of Worms from 1673 to 1675 .
Gustav Abb ( February 23 , 1886 in Berlin - April 28 , 1945 ) was a German librarian and Nazi .

Hans Peter Sørensen ( 1886 - -1962 ) was the second Lord Mayor of Copenhagen , holding that office from 1946 to 1956 as a member of the Social Democratic Party .
Karl Rathgen ( December 6 , 1856 , Weimar - November 4 , 1921 , Hamburg ) was a German Economist .
Isaac Sailmaker ( born Isaac Zeilmaker in Scheveningen , 1633 ; died in London on June 28 , 1721 ) was a Dutch marine painter active in Britain .

Charles du Plessis d'Argentré ( May 16 , 1673 -- October 17 , 1740 ) was a French Catholic theologian and bishop of Tulle .

Saint Flavian of Ricina ( Italian : San Flaviano di Ricina ) is venerated as a martyr and bishop by the Catholic Church .
Austin Lane Crothers ( May 17 , 1860 -- May 25 , 1912 ) , a member of the United States Democratic Party , was the 46th Governor of Maryland in the United States from 1908 to 1912 .

David Gregor Corner , born circa 1585 in Hirschberg , Germany ( now Jelenia Góra , Poland ) was a German Benedictine abbot , hymn writer and theologian best known for his influential 1631 Gross Catholisches Gesängbuch ( `` Great Catholic Hymnal '' ) .
Beriah Magoffin ( April 18 , 1815 -- February 28 , 1885 ) was the 21st Governor of Kentucky , serving during the early part of the Civil War .

Maurice Hallé ( 26 February 1906 -- 5 April 1991 ) was a Liberal party member of the House of Commons of Canada .

Wolfgang Pepper ( 14 October 1910 , Kiel -- 12 October 1997 , Berlin ) was the mayor of Augsburg , Germany between 1964 and 1972 .

Dr. José Miguel Gallardo ( September 29 , 1897 -- July 18 , 1976 ) was a professor at the University of Puerto Rico and two - time ( acting ) Governor of Puerto Rico .
Margaret Ann Hartley , known as Ann Hartley , is a former New Zealand member of parliament , a former Mayor of North Shore City , and a member of the Labour Party .
Hugh Percy , 3rd Duke of Northumberland KG , PC ( 20 April 1785 -- 11 February 1847 ) , styled Earl Percy until 1817 , was a British aristocrat and Tory politician who served as Lord Lieutenant of Ireland under the Duke of Wellington from 1829 to 1830 .

BSV Ölper 2000 is a German association football and sports club from the city of Braunschweig , Lower Saxony .

The Campeonato Uruguayo de Rugby -- named `` Copa Amarok '' due to sponsorship reasons , is the main competition of Uruguayan rugby union league system .
FC Alliance Äischdall Hobscheid - Eischen is an association football club based in Hobscheid , in western Luxembourg .

The Otago Rugby Football Union is the official governing body of rugby union for the Otago Region of New Zealand .
The 1998 Direct Line International Championships was a tennis tournament played on grass courts at the Devonshire Park Lawn Tennis Club in Eastbourne in England that was part of Tier II of the 1998 WTA Tour .

Dicerandra christmanii is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common names Garrett 's mint , yellow scrub balm , and Lake Wales balm .
Apolygus spinolae is a species of true bug in the Miridae family .
Sciadocephala is a genus of Latin American plants in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Anadara diluvii is an extinct species of saltwater bivalves , ark clams , in the family Arcidae .
Streptomyces chartreusis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Africa .

Canna compacta Roscoe is a species of the Canna genus , belonging to the family Cannaceae , distributed between the south of Brazil and northern Argentina .

Pseudopedinella is a silicoflagellate genus found in brackish waters .
Salix nakamurana ( Japanese : renge - iwa - yanagi ) is a rare species of willow native to alpine slopes of central Japan .
Pinaropappus , common name rocklettuce , is a genus of flowering plants in the dandelion tribe within the daisy family , native to Mesoamerica and the southwestern United States .

Asclepias fascicularis is a species of milkweed known by the common names narrowleaf milkweed and Mexican whorled milkweed .
Lysimachia daphnoides is a rare species of flowering plant in the Primulaceae known by several common names , including Pacific loosestrife , lehua makanoe , kolekole lehua , and kolokolo kuahiwi .
Erodium brachycarpum is a species of flowering plant in the geranium family known by the common names hairy - pitted stork's - bill and shortfruit stork 's bill .
Metaloricaria nijsseni is a species of armored catfish endemic to Suriname where it occurs in the Suriname , Saramacca , Nickerie and Corantijn River basins .
Carya glabra , the pignut hickory , is a common , but not abundant species of hickory in the oak - hickory forest association in the Eastern United States and Canada .
Pseudergolinae is a small subfamily of nymphalid brush - footed butterflies .
Leucinodes orbonalis , the eggplant fruit and shoot borer or brinjal fruit and shoot borer , is a moth species in the genus Leucinodes .
Lepidium perfoliatum is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names clasping pepperweed and perfoliate pepperwort .
Limacina helicina is a species of small swimming predatory sea snail in the family Limacinidae , which belong to the group commonly known as sea butterflies ( Thecosomata ) .
Hypselobarbus kolus ( kolus barb ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Hypselobarbus .
The New Britain friarbird ( Philemon cockerelli ) is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .
Hildenbrandiales is an order of crustose forms red alga which bear conceptacles and produce secondary pit - connections .
Caruichthys is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Anisian stage of the Middle Triassic epoch .
Grindelia stricta is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Oregon gumplant , Oregon gumweed and ( in Britain and Ireland ) coastal gumplant .
Diasporus vocator , sometimes known as Agua Buena robber frog after its type locality , Agua Buena , in Golfito canton of Costa Rica , is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family .
Selkirkia is a genus of predatory , tubicolous priapulid worm known from the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale , Ogygopsis Shale and Puncoviscana Formation .
Banksia petiolaris is a species of shrub of the genus Banksia in the Proteaceae family .
Neogastromyzon is a genus of gastromyzontid loaches which are only found within the Malay Archipelago .
Cattleya bicalhoi , commonly known as Laelia dayana , is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil , from southern Minas Gerais to Rio de Janeiro .
Glyptothorax conirostris is a species of catfish that was first described by Steindachner , 1867 .
Gryllus firmus , commonly known as the sand field cricket , is one of many cricket species known as field crickets .
Rhamphochromis macrophthalmus is a species of piscivorous cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it prefers open waters at depths of from 30 to 109 metres ( 98 to 358 ft ) .
Sphenocondor is an extinct genus of sphenodontian reptile from the Middle Jurassic of Argentina .
Berlandiera pumila ( soft greeneyes ) is a North American species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Nephila edulis is a species of large spider of the Nephilidae family .
Pseudomuscari is a genus of bulbous perennials in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Scilloideae .
Helix texta ( Hebrew : שבלול החרמון ) is a species of large , edible , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae , the typical snails .
Geomyoidea is a superfamily of rodent that contains the pocket gophers ( Geomyidae ) , the kangaroo rats and mice ( Heteromyidae ) , and their fossil relatives .
Ardisia japonica is a species of Ardisia native to eastern Asia , in eastern China , Japan and Korea .
Coptodon bythobates is a critically endangered species of fish in the cichlid family .
Ammonitina comprises a diverse suborder of ammonite cephalopods that lived during the Jurassic and Cretaceous periods of the Mesozoic Era .
Malacolimax tenellus is species of air - breathing land slug , a shell - less terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Limacidae .

Rubus audax , the Tampa blackberry , is an uncommon North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .

Loureedia is a genus of araneomorph spiders in the family Eresidae , containing a single species , Loureedia annulipes , found in the Mediterranean .
Lotus stipularis is a species of legume known by the common name balsam bird's - foot trefoil .
Bambusa oldhamii , known as giant timber bamboo or Oldham 's bamboo , is a large species of bamboo .

Gasterosteiformes is an order of ray - finned fishes that includes the sticklebacks and relatives .
Scanisaurus meaning `` Scania lizard '' , is a genus of plesiosaur .
