Microberlinia is a genus in the family Fabaceae ( legume family ) .
Leptopelis zebra is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family found in Cameroon , and possibly in the Republic of the Congo , Equatorial Guinea , and Gabon .
Chelonopsis is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1865 .
Odontoglossum tenue , the Delicate Odontoglossum , is a species of orchid ranging from southern Ecuador to northwestern Peru .
Eriogonum zionis , common name Zion wild buckwheat or Point Sublime wild buckwheat , is a plant species native to the southwestern United States , the states of Utah and Arizona .
Streptomyces alni is a Gram - positive , aerobic , mesophilic bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from roots of the tree Alnus nepalensis in Xishuangbanna on the Nannuo Mountain in China .
Gongronema is a genus of milkweeds first described as a genus in 1844 .
Bidens eatonii ( Eaton 's beggarticks ) is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Sundadanio is a genus of cyprinid fishes from freshwater habitats , typically peat swamps and streams , in Borneo and Sumatra ( as well as nearby smaller islands ) in southeast Asia .
Dendrobium falconeri , known as the Falconer 's Dendrobium is a species of orchid native to Asia .
Acmispon is a genus that includes several species of American bird's - foot trefoils and deervetches formerly contained in the globally distributed genus Lotus .
Anigozanthos preissii , the Albany Cat 's paw , is a herbaceous plant species in the family Haemodoraceae , endemic to Western Australia .
Lepisiota is an Old World genus of ants in the subfamily Formicinae .
Brunfelsia latifolia is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family .
It contains the single species Abrochocis esperanza , which is found in Panama .
The Protolepidodendrales are an extinct order of lycopsids that flourished from the Devonian to the lower Carboniferous ( Mississippian ) periods .
Goniodoridella savignyi is species of sea slug , specifically a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Goniodorididae .
Phacelia rotundifolia is a species of flowering plant in the borage family , Boraginaceae , known by the common name roundleaf phacelia .
Ariusia conspersa is a species of praying mantis in the genus Ariusia in the family Tarachodidae .
Aphyonus gelatinosus also known as the gelatinous blindfish is a species of blind cusk eel found in eastern Atlantic Ocean from Azores and Canary Islands ; western Indian Ocean in Natal , South Africa and southwest Pacific Ocean known in Australia only from the type locality , off Cape York , Queensland .
The Brevicoceratidae , named by Flower in 1941 , is a family of oncocerids that contains genera characterized by exogastric ( or rarely endogastric ) gyrocones , brevicones , and torticones .
Pteryx is a genus of beetles that is typically found in northern bogs in the Northern Hemisphere .
The White sardine ( Escualosa thoracata ) , also known as Deep herring , Deep - bodied herring , Northern herring , and White herring , is a species of amphidromous sardine ( family Clupeidae ) in the genus Escualosa .
Glandirana tientaiensis ( common names : Tiantai frog , Tientai rough - skinned frog ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
Phyllomedusa tomopterna , the barred leaf frog or tiger leg monkey tree frog is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Iguanodectes is a genus of characin found in tropical South America , with eight currently described species :
Rhyssoplax aerea huttoni is a subspecies of chiton in the family Chitonidae , endemic to New Zealand .
Sepia saya is a species of cuttlefish known only from its type locality in the southwestern Indian Ocean .
Tegula brunnea , common name the brown top shell , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tegulidae , .
Lebisia vadoni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Lebisia .
Pentazonia is a taxonomic infraclass of millipedes containing the pill - millipedes ( Oniscomorpha ) which can roll into a ball and the order Glomeridesmida which can not .
Pseudauchenipterus is a genus of driftwood catfish that occur in tropical South America .
Dyraspis is no longer accepted as a genus .
Nacella mytilina is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nacellidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Melipotis fasciolaris , the Fasciolated Melipotis or Bewitching Melipotis , is a species of moth in the Erebidae family .
Agave victoriae - reginae ( Queen Victoria agave , royal agave ) is a small species of succulent flowering perennial plant , noted for its streaks of white on sculptured geometrical leaves , and popular as an ornamental .
Thelenota ananas , also known as pineapple sea cucumber , oloturia ananas , tripang , prickly skin cucumber , pointed teat sea cucumber , armoured sea cucumber , giant sea cucumber , sand fish or prickly redfish , is a species of sea cucumber found in tropical waters from the Red Sea to New Caledonia .
Salix myrsinifolia , known as the dark - leaved willow or myrsine - leaved willow , is a species of willow native to Europe and Western Siberia .
Plaesius javanus , the Jepson 's Beetle , is a species of clown beetles belonging to the family Histeridae .
Nerepisacanthus is an extinct genus of acanthodian , probably acritolepid , from Middle Silurian ( ? late Llandovery ( Telychian ) to Ludlow stages ) deposits of New Brunswick , Canada .
Baurusuchinae is a subfamily of baurusuchid crocodyliforms from the Late Cretaceous of Brazil .
Dendrobium gratiosissimum , the Very Graceful Dendrobium , is a species of orchid .
Gymnomacquartia japonica is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Gymnomacquartia of the family Tachinidae .
The Dinidoridae are a small family of insects comprising about a hundred species in sixteen genera in the Hemipteran suborder Heteroptera , the `` true bugs '' .
Nebria banksi is a metal coloured species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae family that can be found in North Korea and Russia .
Tabebuia maxonii is a species of Tabebuia native to the Dominican Republic .
Agonostomus telfairii is a species of fish in the family Mugilidae , the mullets .
Didymoctenia exsuperata is a species of Ennominae that occurs in Australia .
Salmo akairos is a species of trout , a salmonid fish , endemic to Lake Ifni , a lake less than one square kilometer in size located at an altitude of 2300 m in Morocco .
Stanhopea saccata is a species of orchid occurring from Mexico ( Chiapas ) to Central America .
Niphidium ( J. Smith , 1875 ) is a genus of ferns in family Polypodiaceae .
Thaleia nisonis is a species of minute , ectoparasitic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Eulimidae .
Jentink 's dormouse ( Graphiurus crassicaudatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Gliridae .
The genus Fregata aquila formerly included all four species of large frigatebirds but in 1914 the Australian ornithologist Gregory Mathews split off the other three species leaving Fregata aquila to denote the Ascension frigatebird .
Trichocentrum lanceanum is a species of orchid found from Trinidad to southern tropical America .
Cryptoptila australana , commonly known as the elderberry panax leaf roller , is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae .
Macelognathus is an extinct genus of sphenosuchian crocodile from the Late Jurassic .
Chaetostoma carrioni is a species of armored catfish from South America .
Christensenia aesculifolia is a species of tropical fern found throughout southeast Asia .
Oncidium brunleesianum is a species of orchid native to Brazil ( Rio de Janeiro ) .
Uluella is a spider genus of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) with only one species , the ant - mimic Uluella formosa .
Crepidula cachimilla is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calyptraeidae , the slipper snails or slipper limpets , cup - and - saucer snails , and Chinese hat snails .
Osteochilichthys brevidorsalis , the Kantaka barb , is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the Western Ghats , India .
Porolepiformes is an order of prehistoric lobe - finned fish which lived during the Devonian period ( about 416 to 359 million years ago ) .
The Diphlebiidae are a small family of damselflies , the azure damselflies , with two species in two genera :
Chrysomantis cachani is a species of praying mantis found in Côte d'Ivoire , Ghana , Guinea , and the Congo River region .
Gymnosporia is an Old World genus of plants , that comprise suffrutices , shrubs and trees .
The blackspot allotoca ( Allotoca maculata ) , also known as the blackspot goodeid , tailspot goodeid , or tiro manchado , is a species of fish in the Goodeidae family endemic to Mexico .
Baldellia ranunculoides , the lesser water - plantain , is a species of flowering plant in the family Alismataceae .
Helicoprion is a long - lived genus of extinct , shark - like eugeneodontid holocephalid fish .
Cortinarius porphyroideus , commonly known as purple pouch fungus , is a secotioid species of fungus found in Australia and in beech forests of New Zealand .
Chromis nitida is a species of damselfish in the family Pomacentridae native to the east coast of Australia .
Longitarsus zangherii is a species of beetle in the subfamily Galerucinae that can be found in Romagna , Italy .
Leiolepis triploida , also known as Thai Butterfly Lizard or Malaysian Butterfly Lizard is a species of agamid lizards that is all female ( parthenogenetic ) .
Cryptoheros septemfasciatus ( sometimes called the Seven - stripe Cichlid or Cutter 's Cichlid ) is a fish species in the cichlid family .
Calochortus vestae is a California species of flowering plants in the lily family known by the common name coast range mariposa lily .
Pleurodema borellii ( common name : rufous four - eyed frog ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Hieracium maculatum , the spotted hawkweed , is a flowering plant species in the genus Hieracium found in Europe .
Astylus trifasciatus ( Spanish : ' pololo común ' ) is a species of beetle native to Chile .
Aphaenogaster donisthorpei is an extinct species of ant in formicid subfamily Myrmicinae known from a Late Eocene fossil from North America .
Adineta ricciae is a species of freshwater rotifer in the family Adinetidae .
Digitaria californica is a species of grass known by the common name Arizona cottontop .
Gratiola neglecta is a species of flowering plant known by the common name clammy hedgehyssop .
Mahonia microphylla is a shrub in the Berberidaceae first described as a species in 1999 .
Nemotelus uliginosus , the barred snout , is a European species of soldier fly .
Paulownia kawakamii , commonly known as the Sapphire dragon tree , is a tree species in the Paulowniaceae family .
Oreobates is a frog genus of in the Craugastoridae family .
Bears are mammals of the family Ursidae .
Lethrinus nebulosus is a species of emperor fish .
Shorea praestans ( also called Light Red Meranti ) is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Helianthus praecox is a North American species of sunflower known by the common name Texas sunflower .
Stylocline ( neststraw ) is a small genus of North American plants in the inula tribe within the daisy family .
Pseudogonatodes is a genus of geckos , often known as South American clawed geckos , containing seven described species .
Potentilla nitida is a species of cinquefoil in the Rosaceae family that is endemic to the Alps where it grows on elevation of 3,200 metres ( 10,500 ft ) .
Nebria tatrica dumbirensis is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to the mountain range of Nízké Tatry in Slovakia , and Czech Republic .
The Halomonadaceae are a family of halophilic Proteobacteria .
Anhanga diabolica is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Anhanga .
Rubus felix , the woodland dewberry , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Palpusopsis roseella is a species of snout moth in the genus Palpusopsis .
Leptocircini ( formerly named Graphiini ) is a tribe of swallowtail butterflies that includes the genera Eurytides ( kite swallowtails ) , Graphium ( swordtails ) , and Lamproptera ( dragontails ) .
Saltugilia splendens ( syn . Gilia splendens ) is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names splendid woodland - gilia , Grinnell 's gilia and splendid gilia .
Sinojackia rehderiana ( 狭果秤锤树 , xia guo cheng chui shu ) is a species of flowering plant in the genus Sinojackia .
Helmstedtisuchus is an extinct genus of teleostean fish .
Actinoporus elegans , commonly known as the Elegant Anemone or the Brown - striped Anemone , is a species of sea anemone in the family Aurelianidae .
Ramnogaster is a small genus of sprats found only in South America .
Mongolicosa buryatica is a species of wolf spider only known from the eastern Sayan Mountains in Buryatia , Russia .
Melanthium woodii , common names Wood 's bunchflower or Ozark bunch - flower , is a species formerly known as Veratrum woodii .
Cryosophila williamsii , also known as Lago Yojoa Palm or Root - spine Palm is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family .
Bathurstia was a genus of scrambling Silu - Devonian land plant with isotomously - branching axes that grew to heights of 30 cm . It is aligned with the Zosterophylls , and produced Calamospora - type spores .
Pentameris is a genus of plants in the grass family , native primarily to Africa , with a few species in Yemen and on certain islands in the Indian Ocean .
Gerrini is a tribe of water strider .
Cheirurus is a genus of phacopid trilobite that lived from the Late Cambrian to the Middle Devonian .
Cordia sebestena is a species of flowering plant in the borage family , Boraginaceae , that is native to the American tropics .
Eleutherodactylus pituinus is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to the Cordillera Central , Dominican Republic , at elevations of 1,212 - -1,770 m ( 3,976 - -5,807 ft ) asl .
The Leptonetoidea are a superfamily of haplogyne araneomorph spiders with three families .
Drupella rugosa , common name : the rugose drupe , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Hara horai is a species of South Asian river catfish endemic to West Bengal , India where it is found in the Terai and Duars .
Nebria kumgangi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae family that is endemic to North Korea .
Urtica massaica is a species of flowering plant in the Urticaceae ( nettle family ) known by many English names , including Maasai stinging nettle and forest nettle .
Pinillosia is a genus of Caribbean plants in the cosmos tribe within the daisy family .
Sobareutis conchophanes is a species of moth of the family Yponomeutidae .
Xixiposaurus is a genus of prosauropod dinosaur which existed in what is now Lower Lufeng Formation , China during the lower Jurassic period .
Promegatherium ( `` before Megatherium '' ) is a genus of prehistoric xenarthrans that lived in South America , primarily Argentina , during the Middle to Upper Miocene .
Crataegus mexicana is a species of hawthorn known by the common names tejocote , manzanita , tejocotera and Mexican hawthorn .
Powelliphanta superba is a species of large , carnivorous land snail in the family Rhytididae , which is endemic to the South Island of New Zealand .
Nepenthes ramispina ( /nɨˈpɛnθiːz ˌræmɨˈspaɪnə/ ; from Latin : ramus = branch , spina = spine , spur ) is a highland Nepenthes pitcher plant species , native to Peninsular Malaysia .
Ficus yoponensis is a species of fig tree found in Central and South America .
Favorinus tsuruganus is a species of aeolid nudibranch , a sea slug .
The Tanypezidae , known as the `` stretched - foot flies '' , are small family of acalyptrate Diptera ( Schizophora , Brachycera ) .
Asellota is a suborder of isopod crustaceans found in marine and freshwater environments .
Oliva tessellata , common name the tessellate olive , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
Ulidiotites dakotana is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Ulidiotites of the family Ulidiidae .
Plantago hawaiensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name Hawaiian plantain .
Pentagramma is a small genus of North American ferns .
Fargoa dianthophila , common name the serpulid odostome , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Gnaphosa lonai is a ground spider species found in Italy .
Lepidosperma elatius is a species of plant from sedge family that can be found in Australia and Tasmania .
Phyllodactylus kofordi , commonly known as the coastal leaf - toed gecko , is a species of lizard , which is endemic to South America .
Clathromangelia quadrillum is a fossil species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clathurellidae , dating from the Miocene .
Arctostaphylos regismontana is a species of manzanita known by the common name Kings Mountain manzanita .
Eleocharis pachycarpa is a species of spikesedge known by the common name black sand spikerush .
Zenion is a genus of zeniontid fish which is known from the fossil record , but is still extant .
Geranium umbelliforme is a plant species native to central Sichuan and Yunnan , China at elevations of 2800 - 3200 meters .
Lilium ledebourii ( Persian : سوسن چلچراغ ‎ , Sousan - e Chehel Cheraagh ) is a rare Asian species of plants in the Lily family .
Ligustrum obtusifolium ( border privet or Amur privet ) is a species of privet , native to Japan , Korea and northeastern China ( Heilongjiang , Jiangsu , Liaoning , Shandong , Zhejiang ) .
Akodon albiventer , also known as the white - bellied grass mouse or white - bellied akodont , is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Oniscidae is a family of woodlice , including the common woodlouse Oniscus asellus .
A single species is included today , Telmatornis priscus .
Pareuxesta obscura is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Pareuxesta of the family Tephritidae .
Balanus aquila is a species of acorn barnacle in the family Balanidae .
Pyrenula is a genus of lichenized fungi in the Pyrenulaceae family .
Hulsanpes is the name given to a monotypic genus of eumaniraptoran theropod dinosaurs from the Late Cretaceous of Mongolia .
Meganeuropsis is an extinct genus of griffinfly , order Meganisoptera , known from the Early Permian of North America , and represents the biggest known insect of all time .
Escobaria robbinsiorum ( syn . Coryphantha robbinsiorum ) is a rare species of cactus known by the common names Cochise pincushion cactus and Cochise foxtail cactus .
Limnophyes er is a species of chironomid midge found in Scandinavia and European Russia .
Lacuna pallidula , common name the pale lacuna , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles .
Schizostachyum is a tall or shrub - like tropical genus of bamboo .
Protostegidae is a family of extinct marine turtles that lived during the Cretaceous period .
Ophiclinus ningulus , the Variable snake - blenny , is a species of clinid found in reefs around southern Australia , preferring areas with plentiful growth of sponges at depths of from 5 to 20 metres ( 16 to 66 ft ) .
Pyramidula rupestris is a species of very small , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Pyramidulidae .
Allium amplectens is a species of wild onion known by the common name narrowleaf onion .
Kaatedocus is a genus of diplodocine flagellicaudatan sauropod known from the middle Late Jurassic ( Kimmeridgian stage ) of northern Wyoming , USA .
It contains only one species , Rungsiodes stenopterella , which is found in Morocco .
Gorybia chontalensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae ( Longhorn Beetle ) .
Hainina is an extinct mammal genus from the Upper Cretaceous to the Paleocene of Europe .
Crangonyx dearolfi is a species of crustacean in family Crangonyctidae .
Archips fuscocupreanus , the exotic leafroller moth or apple tortrix , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Oberea apicenigrata is a species of flat - faced longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Breuning in 1961 .
Aristida is a very nearly cosmopolitan genus of plants in the grass family .
Macropodia falcifera , the Cape long - legged spider crab , is a species of marine crab found around the South African coast .
Tubaria punicea is a rare species of agaric fungus in the family Tubariaceae .
Rankinia adelaidensis is a species of heath dragon , small agamid reptiles , occurring in southern regions of Australia .
Juniperus formosana ( Formosan juniper ) is a species of conifer in the Cupressaceae family .
Hemigobius mingi , commonly known as the banded goby , is a species of goby found in brackish and marine waters .
Voraptus tenellus is a species of spider that is endemic to Mahe Island and Silhouette Island of Seychelles .
Euvola raveneli , or Ravenel 's scallop , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae .
Euacanthellinae is a subfamily of leafhoppers , native to Australia , New Caledonia and Madagascar , and adventive in New Zealand .
Pholidogaster ( ' scaly stomach ' ) is an extinct genus of tetrapod that lived during the Middle Carboniferous period ( late Viséan to early Serpukhovian ) .
Currently , eight species of Trichinella are known , only three of which cause trichinellosis , and Trichinella britovi is one of them .
Trichomycterus stawiarski is a species of pencil catfish endemic to Brazil , where it occurs in the upper Iguaçu river basin .
Hypenia is a genus of flowering plants in the mint family , Lamiaceae , first described as a genus in 1988 .
Scarthyla vigilans ( Maracaibo Basin treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Plantago eriopoda is a species of plantain known by the common name redwool plantain .
Musa ornata ( flowering banana ) is one of more than 50 species of banana in the genus Musa of the family Musaceae .
Protostropharia , is a coprophilous agaric fungal genus that produces glutinous , mostly yellowish to yellow brownfruit bodies .
Borrichia peruviana is a Peruvian species of flowering plants in the aster family .
Rajella is a genus of rays native to the Pacific , Atlantic and Indian oceans .
Campylobacter lari ( formerly Campylobacter laridis ) is a species of nalidixic acid - resistant , thermophilic , microaerophilic bacteria first isolated from human faeces .
Anaspididae is a family of freshwater crustacean that is endemic to Tasmania , Australia .
Nanobagrus immaculatus is a species of bagrid catfish endemic to Indonesia where it is found in the Kahayan River drainage of southern Borneo .
Dolichosuchus ( meaning `` long crocodile '' ) is the name given to a genus of dinosaur from the Triassic .
Cinclosomatidae is a family of passerine birds native to Australia and nearby areas .
Euthamia leptocephala ( bushy goldentop or Mississippi Valley goldentop ) is a North American species of plants in the daisy family .
Dorycera brevis is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Dorycera of the family Ulidiidae found in Greece .
Felten 's vole ( Microtus felteni ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Kraenzlinella is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae , first described as a genus in 1903 .
Thomandersia is the sole genus in the Thomandersiaceae , an African family of flowering plants .
Discocharopa mimosa is a species of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Charopidae .
The Pterotracheoidea is , according to the Taxonomy of the Gastropoda ( Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) , a taxonomic superfamily of sea snails or sea slugs , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Cathaymyrus is a genus of Early Cambrian cephalochordate known from the Chengjiang locality in Yunnan Province , China .
Chionanthus retusus ( Chinese Fringetree ; Chinese : 流蘇樹 liúsūshù ) is a species of Chionanthus native to eastern Asia , in eastern and central China , Japan , Korea , and Taiwan .
Acanthonyx dentatus , the toothed decorator crab , is a species of crab in the family Inachidae .
Oligodon albocinctus , commonly known as the light - barred kukri snake , is a species of colubrid snake .
Sorbus alnifolia ( syn . Aria alnifolia ) alder - leafed whitebeam or Korean whitebeam , Chinese : 水榆花楸 ; pinyin : shui yu hua qiu ; literally : `` water elm rowan '' , is a species of whitebeam native to eastern Asia in eastern and northern China , Taiwan , Korea and Japan .
Candida ubatubensis is a yeast species .
Encyclia citrina ( or tulip orchid ) is a species of orchid with a strong lemon fragrance .
Chromobacterium is a genus of gram - negative rods .
Ocynectes is a genus of tide pool dwelling sculpins native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
Amanita pekeoides is a species of fungus in the family Amanitaceae .
Adelphobates quinquevittatus ( Rio Madeira poison frog or more ambiguously , Amazonian poison frog ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family found in the Rio Madeira drainage in the southern Amazon Basin in Brazil and Bolivia .
Ginkgo digitata is an extinct ginkgo species in the family Ginkgoaceae .
Nagia sacerdotis is a species of moth in the Erebidae family .
Mycena renati , commonly known as the beautiful bonnet , is a species of mushroom in the Mycenaceae family .
Sphagnum novo - caledoniae is a species of plant in the Sphagnaceae family .
Acidiphilium cryptum is a species of heterotrophic bacteria , the type species of its genus .
Veronica austriaca ( syn . V. teucrium ) ( broadleaf speedwell , large speedwell , Austrian speedwell , or saw - leaved speedwell ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Plantaginaceae , native to northern temperate Europe .
Cyphelium notarisii or soot lichen is a species of lichenised fungus in the family Caliciaceae .
Solanum huaylasense is a species of plant ( wild tomato ) in the Solanaceae family .
Lardoglyphus zacheri is a species of mite first discovered by Dr. Zacher in a dermestid beetle culture .
Gonocerus acuteangulatus is a herbivorous species of true bug in the family Coreidae .
Oxypilinae is a subfamily of the mantis family Hymenopodidae .
Pseudohemiodon apithanos is a species of armored catfish endemic to Ecuador where it occurs in the San Miguel River basin .
Solandra grandiflora , the showy chalicevine , is a species of Solandra , a vine with large ornamental flowers .
Strombidae , commonly known as the true conchs , is a taxonomic family of medium - sized to very large sea snails in the superfamily Stromboidea .
Hepatocystis taiwanensis is a species of the genus Hepatocystis .
Larinus araxicola is a species of true weevil found in the Araks valley in northeastern Turkey .
Astralium stellare , common name the blue - mouthed turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Dactylis glomerata , also known as cock's - foot or orchard grass , is a common species of grass in the genus Dactylis .
Eucryphia lucida , commonly known as leatherwood is a species of trees or large shrubs endemic to forests of western Tasmania .
Hymenocallis pygmaea is a bulb - forming herb found in bogs and along stream banks It is considerably smaller than most other species of Hymenocallis , with a scape rarely more the 40 cm tall .
Oberea birmanica is a species of flat - faced longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Gahan in 1895 .
Jacksonia furcellata , commonly known as grey stinkwood , is a species of leafless broom - like shrub or small tree that occurs in the south west of Western Australia .
Pontophaedusa funiculum is a species of land snail , a gastropod in the family Clausiliidae , the door snails within the subfamily Serrulininae .
Crateroscelis is a songbird genus of the Australasian `` warbler '' family ( Acanthizidae ) .
Orthodera ministralis , common name garden mantis or Australian green mantis , is a species of praying mantis from Australia .
Caproberyx is an extinct genus of bony fish from the Cretaceous period of Africa and Europe .
Oxytropis is a genus of plants in the legume family .
Georgimarinus barbatus is a species of Cyclopteridae found in north Pacific Ocean .
Shidaisaurus is a genus of basal tetanuran theropod dinosaur .
Orthriophis is a genus of Old World ratsnakes , containing four species of ratsnakes which were formerly assigned to the genus Elaphe .
Pteronarcys californica is a species of insect in the family Pteronarcyidae , the giant stoneflies and salmonflies .
Rayonnoceras is a genus of extinct cephalopods that lived around 325 million years ago during the Carboniferous .
Streptopus is a Eurasian and North American genus of flowering plants in the lily family , found primarily in colder and temperate regions .
Filipinmulciber breuningi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Filipinmulciber .
Terranatos dolichopterus , the saberfin killifish , is a species of rivuline endemic to the Orinoco River basin of Venezuela .
Leporacanthicus heterodon is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Xingu River basin .
Paraceltitidae is a family of Middle and Upper Permian cephalopods , that comprise the earliest of the Ceratitida .
Bythinella gloeeri is a species of very small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Amnicolidae ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
The elephant tusk , scientific name Dentalium elephantinum , is a species of scaphopod mollusc .
Haematoxylum brasiletto , or Mexican logwood , is a species of tropical hardwood tree in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Trachycephalus is a genus of frogs , the casque - headed tree frogs , in the Hylidae family .
Idiastion is a small genus of scorpionfishes found in the Atlantic and Pacific oceans .
Molongum is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1948 .
Euastacus maidae is a species of Australian crayfish in the family Parastacidae .
The primary species , Arginbaatar dmitrievae , was also named by Trofimov .
Clianthus puniceus , common name kaka beak ( Kōwhai Ngutu - kākā in Māori ) , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Clianthus of the legume family Fabaceae , native to New Zealand 's North Island .
Burlingia is a rare and diminutive genus of trilobite , that lived during the early to middle Middle Cambrian ( Acadoparadoxides pinus- to Ptychagnostus punctuosus - zone ) .
Achyranthes splendens ( ʻEwa hinahina ; also called Maui Chaff Flower , Round Chaff Flower , Round - leaf Chaff Flower , or Round - leaved Chaff Flower ) is a species of flowering plant in the pigweed family , Amaranthaceae , that is endemic to Hawaiʻi .
Batrachosauroides is an extinct genus of prehistoric salamander known from several sites across the United States .
Monascus sanguineus is a fungus species in the family Elaphomycetaceae .
Platanthera stricta is a species of orchid known by the common name slender bog orchid .
Allium henryi is a plant species native to Hubei and Sichuan , China .
Desulfacinum infernum is a thermophilic sulfate - reducing bacterium , the type species of its genus .
Turbo tuberculosus is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae the turban snails .
Gallimimus ( /ˌɡælɨˈmaɪməs/ GAL - i - MY - məs ; meaning `` chicken or rooster mimic '' ) is a genus of ornithomimid theropod dinosaurs from the late Cretaceous period ( Maastrichtian stage ) Nemegt Formation of Mongolia .
Falsocularia annulicornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Falsocularia .
Chulpasia is an extinct genus of Eocene marsupial related to today 's shrew opossums .
Buprestina prosternalis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Buprestina .
Rhopalomastix escherichi , is a species of ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae , which can be found from Sri Lanka .
Tritonia affinis is a species of sea slug , dendronotid nudibranch .
The Penaeaceae are a family of evergreen , leathery - leaved shrubs and small trees , native to South Africa .
Pseudolividae is a taxonomic family of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Pseudolivoidea .
Raphictis is an extinct genus of Didymictidae .
Callionymus keeleyi is a species of dragonet native to the western Pacific Ocean where it is known to occur near the Philippines and Papua New Guinea .
Garrya fremontii is a species of flowering shrub known by several common names , including California fever bush , bearbrush , and Frémont 's silktassel .
Juxia is an extinct genus of indricothere , a group of herbivorous mammals that are part of the odd - toed ungulate family tree of rhinoceros and tapirs .
Euchilichthys is a genus of upside - down catfishes native to the Congo River Basin in Middle Africa .
Euvola ziczac , or the zigzag scallop , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae .
Notoacmea parviconoida is a small species of sea snail or true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Lottiidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Agrocybe praecox is a species of brown - spored edible mushroom which appears early in the year in woods , gardens and fields .
Kalopanax septemlobus , common name prickly castor oil tree , is a deciduous tree in the family Araliaceae , the sole species in the genus Kalopanax .
Pachypanchax arnoulti is a species of aplocheilid killifish endemic to Madagascar .
Epinephelus spilotoceps , commonly called foursaddle grouper among various other vernacular names , is a species of marine fish in the family Serranidae .
Blanford 's snowfinch or plain - backed snowfinch ( Montifringilla blanfordi ) is a species of bird in the sparrow family .
Amalda depressa , common name the depressed ancilla , is a species of a small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Olividae , the olive snails or olive shells .
Astraponotus is an extinct genus of herbivorous mammal belonging to the family of astrapotherids .
Dialium ovoideum is a tropical species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
Aojia is an extinct genus from a Yiran class of 2013 fossil marine arthropods , the trilobites .
Micranthocereus polyanthus is a species of cactus .
Chaetoseris is a genus of East Asian flowering plants in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Harpiocephalus is a genus of bats within the Vespertilionidae or `` vesper bats '' family .
Argyrotaenia quercifoliana , the yellow - winged oak leafroller moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Acropora secale is a species of branching staghorn stony coral .
Hypericum dolabriforme , the straggling St. Johnswort or glade St. John's - wort , is a species of flowering plant in the St. John 's wort family .
Auriculella tenella is a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk .
Crocias is a genus of bird in the Leiothrichidae family .
Conus bartschi , common name Bartsch 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Gnetum cleistostachyum is a liana species in the Sessiles subsection of the genus Gnetum described from South East Yunnan .
Cethegus elegans is a species of spider in the genus Cethegus found in Queensland .
Hyala vitrea is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Iravadiidae .
Chiloglanis neumanni , the Neumann 's suckermouth , is a species of upside - down catfish native to Central Africa .
Clubiona decora is a sac spider species found on Madeira , the Azores and the Balkans .
Incilius mazatlanensis ( common name : Sinaloa toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Mastocarpus stellatus , also called Clúimhín Cait ( cats ' puff ) , carragheen , or false Irish moss , is a species of red algae closely related to Irish Moss , or Chondrus crispus .
Constancea is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family containing the single species Constancea nevinii ( formerly Eriophyllum nevinii ) , which is known by the common name Nevin 's woolly sunflower .
Microseris elegans is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name elegant silverpuffs .
The diet of Preuss 's monkey is primarily fruit , leaves and insects , although the species occasionally raids human crops .
Rhinophis zigzag , or Zigzag Shieldtail , is a species of snake in the Uropeltidae family .
Pseudophilautus auratus is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family , endemic to Sri Lanka .
Afzelia africana ( also called Afzelia , Lenke , Lengue , or Doussi ) is a tree species in the Fabaceae family .
Potamocorbula is a genus of very small saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs in the order Myoida .
Megalocranchia fisheri is a species of glass squid .
Perovskia is a genus of flowering plants in the mint family , Lamiaceae .
Trichopodus cantoris is a species of gourami native to Asia .
Nebria diversa is a species of beetle from Carabidae family that can be found in Canada and such US states as California , Oregon , and Washington .
It contains the single species Cyanohypsa stefanellii , which is found in Argentina .
Talpini is a tribe , in the scientific classification system of binomial nomenclature .
Hygrophorus penarioides is a species of mushroom in the Hygrophoraceae .
Euphoberia is an extinct genus of millipede from the Pennsylvanian epoch of the Late Carboniferous , measuring up to 30 centimetres ( 12 in ) in length .
Labidus is a genus of New World army ants in the subfamily Dorylinae .
Eriogonum panamintense is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Panamint Mountain buckwheat .
Arabis blepharophylla is a species of rock cress known by the common names Coast rock cress and Rose rock cress .
Bromelia chrysantha is a species in the genus Bromelia .
Chalcides guentheri , or Günther 's cylindrical skink , is a species of skink , which is endemic to the Near East .
Geopyxis carbonaria is a species of fungus in the genus Geopyxis , family Pyronemataceae .
Dotalabrus is a genus of wrasses native to the Indian Ocean coasts of Australia .
Sterna is a genus of terns in the bird family Sternidae .
This tree is sometimes sold with a braided trunk and is commonly grown as a houseplant , although more commonly what is sold as a `` Pachira aquatica '' houseplant is in fact a similar species , P. glabra .
Eremiaphila anubis , common name Anubis mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Egypt .
Macrarene diegensis is a fossil species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Liotiidae .
Diplorickettsia massiliensis species is an obligate intracellular , gram negative bacterium isolated from Ixodes ricinus ticks collected in Slovak republic forest geographically from southeastern part of Rovinka in 2006 .
Acacia kingiana was a species of wattle that occurred in an area north east of Wagin in the Avon Wheatbelt region of south - west Western Australia .
Phoradendron leucarpum is a species of mistletoe which is native to the United States and Mexico .
Clavariadelphus pistillaris is a rare species of mushroom of the family Gomphaceae native to Europe and North America .
Chalcostephia is a monotypic genus of dragonflies in the family Libellulidae containing the single species Chalcostephia flavifrons .
Cassiopea xamachana , commonly known as the upside - down jellyfish , is a species of jellyfish in the family Cassiopeidae .
Anchomenidius astur is a species of ground beetle which hail from the Platyninae subfamily that is endemic to Spain .
Cetopsidium roae is a species of whale catfish endemic to Guyana where it is only known from the Rupununi region in the southwest .
Scaphohippus is an extinct Miocene genus of equine , with two known species , known from fossils found in California , New Mexico , Montana , and Nebraska .
Oeceoclades cordylinophylla is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is native to Comoros and northern Madagascar .
Rhagoletotrypeta annulata is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Rhagoletotrypeta of the family Tephritidae .
Samoana bellula , common name the `` Polynesian tree snail '' , is a species of tropical , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial , pulmonate , gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Amphisbaena caeca , commonly known as the Puerto Rican worm lizard ( Spanish vernacular : culebrita ciega ) , is a species of worm lizard endemic to Puerto Rico .
Rhizopogon vinicolor is a species complex of ectomycorrhizal fungus which forms a mutualistic relationship with the Douglas - fir ( Pseudotsuga spp . )
Prestonella nuptialis is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Bothriembryontidae .
Caledothele elegans is a spider species in the genus Caledothele found in New Caledonia .
Paralepidocephalus is a genus of loach endemic to Yunnan , China .
Chondracanthus elegans is a red alga species in the genus Chondracanthus .
Aciphylla aurea is a species of Aciphylla , commonly known as golden speargrass or golden Spaniard .
Cyprinodon is a genus of small pupfishes found in fresh , brackish and salt water .
Metzgeria is a genus of thalloid liverworts in the family Metzgeriaceae .
Asteropeia mcphersonii , a species of plant in the Asteropeiaceae family , is a shrub to large tree , up to 25 meters tall .
Orthotelia sparganella is a moth of the Glyphipterigidae family and only species of the Orthotelia genus and Orthoteliinae subfamily .
Reissita simonyi , the Arabian burnet moth , is a species of diurnal moth of the Zygaenidae family .
Chinese celery ( Apium graveolens var . secalinum ) , is a variety of celery cultivated in East Asian countries for its edible , flavorful stalks and leaves .
Bromus orcuttianus is a species of brome grass known by the common name Orcutt 's brome .
The Alcaeorrhynchus grandis is a genus species of the Pentatomidae family .
Haliotis discus , commonly called disk abalone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Apatelodes is a genus of moths of the Bombycidae family .
Psittaculini is a tribe of parrots of the Psittaculidae family .
Boiga cyanea is a Colubrid snake species found in South Asia , China and South - east Asia .
Pygmy flying squirrels ( Petaurillus ) are a genus of flying squirrels .
Its only described species , Vatovia albosignata , is only found in Ethiopia .
Immutatus is a monotypic genus of potter wasps from Madagascar .

Helictotrichon ( alpine oatgras ) is a genus of perennial flowering plants in the grass family .

Samoana burchi is a species of a land snail , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the Partulidae family .

Heteromirafra is a small genus of African larks in the Alaudidae family .
Washingtonia is a genus of palms , native to the southwestern United States ( in southern California , southwest Arizona , Texas ) and northwest Mexico ( in northern Baja California and Sonora ) .
Aiphanes deltoidea , known as shicashic in Peru , is a species of palm which is native to northeastern South America .
The four - season orchid ( Cymbidium ensifolium ) is a species of orchid , also known as the golden - thread orchid , spring orchid , burned - apex orchid and rock orchid .
Barilium is a genus of iguanodontian dinosaur which was first described as a species of Iguanodon ( I. dawsoni ) by Richard Lydekker in 1888 , the specific epithet honouring the discoverer Charles Dawson .
Chlorocardium rodiei ( greenheart ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Lauraceae .
Myxococcus xanthus is a gram - negative , rod - shaped species of myxobacteria that exhibits various forms of self - organizing behavior as a response to environmental cues .
Megacephala gracilis is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Reiche in 1842 .
Albericus brunhildae is a species of frog in the family Microhylidae .
Teichospora is a genus of fungi in the family Teichosporaceae .
Zygogramma bicolorata , variously referred to as the Parthenium Beetle or Mexican Beetle , is a species of leaf beetle in the subfamily Chrysomelinae , native to Mexico , but introduced to India in 1984 to control Parthenium hysterophorus , a noxious weed .
The Parish 's Dendrobium ( Dendrobium parishii ) is a species of orchid natve to Asia .
Cyathea esmeraldensis ( syn . Cyathea esmeraldensis ) is a species of tree fern which is endemic to Ecuador .
Dypsis ambanjae is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family , endemic to the Madagascarian rainforests .
Pinus hartwegii is a very high altitude species , growing at altitudes of 2,500 - -4,300 metres ( 8,200 - -14,100 ft ) .
Andasta siltte is a species of ray spider that is endemic to the Seychelles .
Procontarinia matteiana ( also known as Mango gall fly and Leaf - gall midge ) is a species of Midge in the genus Procontarinia of the family Cecidomyiidae that can be found in India , Kenya , Mauritius , and Réunion .
The Pelecaniformes is an order of medium - sized and large waterbirds found worldwide .
Sitala palmaria is a species of air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helicarionidae .
Megodon is a genus of hoverflies native to Madagascar .
Arctoscopus japonicus , the sailfin sandfish or Japanese sandfish , is a species of fish of the Perciformes ( Perch - likes ) order , Trichodontidae ( sandfishes ) family .
Haumaniastrum is a genus of flowering plants in the mint family , Lamiaceae , first described in 1959 .
Bithynia leachii is species of small freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic prosobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Bithyniidae .
Polyergus rufescens is a species of slave - making ant native to southern Europe and parts of Asia , commonly referred to as the European Amazon ant or as the slave - making ant .
Campanula divaricata , common name Appalachian bellflower , is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family .
Aiptasia is a genus of a symbiotic cnidarian belonging to the class Anthozoa ( sea anemones , corals ) .
Botrychiaceae ( moonwort family ) was recognized as a segregate family of ferns .
Ixodiphagus is a genus of chalcid wasps .
Erigeron canus is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common names hoary fleabane .
Archaeus ( `` the ancient '' ) is a prehistoric genus of jackfish from the Paleogene of Europe .
Harrisia simpsonii ( Simpson 's applecactus ) is a species of cactus .
Omobranchus germaini , Germain 's blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean .

Acacia verniciflua , commonly known as varnish wattle , is a shrub or small tree species that is endemic to Australia .
Tenontosaurus ( /tᵻˌnɒntoʊˈsɔːrəs/ te - NON - to - SAWR - əs ; meaning `` sinew lizard '' ) is a genus of medium- to large - sized ornithopod dinosaur .
Dialommus macrocephalus , the Foureye rockskipper , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the eastern Pacific Ocean from Baja California , Mexico to Colombia .
Cornus capitata is a species of dogwood known by the common names Bentham 's cornel , evergreen dogwood , Himalayan flowering dogwood , and Himalayan strawberry - tree .
Micrablepharus is a small genus of lizards from South America .
Baeotherates is an extinct genus of Early Permian captorinid known from Oklahoma of the USA .
Brontomerus ( from Greek bronte meaning `` thunder '' , and merós meaning `` thigh '' ) is a possibly dubious genus of camarasauromorph sauropod which lived during the early Cretaceous ( Aptian or Albian age , approximately 110 million years ago ) .
Nanoarchaeum equitans is a species of marine Archaea that was discovered in 2002 in a hydrothermal vent off the coast of Iceland on the Kolbeinsey Ridge by Karl Stetter .
Saxifraga bryoides is a species of saxifrage known by the common name of mossy saxifrage .
Tiberia navella is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Aiolosaurus is an extinct genus of monitor lizard from the Late Cretaceous of Mongolia .
The genus contains only one species , Lalanneia mirabilis , which is found in French Guiana .
Poa confinis is a species of grass known by the common names coastline bluegrass and beach bluegrass .
The Bawean deer ( Hyelaphus kuhlii ) , also known as Kuhl 's hog deer or Bawean hog deer , is a highly threatened species of deer found only in the island of Bawean ( Gresik Regency ) in Indonesia .
Mamenchisauridae is a family of sauropod dinosaurs .
Streptomyces pentaticus is a bacterium species in the genus Streptomyces .
Plagiobothrys glyptocarpus is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name sculptured popcornflower .
Haletta semifasciata , the Blue weed whiting , is a species of weed whiting endemic to Australia where it is only found along the southern coast .

Chaetobranchus is a small genus of cichlid fishes from South America where they are native to the Amazon Basin , Orinoco Basin and rivers in the Guianas .

Microlepidogaster perforatus is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Carandaí River .

The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Phyllobolites miniatus , found in tropical South America .

Pterolamia strandi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pterolamia .

Gonypetyllis semuncialis is one of the smallest species of praying mantis and `` scarcely reach(es ) one centimeter in length . ''
Bromus pannonicus is a species of flowering plant in the Poaceae family which can be found in such European countries as Czech Republic , Hungary , Romania , and all states of former Yugoslavia .

Ptereleotris evides , the Blackfin dartfish , is a species of dartfish native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .

Davara rufulella is a species of snout moth in the genus Davara .
Boiga drapiezii , commonly known as the white - spotted cat snake , is a species of long and slender rear - fanged colubrid that is common throughout its range .

Only one species , Songlingornis linghensis , is known at present .

Pollicipes is a genus of goose barnacles , first described by William Elford Leach in 1817 .
Morchella esculenta , ( commonly known as common morel , morel , yellow morel , true morel , morel mushroom , and sponge morel ) is a species of fungus in the Morchellaceae family of the Ascomycota .

Leucauge subblanda is one of several species of orchard spider found in Japan .
The Himalayan pika ( Ochotona himalayana ) is a species of small mammal in the pika family , Ochotonidae .
The Anguillidae are a family of ray - finned fish that contains the freshwater eels .
Encheloclarias tapeinopterus is a species of airbreathing catfish endemic to Indonesia where it is only known from Bangka and Sumatra .
Suessiales is an order of dinoflagellates .
Morus rubra , commonly known as the red mulberry , is a species of mulberry native to eastern and central North America .

Malayochela maassi Is a species of cyprinid fish found in Indonesia , Malaysia and Brunei .
Turbo sandwicensis , common name the Hawaiian top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Emballonura is a genus of sac - winged bat in the family Emballonuridae .
Sambucus pubens or American red elder is a species of elder ( Sambucus ) native to eastern North America .
Rhododendron hunnewellianum ( 岷江杜鹃 ) , named in honor of H. H. Hunnewell and Walter Hunnewell , is a rhododendron species native to southern Gansu and central and northern Sichuan in China , where it grows at altitudes of 1200 - -2400 meters .
The Phrynophiurida ( formerly called Euryalae ) are an order of brittle stars containing the basket stars .
The Spinulosida are an order of sea stars containing at least 120 species in seven genera and two families .
Parabangalaia flavosignata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parabangalaia .
Gloioxanthomyces nitidus , commonly known as the shining waxcap , is a species of fungus in the family Hygrophoraceae .
Helcion pruinosus , common name the rayed limpet , is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Patellidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Estesia ( in honour of Richard Estes ) is an extinct genus of Late Cretaceous helodermatoid lizard found in the Gobi Desert in Mongolia .
Camptoloma is a genus of moth in the family Noctuidae sensu lato .
Tenodera australasiae , the purple - winged mantis , is species of praying mantis .
Alvania canariensis is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod or micromollusk in the family Rissoidae .
Aphaenogaster oligocenica is an extinct species of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae known from a pair of Middle Eocene fossils found in Europe .
Amblycheila is a genus of flightless , nocturnal tiger beetles .
Cryptothylax is a small genus of hyperoliid frogs found in the Congo Basin .
Meketibolodon is a genus of extinct mammal from the Kimmeridgian ( Upper Jurassic ) Camadas de Guimarota of Guimarota , Portugal .
Hibana is a spider genus that is found from the United States to Brazil , including the West Indies .
Angraecum distichum is a species of comet orchid that is found across sub - Saharan and tropical Africa .
Ecsenius schroederi , known commonly as the Schroeder 's combtooth - blenny in Indonesia , is a species of combtooth blenny in the genus Ecsenius .
Texella reddelli , the Bee Creek cave harvestman , is a rare species of troglobitic harvestman that was added to the United States endangered species list in 1988 , at the same time as six other species native to the karst ecosystem in Travis County and Williamson County , Texas , USA .
Microtus is a genus of voles found in North America , Europe , and northern Asia .
Arnoldichthys spilopterus is a tropical freshwater species found only in a limited number of locations in Nigeria ( Ogun and Niger rivers ) .
Treehoppers ( more precisely typical treehoppers to distinguish them from the Aetalionidae ) and thorn bugs are members of the family Membracidae , a group of insects related to the cicadas and the leafhoppers .
Squamosaperdopsis squamosa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Squamosaperdopsis .
Nothofagus dombeyi ( Dombey 's beech , coigue , coihue or coigüe ( from koywe in Mapuche language ) ) is a tree species native to southern Chile and the Andean parts of Argentine Patagonia .
Goeldiella eques is a species of three - barbeled catfish that occurs in the Guianas and the Amazon basin of Brazil , Peru and Venezuela .
Haliotis glabra , commonly called glistening abalone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Ophrys bertolonii , commonly known as Bertoloni 's Bee Orchid , is a species of orchid native to the western and central Mediterranean ( Spain , France , Corsica , Sardinia , Sicily , mainland Italy , Albania , and Croatia ) .
The Anthicidae are a family of beetles that resemble ants .
Neoeucirrhichthys maydelli , the Goalpara Loach , is a species of loach found in Assam , India , and possibly in Bangladesh .
Perkinsozoa is a proposed phylum in the superphylum Alveolata , which was suggested to account for the genus Perkinsus and other protist species that do not fit into existing Alveolata phyla .
Clanculus clanguloides , common name the secret clanculus , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Periclimenes colemani is a species of saltwater shrimp found in the Indo - Pacific Ocean that was first described in 1975 .
Bishopanthus is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae , containing the single species Bishopanthus soliceps .
Cycladenia humilis is the sole member of the monotypic genus Cycladenia .
Printzina is a genus of green algae in the Phylum Chlorophyta .
Ficus altissima , commonly known as the council tree , is a species of flowering plant , a fig tree in the family Moraceae .
Gerygone , the gerygones or peep - warblers , is a genus of bird in the Acanthizidae family .
Ameiva , commonly called jungle - runners , is a genus of whiptail lizards that belongs to the family Teiidae .
Alosa maeotica , known as the Black Sea shad or Azov shad , is a species of clupeid fish endemic to the Sea of Azov and the western part of the Black Sea basin .
Sapheneutis pulchella is a species of bagworm native to eastern Madagascar .
Neoglyphidodon polyacanthus is a species of damselfish of the family Pomacentridae .
Viola riviniana , the common dog - violet , is a species of the genus Viola native to Eurasia and Africa .
Plagiobothrys greenei is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name Greene 's popcornflower .
Cladiscites is an extinct genus of cephalopods in the ammonoid order Ceratitida .
Callipodida ( from Greek kallos `` beauty '' and podus `` leg '' ) is an order of millipedes containing around 130 species , many characterized by crests or ridges .
Trevoa trinervis is a species of actinorhizal plant within the family Rhamnaceae ; this dicotyledon flora is a shrub or small tree .
Coluber constrictor oaxaca , commonly known as the Mexican racer , is a nonvenomous colubrid snake , a subspecies of the eastern racer ( Coluber constrictor ) .
Automeris godartii , Godart 's Bullseye moth , is a species of moth in the Saturniidae in the subfamily of Hemileucinae .
Carex riparia , the greater pond sedge , is a species of sedge found across Europe and Asia .
Cryptocephalus renatae is a species of cylindrical leaf beetles belonging to the family Chrysomelidae , subfamily Cryptocephalinae .
Puma pardoides or Owen 's panther is an extinct prehistoric cat , long regarded as a primitive species of leopard ( genus Panthera ) .
Mammillaria albiflora is a species of plant in the Cactaceae family .
Palaeobalistum is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish which ranged from the Cretaceous to Eocene periods .
Falcitornoceras was named by House and Price , 1985 , and is the type genus for the subfamily Falcitornoceratinae .
The Balanophoraceae ( from the inflorescence which appears to be covered by barnacles ) are a subtropical to tropical family of obligate parasitic flowering plants , notable for their unusual development and obscure affinities .
Andropogon gayanus ( gamba grass , Rhodesian bluegrass , tambuki grass ) is a species of grass native to most of the tropical and sub - tropical savannas of Africa .
Conus adamsonii , common name the rhododendron cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The Oregon slender salamander ( Batrachoseps wrighti ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae from the Northwestern United States .
Salix libani ( Lebanese willow , صفصاف لبناني ) is a species of willow native to the east of the Mediterranean Basin .
Inape arcuata is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family which is endemic to Peru .
Cipangocharax kiuchii is a species of small tropical land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Cyclophoridae .
Oenothera speciosa is a species of evening primrose known by several common names , including pinkladies , pink evening primrose , showy evening primrose , Mexican primrose , and amapola .
The genus has a single species , Bharattherium bonapartei .
Mussardia griseoplagiata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mussardia .
Cerithiopsis minima is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Cerithiopsidae , which is known from the Atlantic and Pacific Ocean .
Solemya parkinsonii is a species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Solemyidae , the awning clams .
Formica uralensis is a species of ant in the genus Formica .
Uraloclymenia is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod genus from the Late Devonian , Famennian stage .
Microlophus duncanensis , the Pinzón lava lizard , is a species of lava lizard endemic to the Galapagos Island of Pinzón .
Ascandra corallicola is a species of the genus Ascandra .
Acanthoceratoidea , formerly Acanthocerataceae , is a superfamily of Upper Cretaceous ammonoid cephalopods belonging to the order Ammonitida , and comprising some 10 or so families .
Miliolidae is a family in the superfamily Miliolacea of miliolid foraminifera .
Hadra wilsoni is a species of air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Camaenidae .
Maxillaria uncata , the Hook - shaped Maxillaria , is a species of orchid ranging from southern Mexico to southern Brazil .

Waltheria indica is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family , Malvaceae , that has a pantropical distribution .

Stanhopea shuttleworthii is a species of orchid endemic to Colombia ( Tolima ) .
Allium rude is a Chinese species of wild onion native to Gansu , Qinghai , Sichuan , and Tibet , at elevations of 2700 - -5000 m. Allium rude produces one egg - shaped bulb up to 15 mm in diameter .
Gnaphosa mongolica is a ground spider species found from Turkey , Hungary to China .
Spinacanthidae is an extinct prehistoric family of tetraodontid bony fish that lived from the Lutetian epoch of Eocene Monte Bolca .
Mesembryanthemum ( meaning `` midday flowering '' ) is a genus of flowering plants native to southern Africa .

Pandanaris convexa is an extinct cowbird genus described in 1947 by Alden H. Miller .
Chyrsactinia is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family , Asteraceae , native to Mexico and the southwestern United States .
Nessia sarasinorum , commonly known as Sarasins ' snake skink or Müller 's nessia , is a species of skink , which is endemic to the island of Sri Lanka .

Apterygocampus epinnulatus is a species of pipefish native to the Pacific Ocean where it occurs around the countries of the Philippines , Indonesia and Papua New Guinea .
Vitis bryoniifolia is a prolific and adaptable , polygamo - dioecious species of climbing vine in the grape family native to China , where it is known as ying yu , or hua bei pu tao ( North China grape ) .
Drilidae is a family of beetles known commonly as the false firefly beetles .

Percursaria dawsonii is a species of seaweed from a family of Ulvaceae that can be found in Canada ( British Columbia ) , Mexico , and US states such as California and Washington .

Lixinae is a subfamily of true weevils , included in the Molytinae in many older treatments .

Thrandina is a genus of jumping spiders , with three species found in Ecuador .
