Erigeron abajoensis ( Abajo Fleabane ) is a species of fleabane in the daisy family .
Hedeoma todsenii is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Todsen 's pennyroyal , or Todsen 's false pennyroyal .
Thermanaeromonas toyohensis is a species of bacteria within the family Thermoanaerobacteraceae .
Rhynchorthoceras is a Middle Ordovician genus characterized by a rapidly expanded , weakly annulate orthocone , like the orthoconic section of Ancistroceras , but with only a curved , cyrtoconic apex instead of juvenile whorls .
Cyanea pinnatifida is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name sharktail cyanea .
Centrodoras hasemani is a species of thorny catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Rio Negro basin .
Nebria ganglbaueri is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Albanian province of Koritnik , and in every state of former Yugoslavia , except for Croatia and Slovenia .
The Platycephalidae are a family of marine fish , most commonly referred to as flatheads .
Sphyraena helleri , the Heller 's barracuda , is a schooling species of barracuda in the family Sphyraenidae .
Carex comans is a plant species in the sedge family , Cyperaceae , endemic to New Zealand .
Labrisomus multiporosus , the Porehead blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the eastern Pacific Ocean from Mexico to Peru including the Galapagos Islands .
Chlorokybus is a genus of charophyte containing the sole species Chlorokybus atmophyticus , a soil alga found in alpine areas .
Lilium washingtonianum is a North American plant species in the lily family .
Pyramidella bairdi is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Paratybe snizeki is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paratybe .
Agave chrysantha , the Golden - flowered Century Plant , is a plant species endemic to Arizona .
Batrachus uranoscopus is a species of fish in the Batrachoididae family .
Psammotermes is a genus of termites in the family Rhinotermitidae .
Ayllusuchus is an extinct genus of sebecid mesoeucrocodylian .
Pseudapis oxybeloides is a species of bees in the genus Pseudapis , of the family Halictidae .
The genus Allactaga contains the four and five - toed jerboas of Asia .
Alluaudia ascendens is a species of Alluaudia endemic to Madagascar .
Amanita lesueurii is a fungi species in the Amanita family found in Western Australia .
Zabrus maroccanus is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that is endemic to Morocco , where it can be found in such provinces as Tangier , Rharb , Si Allel , Schou , and Tazi .
Iris danfordiae ( dwarf iris or Danford iris ) is a bulbous perennial , in the species in the genus Iris , it is also in the subgenus of Hermodactyloides and section reticulatae .
Galathea strigosa is a species of squat lobster found in the northeast Atlantic Ocean , from the Nordkapp to the Canary Islands , and in the Mediterranean Sea and Red Sea .
Cnidoscolus urens is a perennial , tropical American stinging herb belonging to the family Euphorbiaceae , and is one of some 100 species belonging to the genus Cnidoscolus ( Gk . knidē - nettle , skōlos - thorn , Latin urens - burning ) .
Nerita plicata is a species of tropical sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Neritidae , the nerites .
Myrmecia esuriens , also known as Tasmanian Inchman , is a species of bulldog ant that is native to Tasmania .
Cynanchum is a genus of about 300 species including some swallowworts , belonging to the family Apocynaceae .
There is only known species , Philesia magellanica , native to southern Chile and southern Argentina .
Euchilichthys boulengeri is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is found in the Lulua River near Kananga .
Astyanax microschemos is a species of characid fish from Brazil .
Platanthera holochila is a rare species of orchid known by the common name Hawaii bog orchid .
Tetracynodon is an extinct genus of therocephalian .
Sideritis , also known as ironwort , mountain tea and shepherd 's tea , is a genus of flowering plants well known for their use as herbal medicine , commonly as an herbal tea .
G. wardi was first described by B.F. Howell in 1945 , and is the only species in the genus Gymnophyllum .
Cladorhiza is a genus of carnivorous sponges , comprising around 40 species found in oceans around the world .
†Placostylus cuniculinsulae was a species of large air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Bothriembryontidae .
Phrynops williamsi , commonly known as William 's toadhead turtle or William 's South American side - necked turtle , is a species of turtle endemic to South America .
Isthmohyla zeteki , or Zetek 's treefrog , is a species of frog in the family Hylidae native to the Cordillera Central and Cordillera de Talamanca of Costa Rica and western Panama at elevations of 1,200 - -1,800 m ( 3,900 - -5,900 ft ) asl .
Paysonia perforata ( syn . Lesquerella perforata ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Spring Creek bladderpod .
Pseudis is a genus of frogs ( swimming frogs ) in the Hylidae family , and are found in the Guianas , Colombia , Venezuela , Trinidad , Brazil , Paraguay , southeastern Peru , eastern Bolivia , northeastern Argentina , and Uruguay .
The Diadocidiidae are a family of flies(Diptera ) .
Selene brevoortii ( the airfin lookdown , hairfin lookdown , Mexican lookdown , or Pacific lookdown ) , is a species of carangid native to the Pacific coast of the Americas where it is found from southernmost Baja California , Mexico to Ecuador .
Haworthia coarctata is a species of flowering succulent plant from the Eastern Cape Province , South Africa and naturalized in Mexico .
Aloe aristata ( Guinea - fowl Aloe , Lace Aloe ) is a species of evergreen flowering perennial plant in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , from Southern Africa .
Acirsa morsei is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Epitoniidae .
Cucurbita argyrosperma , also the Japanese pie pumpkin or pipian , cushaw pumpkin , and silver - seed gourd , is a species of winter squash originally from the south of Mexico .
Fritillaria is a genus of Eurasian , North African , and North American plants in the lily family .
Nine families of largely arboreal birds make up the order Piciformes , the best - known of them being the Picidae , which includes the woodpeckers and close relatives .
Chaceon fenneri , commonly known as the golden crab or golden deepsea crab , is one of several species of crab harvested for food by humans .
Melanophila is a genus of beetles commonly known as fire beetles .
Gyroporus cyanescens , commonly known as the bluing bolete or the cornflower bolete , is a species of bolete fungus in the family Gyroporaceae .
Bathytoma viabrunnea , common name the brown - banded turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Borsoniidae .
Myrsine africana ( also called Cape myrtle , African boxwood or thakisa ) is a species of shrub in the Primulaceae family .
Opeas pumilum , common name dwarf awlsnail , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Subulinidae .
Florenciellales is an order of Dictyochophyceae .
Chroogomphus rutilus , commonly known as the brown slimecap or the copper spike , is a species of fungus in the Gomphidiaceae family .
Porcellio ovalis is a species of woodlouse in the genus Porcellio belonging to the family Porcellionidae that can be found on Canary Islands .
Limnotilapia dardennii is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it prefers rocky areas near the coast .
Coula is a genus of one to three species of trees native to tropical Africa .
Ebola virus is the single member of the species Zaire ebolavirus , which is the type species for the genus Ebolavirus , family Filoviridae , order Mononegavirales .
Ranitomeya vanzolinii , also known as the Brazilian poison frog or spotted poison frog , is a species of frog from the Dendrobatidae family .
The Savi 's warbler ( Locustella luscinioides ) is a species of Old World warbler in the grass warbler genus Locustella .
Anomochilus weberi , Weber 's pipe snake or Sumatran giant blind snake , is a species of snake in the Anomochilidae family from Indonesia .
Calathus korax is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that is endemic to Greece .
Longirostromeryx is an extinct genus of saber - toothed deer .
Myrmica myrmicoxena is a species of ant that can be found in France and Spain .
Trevoa is a genus of actinorhizal plants ; these dicotyledon flora are trees or small shrubs .
Metasequoia glyptostroboides , the dawn redwood , is a fast - growing , endangered coniferous tree , the sole living species of the genus Metasequoia , one of three species in the subfamily Sequoioideae .
Crocus ( English plural : crocuses or croci ) is a genus of flowering plants in the iris family comprising 90 species of perennials growing from corms .
Haplocyonoides is an extinct genus of terrestrial carnivores belonging to the suborder Caniformia , family Amphicyonidae ( `` bear dog '' ) , and which inhabited Europe from the Early Miocene subepoch ( 20 Mya)--(16.9 Mya ) .
Epitophysis substriata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Epitophysis .
Kerriidae is a family of scale insects , commonly known as lac insects or lac scales .
Poa macrantha is a species of grass known by the common names seashore bluegrass and large - flowered sand dune bluegrass .
Campodea is a genus of small , white , bristle - tailed arthropods in the order Diplura .
Paraplagusia is a genus of tonguefish .
Quercus mongolica , commonly known as Mongolian oak , is a species of oak native to Japan , southern Kuriles , Sakhalin , Manchuria , central and northern China , Korea , eastern Mongolia , and eastern Siberia .
Illicium peninsulare is a species of plant in the family Schisandraceae .
The Solanales are an order of flowering plants , included in the asterid group of dicotyledons .
Melodichthys hadrocephalus is a species of viviparous brotula found in the northeastern Atlantic Ocean off the coast of France .
Malawania is an extinct genus of basal thunnosaur ichthyosaur known from the middle Early Cretaceous ( Hauterivian or Barremian stage ) of Iraq .
Clinus heterodon , the Westcoast klipfish , is a species of clinid that occurs in subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean from Namibia to South Africa where it is a denizen of tide pools .
Hymenoxys rusbyi is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Rusby 's rubberweed or Rusby 's bitterweed .
Cinnamodendron angustifolium is a species of flowering plant in the Canellaceae family .
Amsinckia eastwoodiae is a species of fiddleneck known by the common name Eastwood 's fiddleneck .
Platycryptus undatus , also called tan jumping spider , is a species of jumping spider .
More recent analysis of these fossils , and others , suggests that the New Zealand swan was a subspecies of the black swan , and it is referred to this way in ornithology today .
Dysopsis is a genus of plants in the family Euphorbiaceae , first described in 1858 .
Paraploactis is a genus of velvetfishes native to the Indo - Pacific .
Polposipus herculeanus , the Frégate Island giant tenebrionid beetle or Frégate beetle , is a flightless species of beetle in family Tenebrionidae .
Ancylopsetta is a genus of large - tooth flounders mostly found along the Atlantic coast of the Americas with one species found along the Pacific coast .
The Iolaini are a tribe of butterflies in the family Lycaenidae .
Auxa armata is a species of longhorn beetle in the subfamily Lamiinae .
Ctenodactylus is a genus of rodent in the family Ctenodactylidae .
Parateuthis tunicata , the only known member of the genus Parateuthis , is the scientific name currently given to a species of squid based on a single specimen .
Bothrops insularis , commonly known as the golden lancehead , is a venomous pitviper species endemic to Ilha da Queimada Grande , off the coast of São Paulo state , in Brazil .
Eucalyptus argutifolia , commonly known as Wabling Hill mallee , is a species of Eucalyptus which is endemic to Western Australia .
Rock oysters are true oysters of the genus Saccostrea .
Hylomantis lemur is a species of frog in the Hylidae family that is found in Colombia , Costa Rica , and Panama .
The Hydropsychidae are a family - level taxon consisting of net - spinning caddisflies .
Accinctapubes albifasciata is a species of snout moth in the genus Accinctapubes .
It contains only one species , Fansipaniana fansipana , which is found in Vietnam .
Callipogon barbatus is a species of flat - faced longhorns beetle belonging to the Cerambycidae family , Prioninae subfamily .
Cornularia is a genus of soft corals in the suborder Stolonifera .
Tiarajudens ( `` Tiaraju tooth '' ) is an extinct genus of saber - toothed herbivorous anomodont which lived during the middle Permian period ( Capitanian stage ) in what is now Rio Grande do Sul , Brazil .
Campylocephalus is a genus of prehistoric eurypterid of the Family Hibbertopteridae .
Euphorbia setiloba is a species of euphorb known by the common name Yuma sandmat .
Congolacerta is a genus of equatorial African lacertids of the family Lacertidae .
Monkonosaurus ( meaning `` Monkon lizard '' ) is a dubious genus of herbivorous stegosaurian dinosaur from the Late Jurassic ( Kimmeridgian stage , around 150 - 155 million years ago ) of Tibet .
Combretum apiculatum is a species of tree in the family Combretaceae known by the common name red bushwillow .
Gypsophila petraea is a species of the genus Gypsophila in the plant family Caryophyllaceae .
It contains only one known species , Miersiella umbellata , native to South America ( Brazil , French Guiana , Suriname , Guyana , Venezuela , Colombia , Peru ) .
Chrysopidia elegans is a green lacewing species in the genus Chrysopidia found in China and Nepal .
Pitavia punctata is a species of tree endemic to Chile in the Rutaceae family .
Lubomirskiidae is a family of freshwater sponges from Lake Baikal in Russia .
Juniperus maritima is a species of juniper known by the common name seaside juniper .
Cortinarius is a genus of mushrooms .
Centaurium erythraea is a species of flowering plant in the gentian family known by the common names common centaury and European centaury .
It contains the single species Holochrea xanthogramma , which is found in Sangir .
Two - toed Snake Skink , Nessia didactyla , also known as Two - toed nessia , is a species of skink endemic to island of Sri Lanka .
Zakerana rufescens ( common names : Malabar wart frog , reddish burrowing frog , or rufescent burrowing frog ) is a species of frog that is endemic to the Western Ghats , India .
Jiaodontus is an extinct genus of lonchidiid cartilaginous fish which existed in Liuhuanggou , Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region , northwestern China , during the late Jurassic ( Oxfordian age ) .
Hemisphaeriodon is a genus of lizards containing only one species , Hemisphaeriodon gerrardii , the pink - tongued skink .
The Dipseudopsidae are a family of certain caddisflies .
Salmophasia sladoni is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Salmophasia .
Aleurodiscus grantii is a species of fungus in the family Stereaceae .
Rhodoferax is a genus of Betaproteobacteria belonging to the purple nonsulfur bacteria , a polyphyletic group of phototrophic bacteria .
Oreonectes is a genus of stone loach native to Asia .
Placodus ( meaning ' flat tooth ' ) was a genus of marine reptiles , belonging to the order Placodontia , which swam in the shallow seas of the middle Triassic period ( c. 240 million years ago ) .
Morchella frustrata is a later synonym of Morchella tridentina , a species originally described by Giacomo Bresadola from north Italy in 1898 .
Olgaea is a genus of Asian flowering plants in the thistle tribe within the sunflower family , having a typical thistle appearance .
Junodia lameyi is a species of praying mantis found in Angola , Côte d'Ivoire , Ghana , Guinea , Cameroon and the Congo River region .
The Valdivian lizard , Liolaemus cyanogaster , is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Osmunda wehrii is an extinct species of fern in the modern Osmundaceae family genus Osmunda .
Oulactis muscosa , also known as the sand anemone and speckled anemone , is a species of sea anemone in the family Actiniidae .
Placida dendritica is a species of minute sea slug , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Limapontiidae .
Ilex chapaensis is a species of holly native to China .
Tenthredo zonula , a Common Sawfly , is a species belonging to the family Tenthredinidae subfamily Tenthrediniinae .
Hordeum arizonicum is a species of wild barley known by the common name Arizona barley .
Begonia elaeagnifolia is a plant species in the Begoniaceae family , endemic in Africa from Cameroon to the Congo .
The Orinoco agouti ( Dasyprocta guamara ) is a species of rodent in the family Dasyproctidae .
The Chaoboridae , commonly known as phantom midges , are a family of fairly common midges with a cosmopolitan distribution .
Nothochelone is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the plantain family containing the single species Nothochelone nemorosa , which is known by the common name woodland beardtongue .
Charaxes pleione is a member of the species group Charaxes paphianus .
Masdevallia wendlandiana is a species of orchid native to the tropical South America .

Sagina decumbens is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names trailing pearlwort and western pearlwort .

Rhyssostelma is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1844 .
Sarcophrynium villosum is a species of plant in the Marantaceae family .
The Mindanao blue fantail ( Rhipidura superciliaris ) is a species of bird in the Rhipiduridae family .
Hemigrapsus estellinensis is an extinct species of crab , formerly endemic to the Texas Panhandle .
Lysmata debelius is a species of cleaner shrimp indigenous to the Indo - Pacific .
Temnocidaris is an extinct genus of echinoid that lived from the Late Cretaceous to the Paleocene .

Jaregoceras is a nautiloid genus from the Upper Devonian discosorid that probably belongs to the family Discosoridae .
Montagnea arenaria is a species of secotioid fungus in the Agaricaceae family .
Ageratina occidentalis is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name western snakeroot or western eupatorium .
Lufengia is a genus of tritylodont therapsid from the Sinemurian ( Early Jurassic ) of Yunnan , China .
Psathyrotes annua is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name annual psathyrotes .
Asperoteuthis acanthoderma is a large species of squid belonging to the family Chiroteuthidae .
Siparuna guajalitensis is a species of plant in the Siparunaceae family .
Stenolemus alikakay is a species of assassin bug , found in Taiwan .
Spilostethus is a genus in the insect family Lygaeidae ( seed bugs ) .
Acer saccharinum , commonly known as silver maple , creek maple , silverleaf maple , soft maple , water maple , swamp maple , or white maple -- is a species of maple native to eastern and central North America in the eastern United States and Canada .
Andreaea is a genus of rock mosses described as a genus in 1801 .
Aplysina archeri ( also known as stove - pipe sponge because of its shape ) is a species of tube sponge that has long tube - like structures of cylindrical shape .
Mimulopsis solmsii is a flowering plant from the family Acanthaceae and is the type species for the genus Mimulopsis .
Brachodidae is a family of day - flying moths , commonly known as little bear moths , which contains about 135 species distributed around much of the world ( Edwards et al . 1999 ) .
Psittaculirostris is a genus of parrot in the Psittaculidae family found in Indonesia and Papua New Guinea .
The African brush - tailed porcupine ( Atherurus africanus ) is a species of rat - like Old World porcupine , indigenous to a broad belt of Africa ranging from Guinea on the west coast to Kenya on the east .
Maytenus cunninghamii is a species of shrub endemic to Australia .
Xylanthemum is a genus of Asian plants in the daisy family .
Phreatodrobia is a genus of very small or minute freshwater snails with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Lithoglyphidae .
Rhododendron beyerinckianum is a rhododendron species native to Indonesia and western Papua New Guinea , extending as far east as Mount Victoria and Mount Dayman , where it grows at altitudes of 1400 - 4000 meters .
Turbonilla interrupta , common name the interrupted turbonille , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Right whales are three species of large baleen whales of the genus Eubalaena : the North Atlantic right whale ( E. glacialis ) , the North Pacific right whale ( E. japonica ) and the southern right whale ( E. australis ) .
Adelpha eulalia , commonly known as Arizona Sister , is a species of butterfly in the family Nymphalidae .
Tetracoccus ilicifolius is a rare species of flowering shrub in the family Picrodendraceae known by the common names hollybush and holly - leaved tetracoccus .
Sclerochloa dura is a species of grass known by the common names common hardgrass and fairground grass .
Plagiotremus spilistius is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Pacific ocean .
Dipodium squamatum is a mycoheterotrophicorchid species of the tribe Cymbidieae .
Agathis endertii is a species of conifer tree , in the Araucariaceae family .
Hedypnois rhagadioloides , the Cretanweed or scaly hawkbit , is a species of plants in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Monascella botryosa .
Eulipotyphla ( `` truly fat and blind '' ) is an order of mammals suggested by molecular methods of phylogenetic reconstruction , and includes the laurasiatherian members of the now - invalid polyphyletic order Lipotyphla , but not the afrotherian members ( tenrecs and golden moles , now in their own order Afrosoricida ) .
Avicularia metallica ( whitetoe tarantula ) is a relatively docile species of tarantulas . Avicularia metallica is considered by some to be a communal species .
Prunus americana , commonly called the American plum , wild plum , or Marshall 's large yellow sweet plum , is a species of Prunus native to North America from Saskatchewan and Idaho south to New Mexico and east to Québec , Maine and Florida .
Ardeosaurus is an extinct genus of basal lizards , known from fossils found in the Late Jurassic Solnhofen Plattenkalk of Bavaria , southern Germany .
Triops is a genus of small crustaceans in the order Notostraca ( tadpole shrimp ) .
Hapalorchis is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae , native to Central America , South America , and the West Indies .
Lampropeltis triangulum sinaloae , commonly known as the Sinaloan milk snake , is an egg laying subspecies of nonvenomous colubrid snake .
Stegastes acapulcoensis , commonly called the Acapulco major , the Acapulco damselfish , or the Acapulco gregory , is a species of damselfish of the family Pomacentridae .
Antygomonas is a genus of marine invertebrates known as mud dragons .
Cothurus bordoni is a species of beetle in the Cothurus genus .

Lasthenia californica is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name California goldfields .

Pepemkay is an extinct genus of lissoberycine trachichthyid fish known from the Late Cretaceous Sierra Madre Formation ( Cenomanian stage ) of Chiapas State , southern Mexico .
Acantholycosa azyuzini is a species of wolf spider only known from the Altai Mountains .
The Zygnematales ( Greek : ζυγός ( zygos ) + νήμα ( nēma ) ( nom . ) , νήματος ( nēmatos ) ( gen . ) ) , also called the Conjugales , are an order of green algae , comprising several thousand different species in genera such as the well - known Zygnema and Spirogyra .
Cheiridopsis denticulata is a species in the Cheiridopsis genus that consists of 100 flowering succulent perennial plants , native to semi - arid regions of Namibia and southern Africa .

Sclerolobium is a genus of 40 species of flowering plants in the Leguminosae .
Aulacopone is a genus of ant in the subfamily Heteroponerinae containing the single species Aulacopone relicta .
Fleischmannia sonorae , the Sonoran slender - thoroughwort or Sonoran thoroughwort , is a North American species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Sparganium angustifolium is a species of flowering plant in the cat - tail family known by the common names floating bur - reed and narrowleaf bur - reed .
Cibotium cumingii is a species of tree fern , of the genus Cibotium .
The Anatidae are the biological family of birds that includes ducks , geese and swans .
Grammatotria lemairii is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika in East Africa where it prefers areas with sandy substrates .
The Sula hanging parrot ( Loriculus sclateri ) is a small species of parrot in the Psittaculidae family .
Scutellastra laticostata is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Patellidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Gryposuchinae is an extinct subfamily of gavialid crocodylians .

Liometopum eremicum is an extinct species of Miocene ant in the genus Liometopum .

The Shokihaze goby ( Tridentiger barbatus ) is a species of goby native to marine and brackish waters along the coasts of eastern Asia .
Oxynoemacheilus ceyhanensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Oxynoemacheilus .
Sesuvium is a genus of flowering plants in the ice plant family , Aizoaceae .
Arctosa similis is a wolf spider species in the genus Arctosa found in Canary Islands , Morocco , Portugal to Croatia .
Aplectana is a genus of nematodes .
Corydoras panda is a species of catfish belonging to the genus Corydoras , of the family Callichthyidae , and is a native member of the riverine fauna of South America .
Euzopherodes vapidella , the yam moth or citrus stub moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Euzopherodes .
Gastrotheca rebeccae ( common name : Rebecca 's marsupial frog ) is a species of frog in the Hemiphractidae family .
Ramphotyphlops acuticaudus , or the Palau blind snake , is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Halolimnohelix conradti is a species of air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Halolimnohelicidae .
Astylosternus occidentalis is a species of frog in the family Arthroleptidae .
Iris laevigata , known as Japanese iris , rabbit - ear iris or kakitsubata , is a Japanese species of iris related to other members of Iris subgenus Limniris , including other species of Japanese irises .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Uropolystigma atrotestaceum .
Bdellocephala is a genus of freshwater triclad that inhabits different regions of Eurasia .
Leucopogon fasciculatus ( also known as tall mingimingi ) is a species of shrub within the heath family .
Acantholycosa oligerae is a species of wolf spider only known from Primorsky Krai , Russia .
Symphurus thermophilus is a species of tonguefish notable for being the only flatfish known to be an obligate inhabitant of hydrothermal vents .
Neotinea is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Ameerega berohoka is a species of poison dart frog that is endemic to Goiás and Mato Grosso in Brazil .
The Ulidiidae ( formerly Otitidae ) are a large and diverse cosmopolitan family of flies ( Diptera ) , and as in related families , most species are herbivorous or saprophagous .
Acromyrmex aspersus is a species of New World ants of the subfamily Myrmicinae found in the wild naturally in southern Brazil and Peru .
Audeoudia haltica is a species of snout moth in the genus Audeoudia .
Opisthorchiidae is a family of digenean parasitic flatworms .
Calocoris nemoralis is a species of true bugs belonging to the family Miridae or jumping tree bugs , subfamily Mirinae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Trichangium vinosum .
Limonium strictissimum is a species of plant in the Plumbaginaceae family .
Aggregata is a genus of parasitic protozoa belonging to the phylum Apicomplexa .
Tilemsisuchus is an extinct genus of dyrosaurid crocodyliform which existed in what is now Mali during the Eocene period .
Ranularia sarcostoma , common name : the flesh - coloured hairy triton , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ranellidae , the triton snails , triton shells or tritons .
Jatropha macrantha , also called the Huanarpo Macho or more recently Peruvian Viagra , is a medium size shrubby tree species in the genus Jatropha with orange red flowers .
Laurasiatheria is a superorder of placental mammals believed to have originated on the northern supercontinent of Laurasia .
Scutellaria bolanderi is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Sierra skullcap .
The tarantula spider Acanthoscurria brocklehursti , was a species described by F. O. Pickard - Cambridge ( 1896 ) .
Procecidochares atra is a species of fruit flies in the genus Procecidochares of the family Tephritidae .
Eriogonum niveum is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name snow buckwheat .
Records of Brachodes fallax from the European part of Russia as well as the eastern Palearctic ecozone were identified as a distinct species ( Brachodes staudingeri ) in 1998 .
Alluaudia insignis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Alluaudia .
Doto pita is a species of sea slug , a small nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusc in the family Dotidae .
Cleome lutea is a species of cleome known by the common names yellow bee plant and yellow spiderflower .
Cyclopsitta is a genus of parrot in the Psittaculidae family .
The species Phormia regina , more commonly known as the black blow fly , belongs to the blow fly family Calliphoridae .
Atelopus laetissimus is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae endemic to Colombia and only known from the vicinity of its type locality in the Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta .
Telorchis is a genus of trematode parasites found in many herps , comprising around 70 species .
Eithea is a plant genus in the Amaryllis family , endemic to southern Brazil .
Pachydactylus austeni , commonly known as Austen 's thick - toed gecko , is a species of small thick - toed gecko that is indigenous to the western coast of South Africa .
Prosartes parvifolia ( Siskiyou bells ) is a rare plant species endemic to a small region in the Siskiyou Mountains of the United States .
Melithaea ochracea is a species of colonial soft coral in the family Melithaeidae , commonly known as knotted fan coral .
Tragelaphus is a genus of medium- to large - sized spiral - horned antelopes .
The genus Hieraaetus , sometimes known as hawk - eagles , denotes a group of smallish eagles usually placed in the Buteoninae or Aquilinae subfamilies of accipitrids .
Liatris chapmanii , also known as Chapman 's blazing star or Chapman 's gayfeather , is a plant species in the aster family Asteraceae and genus Liatris .
Longitarsus gracilis is a species of beetle in the subfamily Galerucinae that can be found in Asian counties like Turkey and Israel , and also in African ones such as Algeria and Morocco .
Pyrgomantis jonesi , common name Jones ' Mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Burkina Faso , Ghana , Cameroon , Nigeria , Niger , and Senegal .
Rhododendron leptothrium ( 薄叶马银花 ) is a rhododendron species native to Myanmar and southwestern Sichuan , southeastern Xizang , and western Yunnan , China , where it grows at altitudes of 1700 - -3200 meters .
Petrotilapia genalutea is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it inhabits areas with rocky substrates from which it grazes algae . This species can reach a length 13.1 centimetres ( 5.2 in ) SL .
Neopempelia hieroglyphella is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Neopempelia .
Sidalcea covillei is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common names Owens Valley sidalcea , and Owens Valley checkerbloom .
Prostacheoceras is genus of ammonoid cephalopod belonging to the Vidrioceratidae family .
Pisaster is a genus of Pacific sea stars that includes three species , P. brevispinus , P. giganteus , and P. ochraceus .
Pseudoliotia henjamensis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tornidae .
The Antillean scallop , Bractechlamys antillarum , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae .
Nephropides caribaeus is a species of lobster , the only species in the genus Nephropides .
Nephrotoma crocata is a species of cranefly found in most of Europe and northern Russia .
Isocoma felgeri is a rare Mexican plant species in the sunflower family .
Cephalastor is a small neotropical genus of potter wasps ( Hymenoptera : Vespidae : Eumeninae ) currently containing 14 species .
Cantherhines pullus is a species of filefish described by Ranzani in 1842 .
Notoplax cuneata is a rare species of chiton in the family Acanthochitonidae .
Heteropappus is a genus of Asian flowering plants in the daisy family .
Echinopsis spachiana , commonly known as the golden torch , ( white ) torch cactus or golden column , is a species of cactus native to South America .
Juniperus standleyi is a species of juniper native to Guatemala and the adjacent extreme southeast of Mexico ( Volcán Tacaná in Chiapas ) , where it occurs at high altitudes of 3,000 - -4,250 m. Its local common names include huitó , cipres , and huitum .
Anatrytone is a genus of skippers in the family Hesperiidae widespread New World .
Pelophryne misera , the black flathead toad or Kinabalu dwarf toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Arnoldius flavus is a species of ant apart of the Arnoldius genus , which is only one of the three species described in it .
Phlyctibasidium is a fungal genus of uncertain taxonomic placement in the Agaricomycetes .
Crepis incana ( pink dandelion ) is a species of flowering plant in the genus Crepis of the sunflower family , native to southern Greece .
Toxicoscordion nuttallii ( Nuttall 's death camas , death camas , poison camas , poison sego ) is a species of poisonous plant native to the south - central part of the United States ( Arkansas , Oklahoma , Tennessee , Missouri , Louisiana , Mississippi , Kansas , and Texas ) .
Baculitidae is a family of extinct ammonoid cephalopods that lived mostly during the Late Cretaceous , and often included in the suborder Ancyloceratina .
Kurixalus odontotarsus ( serrate - legged small treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Clupeoides is a genus of sprats that occur in rivers in Southeast Asia .
Pilocarpus microphyllus , the Maranham Jaborandi , is a plant species in the genus Pilocarpus found native to several states in northern Brazil .
Hyaenodontidae ( `` Hyena teeth '' ) is a family of the extinct predatory mammals .
Zakerana is a genus of frogs in the Dicroglossidae family from southern Asia ( Sri Lanka , the Indian subcontinent including Pakistan , Nepal , and Bangladesh ) , and Nepal and Bhutan .
Peristeria pendula is a species of orchid occurring from Trinidad to Central America and tropical South America .

Halitherium is the type genus of the subfamily Halitheriinae , which includes the well - known genera Eosiren and Eotheroides and lived from the Eocene to the Pliocene .
Weigeltisauridae is a family of gliding neodiapsid reptiles that lived during the Permian period .
Orthotylus intricatus is a species of bug in the Miridae family that is endemic to North Aegean islands .
Parapholis incurva is a species of grass native to Europe , Asia and northern Africa , and widely naturalised elsewhere .
Acropora striata is a species of acroporid coral found in the southwest Indian Ocean , the central Indo - Pacific , Japan and the East China Sea .
Oliva flammulata , common name the flame olive , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
Squalomorphii is a superorder of cartilaginous fishes , generally characterized by lacking traits such as an anal fin , nictitating membrane , or suborbital shelves in the cranium .
Akysis recavus is a species of fish in the family Akysidae , the stream catfishes .
Parosphromenus harveyi is a species of gourami endemic to Malaysia , where it is only known from Selangor .
Inape reductana is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family and is endemic to Peru .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Merulicium fusisporum .
Nephrurus is a genus of nine species of gecko , commonly known as knob - tailed geckos .
Tetraparvovirus are a genus of viruses in the family Parvoviridae .
Pleurobranchus mamillatus is a species of sidegill slug , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Pleurobranchidae .
Euthlastus is an extinct genus of Late Jurassic ( Kimmeridgian - Tithonian ) mammal from the Morrison Formation .
Hunteria ghanensis is a species of small to medium tree of the Apocynaceae family .
Cormocephalus aurantiipes is a common species of centipede found throughout Australia , often confused with Cormocephalus westwoodi .
Carabus parreyssi plassensis is a subspecies of beetle from Carabidae family , that can is endemic to Bosnia and Herzegovina .
Calliostoma simulans is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family One of its family 's common names is the New Zealand Mollusks .
Aegilops triuncialis , or barbed goatgrass , is a winter annual grass species of the Poaceae family .
Comarum is a genus of plants formerly included with the genus Potentilla ( `` typical cinquefoils '' ) .
Elassodiscus is a genus of snailfishes native to the Pacific Ocean .
Megalovalvata baicalensis is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Valvatidae , the valve snails .
Penstemon navajoa is a rare species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name Navajo Mountain beardtongue , or Navajo beardtongue .
Solidago bicolor , with several common names including white goldenrod , silverrod and ( in Québec ) verge d’or bicolore , is a plant species native to much of eastern North America .
Coelastrea aspera is a species of stony coral in the family Merulinidae .
Hupehsuchus is an extinct genus of small marine reptile , about 1 meter ( 3 ft ) long .

Dalbergia lanceolaria is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family native to India , Sri Lanka , Nepal , and Burma .

In Paramecium aurelia , a cryptic species complex was discovered by observation .
Ceanothus foliosus is a species of flowering shrub known by the common name Wavyleaf ceanothus .

Acer tutcheri ( Tutcher 's Maple ) is a species of deciduous maple tree native to the Fujian , Guangdong , Guangxi , south Hunan , south Jiangxi , Taiwan and south Zhejiang provinces of southern China including certain districts of Hong Kong .
Figitidae is a family of parasitoid wasps .
Magnolia vrieseana is a tree species of Magnoliaceae family endemic to Indonesia , occurring in Sulawesi and Maluku .

Turricula javana , common name the Java turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clavatulidae .
Angelica dahurica is a wildly grown species of angelica native to Siberia , Russia Far East , Mongolia , Northeastern China , Japan , Korea , and Taiwan .
Ommatoiulus moreleti ( spelt moreletii in older publications ) , commonly known as the Portuguese millipede , is a herbivorous millipede native to the southern Iberian Peninsula where it shares its range with other Ommatoiulus species .
Apatelodidae , the American silkworm moths , is a family of insects in the order Lepidoptera .
Greniodon is a genus of extinct gondwanatherian mammal known from the early - middle Eocene ( Lutetian age ) of Argentina .
Aquilegia nuragica or Aquilegia di Gorropu , commonly called Nuragica Columbine , is a species of plant in the Ranunculaceae family .

Rorippa barbareifolia , the hoary yellowcress , is a plant species reported from Manchuria , Inner Mongolia , Mongolia , Siberia , Alaska , Yukon and Saskatchewan .
The Syrian wild ass ( Equus hemionus hemippus ) , less commonly known as a hemippe , is an extinct subspecies of onager native to the Arabian peninsula .
Melanophidium bilineatum , commonly known as the two - lined black shieldtail or iridescent shieldtail , is a species of snake endemic to India .
Poa palustris ( fowl bluegrass , fowl meadowgrass , swamp meadowgrass , woodland bluegrass ) is a species of grass native to Asia , Europe and Northern America .

It contains only one species , Afghanotinea klapperichi , which is found in Afghanistan .
Trifolium stoloniferum , the running buffalo clover , is an endangered species of perennial clover native to the eastern and midwestern United States .
Pseudochirulus , also known as the ringtail possum , is a genus of marsupial in the family Pseudocheiridae native to Indonesia , Papua New Guinea and Queensland , Australia .
Loxonematidae is an extinct taxonomic family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs .
Ecsenius aequalis , known commonly as the Fourline blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean .
Microcharacidium is a genus of South American darters .
Phoebanthus , called the false sunflower , is a genus of North American plants in the sunflower tribe within the daisy family .
Rumuara fasciatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Rumuara .
Calandrinia galapagosa is a species of plant in the Portulacaceae family .
Calyptranthes thomasiana ( Thomas ' Lidflower ) is a rare species of plant in the Myrtaceae family .
It was described by Pribyl and Vanek in 1985 , and the type species is Demeterops loella , which was originally described as a dubious species in the genus Pilekia by Demeter , in 1973 .
Perkinsea is a class of alveolates .
Ratibida pinnata is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names pinnate prairie coneflower , gray - head coneflower , yellow coneflower , and prairie coneflower .

Parahollardia is a genus of spikefishes native to the western Atlantic Ocean .
Romanzoffia is a genus of flowering plants in the waterleaf family known as mistmaids or mistmaidens .
Carex heteroneura is a species of sedge known by the common name different - nerve sedge .
Cheiracanthium macedonicum is a spider species found in Bulgaria and Macedonia .
Plectania nannfeldtii , commonly known as Nannfeldt 's Plectania , the black felt cup , or the black snowbank cup fungus , is a species of fungus in the family Sarcosomataceae .
The infraorder Astacidea comprises five extant superfamilies , two of crayfish ( Astacoidea and Parastacoidea ) , one of true lobsters ( Nephropoidea ) , one of reef lobsters ( the genus Enoplometopus ) , and a number of fossil taxa .
Pemphigostola synemonistis is a species of moth in the genus Pemphigostola .
The gafftopsail pompano , ( Trachinotus rhodopus ) is a species of jack in the family Carangidae .
Brachinus bellicosus is a species of ground beetle in the Brachininae subfamily that can be found in France , Portugal , and Spain .
Asphodeline is a genus of perennial plants in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , first described as a genus in 1830 .
Amanita albocreata , also called the ringless panther , is a species of fungus in the Amanitaceae family .
Acourtia thurberi , common name Thurber 's desertpeony , is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Fadenia is an extinct genus of eugeneodontid holocephalid from the Permian of Greenland .
Pseudozelota is a genus of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , containing the following species : subgenus Hefferniella Pseudozelota mima ( Breuning , 1938 ) Pseudozelota punctipennis ( Schwarzer , 1930 ) subgenus Pseudozelota Pseudozelota capito ( Pascoe , 1865 )
Batillariidae , common name batillariids or mudcreepers , are a family of marine , cerithioidean gastropod molluscs in the clade Sorbeoconcha .
Cirsium mexicanum is a Mesoamerican and Caribbean species of plants in the thistle tribe within the sunflower family .
Penicillium brunneum is an anamorph fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated in imported rice an produces rugulosin a substance which is hepatocarcinogenic to mice and rats .
Nerodia clarkii , commonly known as the salt marsh snake , is a species of semiaquatic , nonvenomous , colubrid snake found in the southeastern United States , in the brackish salt marshes along the Gulf of Mexico from Florida to Texas , with a population in northern Cuba .
Amaryllididae is a family of marine benthic amphipods found throughout the southern hemisphere .
The superfamily Apoidea is a major group within the Hymenoptera , which includes two traditionally recognized lineages , the `` sphecoid '' wasps , and the bees .
Spiraeanthus is a monotypic genus of shrub in the rose family containing the single species Spiraeanthus schrenkianus .
Thiorhodospira sibirica is a species of alkaliphilic purple sulfur bacterium .
Halomonas titanicae is a gram - negative , halophilic species of proteobacteria which was discovered on rusticles recovered from the wreck of the RMS Titanic .
Mimacanthocinus tonkinensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimacanthocinus .
Notoseris is a genus of Asian flowering plants in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Nitrophila is a small genus of flowering plants in the amaranth family sometimes known by the common name niterworts .
Lockhartia imbricata is a species of orchid found from Trinidad to tropical South America It is an epiphytic species growing in humid forests .
Amauropelma is a spider genus that is endemic to Queensland , Australia .
Dugesia afromontana is a species of dugesiid triclad found in the Amatola Mountains , Eastern Cape , South Africa .
Xyris baldwiniana , Baldwin 's yelloweyed grass , is a North American species of flowering plant in the yellow - eyed - grass family .
Melaleuca pomphostoma was first formally described in 1992 by Bryan Barlow in Nuytsia as a new species .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Crustospathula cartilaginea .

It consists of one species , Abeliophyllum distichum Nakai , endemic to Korea , where it is endangered in the wild , occurring at only seven sites .
Ptinus is a genus of beetles distributed throughout much of the world , including Africa , the Australian region , the Palearctic , the Near East , the Nearctic , and the Neotropic ecozone .
Tetanops parallelus is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Tetanops of the family Tephritidae .

Liarea ornata is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial gastropod mollusc in the family Pupinidae .

Bathymophila asphala is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Solariellidae .
Vanda testacea is a species of orchid occurring from the Indian subcontinent to Indochina at the elevations of 500 to 2000 meters .
The Dwarf Tegu or Spotted False Monitor ( Callopistes maculatus ) is a species of lizard in the Teiidae family .
Magicicada septendecim , sometimes called the Pharaoh cicada or the 17 year locust , is native to Canada and the United States and is the largest and most northern species of periodical cicada with a 17-year life cycle .
Corymbia zygophylla , commonly known as the Broome Bloodwood , is a species of plant in the myrtle family that is native to northern Western Australia .

Neoplecostomus variipictus is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Paraíba do Sul River basin .

Cavanillesia is a genus of flowering plants in the Malvaceae family .

Alyxia is an Australasian genus of flowering plant in the dogbane family , Apocynaceae .

Cosmosoma is a genus of tiger moths in the Arctiidae subfamily .
Keissleriella rara is a rare species of fungus in the Lophiostomataceae family .
Marcgodinotius is a genus of adapiform primate that lived in Asia during the early Eocene .

Cucurbita okeechobeensis , the Okeechobee gourd , is a species of gourd in the Cucurbitaceae family , native to Mexico and the United States .
Packera bolanderi is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Bolander 's ragwort and seacoast ragwort .
Schismatogobius fuligimentus is a species of freshwater goby endemic to New Caledonia where it is found in shallow , slow - moving streams with gravel substrates at altitudes of up to 250 metres ( 820 ft ) , although it is suspected of being amphidromous .
Austrochaperina pluvialis , commonly known as the Rain Frog or White - browed Whistling Frog , is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Chrysophora chrysochlora , the Shining leaf chafer beetle , is a species of beetles of the scarab beetle family .
Hibbertia hypericoides , commonly known as Yellow Buttercups , is a small shrub species that is endemic to the south - west of Western Australia .
Bothrops leucurus , commonly known as the whitetail lancehead or the Bahia lancehead , is a venomous pit viper species endemic to Brazil .
Rubiales was an order of flowering plants in the Cronquist system , including the families Rubiaceae and Theligonaceae .
Sitticus inexpectus is a species of spider from Salticidae family , that can be found in Central Asia , presumably in Kazakhstan .
Haematopota grandis is a species of fly in the horse - fly family , Tabanidae .
Dipha aphidivora is a species of snout moth in the monotypic genus Dipha .
Myloplus is a genus of serrasalmids from South America .
Cyatta is a genus of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae containing the single species Cyatta abscondita .
Acer washingtonense is an extinct maple species in the family Sapindaceae described from one fossil leaf and four fossil samaras .
Callistus lunatus is a species of ground beetle , and the only species of the monotypic genus Callistus .
Thopha saccata , commonly known as the double drummer , is the largest Australian species of cicada and reputedly the loudest insect in the world .
Alcithoe fissurata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Larinus sibiricus is a species of true weevil found in Eastern Europe and the Middle East .
Isopeda villosa is a species of huntsman spider native to New South Wales , Australia , and possibly established in Auckland , New Zealand .
Corythucha ciliata , the sycamore lace bug , is a species of lace bug Tingidae that is linked to sycamores in the New and Old Worlds .
Couma macrocarpa , known by the common names leche caspi , leche huayo , sorva , and cow tree , is a species of tropical plant native to tropical , humid Central and South America from Belize to Bolivia .
Calyptommatus is a genus of Brazilian lizards in the family Gymnophthalmidae .
Optivus is a fish genus from the family Trachichthyidae found from near the surface to depths of 320 m ( 1,050 ft ) in the southwest Pacific Ocean off Australia ( O. agastos and O. agrammus ) and New Zealand ( O. elongatus ) .
Bulganbaatar is a Central Asian mammal genus from the Upper Cretaceous .
Pseuderanthemum carruthersii , the Carruthers ' falseface , is a species of plant in the Acanthaceae family .
Chorinea licursis is a species of butterflies belonging to the family Riodinidae .
Symphodus melanocercus is a species of wrasse native to coastal waters throughout the Mediterranean Sea and the Sea of Marmara .
Chondrodendron tomentosum is a species in the Menispermaceae family .
Phaius flavus is a species of orchid in the genus Phaius described by John Lindley in 1831 .
Haplochromis microdon is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria though it may now be extinct .
The Kongana shrew ( Sylvisorex konganensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae endemic to Central African Republic .
Amatorculus is a genus of the jumping spiders , with two described species from Brazil .
Dawsonellidae is an extinct taxonomic family of fossil sea snails , marine , gastropod mollusks .
The Torymidae are a family of wasps that consists of attractive metallic species with enlarged hind legs , and generally with long ovipositors in the females .
The Pentatomomorpha comprise an infraorder of insects in the true bug order Hemiptera .
Meniscotherium is an extinct genus of dog - sized mammal which lived 54 - 38 million years ago .
Lycodonomorphus is a genus of colubrid snakes commonly referred to as African water snakes .
Retinella stabilei is a species of snail in the family Zonitidae , the true glass snails .
The Leuctridae are a family of stoneflies .
Parajubaea cocoides , the Mountain Coconut , Coco Cumbe or Quito palm , is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family , and a coconut palm .
Callerya megasperma , also known as native wisteria , is a species of vine in the family Fabaceae native to eastern Australia .
Hypericum barbatum is a species in the genus Hypericum .
Granulina is a genus of minute sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Marginellidae .
Sphaeralcea gierischii , Gierisch 's globemallow or Gierisch mallow , is a rare species of flowering plant in the mallow family , Malvaceae .
Lycothrissa crocodilus , the Sabretooth thryssa , is a species of anchovy which occurs in fresh and brackish water in Southeast Asia .
Epicyon ( `` more than a dog '' ) is a large , extinct , canid genus of the subfamily Borophaginae ( `` bone - crushing dogs '' ) , native to North America .
Solidago puberula , the downy goldenrod , is a plant species native to eastern North America from Nova Scotia and Ontario south to Florida and Louisiana .
Stygimys is an extinct mammal genus from the Upper Cretaceous and Paleocene of North America .
Fiona pinnata , common name Fiona , is a species of small pelagic nudibranch ( sea slug ) , a marine gastropod mollusk in the superfamily Fionoidea .
Krachia obeliscoides is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Cerithiopsidae , which is known from European water .
Cicadulina is a leafhopper genus in the tribe Macrostelini .
Protoreaster nodosus , commonly known as the horned sea star or chocolate chip sea star , is a species of sea star found in the warm , shallow waters of the Indo - Pacific region .
Megalena crassa , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Enidae .
Muggiaea kochii is a species of small hydrozoan jellyfish , a siphonophore in the family Diphyidae .
Stenophalium is a genus of Brazilian plants in the pussy's - toes tribe within the daisy family .
Erigeron anchana , the Sierra Ancha fleabane , is a rare Arizona species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Aegiphila sellowiana is a species of tree or shrub in the family Lamiaceae .
Loxogramme dictyopteris , commonly known as lance fern , is a species of fern found in New Zealand .
Ammophila arenaria is a species of grass known by the common names European marram grass and European beachgrass .
Senecio haloragis is a species of the genus Senecio and family Asteraceae and a native of Chile .
Calibrachoa parviflora is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family known by the common name seaside petunia .
Acontista concinna is a species of praying mantis in the Acanthopidae Family that is native to Ecuador .
Asperugo procumbens , known as madwort or German madwort , is the single species in the monotypic plant genus Asperugo .
Siapaea is a genus of flowering plants in the boneset tribe within the daisy family .
Plantago aristata is a species of plantain known by the common name bracted plantain or largebracted plantain .
Meiracyllium , abbreviated as Mrclm in horticultural trade , is a genus of orchids and the sole genus of the subtribe Meiracyllinae .
Boreotrophon truncatus , common name the bobtail trophon , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Sturisomatichthys leightoni is a species of armored catfish of the family Loricariidae endemic to Colombia where it occurs in the upper Magdalena and Cauca River basins .
Agaricomycetidae is a subclass of mushrooms , in the phylum of Basidiomycota .
Ramphotyphlops leucoproctus is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Calophasia lunula is a species of noctuid moth known by the common names toadflax moth and toadflax brocade moth .
Salix miyabeana is a species of willow native to northern Japan .
Hexurella rupicola is a species of spider .
Bulbophyllum rhodoglossum is a species of orchid in the genus Bulbophyllum , first described by Rudolf Schlechter in 1913 in Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis .
Diptychus sewerzowi is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Diptychus .
Petrophile biloba , Granite Petrophile , is a perennial species of shrub in the plant genus Petrophile .
Dicologlossa is a genus of soles native to the tropical and subtropical eastern Atlantic Ocean .
Maoricolpus roseus is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Turritellidae , found only in New Zealand .
Aplysia fasciata , common name the `` mottled sea hare '' , or the `` sooty sea hare '' , is an Atlantic species of sea hare or sea slug , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Aplysiidae .
Oxydoras sifontesi is a species of thorny catfish found in the Orinoco River basin in Colombia and Venezuela .
Acroloxus lacustris , or the lake limpet , is a small freshwater limpet or snail , a species of aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Acroloxidae .
Euhyparpax is a genus of moths of the family Notodontidae , the prominents .
Olearia viscidula , commonly known as the sticky daisy bush , is a shrub or subshrub species in the Asteraceae family .
Anguidae is the name of a large and diverse family of lizards native to the Northern Hemisphere .
Halicampus dunckeri or also commonly known as the Duncker 's pipefish or ridgenose pipefish is a species of fish in the Syngnathidae family .
Ceraceopsis is a fungal genus in the class Agaricomycetes .
Furcifer tuzetae is a species of chameleon that is endemic to Madagascar in Befandriana Sud and Andrenalamivola .
Distichlis distichophylla is a species of grass commonly known as Australian Salt - grass , Emu Grass or Pineapple Grass .
Vexillum sykesi is a species of small sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk within the family Costellariidae , the ribbed miters .
Ctenosaura is a lizard genus commonly known as spinytail iguanas or Ctenosaurs .
Yakudza vicarius is a moth in the Cossidae family and only species in the genus Yakudza .
Hauffiosaurus is an extinct genus of Early Jurassic ( early Toarcian stage ) pliosaurid plesiosaur known from Holzmaden of Germany and from Yorkshire of the United Kingdom .
Agonum superioris is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in the United States .
Lotus nuttallianus is a species of legume known by the common names beach lotus , Nuttall 's lotus , and wire bird's - foot trefoil .
Notylia bungerothii is a species of orchid that occurs from Venezuela , Guyana and Ecuador .
Kronichthys heylandi is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in coastal streams between Santos and Rio de Janeiro .
Coptis chinensis , the Chinese goldthread , is a species of goldthread native to China .
Potentilla rimicola is a species of cinquefoil - Potentilla , known by the common name cliff cinquefoil .
Libocedrus austrocaledonica is a species of Libocedrus , endemic to New Caledonia , occurring mainly in the southern half of the island ( also one site in the northern half ) , at 750 - -1,400 m altitude in montane cloud forest scrub .
Labeo weeksii is species of fish in genus Labeo .
Draperia is a monotypic genus of plants which includes the single species Draperia systyla , known by the common name violet draperia .
Thelymitra antennifera , commonly called the Rabbit - eared Sun Orchid , Lemon -- scented Sun orchid or Vanilla orchid is a species of orchid which is native to Western Australia , South Australia and Victoria and northern parts of Tasmania .
Cochlostoma is a genus of land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Cochlostomatidae .
Neisseria cinerea is a commensal species grouped with the Gram - negative , oxidase - positive , and catalase - positive diplococci .
Oenothera is a genus of about 145 species of herbaceous flowering plants native to the Americas .
Styrax vilcabambae ( syn . Pamphilia vilcabambae D.R.Simpson ) is a species of flowering plant in the genus Styrax and the family Styracaceae .
Acrobasis eva is a species of snout moth in the genus Acrobasis , found on Sumatra .
Dichanthium , known commonly as bluestem , is a genus of African , Asian , and Australian plants in the grass family some of which have become naturalized in the Americas and on various oceanic islands .
Homona magnanima , the Oriental tea tortrix moth , is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae .
Helichrysum stoechas is similar to the Helichrysum arenarium species , but the leaves are all linear , with rolled under Edges .
Hemisaurida ( meaning `` half lizard '' ) is a genus of prehistoric fish , known from Cretaceous fossils found in Europe .
Shimogia fasciata is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Shimogia .
Tropidophis battersbyi , or the Ecuadorian dwarf boa , is a species of snake in the Tropidophiidae family .
Leymus triticoides , with the common names creeping wild rye and beardless wild rye , is a species of wild rye .
Colpophyllia is a genus of stony corals in the Mussidae family .
Under the International Code of Nomenclature for algae , fungi , and plants ( ICN ) , Rosidae is a botanical name at the rank of subclass .
Fasciculacmocera griseovaria is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Fasciculacmocera .
Mertensia maritima a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names oysterleaf , oysterplant or sea bluebells .
Pithauria murdava is a species of Skipper butterfly found in tropical Asia .
The spider genus Tetrablemma is unusual in possessing only four eyes , a trait only found elsewhere in most species of the family Caponiidae .
Arizona elegans philipi , commonly known as the Painted Desert glossy snake , is a subspecies of glossy snake , a nonvenomous colubrid endemic to North America .
Ellobiopsis is a genus of alveolae parasitic protozoa .
Claudea elegans is a marine red alga species in the genus Claudea .
Ocimum gratissimum , also known as clove basil , African basil , and in Hawaii as wild basil , is a species of Ocimum .
Stylocheilus ( Gould , 1852 ) is a genus of sea slugs , specifically sea hares , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Aplysiidae , the sea hares .
The typical helmetshrikes , Prionops , form a bird genus in the helmetshrike family Prionopidae .
Valanga nigricornis , the Javanese grasshopper , is a species of grasshopper in the subfamily Cyrtacanthacridinae of the family Acrididae .
Teyl is a genus of nemesiid spiders with four described ( and many undescribed ) species , all of which are endemic to Australia .
Climatius ( meaning inclined fish or tilted fish ) is an extinct genus of spiny shark .
Stanhopea ( J. Frost ex Hook . 1829 ) is a genus of the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) from Central and South America .
Solidago juncea , the early goldenrod , plume golden - rod , or yellow top , is North American species of herbaceous perennial plants of the sunflower family native to eastern and central Canada and the eastern and central United States .
Echinacea purpurea ( eastern purple coneflower or purple coneflower ) is a North American species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Crepis pleurocarpa is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name nakedstem hawksbeard .
Tagetes argentina South American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Nebria cinctella is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in India and Nepal .
Obelia longissima is a colonial species of hydrozoan in the order Leptomedusae .
Criocephalosaurus is an extinct genus of tapinocephalian therapsid which existed in Southern Africa .
Crocidura sapaensis is a species of white - toothed shrew native to northern Vietnam .
Misthodotes is an extinct genus of mayflies which existed during the Permian of what is now the United States and Russia .
The species rank of Melitaea ornata ( type location Guberlya , Russia ) was only very recently recognised in two publications by Russell , et al .
Hyalenna is a genus of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies , named by Forbes in 1942 .
The mimids are the New World family of passerine birds , Mimidae , that includes thrashers , mockingbirds , tremblers , and the New World catbirds .
Solidago tarda , commonly known as Atlantic goldenrod , is a rare North American species of goldenrod in the sunflower family .
Phyllophryne scortea , the Smooth anglerfish , is a species of frogfish endemic to the waters around Australia .
Colchicum pusillum is a species of perennial flowering plant in the family Colchicaceae that is easily identified by its up to 6 narrow ( 2 mm or 1/16 `` ) leaves produced during or shortly after flowering .
Allium tuncelianum is a species of wild onion which is endemic to the Munzur Valley in Tunceli , in eastern Turkey .
Cornisepta monsfuji is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Helianthus bolanderi is a species of sunflower known by the common names Bolander 's sunflower and serpentine sunflower .
Eleocharis quinqueflora is a species of spikesedge known by the common names fewflower spikerush and few - flowered spike - rush .
Prunus serrulata or Japanese cherry ; also called hill cherry , oriental cherry or East Asian cherry , is a species of cherry native to Japan , Korea and China and is used for its spring cherry blossom displays and festivals .
Cassida viridis , common name green tortoise beetle , is a species of beetle in the leaf beetle family ( Chrysomelidae ) .
Ipomoea nil is a species of Ipomoea morning glory known by several common names , including picotee morning glory , ivy morning glory , and Japanese morning glory .
Cordyline minutiflora is a plant species native to Irian Jaya on the island of New Guinea in eastern Indonesia .
Espeletia , commonly known as frailejón or fraylejón , is a genus of perennial subshrubs , in the sunflower family .
Lachnanthes is a genus of monocotyledonous plants in the bloodwort family containing only one species , i.e. , Lachnanthes caroliniana , commonly known as Carolina redroot or bloodroot .
The Gjaerumiaceae are a family of smut fungi in the Basidiomycota , class Exobasidiomycetes .
Bombus bohemicus , also known as the Gypsy 's Cuckoo Bumblebee , is a species of socially parasitic cuckoo bumblebee found in most of Europe and the United Kingdom with exception of the southern Iberian Peninsula and Iceland .
Mahonia fremontii ( syn . Berberis fremontii ) is a species of barberry known by the common name Frémont 's mahonia ( after John C. Frémont ) .
Crepis bursifolia is a European species of flowering plant in the daisy family with the common name Italian hawksbeard .
Pseudocnella insolens is a species of sea cucumber from the family Cucumariidae , placed in the genus Pseudocnella .
Arenaria congesta is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name ballhead sandwort .
Scorpio maurus is a species of North African and Middle Eastern scorpion , also known as the Large - clawed Scorpion or Israeli gold scorpion .
Bullina vitrea is a species of small sea snail , a bubble snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Bullinidae , one of the families of bubble snails .
Certonardoa semiregularis is a species of sea star in the family Ophidiasteridae .
Anaplasmataceae is a Proteobacteria family that includes genera Anaplasma , Ehrlichia , Neorickettsia and Wolbachia .
Hapalodectes ( literally `` soft biter '' ; ἁπαλός , hapalos = `` soft , tender '' , δῆκτῆς , dêktês = `` biter '' ) is an extinct genus of otter - like mesonychids from the Late Paleocene to Early Eocene some 55 million years ago .
Bactrodes is a genus of reduviids ( assassin bugs ) .
Podolaspis is an extinct genus of pteraspidid heterostracan agnathan which existed during the early Devonian period .
Puff - faced Water Snake or Masked Water Snake ( Homalopsis buccata ) is a species of water snake found in tropical areas of South and Southeast Asia .
The Ceylonthelphusa alpina is a species of freshwater crabs in the family Gecarcinucidae .
Osornophryne antisana , the Napo Plump Toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Perizoma blandiata , the pretty pinion , is a species of moth of the Geometridae family .
Cyathea cranhamii is an extinct species of tree fern .
Peniophora is a genus of fungi which are plant pathogens .
Prorocentrum donghaiense is a bloom - forming species of planktonic dinoflagellate .
The lagomorphs are the members of the taxonomic order Lagomorpha , of which there are two living families : the Leporidae ( hares and rabbits ) and the Ochotonidae ( pikas ) .
Frullania dilatata , the dilated scalewort , is a species of liverwort in the Jubulaceae family .
Stictococcidae is a family of scale insects commonly known as stictococcids .
Ilex qianlingshanensis , commonly known in China as 黔灵山冬青 ( Qianling Mountain Holly ) is a species of plant in the Aquifoliaceae family .
Awaous macrorhynchus is a species of goby endemic to Madagascar where it is known from brackish and fresh waters .
Ichthyolestes ( `` fish thief '' ) is a genus of extinct early whale belonging to the family Pakicetidae endemic to northern Pakistan , living during the Lutetian stage .
Caesia parviflora , the pale grass lily , is a species of flowering plant in the Xanthorrhoeaceae native to Australia .

Silverstoneia is a genus of poison dart frogs ( family Dendrobatidae ) from southern Central America and northern South America , between southwestern Costa Rica and southwestern Colombia .
Hymenoxys hoopesii ( formerly Dugaldia hoopesii ) is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names owl 's claws and orange sneezeweed .
Gobio gobio , or the gudgeon , is a species of fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Penicillium spathulatum is a species of the genus of Penicillium which produces asperphenamate .
Achatinella cestus is a species ofair - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinellidae .
Malus honanensis is a wild species in the genus Malus ( mostly referred for the crabapple or wild apple ) , in the family Rosaceae , with no established common name , and used as rootstock for the domesticated apple .
Pseudostomatella decolorata , common name the coloured stomatella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Cosmioconcha nitens , common name : the shiny dove shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae , the dove snails .
Rhinotyphlops somalicus , commonly known as the Ethiopian blind snake or the highland beaked snake , is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Sommerxylon a genus is described from petrified trunks of Gymnosperms that lived in the Triassic , found in the Caturrita Formation on Linha São Luiz in the municipality of Faxinal do Soturno in the region of Paleorrota .
The Protura constitute an order of hexapods that were previously regarded as insects , and sometimes treated as a class in their own right .
Enobius is a genus of dinocephalian therapsid .
Velociraptor ( /vɨˈlɒsɨræptər/ ; meaning `` swift seizer '' ) is a genus of dromaeosaurid theropod dinosaur that lived approximately 75 to 71 million years ago during the later part of the Cretaceous Period .
Pseudolatisternum jeanneli is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudolatisternum .
Pulsatilla patens is a US native species of flowering plant in the family Ranunculaceae ;
Meriandra is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae family .
The Hemphillia dromedarius , common name the dromedary Jumping - slug , is a species of air - breathing land slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Arionidae , the roundback slugs .
Metacarcinus anthonyi , the yellow rock crab or yellow crab , is a species of edible crab native to the Pacific coast of North America .
Sarcodes is a monotypic genus of a single springtime flowering plant in the heath family ( Ericaceae ) containing the single species Sarcodes sanguinea , commonly called the snow plant or snow flower .
Lingoria sanguinicollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Lingoria .
Dactylorhiza hatagirea is a species of orchid generally found growing in the Himalayas , from Pakistan to SE Tibet , at altitudes of 2,800 - -4,000 metres ( 9,200 - -13,100 ft ) .
Xanthorrhoea arborea a species of grasstree of the genus Xanthorrhoea native to New South Wales and Queensland .
Phyllobacterium trifolii is a root - nodulating bacteria that was first isolated from nodules in Trifolium and Lupinus species .
Skenea coronadoensis , common name the Coronado Island skenea , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae .
Xinjiangovenator ( meaning `` Xinjiang hunter '' ) is a genus of coelurosaurian dinosaur of the Valanginian to Albian stages of the Early Cretaceous period .
Neopilina is a highly derived genus of modern monoplacophoran .
Harrisia bonplandii is a species of cactus . The cactus plants in the Gran Chaco ( Paraguay , Argentina , Bolivia ) are generally called Tuna and this specific variety Reina de la Noche ( Queen of the Night ) .
Hemichromis fasciatus , also called the banded jewelfish and five - spot cichlid , is a species of fish in the cichlid family .
Maytenus krukovii is a tree species native to the Amazon rainforest ; it grows in Bolivia , Colombia , Ecuador , and Peru .
Synodontis polyodon is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Gabon where it occurs in the Ogowe River basin .
Sphodromantis elegans is a species of praying mantis found in Ethiopia , Burkina Faso , Guinea , Mauritania , Niger , Senegal and the Congo River region .
It contains only one species , Exonomasis exolescens , which is found in South Africa .
Amphimallon assimile is a species of beetle in the Melolonthinae subfamily that can be found in France and Italy .
Melanopsidae , common name melanopsids , is a family of freshwater gastropods in the clade Sorbeoconcha .
Paltothyreus ( also known as African stink ant ) is a monotypic genus of ants in the subfamily Ponerinae .
Pameridea is a genus of insects comprising two species , P. roridulae and P. marlothii , that live in symbiotic relationships with carnivorous plants in the genus Roridula .
Crocodilaemus is an extinct genus of pholidosaurid mesoeucrocodylian .
Hemitripterus is a genus of sea ravens native to the northern Pacific and Atlantic Oceans .
Tillandsia flexuosa , the twisted airplant , is a species in the genus Tillandsia .
Zabrus socialis is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that can be found in Near East , former Yugoslavia and Turkey ( Bursa ) .
Forficula is a genus of earwigs in the family Forficulidae .
Astragalus linifolius is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Grand Junction milkvetch .
Cristoberea assamensis is a species of longhorn beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily , and the only species in the genus Cristoberea .
Chondrus is a genus of red algae containing 11 accepted species :
Laomenes amboinensis is a species of shrimp found in waters off Indonesia , Queensland , New Caledonia , the Marshall Islands , the Ryukyu Islands and Papua New Guinea .
Pseudotropheus flavus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from Chinyankwazi Island .
Carabus gyllenhali is a species of ground beetle from Carabinae family that is endemic to Ukraine .
Brahmaea celebica is a species of moth of the Brahmaeidae family .
Myriocephalus is a genus of Australian flowering plants in the daisy family .
Baetoidea is a superfamily of mayflies , which probably includes the most primitive living species .
Taczanowski 's ground tyrant or plain - capped ground tyrant ( Muscisaxicola griseus ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
The Mississippi slimy salamander , Plethodon mississippi , is a species of terrestrial plethodontid salamander found throughout most of the U.S. state of Mississippi , western Alabama , western Tennessee , far western Kentucky , and eastern Louisiana .
The New Granada cross - banded tree frog ( Smilisca phaeota , also known as the masked tree frog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia , Costa Rica , Ecuador , Honduras , Nicaragua , and Panama .
