Ameles limbata is a species of praying mantis that lives on the Canary Islands .
Afroablepharus is a genus of skinks endemic to Africa .
Spirillum volutans is one of the largest bacteria species .
Volia is an extinct genus of mekosuchine crocodylian from Fiji .
Sphaerodactylus ariasae , the Jaragua sphaero or dwarf gecko , is a very small Gekkonidae species in the Sphaerodactylus genus .
Papilio albinus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in west Irian Jaya and Papua New Guinea .
Ficinia is a genus of tufted or rhizotamous sedges .
Kageneckia angustifolia ( also known as Frangel ) is a species of plant in the Rosaceae family .
Antrophyum austroqueenslandicum ( previously A. sp . Blue Pool ) was a species of epiphytic or lithophytic fern known from subtropical rainforest in Lamington National Park in the state of Queensland , Australia .
Dodonaea hirsuta is a species of shrub endemic to New South Wales , and Queensland .
Atriplex lindleyi is a species of saltbush known by the common name Lindley 's saltbush .
Agyneta flavipes is a species of sheet weaver found in Japan .
Marsupenaeus japonicus , known as the kuruma shrimp , kuruma prawn , or Japanese tiger prawn , is a species of prawn .
Bromus sterilis is an annual or biennial species of bromegrass known as barren brome , poverty brome , and sterile brome .
Taningia persica is a species of squid in the family Octopoteuthidae .
Eucrenonaspides oinotheke is a species of crustacean in the family Psammaspidae ( Order Anaspidacea ) , endemic to Tasmania , the only species described in the genus Eucrenonaspides .
Alopoglossus is a genus of lizards endemic to tropical South America .
Roboastra leonis is a species of sea slug , a polycerid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Polyceridae .
Pseudosybra cristata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudosybra .
Datura ferox , commonly known as Long Spined Thorn Apple and Fierce Thornapple , as well as Angel's - trumpets , is a species of Datura .
Lethrinops oculatus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from the southern part of the lake over sandy substrates .
Glebocarcinus oregonensis , commonly known as the pygmy rock crab , is a species of crab found on the Pacific coast of North America .
A family Plesiosauridae was first named by John Edward Gray in 1825 .
Himatanthus obovatus is a species of Himatanthus genus in the Apocynaceae family , which is native Brazil , Bolivia , Guyana .
Halogeton glomeratus is a species of flowering plant in the amaranth family known by the common names saltlover , Aral barilla , and halogeton .
Ilex opaca , the American holly , is a species of holly , native to the eastern and south - central United States , from coastal Massachusetts south to central Florida , and west to southeastern Missouri and eastern Texas .
Cyathus stercoreus , commonly known as the dung - loving bird 's nest , is a species of fungus in the genus Cyathus , family Nidulariaceae .
Smithella propionica is a species of bacteria , the type species of its genus .
Indirana tenuilingua is a species of frog from the Western Ghats of India .
Hyla graceae is a species of tree frog from Panama .
Edwardsina gigantea or the giant torrent midge is a species of fly in family Blephariceridae .
Gibbula ardens is a species of small sea snail , known as top snails or top shells , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Acanthocalycium is a genus of cactus consisting of several species from Argentina .
Streptomyces galbus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from West Bengal .
Rhadia pusio is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Rhadia .
Gnathosaurus ( meaning ' jawed lizard ' ) is a genus of ctenochasmatid pterosaurs containing two species :
Escobaria vivipara is a species of cactus known by several common names , including spinystar , and viviparous foxtail cactus .
Amblyomma is a genus of hard ticks .
Weigeltaspis is a genus of extinct heterostracan agnathan fish known from the Late Silurian and Early Devonian periods .
The variants Russula heterophylla var . chlora Gillet 1876 , and Russula heterophylla var . virginea ( Cooke and Massee ) A.Pearson & Dennis , have been given species status as Russula violeipes , and Russula virginea respectively .
Boschniakia strobilacea is a species of parasitic plant in the broomrape family known by the common name California groundcone .
Boletus semigastroideus is a species of secotioid fungus in the family Boletaceae .
Amsinckia calycina , also known as hairy fiddleneck or yellow burweed , is a species of fiddleneck .
Blastogregarinorina is a suborder of parasitic protozoa of the phylum Apicomplexia
Drombus is a genus of gobies native to fresh , brackish and marine waters of the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Cribbea is a genus of secotioid fungi in the family Physalacriaceae .
Toxopneustidae is a family of globular sea urchins in the class Echinoidea .
Futalognkosaurus ( /ˌfuːtəˌlɒŋkoʊˈsɔːrəs/ FOO - tə - long - ko - SAW - rəs ; meaning `` giant chief lizard '' ) is a genus of titanosaurian dinosaur .
Epeoloides is a genus of kleptoparasitic bees which lay their eggs in the nests of melittid bees of the genus Macropis .
Drymocallis glandulosa , known by the common name sticky cinquefoil and formerly as Potentilla glandulosa , is a species of cinquefoil .
Erigeron glaucus is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name seaside fleabane , beach aster , or seaside daisy .
Lathraea ( toothwort ) is a small genus of five to seven species of flowering plants , native to temperate Europe and Asia .
Balaenoptera , from the Latin balaena ( whale ) and pteron ( fin ) , is a genus of Balaenopteridae , the rorquals , and contains eight extant species .
' Akrav israchanani ' is an extinct species of scorpion from the Ayyalon Cave in Israel .
Nursery web spiders are spiders of the family Pisauridae .
Megacephala laevicollis is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by C.O. Waterhouse in 1880 .
Appearing in summer and autumn , Caloboletus radicans grows with Quercus and Fagus species ( Oak and Beech ) , and is sometimes found in fairly large numbers .
Iridoteuthis iris is a species of bobtail squid native to the northern central Pacific Ocean ; it occurs near the Hawaiian Islands off the southeast and northwest Hancock , Colahan , and Kammu seamounts .
Metaphidippus manni is a species of jumping spider found in North America .
Jacobaea gibbosa is a species ( synonym Senecio gibbosus ) of the genus Jacobaea and the family Asteraceae .
Erechtites minimus , common names toothed fireweed , and coastal burnweed is a species of plants in the sunflower family .
Chamaeleo is a genus of chameleons found primarily in the mainland of sub - saharan Africa , but a few species are also present in northern Africa , southern Europe and southern Asia east to India and Sri Lanka .
Pseudopanax is a small genus of 12 - -20 species of evergreen plants , the majority of which are endemic to New Zealand , although they also occur in Tasmania ( Australia ) and some plants from South America have at times been included in this genus .
Solariella obscura , common name the obscure solarelle , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Solariellidae .
Stictosomus semicostatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Stictosomus .
Paraphlebia hyalina is a species of damselfly native to Mexico .
Drosera stricticaulis , the erect sundew , is an erect perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera .
Heterodontosaurus is a genus of heterodontosaurid dinosaur that lived during the Early Jurassic period , 200 - -190 million years ago .
Enneanectes jordani , known commonly as the Mimic triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny .
Wapkia is a genus of sponge with radial sclerites , known from the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale .
Haliotis pourtalesii aurantium is a subspecies of edible sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Acanthomintha ilicifolia , known by the common name San Diego thornmint , is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family .
Peziza is a large genus of saprophytic cup fungi that grow on the ground , rotting wood , or dung .
Sporobolus junceus is a species of grass known by the common name pineywoods dropseed .
Hilaria belangeri is a species of grass known by the common name curly - mesquite , sometimes written curlymesquite or curly mesquite .
Socognathus is a genus of prehistoric chamopsiid polyglyphanodontian lizards containing species that lived from the Middle Campanian stage to the late Maastrichtian .
Paragomphus cognatus ( Rock Hooktail ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae .
Tohoraata is a genus of eomysticetid baleen whale from the Late Oligocene ( Chattian ) of New Zealand .
Sepia koilados is a species of cuttlefish native to the southeastern Indian Ocean , specifically the North West Shelf in western Australia ( 18 ° 31′S 118 ° 09′E to 19 ° 12.6′S 116 ° 25.8′E ) .
Actia lamia is the type species of the genus Actia of the family Tachinidae .
Meteuproctis is a genus of moths in the family Lymantriidae .
The Helvellaceae are a family of ascomycete fungi , the best known members of which are the elfin saddles of the genus Helvella .
Oberonioides is a genus of orchids native to China and Thailand .
Capsus ater is a species of bug in the Miridae family that likely originated in North America , but that is now found in Africa , Europe , northern Asia and North America .
Cherax is the most widespread genus of fully aquatic crayfish in the Southern Hemisphere .
Proxiuber hulmei is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Naticidae .
Philobryidae is a taxonomic family of very small equivalved triangular saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks , related to the ark clams and the bittersweets .
Ventricolaria rigida , or the rigid venus clam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae .
Hypodactylus adercus is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family endemic to Colombia .
Amphilestes is a genus of extinct triconodont mammal from the Middle Jurassic It is known from various dental and mandibular remains .
It consists of only one species , Hyposhada pellopis , which is found in Australia , where it has been recorded from Queensland .
Persephonella marina is a thermophilic , hydrogen - oxidizing microaerophile first isolated from a deep - sea hydrothermal vent , the type species of its genus .
It consists of only one species , Denteilema unicolora , which is endemic to Vietnam .
Quercus tonduzii is a species of oak , of the Fagaceae family .
The Judomioidea are a superfamily of trilobites , a group of extinct marine arthropods .
Pluchea glutinosa is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family that is endemic to the Island of Socotra in the Indian Ocean , part of the Republic of Yemen .
The Donald 's hawker , ( Anaciaeschna donaldi ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Aeshnidae .
Brachys is a genus of beetles in the family Buprestidae , containing the following species :
Brachyprosopus is an extinct genus of dicynodont therapsid from the middle Permian of the Karoo Basin , South Africa .
Conus clerii , common name Clery 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Vexilla vexillum , common name the vexillum rock shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
